<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="LUK" stage="Rev" version="D">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:44:05Z" when="2009-10-02 03:44:05Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Max Jacob; team advisors C&amp;B Grimes; revised by Max Jacob; team revision Max Jacob and Mus Zacharias Jan-Feb 2002 looking at NLT, CEV and Trans. Notes; team exegetical pass in Darwin Feb/Mar. 2002 with June, Max, Mus, and Chuck; TW3, Trans. Notes, NLT, CEV, NIGTC (I. Howard Marshall) ; 2:1-20 consultant checked by Gilles Gravelles in Kupang (1 April 1999); UNS check Luke 1-11 in Kupang, Gereja Anugerah, 28-30 May 2002; Aug-Sept 2002 Max, Mus and Barbara worked through Luke 12-24 (with Thomas Ly); Community Check: Jemaat Pniel Oebobo; Lukas 12 s/d 24: UNS: Mesker Lak Apu, 30 thn, Tata Usaha Gereja Pniel; SMA; Jerry Adu, 25 thn, Petugas Komputer Kantor Gereja Pniel, SLTA; Wendy Eo-Ndolu ST UNDANA, 25 thn.; Final check: 29 Oct - 2 Nov 2002: Consultant: Gilles Gravelle; Translators Max Jacob and Muz Zacharias; Last correstion by Max Jacob, 19 Feb. 2003. ; Corrections reviewed by Chuck May-October 2003; further corrections after input from Belu check in Nov 2005 &amp; Feb 2006; BT by Barbara, March 2006; more after Helong check in Sept 2006; read thru for NT by Chuck, Mus, Adriana, with exegetical adjustments reviewed by Marge</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:43:32Z" when="2014-02-24 10:43:32Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 29 October - 2 November 2002 in Kupang; Consultant: Gilles Gravelle, approved. Report: KM Luke Cons Check.doc; Consultant checking report Kupang Luke.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-08 23:49:41Z" when="2015-01-08 23:49:41Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible completed 9 Jan 2015 with Chuck, Lena, Oma, Rina at UBB. BT cleaned up a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Lukas</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae,<bt>Lord Yesus' *Gospel1 (Good Story)</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">iko<bt>according to</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Lukas<bt>Lukas</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kanapa ko Lukas tulis ini carita<bt>Why Lukas writes this story</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-3" />Bapa Teofilus<bt>Father Teofilus</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Nama <span class="Italic">Teofilus</span> dalam bahasa Yunani pung arti bilang, &lt;orang yang sayang sang Tuhan&gt;. Ini Lukas pung buku partama yang dia tulis kasi sang Teofilus. Yang kadua tu, andia <span class="Italic">Utusan dong pung Carita</span>.<bt>The name <span class="Italic">Teofilus</span> in the Yunani language means &lt;person/people who love/s the Lord&gt;. This is Lukas' first book which he wrote to Teofilus. The second is <span class="Italic">Acts of the Apostles</span>.</bt></note>yang terhormat.<bt>who is honored/respected (=typical greeting in a letter).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Salamat.<bt>Greetings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Banya orang su coba tulis carita so'al hal-hal yang su jadi di botong pung teng-tenga. Dong tulis itu carita dong, pake carita-carita yang bataputar dari botong pi botong dari dolu, yang botong dapa tau dari Tuhan Yesus pung orang dalam dong, deng dari orang laen ju yang lia deng mata kapala sandiri. Samua carita tu, iko parsís-parsís ke Tuhan Allah pung janji memang dari dolu.<bt>Many people have already tried to write the story about the things which have already happened in our-exc midst. They wrote those stories, using stories which have circulated from us-exc to us-exc from long ago, which we-exc got to know from the Lord Yesus' inside people, and from other people who also saw with their very own eyes. All those stories, follow/are.in.accord exactly with what the Lord God promised beforehand from long ago. [NOTE to daughter translations: if first sentence above too vague, try “the story about the life and work (doublet) of Yesus which have already happened in our-exc midst.”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi beta su pareksa sampe alus-alus itu hal dong samua, mulai dari dia pung akar carita. Ais beta putus ko tulis ame itu samua deng bae-bae, iko dia pung urutan. Deng bagitu, pak bisa tau parsís apa yang su jadi.<bt>So (consequently), I have examined in the finest details all those matters, beginning from the root/cause of the story. So I decided to write up all those things carefully/well, according to its (chronological) order.in.a.series. In that way, sir can know exactly what has occurred.</bt><v n="4" />Deng pak ju bisa parcaya bilang, apa yang orang dong su carita kasi tu, bukan carita putar-balek. Samua tu, batúl-batúl ada!<bt>And sir can also trust what people have told (you), that it is not distorted/deceptive. All of it really happened!</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga kasi tau memang Yohanis tukang sarani pung jadi<bt>The Lord's underling from heaven (*angel) tells beforehand the birth of Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ini carita pung akar bagini: waktu raja Herodes pegang parenta di propinsi Yudea, ada satu orang, nama Sakaria. Dia tu, satu kapala agama Yahudi. Deng dia ju anggota dari ba'i Abia pung kalompok kapala agama dong. Sakaria pung bini, nama Elisabet. Dia ju dari turunan kapala agama dong, te dia tu, ba'i Musa pung kaka Harun pung turunan.<bt>This story's root/beginning is like this: when raja Herodes was holding power in Yudea province, there was a person, named Sakaria. He was a head of the Yahudi religion (*priest). And he also was a member of grandfather/forefather Abia's group of priests. Sakaria's wife, was Elisabet. She also was a descendant of priests, cuz (elaboration) she was a descendant of Gf/Ff Musa's older.sibling Harun. [EXEG: according to Ex. 7:7, Aaron is older than Moses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***adi changed to kaka (Ex. 7:7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***adi changed to kaka (Ex. 7:7)</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 24:10; Kaluar dari Masir 7:7</note><v n="6" />Dong dua idop lurus iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta deng atoran samua. Orang ju hormat sang dong.<bt>The two of them lived straight following/according to all of the Lord God's commands and regulations. People respected them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="amemptoi: blameless, without fault"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">amemptoi: blameless, without fault</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dong dua ju su tua, ma sonde ada pung ana, te Elisabet pung tampa ana tu, ada tatutu.<bt>The two of them were also old, but did not have a child, cuz (elaboration) that child place (=womb) of Elisabet's was closed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ reordered clauses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ reordered clauses</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Satu kali, Sakaria deng dia pung kalompok Abia dong dapa roster karjá di Ruma Sambayang Pusat di kota Yerusalem.<bt>One time, Sakaria and his Abia group got rostered to work at the Central Worship House (*Temple) in Yerusalem city. [NOTE to daughter translations: try /bagian/ in place of /roster/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="roster ; giliran (BI)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">roster ; giliran (BI)</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Iko dong pung biasa, itu kapala agama dong hela lot, ko mau tau sapa yang dapa tugas maso pi itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung Kamar Paling Barisi. Di situ, itu orang musti bakar kayu wangi di Tuhan Allah pung muka. Itu hari, lot jato kaná di Sakaria.<bt>Following their tradition/habit, those priests drew lots, to find out who got the job/task of entering that Central Worship House's Very Cleanest/Holiest Room. There, that person should/would burn fragrant wood in front of Lord God. That day, the lot fell on Sakaria.</bt><v n="10" />Ais ju dia maso pi. Waktu dia ada bakar kayu wangi dalam itu Kamar, orang bam-banya dong ada sambayang di kintal situ.<bt>And so he went in. When he was burning fragrant wood in that Room, many people were worshiping/praying in the yard there.</bt><v n="11" />Takuju sa, ju Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga, datang badiri di tampa bakar kayu wangi pung sablá kanan.<bt>Unexpectedly/Suddenly, then Lord God's underling from heaven came and stood at the right side of the place for burning fragrant wood.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00263C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Kapala agama Yahudi bakar kayu wangi<bt>A Yahudi priest burns fragrant wood (*incense)</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Lia bagitu, ju Sakaria taku mau mati, sampe sonde tau mau bekin apa.<bt>Seeing like that, then Sakaria was exceedingly afraid, to the point that he did not know want to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(taku) sama ke mayat idop ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">(taku) sama ke mayat idop = like a living corpse</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma itu ana bua dari sorga omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakaria! Jang taku, é! Te Tuhan Allah su dengar lu pung sambayang. Jadi lu pung bini nanti barana satu ana laki-laki kasi sang lu. Lu musti kasi nama sang dia, Yohanis.<bt>But that underling from heaven spoke saying, “Sakaria! Don't be afraid! Cuz (elaboration) Lord God has heard your-sg prayer. So (consequently), your wife will give.birth to a male child for you. You must name him, Yohanis.</bt><v n="14" />Nanti banya orang ju iko sanáng sama-sama deng bosong, tagal bosong su dapa ana. Ini ana nanti bekin lu pung hati babunga.<bt>Later many people will follow.along being happy together with you-pl, because you-pl have a gotten a child. This child will make your-sg liver flower (=make you be joyful/happy). [NOTE to daughter translations: if /bosong su dapa ana/ carries impression of by means other than giving birth, change to /melahirkan/.]</bt><v n="15" />Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi pung kuasa ada sama-sama deng dia, mulai dari dia pung mama masi dudu parú. Dia musti pamali minum samua minuman karás. Waktu dia su bésar datang, Tuhan Allah pake sang dia jadi orang pantíng.<bt>The Lord's Holy Spirit's power/authority will be with him, starting from when his mother is still pregnant with him. He must avoid/have.a.taboo.against drinking all hard drinks. When he is grown, the Lord will use him to be an important person.</bt><note reference="1:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 6:3</note><v n="16" />Nanti dia buju banya orang Isra'el ko bale iko sang Tuhan Allah, yang ada hak parenta sang dong.<bt>Later he will (attempt to) persuade many Isra'el people to turn and follow/obey God, who has the say-so/ordering rights over them.</bt><v n="17" />Dia pung sifat deng kuasa nanti parsís ke ba'i Elia, andia Tuhan pung jubir dari dolu. Dia datang lebe dolo dari kotong pung Bos. Dia bekin orang tua pung hati bale sayang sang dong pung ana-ana. Deng orang yang bale balakang sang Tuhan dia oba ju, ko dong bale iko sang Tuhan pung mau. Deng bagitu, dia bekin orang dong sadia dong pung hati ko tarima Bos pung datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>His characteristics and power/authority will be exactly like Gf/Ff Elia, who was God2's spokesperson long ago. He came/comes ahead of our Bos. He will make old people (=parents) livers=hearts turn to love their children. And people/person who have turned their backs against the Lord he will also change, so that they turn around and follow the God2's will. In that way, he make people prepare their livers to receive the Bos's coming.”</bt><note reference="1:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 4:5-6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma Sakaria bale tanya itu ana bua bilang, &lt;&lt;Mana bisa?! Beta deng beta pung bini su tua bagini! Karmana ko beta bisa tau ini hal samua bisa jadi?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Sakaria responded asking that underling saying, “How can that be?! (=impossible) I and my wife are already old like this! How can I know all these things will/can happen?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais, itu ana bua manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Beta ni, Gabriel, Tuhan Allah pung tukang suru-suru. Dia sandiri yang suru beta datang ko kasi tau ini kabar bae sang lu.<bt>Then, that underling replied saying, “Like this! I am Gabriel, the Lord God's *servant. He himself is the one who ordered me to come and tell this good news to you-sg.</bt><note reference="1:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 8:16, 9:21</note><v n="20" />Ma lu sonde mau parcaya beta pung omong. Jadi dia pung tanda yang lu minta bagini! Lu pung lida takancing, deng lu sonde bisa omong apa-apa mulai sakarang, sampe deng bosong barana ame itu ana. Nanti lu lia sandiri sa. Te apa yang beta bilang ni nanti jadi, pas deng dia pung waktu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you don't want to believe what I say. So (consequently), the sign which you ask will be like this! Your tongue will be tightened/locked, and you will not be able to speak anything starting from now, until you-pl get/obtain that child. Later you-sg will see for yourself. Cuz what I am saying here will happen, exactly at the right time.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Orang banya yang ada sambayang di luar, su tabingung-bingung, tagal Sakaria sonde tau kaluar-kaluar.<bt>The many people who were worshipping/praying outside, were already confused, because Sakaria wasn't coming out.</bt><v n="22" />Waktu dia kaluar datang, dia su sonde bisa omong apa-apa lai. Ais dia kasi sein sang dong pake tangan, ju dong mangarti bilang, Tuhan su kasi tunju sang dia satu hal yang heran dalam itu Kamar Paling Barisi.<bt>When he came outside, he already could not speak anything. So he gave a sign to them using his hand/s, and they understood that the Lord had shown him an amazing thing inside that Most Clean/Holy Room.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dong pung tugas abis, ju Sakaria pulang pi dia pung ruma.<bt>When their task was over, then Sakaria went.home to his house.</bt><v n="24-25" />Sonde lama ju Elisabet dudu parú. Ju dia kurung diri dalam ruma sampe lima bulan. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Puji Tuhan! Ahirnya Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta. Kalo beta su dapa turunan, orang dong su sonde bekin malu sang beta lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long then Elisabet was pregnant. Then she secluded herself in the house for five months. She spoke saying, “Praise the Lord! Finally the Lord has shown His good liver (=grace) to me. If/when I have a descendant, people will no longer shame me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kurung diri = isolate herself, seclude"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kurung diri = isolate herself, seclude herself (if s.t. if wrong with you (physical, social or emotional), if you're going to get married, gila)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga datang katumu deng Maria<bt>The Lord's underling from heaven comes to meet with Maria</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Waktu Elisabet pung parú su jalan anam bulan, ju Tuhan Allah kirim Dia pung ana bua dari sorga, pi satu kampong di propinsi Galilea, nama Nasaret. Itu ana bua pung nama, Gabriel.<bt>When Elisabet's stomach=womb had been going for six months, then the Lord God send His underling from heaven, to go to a village in Galilea province, named Nasaret. That underling's name was Gabriel.</bt><v n="27" />Di Nasaret ada satu nona, nama Maria. Maria su batunangan deng satu laki-laki, nama Yusuf. Yusuf tu, raja Daud pung turunan. Naa, Gabriel pi katumu deng itu nona Maria.<bt>In Nasaret there was a young.girl, named Maria. Maria was already engaged with a male, named Yusuf. That Yusuf was a descendant of raja Daud. So [shift=story starts] Gabriel went to meet that young.girl Maria.</bt><note reference="1:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 1:18</note><v n="28" />Dia kasi tunju dia pung diri sang itu nona, ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Salamat, nona, ó! Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang lu, ko mau bekin satu hal bae kasi sang lu. Tuhan Allah ada sama-sama deng lu, Maria.&gt;&gt;<bt>He showed himself to that young.girl, then he said, “Greeting, young.girl! The Lord God has chosen you-sg, in order to do something good for you. The Lord God is with you, Maria.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, ju Maria bingung deng itu ana bua pung omong. Dia sonde mangarti dia pung maksud apa.<bt>Hearing like that, then Maria was confused at that underling's speaking. She did not understand what is meaning/intention was.</bt><v n="30" />Ju itu ana bua sambung lai bilang,<bt>Then that underling continued again saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Maria! Lu sonde usa taku.<bt>“Maria! You-sg do not need to be afraid. (=polite imperative, assuring, don't be afraid)</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Tuhan Allah pung maksud kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang lu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord God's intention is to show His good liver (*grace) to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="31" />Sonde lama lai, lu su dudu parú,<bt>Not much longer, you will be pregnant,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais nanti lu barana ame satu ana laki-laki.<bt>then later you will give.birth to a male child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Lu musti kasi nama sang Dia, <span class="Italic">Yesus.</span><bt>You must name Him, <span class="Italic">Yesus.</span></bt><note reference="1:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Ibrani, <span class="Italic">Yeshua</span> pung arti bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah kasi salamat orang&gt;. &lt;Yeshua&gt; tu, andia <span class="Italic">Yesus</span> dalam bahasa Yunani. Lia ju Mateos 1:21.<bt>In the Ibrani language, the meaning of <span class="Italic">Yeshua</span> is &lt;Lord God saves people&gt;. That &lt;Yeshua&gt; [name], is <span class="Italic">Yesus</span> in the Yunani language. See also Mateos 1:21.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="32" />Dia nanti jadi Orang bésar.<bt>He will become a big=important Person.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti Tuhan subu sang Dia bilang, &lt;Dia tu, Beta pung Ana sandiri.&gt;<bt>Later God will refer to Him saying, ‘He is My very own Child.’ [EXEG: "God calls Him" from Gk grammar, Marshall p. 67, and HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Andia, Ana dari Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi.<bt>That is, the Child from the Lord God who is the Very Highest.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Tuhan Allah angka sang Dia ko pegang parenta,<bt>Later Lord God will lift/raise (appoint) Him up to hold power,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke Dia pung nene-moyang raja Daud.<bt>the same as His ancestor raja Daud.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypsistos: taken as equivalent to 'El"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hypsistos: taken as equivalent to 'El 'Elyon in the Melchizedek story.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="33" />Dia yang nanti pegang parenta tarús-tarús sang orang Isra'el dong.<bt>He will be the one who later rules continually over the Israel people.</bt><note reference="1:33" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;Dia parenta sang Yakob pung ruma&gt;. Dia pung maksud bilang, &lt;Dia parenta sang orang Isra'el dong&gt;.<bt>The Yunani language writes saying, ‘He rules/commands Yakob's house’. It's meaning/intention says, ‘He rules/commands Israel people’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Dia pung parenta sonde tau abis-abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) His ruling/commanding will not end.”</bt><note reference="1:32-33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:12, 13, 16, Yesaya 9:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma Maria tanya sang Gabriel bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, sonde parná tidor bakumpul deng satu laki-laki ju! Karmana ko beta bisa dudu parú?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Maria asked Gabriel saying, “I here, have never slept together with a single male! How can I become pregnant?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais Gabriel manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Nanti Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi datang sang lu. Deng Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung kuasa nanti tutu ame sang lu. Deng bagitu, Ana yang nanti lu barana ame tu, batúl-batúl barisi. Te Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana.<bt>Then Gabriel replied saying, “Like this! Later God's Holy Spirit will come to you. And the power of the Lord God who is the Very Highest will later cover over you. In that way, that Child which later you will give.birth.to, will be truly-truly clean/holy. Cuz (elaboration) He will be the Lord God's Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to gennoomenon: the baby that is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">to gennoomenon: the baby that is being conceived kleetheesetai: will be called (by God) Holy and Son of God<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Jang heran! Te lu pung kelu satu, nama Elisabet, su dudu parú ju. Orang bilang dia su sonde bisa barana tagal dia su tua. Ma sakarang dia pung parú su jalan anam bulan.<bt>Don't be amazed/surprised! Cuz (elaboration) one of your family members named Elisabet, is already pregnant too. People say/said she was not able to give.birth, because she is already old. But now her stomach/womb has been going for six months. [EXEG: commentators do not know the precise relationship between Mary and Elizabeth. See Ex. Summ for best synopsis. So can't determine vocative for vs.42 as “kakak” or “adik”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@streamlined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@streamlined</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Te buat Tuhan Allah, samua bisa jadi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) for the Lord God, everything can happen!”</bt><note reference="1:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ais Maria manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae. Beta ni Tuhan Allah pung hamba. Biar ko samua jadi iko ke bapa pung omong tu. Beta sadia iko Tuhan pung mau sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Maria replied saying, “Ok. I here am the Lord God's servant. May it be that everything happens according to that speaking of yours. I am prepared to follow only the Lord's will.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais ju itu ana bua dari sorga jalan kasi tenga sang dia.<bt>And then that underling from heaven went leaving her behind.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Maria pi lia sang Elisabet<bt>Maria goes to see Elisabet</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39-40" />Lewat barapa hari, ju Maria buru-buru barangkat dari Nasaret pi Sakaria pung kampong di propinsi Yudea pung da'era bagunung. Sampe di situ, dia maso memang di Sakaria pung ruma. Ju dia kasi salam sang Elisabet.<bt>After several days, then Maria quickly left Nasaret and went to Sakaria's village in the mountain region of Yudea province. Arriving there, she entered straight away into Sakaria's house. Then she gave greetings to Elisabet. [DISCOURSE: Nasaret from v.26--required here from RL discourse patterns for foreground-background structure.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Waktu Elisabet dapa dengar Maria pung salam tu, ju itu ana dalam Elisabet pung parú bakosi. Deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi datang maso sang Elisabet.<bt>When Elisabet heard those greetings of Maria, then that child in Elisabet's stomach kicked. And the Lord's Holy Spirit came and entered Elisabet.</bt><v n="42" />Ais dia pange kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Maria! Nanti orang dong angka nae lu pung nama lebe dari samua parampuan di ini dunya! Nanti orang dong ju angka nae itu Ana yang ada di dalam lu pung parú!<bt>Then she called out saying, “Maria! Later people will elevate your name (=praise, axalt) more than all the women in this world! Later people will also elevate that Child which is in your stomach! [NOTE to daughter translations: see note at 1:36 re: Elizabeth's relationship to Mary.]</bt><v n="43" />Beta ju iko ta'angka, tagal beta pung Bos pung mama datang katumu sang beta.<bt>I also follow/participate.in elevating, because my Bos' mama has come to meet me.</bt><v n="44" />Bagitu lu maso datang kasi salam sang beta, langsung beta pung ana dalam parú ju bakosi tagal sanáng.<bt>When you came in and gave greetings to me, immediately my child in [my] stomach also kicked because of being happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***dropped second vocative and \p"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***dropped second vocative and \p</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang lu, tagal lu parcaya bilang, Dia mau bekin iko Dia pung janji.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Lord God has shown His good lier to you, because you believe that He will do according to His promise.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Maria puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah<bt>Maria praise the Lord God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Maria angka suara bilang,<bt>Maria lifted her voice (=began to talk) saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dari beta pung hati yang paling dalam,<bt>“From my inner-most liver,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">beta angka nae tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan!<bt>I lift the Lord up high!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="47" />Beta pung hati babunga,<bt>My liver is happy,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati babunga = hati sanang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">hati babunga = hati sanang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang beta!<bt>because the Lord God has saved me!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="48" />Dia su taro mata bae-bae sang beta,<bt>He has put his eye carefully on me (=watched over me),</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Helong &lt;&lt;he looks at me well,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Helong &lt;&lt;he looks at me well, even though I am His slave who has no meaning&gt;&gt; CHECK @@@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung orang suru-suru yang sonde ada pung arti ni.<bt>this servant of His who has no meaning (=is worthless).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doulees: cannot be &quot;worka guy.&quot; SK."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">doulees: cannot be "worka guy." SK.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mulai sakarang samua orang nanti anggap beta ni,<bt>Starting from now all people will regard me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">parampuan yang paling ontong,<bt>as the woman who is the most fortunate, [EXEG: Gk /makarios/ means “in a fortunate state of affairs”. “Blessed” is church lg and /berkat/ doesn't fit context. Translations of “happy” and “berbahagia” skew the focus unacceptably, because Gk term does not have element of “feelings” in it.]</bt><note reference="1:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 1:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="49" />tagal Tuhan bekin hal-hal heran kasi sang beta.<bt>because God does/has.done amazing things for me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia tu, yang Paling Kuasa deng Paling Barisi.<bt>He is the one who is Most Powerful and Most Clean/Holy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="onoma: name = character"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">onoma: name = character</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="50" />Tuhan Allah salalu kasi tunju rasa kasian sang samua orang yang hormat deng sémba sang Dia,<bt>The Lord God always shows his compassion to all people who honor and worship Him,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi hati = 1) manjakan, spoil,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kasi hati = 1) manjakan, spoil, 2) show mercy, murah hati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari turunan satu pi turunan laen.<bt>from one descendant.group (generation) to the other descendant.group.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="51" />Dia pake Dia pung kuasa,<bt>He uses His power/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko bekin kaco sang orang yang kapala bésar dong.<bt>to confuse people who have big heads (=proud). [EXEG: 1) scatter proud people (ignores some Gk words and has collocational problems), or 2) mess up plans of proud people -- we take #2; Gilles says “UNS interpreted dong pung akal busuk as evil, cagey”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko bekin kaco sang orang kapala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ko bekin kaco sang orang kapala bésar dong pung akal busuk.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="52" />Dia kasi jato orang yang pegang kuasa dong,<bt>He drops/topples.over people who hold power,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dong pung tinggi hati.<bt>because of their high liver (=pride).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Ma Dia angka nae orang yang randá hati dong.<bt>But He lifts up people who have low livers (=humble)</bt><note reference="1:52" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 5:11, 12:19</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="53" />Dia kasi makan orang lapar dong sampe kinyang,<bt>He feeds hungry people until they are full,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia usir buang orang kaya dong<bt>but He chases away the rich people</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko pi deng tangan kosong.<bt>to go with empty hands.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="54" />Dia tolong Dia pung orang Isra'el dong,<bt>He helps His Israel people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng salalu tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang dong.<bt>and always shows His compassion to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="55" />Dolu Dia ika janji deng kotong pung nene-moyang,<bt>Previously He tied a promise with our ancestor,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">andia ba'i Abraham deng dia pung turunan samua.<bt>that is, grandfather/Ancestor Abraham and all his descendants.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Sakarang itu janji ada ta'ika tarús-tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>Now that promise is continually tied.”</bt><note reference="1:46-55" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:7; 1 Samuel 2:1-10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="56" />Ais Maria tenga deng Elisabet sampe tiga bulan. Ju dia pulang pi dia pung ruma di Nasaret.<bt>Then Maria stayed with Elisabet for three months. Then she went.home to her house in Nasaret.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Elisabet barana ame sang Yohanis<bt>Elisabet gives birth to Yohanis</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Bagitu dia pung waktu su sampe, ju Elisabet barana ame satu ana laki-laki.<bt>When the time arrived, then Elisabet gave.birth to a male child.</bt><v n="58" />Itu kabar tasiar pi dia pung kelu deng isi kampong dong bilang, Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae deng kasi satu ana sang Elisabet. Ju dong samua iko sanáng.<bt>That news spread to her family and the entire village, that the Lord God has shown his good liver and given a child to Elisabet. And they all followed along (=participated.in) happiness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emegalynen ... to eleos autou met'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">emegalynen ... to eleos autou met' autees:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Waktu itu ana umur dalapan hari, ju dong sunat sang dia, iko orang Yahudi pung atoran. Dong mau kasi nama itu ana, Sakaria, iko dia pung bapa pung nama.<bt>When that child was eight days old, then they circumcised him, according to the Yahudi people's regulation. They want to name that child, Sakaria, following his father's name.</bt><note reference="1:59" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:3</note><v n="60" />Ma dia pung mama protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde bisa bagitu! Dia pung nama, musti Yohanis!&gt;&gt;<bt>But his mama protested saying, “It can't be like that! His name must be Yohanis!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Ma dong balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Kanapa pili nama Yohanis? Sonde ada satu orang ju di bosong pung kelu, yang ada pake itu nama!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they replied saying, “Why choose the name Yohanis? There is not a single person in your family who uses that name!”</bt><v n="62" />Ju dong kasi sein sang Sakaria, ko mau cari tau dia mau kasi nama sapa sang itu ana.<bt>Then they gave a sign to Sakaria, to find out what he wanted to name that child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Sakaria sein ko minta batu tulis. Dong kasi, ais dia tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung nama Yohanis!&gt;&gt; Ju samua orang taheran-heran.<bt>Sakaria made a sign asking for a writing stone. They gave it, then he wrote saying, “His name is Yohanis!” Then all the people were amazed. [NOTE to daughter translations: ‘writing tablet’ was probably wood with a layer of wax. In Timor region some older generation knows ‘slate tablet’ for schools, which is fine (maps function). But if younger generation doesn't know it, consider descriptive phrase ‘board/wood for writing on’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="64" />Takuju sa, ju Sakaria pung lida yang takancing tu, noe memang. Ju dia angka puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly, that tongue of Sakaria's which was tight/locked, became immediately loose/pliable. And he lifted up praise to the Lord God.</bt><v n="65" />Samua orang yang tenga deka-deka di situ dong, taku deng heran. Ju itu carita tasiar dari mulu pi mulu, sampe orang di gunung-gunung di propinsi Yudea dong ju tau abis.<bt>All the people who were staying/living nearby, were afraid and amazed. Then that news spread from mouth to mouth, until the people in the mountains fo Yudea province also knew all about it.</bt><v n="66" />Orang dong yang dengar itu carita, pikir-pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Su jalás, Tuhan pung kuasa ada sama-sama deng itu ana. Nanti dia bésar datang, dia jadi manusia model ke apa, ó?&gt;&gt;<bt>People who heard that story, thought saying, “It's clear, the Lord's power is with that child. Later when he grows up, what kind of human will he be, ó [=we wonder]?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="campor tangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">campor tangan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ethento ... en teei kardiaai autoon:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ethento ... en teei kardiaai autoon: pondered, stored it up in their hearts (synonymous with 2:19)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sakaria puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah<bt>Sakaria praises the Lord God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="67" />Ais ju Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi datang maso di Sakaria. Andia ko dia omong bilang,<bt>Then the Lord's Holy Spirit came and entered Sakaria. That's why he spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="68" />&lt;&lt;Puji Tuhan, orang Isra'el pung Allah!<bt>“Praise the Lord, the Israel people's God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Dia su datang ko tabús ame Dia pung orang dong,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He has already come to redeem His people,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***kasi tabus &gt; tabus ame tabús"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***kasi tabus &gt; tabus ame tabús - redeem<span class="Italic">(68)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar dong jang sama ke budak.<bt>so that they are not like slaves [EXEG: expanding "freed from what?"].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lytroosin: moral or political: the prayer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">lytroosin: moral or political: the prayer sounds more political.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="69" />Tuhan su angka ame satu Orang yang Dia pung kuasa hebat,<bt>The Lord has lifted up a Person whose power is amazing,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko nanti kasi salamat sang kotong.<bt>in order to later save us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sooteeria: nonspecific - doesn't say whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">sooteeria: nonspecific - doesn't say whether it's a bad situation (this prayer seems to have political overtones) or moral evil inside us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia tu, dari raja Daud pung turunan.<bt>That person, is from raja Daud's decendants.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="70" />Tuhan su janji memang ini samua dari dolu-dolu,<bt>The Lord has promised beforehand all this from long ago,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** clarified pronoun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** clarified pronoun</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pake Dia pung jubir yang satia dong.<bt>using His faithful spokespersons. [EXEG: "holy prophets" nonsensical in literal translation "clean prophets"; "holy" = set aside, dedicated, consecrated, special &gt; faithful, as a quality which can distinguish spokespersons.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="71" />Sakarang Dia mau kasi lapás sang kotong<bt>Now He want to free us-inc</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari kotong pung musu-musu,<bt>from our enemies,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dari orang-orang yang saki hati sang kotong.<bt>and from people who are sick.livered (=hate, resentful) toward us-inc.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="72-73" />Dia kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong,<bt>He showed His good liver to our-inc ancestors,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dia inga tarús Dia pung janji sang dong,<bt>because He continually remembered His promise to them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang Dia ika deng ba'i Abraham.<bt>which He tied with grandfather Abraham.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="74" />Dia su kasi lapás sang kotong dari kotong pung musu dong,<bt>He has freed us-inc from our enemies,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko kotong bisa sémba sang Dia,<bt>so that we-inc can worship Him, [EXEG: interlinear 'serve' is actually 'worship' in the lexicon.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng sonde parlú taku-taku lai.<bt>and don't need to be afraid again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@use of pake ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@use of pake ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="75" />Dia su kasi lapás sang kotong,<bt>He has freed us,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar kotong bisa idop barisi deng lurus tarús-tarús di Dia pung muka.<bt>so that we can live continually live cleanly/holy and straightly (=righteously) in front of Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="76" />Anis! Lu ni, beta pung ana.<bt>Anis (Johnny, nickname)! You here are my child. [DISCOURSE: Vocative to show shift from addressing God to addressing the baby.] [CAUTION: Some lgs can address an infant as “Father, ee [+how you address a child affectionately]”. But this causes a clash from just having addressed God. Could insert quote margin for change of addressee.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang nanti kanál sang lu bilang, lu ni, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung jubir.<bt>Later people will recognise you, saying that you here, are the spokesperson of the Most High Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lu nanti pi kasi tau orang dong,<bt>You will go tell people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong buka tangan tarima Bos pung datang.<bt>so that they open their hands (=are hospitable) to receive the Boss' coming. [EXEG: Bos from Gk. kyrios.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sadia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sadia</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypsistos: equivalent to 'El 'Elyon (Da"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hypsistos: equivalent to 'El 'Elyon (Da Start 14:19)</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:76" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="77" />Lu nanti pi kasi tunju jalan sang Tuhan pung orang dong,<bt>You will go show/reveal the path to the Lord's people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong dapa tau bilang, dong dapa salamat,<bt>so that they can know that, they can be be saved, [NOTE to daughter translations: If in your language /dapa salamat/ is the same as /dapa idop/, then change to /dong bisa idop deng Tuhan Allah/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan hapus buang dong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>because the Lord has erased away their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamartia: this is &quot;sin,&quot; not &quot;difficulties&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hamartia: this is "sin," not "difficulties" or "bad circumstances."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="78-79" />Tagal Tuhan pung hati noe deng kasian sang kotong,<bt>Because the Lord's liver is soft/tender and merciful/pityful toward us,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="splagkhna: here &quot;big heart&quot; is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">splagkhna: here "big heart" is the functional equivalent</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">andia ko Dia kasi kotong kasampatan baru,<bt>that's why He has given us new opportunity,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke hari baru bawa taráng yang baru.<bt>like a new day bring new light.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong yang jalan dalam galáp,<bt>We who walk in the dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kotong yang taku mati,<bt>and we who are afraid to die,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal balóm babae deng Tuhan,<bt>because we are not yet in a good.relationship (=relational peace) with the Lord, [EXEG: one sense of Gk /eirene/]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dapa taráng ko antar sang kotong pi jalan dame.&gt;&gt;<bt>later will get light to escort us to the path of peace (broader range for peace).” [EXEG: another sense of Gk /eirene/] [NOTE: in next to last clause, /badame/ changed to /babae/ so not heavy with last clause, Both reinforce the picture of what the problem and solution are in 77-79.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:79" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 9:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="80" />Ais ju Yohanis tamba hari, tamba bésar. Deng Tuhan pung Roh bekin kuat sang dia. Dia bésar datang, ju dia pi tenga di tampa sunyi, sampe dia mulai angka dia pung karjá kasi orang Isra'el dong.<bt>Then Yohanis got older, got bigger. And the Lord's Spirit made him strong. When he grew up, then he went to live in a desolate/quiet place, until he started his work among the Israel people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Maria barana sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Maria gives.birth to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 1:18-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1-2" />Satu kali, waktu Kirenius jadi kapala da'era di Siria, ais raja bésar, nama Agustus, kasi kaluar parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua orang yang di bawa pamarenta Roma pung kuasa musti pulang kampong ko iko sensus!&gt;&gt; Itu kali partama ko pamarenta Roma itong dia pung rakyat bagitu.<bt>One time, when Kirenius was the head of the region in Siria, then the big raja, named Agustus, sent out a command saying, “All people who are under the governance of Roma's authority must return.home to their [ancestral] village to participate in a census!” That was the first time for the Roma government to count is populace like that.</bt><v n="3" />Jadi samua orang pulang kampong ko iko sensus.<bt>So (consequently) all the people returned to their [ancestral] village to participate in the census.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-5" />Naa, itu waktu, Yusuf tenga di kampong Nasaret di propinsi Galilea. Dia su batunangan deng satu nona, nama Maria, yang ada dudu parú. Yusuf tu, raja Daud pung turunan, jadi dia musti pulang pi Daud pung kota Betlehem di propinsi Yudea ko iko sensus.<bt>Naa [discourse shift], at that time, Yusuf was living in Nasaret village in Galilea province. He was already engaged to a young.girl, named Maria, who was pregnant. That Yusuf was raja Daud's descendant, so he had to return.home to Daud's Bethlehem city in Yudea province to participate in the census.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** 1st clause changed so doesn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** 1st clause changed so doesn't sound like first introduction of Yusuf (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Andia ko dong dua barangkat pi kota Betlehem.<bt>That's why the two of them left to go to Bethlehem city.</bt><v n="6" />Waktu dong su ada di sana, Maria pung waktu mau barana su sampe.<bt>While they were already there, Maria's time for giving.birth arrived. [EXEG: It sounds as if they were in Bethlehem for some time, because it was "during" (en tooi einai autous ekei) that time that the baby came due.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added /su/ to 1st"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) added /su/ to 1st sentence to get them arrived in Bethlehem (DISCOURSE)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong pung sampe di sana, pas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Dong pung sampe di sana, pas deng Maria pung waktu mau barana.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma di situ, dong sonde dapa kamar di losmen. Andia ko dong maso pi dalam kandang. Ais ju dia barana Ana partama, Ana laki-laki. Ju dong bungkus sang Dia deng kaen, ko kasi tidor dalam binatang dong pung tampa makan.<bt>But there, they did not find a room in the inn. That's why they entered into a stall/stable/pen. Then she gave.birth to her first Child, a male Child. Then they wrapped Him with cloth, and laid him to sleep in the animal's eating place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hako = tampa makan-minum babi; dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">hako = tampa makan-minum babi; dari kayu, batang tuak, giant clam, feeding trough; kaen puruk = old cloth suda lama sehingga robek-robek. kaen loyor; maslili = wrap &amp; carry; masa'a = shoulder.carry; su'u = carry on head; pasanggrahan = tempat penginapan (commercial) (etym from persinggahan); losmen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Note Bailey's reading of &quot;katalyma&quot; as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Note Bailey's reading of "katalyma" as "guest room," not "inn." The scenario is that Joseph had relatives in Bethlehem, his family town of origin. Their guest room (katalyma is also translated "upper room" in the Last Supper story) was already occupied with other relatives who had come in for the registration, so Joseph and Mary lived with the family on the ground floor, in the raised living area bordered by a dirt area for the animals, whose mangers were built into the outside wall. It sounds as if they were in Bethlehem for some time, because it was "during" (en tooi einai autous ekei) that time that the baby came due.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang gambala dong<bt>The Lord God tells the shepherds</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Itu malam, ada gambala barapa orang yang mete jaga dong pung kambing-domba di padang di luar kota.<bt>That night, there were several shepherds who were staying.awake.at.night watching their goats-sheep in a field outside the city.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00013C.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top">Gambala dong mete jaga kambing-domba<bt>Herders stay awake guarding flocks</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Takuju sa, dong dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga. Ais Tuhan pung taráng bacaya kuliling sang dong, ju dong taku mau mati.<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly, they saw the Lord God's underling from heaven. Then the Lord's light shone surrounding them, and they were very afraid. [EXEG: Gk: glory shone here]</bt><v n="10" />Ma itu ana bua kasi tau bilang,<bt>But that underling told saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong jang taku dolo! Dengar bae-bae, é! Te beta ni, datang mau kasi tau satu kabar bae kasi bosong. Samua yang dengar ini kabar, pasti sanáng.<bt>“You-pl don't be afraid [imperative]! Listen well! Cuz I have come to tell a good news/report to you. Everyone who hears this news, will certainly be happy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Ini kabar bae pung isi bagini:<bt>The contents of the good news are like this: [DISCOURSE: common intro to contents of a message]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ini hari satu mama su barana sang Kristus di Betlehem, di raja Daud pung kota.<bt>Today a mother has given.birth to Kristus, in Bethlehem, the city of raja Daud's.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ reordered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ reordered</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Kristus tu, Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu.<bt>That Kristus is the Person whom the Lord God has promised beforehand from long ago. [EXEG: explicates “Christ” following TBT article on translating meaning of Christ (the rank). Smith, Jill and Dr. Harold Fehderau. 1981. Translating Christ and Messiah in the NT. TBT 32(4):423-431. (Also, for help with the meaning of “in Christ,” see Hale, Clarence B. 1991. The Meaning of “in Christ.” SIL.) This is following standard SIL and UBS practice, based on those (and related) articles. This is part of the meaning that the shepherds would have understood.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** restructured (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** restructured (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan kirim datang sang Dia ko kasi salamat orang dari dong pung sala-sala!<bt>The Lord send Him to save people from their wrongs! [EXEG: explicates “Saviour”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia ni, yang nanti orang dong pange, &lt;Bos&gt;, te Dia yang hak parenta samua!<bt>He is the one whom people will call, &lt;Bos&gt;, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who has the right to command/govern every(one/thing)! [EXEG: explicates “Lord”. Note: In English church language ‘Lord’ can stand alone. But in Kupang and other lgs, Bos/Lamatua (etc.) either needs to be possessed, or be in relation to something or someone. /Kotong pung Bos/ would be misread here as ‘Bos of the angels’, but the context is clearly announcing the coming of the Messiah in relation to salvation of humans--hence this rendering. In local church usage ‘Tuhan, Lamatua (etc)’ by itself will almost always trace back to God, not Christ, and is described as ‘the being we worship’, and never ‘the one we obey, who has the say-so rights over us’. By making it possessed, or in relation to something, we can force the latter understanding, which brings out a meaning element important to the Gk /kurios/. Last clause added after stand-alone term ‘Bos’ was shown to repeatedly skew the focus. May not be needed in daughter translations.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Nanti bosong dapa kanál sang Dia bagini: bosong katumu satu Ana mea yang ada tabungkus deng kaen. Dia ada tidor dalam binatang dong pung tampa makan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later you will recognise Him like this: you-pl will meet/find a red/newborn Child who is wrapped with cloth. He is sleeping/lying in animal's eating place.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katumu = meet ; find (wallet)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">katumu = meet ; find (wallet)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu ana bua omong abis ju, takuju sa, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua yang laen dong dari sorga datang bam-banya ko bakumpul deng dia. Ju dong puji Tuhan Allah deng manyanyi bilang,<bt>He finished speaking like that, then unexpectedly, lots and lots of the Lord God's angels came and gathered with him. Then they praise the Lord God and sang saying, [NOTE to daughter translations: ‘singing’ is not in Greek. It is here as generic action (praise) -- specific symbolic action associated with praise (singing). The contextual sense of celebration doesn't come through without it. NRSV similarly translates /legei/ as ‘sing’ in several places in Rev.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />&lt;&lt;Botong angka nae tinggi-tinggi Tuhan Allah pung nama!<bt>“We lift up high the Lord God's name! [EXEG: Gk: glory to God, here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang dudu parenta di langit yang paling tinggi.<bt>He is the one who sits holding power in the highest sky.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypsistois: the highest realms (probably not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hypsistois: the highest realms (probably not "the most high God"; the contrast is with "on earth")</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan Allah mau kasi dame sang orang di bumi,<bt>The Lord God wants to grant peace to people on earth,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin dame = make peace with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bekin dame = make peace with ; kirim kasi dame = grant peace to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peace: spiritual prosperity, wholeness, salvation; shalom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">peace: spiritual prosperity, wholeness, salvation; shalom</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bekin sanáng Dia pung hati!&gt;&gt;<bt>who make His liver happy!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais ju Tuhan pung ana bua dong pulang kambali pi sorga. Ju itu gambala dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mari kotong pi Betlehem ko pi lia itu Ana dolo! Te Tuhan su kirim itu kabar kasi kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the Lord's *underlings returned back to heaven. Then those shepherds spoke to each other saying, “We! [+get attention] Let's go to Bethlehem to see that child! Cuz the Lord has sent that news to us-inc.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais dong jalan capát-capát pi Betlehem. Ju dong katumu sang Maria deng Yusuf. Dong ju dapa lia itu Ana mea, yang ada tidor dalam binatang pung tampa makan.<bt>Then they quickly went to Bethlehem. And they met Maria and Yusuf. They also saw that newborn Child, who was sleeping in the animal's eating place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu dong dapa lia itu Ana, ju dong carita bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadi Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga dong su kasi tau so'al ini Ana sang botong!&gt;&gt; Ju dong carita samua sampe abis.<bt>When they saw that Child, then they narrated saying, “Earlier the Lord God's underlings from heaven told about this Child to us-exc!” And they told the entire story.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Samua orang taheran-heran dengar itu gambala dong pung carita.<bt>Everyone was amazed at hearing those shepherd's story.</bt><v n="19" />Ma Maria taro dalam dia pung hati samua yang su jadi tu. Deng dia pikir diam-diam ko mau cari tau dia pung arti bilang apa.<bt>But Maria put in her liver, all those things that happened. And she thought quietly seeking to understand what they meant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="simpan dalam hati does not mean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">simpan dalam hati does not mean simpan hati</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ais ju itu gambala dong bale pi dong pung kambing-domba dong. Ju dong angka nae tinggi-tinggi Tuhan Allah pung nama. Dong minta tarima kasi sang Dia, tagal yang dong dengar deng lia, sama parsís ke apa yang Tuhan pung ana bua su omong tu.<bt>Then those shepherds returned to their goats-sheep. And they lifted up high the Lord God's name. They reciprocated thankyou to Him, because what they heard and saw, was exactly like that speaking of the Lord's underling.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Itu Ana mea, dong kasi nama <span class="Italic">Yesus</span><bt>That newborn, they name <span class="Italic">Yesus</span></bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Barana abis dalapan hari, ju dong sunat itu Ana mea iko ba'i Musa pung atoran. Ju Dia pung mama-bapa kasi nama sang Dia, &lt;Yesus&gt;. Itu nama tu, nama yang ana bua dari sorga su kasi tau sang dong, waktu Dia pung mama balóm dudu parú sang Dia.<bt>Eight days after giving.birth, then they circumcised that Newborn, according to Gf/Ff Musa's regulation. Then His father-mother named Him, ‘Yesus’. That name, is the name which the underling from heaven told to them, when His mother was not yet pregnant with Him.</bt><note reference="2:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 1:31, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa Ana mea Yesus pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>They bring newborn Yesus to the Central Worship House</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ada satu atoran dari ba'i Musa yang bilang, parampuan yang su barana abis ampa pulu hari, musti pi bekin iko adat kasi barisi diri di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Deng bagitu, dong su bisa maso di ruma sambayang sama ke biasa. Andia ko Yusuf deng Maria pi kota Yerusalem, ko mau bekin iko itu adat. Ju dong bawa dong pung Ana mea tu pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ko sarakan sang Dia jadi Tuhan pung milik.<bt>There is a regulation from grandfather Musa that says, forty days after a woman has given.birth, [she] must go do the ritual of cleaning herself in the Central Worship House. By doing like that, they could enter the worship house like usual. That's why Yusuf and Maria went to Yerusalem city to carry out that ritual. Then they brought that Newborn to the Central Worship House, to surrender Him to become the Lord's possession.</bt><note reference="2:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:1-8</note><v n="23" />Dong iko Tuhan pung atoran yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Tiap parampuan yang barana ana partama, kalo laki-laki, na, dia musti sarakan itu ana jadi Tuhan pung milik.&gt;&gt;<bt>They followed the Lord's regulation which says, “Every woman who gives.birth to [her] first child, if it is a male, na, she must surrender that child to become the Lord's possession.”</bt><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 13:2,12</note><v n="24" />Iko Tuhan pung atoran, kalo sarakan itu ana sang Tuhan, na, dia pung orang tua musti kasi korban burung takukur satu pasang, ko, burung pompa muda dua ekor. Andia ko Yusuf deng Maria ju bekin iko itu atoran.<bt>According to the Lord's regulation, if/when surrendering that child to the Lord, na, his parents must sacrifice a pair of takukur birds, or, a pidgeons/doves. That's why Yusuf and Maria also did according to that regulation.</bt><note reference="2:22-24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 12:6-8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ba'i Simeon bilang itu Ana mea Yesus tu, andia Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su janji<bt>Old grandfather Simeon says that that newborn Yesus, is Kristus whom the Lord God had promised</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Itu waktu, ada satu ba'i tua, nama Simeon, yang tenga di kota Yerusalem. Dia tu, orang yang hati lurus deng rindu sang Tuhan. Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi su kasi tau sang dia bilang, dia nanti dapa lia sang Kristus dolo, baru dia mati. Kristus tu, yang nanti kasi salamat sang orang Isra'el dong.<bt>At that time, there was an old grandfather, named Simeon, who lived in Yerusalem. He was a person whose liver was straight (=righteous) and he yearned for the Lord. The Lord's Holy Spirit had told him, that he would later get to see Kristus first, only then would he die. That Kristus is the one who will save the people of Isra'el.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** “consolation of Israel” added (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** “consolation of Israel” added (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu waktu, Tuhan pung Roh antar bawa sang Simeon pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Itu pas deng Yesus pung mama-bapa ada bawa sang Dia pi situ, ko sarakan sang Dia jadi Tuhan pung milik.<bt>At that time, the Lord's Spirit escorted brought Simeon to the Central Worship House. That was exactly when Yesus' father-mother were bringing Him there, to surrender Him to become the Lord's possession.</bt><v n="28" />Lia ame itu Ana, ais ba'i Simeon koko ame sang Dia, ju dia angka puji kasi Tuhan Allah bilang,<bt>Seeing that Child, then old.grandfather Simeon cuddled Him, and he lifted up praises to the Lord God saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="29" />&lt;&lt;Puji Tuhan!<bt>“Praise the Lord!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan su bekin iko Dia pung janji sang beta.<bt>The Lord has done according to His promise to me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi sakarang Tuhan su bisa kasi lapás sang beta,<bt>So (consequently) now the Lord can release me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar beta bisa mati deng tanáng,<bt>so that I can die quietly/peacefully,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireenee: inner peace, more than happiness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eireenee: inner peace, more than happiness</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="30" />te beta su lia ame Orang yang Tuhan kirim datang,<bt>cuz I have seen the Person whom the Lord sent/sends,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko kasi salamat sang botong dari botong pung sala-sala dong!<bt>to save us-exc from our-exc wrongs!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="31" />Tuhan mau pake ini Ana<bt>The Lord will use this Child</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko kasi salamat samua suku-bangsa.<bt>to save all nations/ethnic groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="32" />Dia nanti sama ke cahaya,<bt>Later he will be like rays.of.light,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bawa hormat kasi Tuhan pung bangsa Isra'el dong.<bt>which brings honour to the Lord's Israel ethnic groups/nations. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia ju sama ke taráng,<bt>He is/will.be also like light,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang kasi tunju Tuhan pung jalan<bt>which shows/reveals the Lord's path</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">kasi samua suku-bangsa laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>to all other ethnic groups/nations.” [NOTE: order reversed, structured as parallelism; "glory" -- "bring honor" (CEV)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: a light for revelation to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">NRSV: a light for revelation to the Gentiles and for glory to your people Israel.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 42:6, 49:6, 52:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yusuf deng Maria taheran-heran deng apa yang ba'i Simeon omong so'al dong pung Ana.<bt>Hearing like that, then Yusuf and Maria were amazed about what old.grandfather Simeon said about their Child.</bt><v n="34" />Ais itu, Simeon omong kasi berkat sang dong. Tarús dia kasi tau sang Maria bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus pung mama, é! Nanti banya orang di Isra'el tola buang mama pung Ana ni. Ma dong pung bekin-bekin sang Dia tu, nanti kasi jato bale sang dong. Mama pung Ana ni, ju bekin banya orang dong hati babunga.<bt>After that, Simeon spoke giving blessing to them. Then he told Maria saying, “Yesus' mother! Later many people in Israel will push.away/reject this child of mother's (=yours). But those doings/deeds of theirs, will later fall back on them. This Child of mother's (=yours), will also make many people liver flower (=happy/joyful).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seemeion: sign"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">seemeion: sign</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Deng bagitu, nanti Tuhan buka talanjang orang dong pung isi hati. Ma lu, Maria, nanti lu dapa sangsara barát, sama ke kalewang tikam maso di lu pung ulu hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>In that.way, later God will open naked the contents of people's livers. But you, Maria, later you will obtain heavy suffering, as if a sword pierces entering into your upper liver (=depths of your soul).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ulu hati = 2) inner core"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ulu hati = 2) inner core of your being/soul, the depths of your soul 1) be pung ulu hati saki = I have heart-burn/ heart attack</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng bagitu, nanti Tuhan buka kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Deng bagitu, nanti Tuhan buka kasi talanjang orang dong pung isi hati. yang batúl pung.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nene Hana minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan, tagal Yesus<bt>Grandmother Hana gives thanks to the Lord, because of Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36-37" />Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat ju ada satu nene, nama Hana. Dia pung umur su 84 taon. Dia pung bapa, nama Fanuel, dari suku Aser. Dia kawin tuju taon, ju dia pung laki mati kasi tenga sang dia. Nene Hana tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Dia pung karjá, andia sambayang deng puasa di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah siang-malam.<bt>In the Central Worship House, there was also a grandmother, named Hana. Her age was already 84 years. Her father, named Fanuel, was from the Aser clan. She was married seven years, then her husband died leaving her. That Grandmother Hana, was the Lord God's spokesperson. Her work was to pray and fast in the Central Worship/Prayer House to worship the Lord God day and night.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="latreuousa: performing religious rites"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">latreuousa: performing religious rites</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Waktu Simeon ada ba'omong deng Yusuf deng Maria, itu nene datang deka-deka. Ju dia dengar sang dong, ais dia angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah. Tarús dia omong so'al Yesus kasi samua orang yang ada tunggu-tunggu Raja yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang ko kasi bebas bangsa Isra'el.<bt>When Simeon was speaking with Yusuf and Maria, that grandmother came close by. Then she heard them, and she lifted up praises to the Lord God. Next she spoke about Yesus to all people who were waiting and waiting for the Raja whom the Lord had promised to send to free the Israel ethnic group. [EXEG: Marshall p.124 points out that Jerusalem is synecdoche for Israel. Also Green.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mama-bapa deng Ana kambali pi kampong Nasaret<bt>Father-mother and Child return to Nasaret village</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Waktu Yusuf deng Maria su bekin iko ba'i Musa pung atoran samua di kota Yerusalem, ju dong pulang pi propinsi Galilea, di dong pung kampong Nasaret.<bt>When Yusuf and Maria had did according to all grandfather Musa's regulations in Yerusalem city, then they returned.home to Galilea province, to their village Nasaret.</bt><note reference="2:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 2:23</note><v n="40" />Ju Yesus bésar datang. Ais Dia tamba kuat, tamba pintar, deng mangarti banya hal. Tuhan Allah ju kasi tunju hati bae sang Dia.<bt>And Yesus grew up. So He became increasingly strong, increasingly smart, and understood many things. The Lord God also showed his good liver (=was gracious) to Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nyong Yesus di Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>Young.boy Yesus at the Central Worship House</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Tiap taon, Yusuf deng Maria jalan pi kota Yerusalem, ko makan pesta Paska di situ.<bt>Each year, Yusuf and Maria travelled to Yerusalem city, to eat the Paska feast there.</bt><note reference="2:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 16:1-8</note><v n="42" />Satu kali, waktu Yesus pung umur dua blas taon, ju dong jalan sama-sama pi Yerusalem ko iko itu pesta sama ke biasa.<bt>One time, when Yesus was twelve years old, then they also went together to Yerusalem to participate in that feast like usual.</bt><v n="43-44" />Waktu hari-hari Paska su abis, ju Yusuf deng Maria mulai jalan pulang pi Nasaret sama-sama deng banya orang yang mau pulang pi Galilea. Ma dong sonde tau, Yesus ada tatenga di Yerusalem. Dong sangka Dia ada jalan sama-sama deng Dia pung tamán dong. Ma sampe sore, dong sonde dapa lia sang Dia. Ais dong mulai pal pi-datang cari sang Dia di dong pung kelu deng tamán dong.<bt>When the Paska days were over, then Yusuf and Maria began to travel home to Nasaret together with many people who want to go.home to Galilea. But they did not know, that Yesus was left.behind in Yerusalem. They assumed He was travelling together with His friends. But when it got to be late.afternoon, they could not see him. So they began to go back and forth hunting for Him among their family and friends.</bt><v n="45" />Tagal sonde tau-tau dapa katumu sang Dia, ju dong jalan kambali pi Yerusalem, ko mau cari sang Dia di sana.<bt>Because it became it apparent they were not finding Him, they travelled back to Yerusalem to look for Him there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Sampe di sana, dong cari-cari sang Dia sampe tiga hari, baru dapa katumu sang Dia dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dia ada dudu baso'al-jawab deng guru agama Yahudi dong.<bt>Arriving there, they kept hunting for Him for three days, only then finding Him in the Central Worship House. He was sitting mutually questioning-answering (=debating) with the Yahudi religion teachers.</bt><v n="47" />Orang dong samua yang ada dengar sang dong taheran-heran, tagal Dia batúl-batúl mangarti isi dari Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi, deng Dia bisa jawab dong pung so'al-so'al deng bae.<bt>All the people who were listening were amazed, because He truly understood the contents of the Lord God's Writing, and He could answer their questions well. [EXEG: Gk is "heard him", KM above is "heard them" focusing on situational context; this was a problem in Helong; if this comes up in another lg, suggest we change back to "heard him".]</bt><v n="48" />Lia bagitu, ju Dia pung mama-bapa dong heran. Ais Dia pung mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Akurang ko Lu bekin botong susa bagini? Lu pung bapa deng beta su tabingung-bingung bataputar pi-datang cari sang Lu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing that, then His father-mother were amazed. Then His mother said, “Yesus! Why are You causing trouble/worry for us-exc like this? Your father and I have been worried/confused going.all around here-there looking for You!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin susa sang botong = make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bekin susa sang botong = make trouble for us ; bekin botong susa = make us troubled/worried</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko mama-bapa susa-susa cari sang Beta? Tau sa, to? Beta ada urusan di Beta pung Bapa pung Ruma.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Why is mother-father worrying looking for Me? You know, don't you? I have matters.to.deal.with in My Father's House.”</bt><v n="50" />Ma dong sonde mangarti batúl Dia pung maksud.<bt>But they did not really understand His meaning/intent.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ais ju dong samua pulang pi Nasaret. Yesus iko Dia pung mama deng bapa pung parenta dong. Ju Dia pung mama taro itu hal dong samua dalam dia pung hati.<bt>Then they all returned.home to Nasaret. Yesus did according to his mother and father's commands. And his mother put all those things in her liver.</bt><v n="52" />Bagitu su, Yesus tamba dewasa, deng tamba pintar bawa diri. Tuhan Allah deng manusia ju ada sayang sang Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus increasingly became adult/mature, and increasely competent in handling himself. The Lord and humans also loved Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@I think the translation of this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@I think the translation of this verse can be improved (see Dhao) "increase in 1) physical development, 2) intellectual wisdom development, 3) spiritual development relationship with God, &amp; 4) social development, relationship with others." Bagitu ju - deleted</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:52" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 2:26, Kata-kata Mutiara 3:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani angka dia pung karjá<bt>Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer starts his work</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:1-12; Markus 1:1-8; Yohanis 1:19-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1-2" />Itu waktu, Tiberius jadi keser yang pegang parenta di Roma su lima blas taon. Pontius Pilatus jadi gubernor di propinsi Yudea. Herodes jadi gubernor di propinsi Galilea. Herodes pung kaka Filipus jadi gubernor di propinsi Iturea deng propinsi Trakonitis. Deng Lisanias jadi gubernor di propinsi Abilene.<bt>At that time, Tiberius was the keser who had been holding rule/government in Roma already fifteen years. Pontius Pilatus was governor in Yudea province. Herodes was governor in Galilea province. Herodes' elder.sibling Filipus, was governor in Iturea province and Trakonitis province. And Lisanias was governor in Abilene province. [EXEG: see IVP dict for kinship chart for the two Philips, plus discussion based on Josephus; also more complete under entry for ‘Herod’; TH says “Philip was Herod's older brother, of a different mother”; different Philip than the one in 3:19. See FTN.]</bt><note reference="3:1-2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pamarenta Roma pake satu orang Yahudi, nama <span class="Italic">Yosefus</span>, ko tulis sajara Isra'el di ini jaman. Dia ju tulis so'al orang yang pegang parenta deng dong pung kelu. Andia ko kotong tau bilang, Herodes di sini, pung nama laen, andia <span class="Italic">Herodes Antipas</span>. Dia pung bapa, andia <span class="Italic">Herodes Bésar</span> (Mateos 2:1-22; Lukas 1:5). <span class="Italic">Filipus</span> di sini, andia Herodes Antipas pung kaka. Filipus pung bapa, andia Herodes Bésar; dia pung mama, nama Kleopatra dari Yerusalem. Dia kawin deng Salome, andia Herodias pung ana. Di ayat 3:19 di bawa, ada <span class="Italic">Filipus</span> laen. Dia tu, Herodes Antipas pung adi. Dia pung bapa, Herodes Bésar ju; ma dia pung mama, nama Mariamne. Dia kawin deng Herodias. Dong dua pung ana nona, nama Salome. Ma dia pung kaka Herodes Antipas rampas ame dia pung bini. (Mateos 14:3; Markus 6:17; Lukas 3:19).<bt>The Roma government used a Yahudi person named <span class="Italic">Yosefus</span>, to write the history of Isra'el during this (time) period. He also wrote about people who ruled/governed and their families. That is why we-inc know that the Herodes here had another name, that is <span class="Italic">Herodes Antipas</span>. His father was Herodes the Great (Mateos 2:1-22; Lukas 1:5). The <span class="Italic">Filipus</span> here is Herodes Antipas' older brother. Filipus' father was also Herodes the Great; his mother was named Kleopatra from Yerusalem. He married Salome, that is Herodias' daughter. In verse 3:19 below, there is a different <span class="Italic">Filipus.</span> He is Herodes Antipas' younger brother. His father was also Herodes the Great; but his mother was named Mariamne. He married Herodias. The two of them had a daughter named Salome. But his older brother Herodes Antipas took/snatched away his wife. (Mateos 14:3; Markus 6:17; Lukas 3:19).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu ju, Hanas deng Kayafas jadi kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar di kota Yerusalem.<bt>At that time also, Hanas and Kayafas were the *high priests in Yerusalem city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu, Yohanis, Sakaria pung ana tu, ada tenga di tampa sunyi yang jao dari kampong. Di situ, Tuhan kasi pasán sang dia.<bt>At that time, Yohanis, that child of Sakaria's, was staying in a desolate/quiet place far from villages. There, the Lord gave instructions to him.</bt><v n="3" />Dengar abis, ju Yohanis jalan pi samua kampong yang deka-deka deng kali Yarden, ko kasi tau orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti mangaku deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala samua, ko biar Tuhan Allah hapus buang itu sala dong. Ais bosong musti sarani dolo, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong su babae deng Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>After hearing [them], then Yohanis travelled to all the villages which were near the Yarden river, to tell people saying, “You-pl must confess and leave behind all your wrongs, in order that the Lord God erase away those wrongs. Then you must get baptised [imperative], as a sign that you are in a good.relationship with God.” [NOTE: Gk in 3:3 is identical with Gk. in Mk 1:4.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dolu-dolu Tuhan pung jubir ba'i Yesaya ada tulis so'al Yohanis ni bilang,<bt>Long.ago, the Lord's spokesperson grandfather Yesaya wrote about this Yohanis saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada orang di tampa sunyi yang batarea bilang,<bt>“There is a person in an empty place (=wilderness) who is shouting saying, [NOTE: Gk in 3:4 is identical to Gk. in Mk 1:3]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Ada orang nanti pi di tampa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">&lt;&lt;Ada orang nanti pi di tampa yang sonde ada orang, ko batarea bilang:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Samua orang siap-siap bekin bae jalan, ko tarima Tuhan pung datang!<bt>&lt;All people prepare to make good/fix the way/path, to receive the Lord's coming!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin lurus jalan ko sambut sang Dia.<bt>Make straight the path to greet Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Tutu bekin rata tiap jurang.<bt>Close make flat every ravine/gorge.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="okofol = bekin rata, isi lobang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">okofol = bekin rata, isi lobang ; lagóng = jurang, lembah (not that big)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Puku bekin rata tiap gunung.<bt>Beat make flat every mountain.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin lurus jalan bengko dong,<bt>Make straight the crooked paths,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bekin licin jalan kasar dong.<bt>make smooth the rough paths.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Biar ko orang dari samua suku-bangsa<bt>So that people from every ethnic group</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bisa dapa tau bilang, Tuhan mau kasi salamat orang<bt>can know that the Lord wants to save people</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dari dong pung sala-sala.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>from their wrongs.”&gt;</bt><note reference="3:4-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3-5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Orang banya datang dari mana-mana ko minta Yohanis sarani sang dong. Ma dia masparak sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong tukang putar-balek! Bosong sama ke ular baracon sa! Jang kira bosong bisa talapás dari Tuhan pung hukuman deng tobat pura-pura sa! Sonde! Tar lama lai, Tuhan kasi hukum samua orang yang sonde tobat batúl.<bt>Many people came from all over the place to request Yohanis to baptise them. But he spoke angrily to them saying, “Weh! [+attention, + rebuke] You-pl habitual evil decievers! You are just like poisonous snakes! Don't think that you can be freed of the Lord's punishment by merely pretending to repent! No! (=you can't) Not much longer and the Lord will punish all people who do not truly repent. [EXEG: why “from all over the place”? 1) context, vs.3 “into all the region”; 2) Gk here “coming out” in Kupang /kaluar datang/ and other lgs needs a “from where”? 3) support from Mark 1:5 (normal hyperbole).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tobat = repent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tobat = repent</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tees mellousees orgees: the impending wrath."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">tees mellousees orgees: the impending wrath. This is not "bad kine stuff" in the same sense as the same phrase is used later in the same verse, also connected with "orgees".</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:34, 23:33</note><v n="8" />Bosong jang pikir bilang, &lt;Beta ni sonde kaná hukum tagal beta ni, ba'i Abraham pung turunan.&gt; Dapa di mana bagitu? Itu sonde bisa bantu bosong, tagal sonde bekin bosong jadi orang barisi. Tuhan mampu bekin ini batu dong ko jadi ba'i Abraham pung turunan. Beta kasi tau, é! Kasi tunju deng bosong pung idop bilang, bosong su bale balakang kasi tenga bosong pung sala dong, deng bosong su bale iko sang Tuhan.<bt>Don't you-pl think saying, ‘I won't get punishment because I am grandfather Abraham's descendant.’ Where did you get that? (=Where did you come up with that nonsense?) That cannot help you, because it doesn't make you become clean/holy people. The Lord is capable of making these stones here become grandfather Abraham's descendants. I'm telling (=I'm setting you straight here)! Show with your lives that you have turned your backs and left behind your wrongs, and you have turned to follow the Lord. [NOTE to daughter translations: if “Itu” isn't clear, clarify referent with “Being a descendant of Abr cannot...” Menjadi Abr pung turunan sonde bisa.../] [[NOTE to daughter translations: if focus is on repent, and the Abraham connection isn't coming through, put in ellipsed proposition at beginning /Kotong tau, bilang, ba'i Abraham tu, Tuhan Allah pung tamán. Ma bosong jang pikir.../]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Urus do! = No way! ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Urus do! = No way! ; Dapa di mana bagitu? = Where did you come up with that nonsense? ; Be kasi tau, é! = I'll set you straight. @@ have KM team help rephrase "Yes, you really are Abraham's descendants. But that's not enough to make /going to make you into good people!" *** (2009) last note added on focus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="be = beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">be = beta</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metanoia: &quot;like pau all da kine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">metanoia: "like pau all da kine bad stuff you doing" is more generic than "da bad kine stuff," which is more specific.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 8:33</note><v n="9" />Bosong musti bekin hal yang bae. Kalo sonde, Tuhan pung hukum barát jato kaná sang bosong, sama ke orang pake kapak ko potong buang pohon dari dia pung akar. Bagitu su! Pohon sonde ada pung guna, kalo dia sonde ada pung hasil bae! Jadi lebe bae potong sang dia, ais lempar buang pi dalam api.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl must do good things. If not, the Lord's heavy punishment will fall on you, like a person who uses an axe to cut down throw away a tree from its roots. Like that! A tree has no use, if it does not have good results/yield! So it's better to cut it, then throw it away in the fire.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hungga ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">hungga =</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais, itu orang banya dong tanya sang Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi botong musti bekin apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those people (crowds) asked Yohanis saying, “So (consequently), what must we-inc do?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu ada pung baju dua, na, kasi satu di orang yang sonde ada pung baju. Kalo lu ada pung makanan, na, bagi kasi sang orang yang sonde ada pung makanan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he answered saying, “If you-sg have two shirts, then give one to someone who does not have a shirt. If you have food, then give it to someone who does not have food.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais tukang tagi bea ju datang ko minta Yohanis sarani sang dong. Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa guru! Botong musti bekin karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the tax collectors also came and asked Yohanis to baptise them. They asked saying, “Father teacher! What must we-exc do?”</bt><note reference="3:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 7:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong suka maen putar-balek. Ma sakarang bosong musti karjá jujur. Jang hela pajak lebe-lebe dari pamarenta pung atoran. Biar ko rakyat bayar pajak pas-pas deng atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>He replied saying, “You-pl like to habitually decieve. But now you must work honestly. Don't pull more tax than the government's regulation. It's should be that the populace pays tax exactly according to the regulation.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="masarakat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">masarakat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong jang puku pajak lebe bésar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Bosong jang puku pajak lebe bésar dari yang pamarenta su putus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ada ju barapa tantara di situ. Dong tanya sang Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo botong, karmana? Botong musti bekin apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>There were also several soldiers there. They asked Yohanis saying, “What about us? What must we do?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang maen bapajak orang dong pung doi, iko bosong pung suka. Deng jang maen batudu orang sambarang. Bosong musti sukur deng puas tarima barisi bosong pung gaji.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he answered saying, “Don't habitually extort people's money, according to your own desires. And don't habitually accuse people heedlessly. You must be thankful and satisfied recieving your honest wage.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bapajak = extort ; gaji barisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bapajak = extort ; gaji barisi = official wages (no skims, extortions or additions ; Lawan = gaji kotor, makan gaji (al) Waktu tarima gaji, bosong musti minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan, deng rasa itu gaji cukup.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Dengar dia pung omong tu, ju samua orang mulai bakorek ko bakusu-kusu bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Jang-jang Yohanis ni, Kristus, yang Tuhan su janji mau kirim datang dari dolu tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing his speaking like that, then all the people began to scrap around (=investigate, look for clues) and to whisper to each other saying, “Awii! [+impressed] What if this Yohanis here is Kristus, that one whom the Lord promised to send long ago!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma Yohanis togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Nanti ada satu Orang yang lebe hebat dari beta mau datang. Biar cuma jadi Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa, ju beta sonde pantas.<bt>But Yohanis rebuked them saying, “Listen well! Later there is a Person who is more noteworthy than me going to come. Even to just be His *slave (person who is habitually ordered about), I'm not fitting/appropriate.</bt><note reference="3:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli bilang, &lt;mau buka dia pung tali sapatu sa ju, beta sonde pantas.&gt; Dia pung arti bilang, Yohanis cuma orang kici sa, biar jadi Tuhan Yesus pung tukang suru-suru ju, dia rasa sonde pantas.<bt>The original Yunani writing says, ‘even to open/untie his shoe strings, I am not worthy.’ That means that Yohanis is only just a small (=unimportant) person, and even just to become the Lord Yesus slave, he does not feel worthy.</bt></note>Beta cuma bisa sarani sang bosong pake aer sa, ma nanti Dia bekin lebe dari beta, te Dia bekin ponu bosong pung hati deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Dia nanti bekin barisi sang bosong, sama ke orang pake api ko bakar buang kotoran.<bt>I'm only able to *baptize you with water, but later He will do more than me, and He will make your-pl hearts (livers) full with *Lord's *Holy Spirit (=clean, free from impurities, undefiled, holy). He will make you clean, like a person uses fire to burn off crud/rubbish/filth. [EXEG: Gk almost identical to Mk. 1:7-8; Mk has ‘stoop’, Lk adds ‘with fire’ at end. For wind and fire vs. spirit and fire, and fire as judgment leading into vs. 17, see Marshall pp 145-148; wide agreement that ‘fire’ here is not clear, also Trans. Notes p.82. PRINCIPLE: Where leaving it open yields multiple legitimate interpretations, we want to do that. But where it yields zero meaning, we want to give the most likely interpretation in the context--here vs. 17 (not Acts 2). Fire imagery changed to burning rubbish (to resonate with context of vs. 17 and better match 12:49.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tapa = cut in, respond (keras,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tapa = cut in, respond (keras, hit); ****</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sama ke tukang mas bekin barisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sama ke tukang mas bekin barisi mas deng api ko buang dia pung kotoran, ko biar dia dapa mas tulen.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Dia hukum orang yang bekin sala dong, sama ke orang tani yang pake angin ko pisa buang kotoran dari padi. Ais dia simpan padi yang barisi dalam sokal, ma bakar buang dia pung kotoran. Bagitu ju, nanti Kristus hukum orang yang bekin sala dong, deng lempar buang sang dong pi dalam api yang sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>He will punish people who do wrongs, like a farmer who uses wind to separate away the impurities from the padi. Then he stores the clean padi in a grain storage basket, but burns up the impurities. Like that also, Kristus will punish people who do wrongs, and throw them away into the fire which never ends. [EXEG: Explication follows HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kotoran = impurities ; sokal ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kotoran = impurities ; sokal = huge grain storage basket.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="However &quot;fire&quot; is handled, it has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">However "fire" is handled, it has to be clear that it's forever.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00097C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Orang tani kasi angin ko fuu kotoran dari padi-gandum<bt>A farmer lets the wind blow the impurities from the grain-wheat</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Deng bagitu, Yohanis kasi inga orang macam-macam hal, deng kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang dong.<bt>In that way, Yohanis made people aware of all sorts of things, and told the Lord's Good News to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19-20" />Itu waktu, Yohanis ju mulai omong taráng-taráng so'al Herodes pung bekin-bekin. Dia pung parkara bagini: Herodes tu, gubernor di propinsi Galilea. Dia pung sala su satu mal'unuk pung. Conto ke dia su rampas bawa dia pung adi pung bini, nama Herodias. Padahal dia pung adi masi idop, deng balóm bacere deng Herodias. Herodes pung cara idop yang sonde batúl tu, bekin Yohanis togor sang dia taráng-taráng, sampe Herodes doak sang dia. Ais Herodes tangkap ame sang dia, ju lempar buang sang dia pi dalam bui.<bt>At that time, Yohanis also started to speak openly about Herodes' deeds. The problem/dispute was like this: That Herodes, was governor of Galilea province. He had done heaps of wrongs. For example he had snatched away his younger sibling's wife, named Herodias. In.actual.fact, his younger sibling was still alive and had not yet divorced Herodias. That way of living of Herodes' that was incorrect, made Yohanis rebuke him openly, to the point that Herodes burped him (=was feed up with him). Then Herodes capture him, and threw him away in jail. [EXEG: Different Philip than in 3:1. See FTN at 3:1; younger brother from same father, different mother]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[younger brother from same father, different"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">[younger brother from same father, different mother] adi laen mama<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:19-20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Baca catatan kaki di Lukas 3:1-2. Lia ju Mateos 14:3-4; Markus 6:17-18.<bt>Read the footnote at Lukas 3:1-2. See also Mateos 14:3-4; Markus 6:17-18.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis sarani sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis baptizes the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:13-17; Markus 1:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dulu waktu dong balóm tangkap sang Yohanis, dia ada sarani orang banya. Deng dia ju sarani sang Yesus. Ais itu Yesus sambayang, ju langit tabuka.<bt>Previously when they still had not yet captured Yohanis (=before they had...), he was baptising many people. And he also baptised Yesus. After that Yesus prayed, and the sky opened.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***Changed to /dulu/"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***Changed to /dulu/</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Tarús Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi turun datang pi Dia. Itu Roh pung rupa sama ke burung pompa. Ju ada suara dari langit bilang,<bt>Next the Lord's Holy Spirit came down on Him. That Spirit's form/shape was like a dove/pidgeon. And there was a voice from the sky saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu ni, Beta pung Ana sayang.<bt>“You-sg here, are My dear Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu salalu bekin sanáng sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>You always make Me happy.” [NOTE: Gk in Lk and Mk identical in quote.]</bt><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:2, Lagu Puji dong 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 3:17, Markus 1:11, Lukas 9:35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung nene-moyang dong, iko bapa Yusuf<bt>The Lord Yesus' ancestors, following father Yusuf's</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 1:1-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu Yesus mulai kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan pung jalan idop, Dia pung umur kira-kira tiga pulu taon. Orang kanál bilang, Yesus tu, Yusuf pung Ana. Yusuf pung nene-moyang dong, andia:<bt>When Yesus began to tell people about the Lord's life way, His age was approximately thirty years. People recognised that Yesus was Yusuf's Child. Yusuf's ancestors, are like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stambom = genealogy (Dutch) June knows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">stambom = genealogy (Dutch) June knows it</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yusuf pung bapa, Eli.<bt>Yusuf's father, was Eli.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="24" />Eli pung bapa, Matat.<bt>Eli's father, Matat.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Matat pung bapa, Lewi.<bt>Matat's father, Lewi.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lewi pung bapa, Melki.<bt>Lewi's father, Melki.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Melki pung bapa, Yanai.<bt>Melki's father, Yanai.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yanai pung bapa, Yusuf.<bt>Yanai's father, Yusuf.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="25" />Yusuf pung bapa, Matatias.<bt>Yusuf's father, Matatias.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Matatias pung bapa, Amos.<bt>Matatias' father, Amos.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Amos pung bapa, Nahum.<bt>Amos' father, Nahum.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nahum pung bapa, Hesli.<bt>Nahum's father, Hesli.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hesli pung bapa, Nagai.<bt>Hesli's father, Nagai.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="26" />Nagai pung bapa, Maat.<bt>Nagai's father, Maat.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Maat pung bapa, Matatias.<bt>Maat's father, Matatias.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Matatias pung bapa, Semein.<bt>Matatias' father, Semein.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Semein pung bapa, Yosek.<bt>Semein's father, Yosek.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yosek pung bapa, Yoda.<bt>Yosek's father, Yoda.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="27" />Yoda pung bapa, Yohanan.<bt>Yoda's father, Yohanan.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanan pung bapa, Resa.<bt>Yohanan's father, Resa.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Resa pung bapa, Serubabel.<bt>Resa's father, Serubabel.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Serubabel pung bapa, Sealtiel.<bt>Serubabel's father, Sealtiel.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sealtiel pung bapa, Neri.<bt>Sealtiel's father, Neri.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="28" />Neri pung bapa, Melki.<bt>Neri's father, Melki.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Melki pung bapa, Adi.<bt>Melki's father, Adi.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Adi pung bapa, Kosam.<bt>Adi's father, Kosam.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kosam pung bapa, Elmadam.<bt>Kosam's father, Elmadam.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Elmadam pung bapa, Er.<bt>Elmadam's father, Er.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="29" />Er pung bapa, Yosua.<bt>Er's father, Yosua.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yosua pung bapa, Elieser.<bt>Yosua's father, Elieser.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Elieser pung bapa, Yorim.<bt>Elieser's father, Yorim.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yorim pung bapa, Matat.<bt>Yorim's father, Matat.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Matat pung bapa, Lewi.<bt>Matat's father, Lewi.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="30" />Lewi pung bapa, Simeon.<bt>Lewi's father, Simeon.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simeon pung bapa, Yahuda.<bt>Simeon's father, Yahuda.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yahuda pung bapa, Yusuf.<bt>Yahuda's father, Yusuf.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yusuf pung bapa, Yonam.<bt>Yusuf's father, Yonam.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yonam pung bapa, Elyakim.<bt>Yonam's father, Elyakim.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="31" />Elyakim pung bapa, Melea.<bt>Elyakim's father, Melea.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Melea pung bapa, Mena.<bt>Melea's father, Mena.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mena pung bapa, Matata.<bt>Mena's father, Matata.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Matata pung bapa, Natan.<bt>Matata's father, Natan.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Natan pung bapa, Daud.<bt>Natan's father, Daud.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="32" />Daud pung bapa, Isai.<bt>Daud's father, Isai.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Isai pung bapa, Obet.<bt>Isai's father, Obet.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Obet pung bapa, Boas.<bt>Obet's father, Boas.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Boas pung bapa, Salmon.<bt>Boas' father, Salmon.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Salmon pung bapa, Nahason.<bt>Salmon's father, Nahason.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="33" />Nahason pung bapa, Aminadab.<bt>Nahason's father, Aminadab.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aminadab pung bapa, Admin.<bt>Aminadab's father, Admin.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Admin pung bapa, Arni.<bt>Admin's father, Arni.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Arni pung bapa, Hesron.<bt>Arni's father, Hesron.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hesron pung bapa, Peres.<bt>Hesron's father, Peres.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Peres pung bapa, Yahuda.<bt>Peres' father, Yahuda.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="34" />Yahuda pung bapa, Yakob.<bt>Yahuda's father, Yakob.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakob pung bapa, Isak.<bt>Yakob's father, Isak.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Isak pung bapa, Abraham.<bt>Isak's father, Abraham.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abraham pung bapa, Tera.<bt>Abraham's father, Tera.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tera pung bapa, Nahor.<bt>Tera's father, Nahor.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="35" />Nahor pung bapa, Seruk.<bt>Nahor's father, Seruk.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Seruk pung bapa, Rehu.<bt>Seruk's father, Rehu.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rehu pung bapa, Pelek.<bt>Rehu's father, Pelek.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pelek pung bapa, Eber.<bt>Pelek's father, Eber.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Eber pung bapa, Sela.<bt>Eber's father, Sela.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="36" />Sela pung bapa, Kenan.<bt>Sela's father, Kenan.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kenan pung bapa, Arpaksad.<bt>Kenan's father, Arpaksad.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Arpaksad pung bapa, Sem.<bt>Arpaksad's father, Sem.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sem pung bapa, Noh.<bt>Sem's father, Noh.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Noh pung bapa, Lamek.<bt>Noh's father, Lamek.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="37" />Lamek pung bapa, Metusalak.<bt>Lamek's father, Metusalak.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Metusalak pung bapa, Henok.<bt>Metusalak's father, Henok.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Henok pung bapa, Yared.<bt>Henok's father, Yared.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yared pung bapa, Mahalalel.<bt>Yared's father, Mahalalel.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mahalalel pung bapa, Kenan.<bt>Mahalalel's father, Kenan.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="38" />Kenan pung bapa, Enos.<bt>Kenan's father, Enos.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Enos pung bapa, Set.<bt>Enos' father, Set.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Set pung bapa, Adam.<bt>Set's father, Adam.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Adam tu, Tuhan Allah pung ana cipta'an.<bt>That Adam, was the Lord God's created child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cipta'an = KM?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">cipta'an = KM?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Setan dong pung bos coba sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The evil spirits' Bos tempts the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:1-11; Markus 1:12-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yohanis sarani abis sang Yesus, ju Yesus jalan kasi tenga kali Yarden. Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada sama-sama deng Dia. Ais, itu Roh bawa sang Dia pi tampa sunyi.<bt>When Yohanis had finished baptising Yesus, then Yesus went leaving behind Yarden river. The Lord's Holy Spirit was with Him. After that the Spirit brought Him to a desolate/lonely place.</bt><v n="2" />Yesus tenga di situ sampe ampa pulu hari. Itu waktu ju Dia sonde makan apa-apa, sampe Dia lapar mati pung. Ju setan dong pung bos datang coba hiki sang Dia.<bt>Yesus stayed there for forty days. At that time He also did not eat anything, until He was very hungry. And, the boss of the evil spirits came and tried to trick Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure it's clear that these are all simultaneous, not sequential.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dia omong sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Lu memang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, Lu ada pung kuasa. Jadi suru ini batu dong jadi roti, ko Lu makan sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He spoke to Yesus saying, “If You-sg truly are the Child of the Lord God, You have power. So (consequently), command these rocks to become bread, so that You can eat them.” [NOTE: Gk for bread is sg, but KM is plural for fitting worldview, from their kinds of bread (like small rolls in plastic on a ferry) plus context of hungry person--people buy several per individual.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***deleted last sentence from previous versions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***deleted last sentence from previous versions (before (Ni), as clear from immediate context in vs. 2.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, suru ini batu dong jadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Jadi, suru ini batu dong jadi roti, ko Lu makan sampe doak sang dong. Sonde usa mati lapar lai!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung mau lai! Sonde tau, ko? Ada tulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>But Yesus responded saying, “Don't you wish! (=idiom refusing a suggestion) Don't you know? It's written in the *Scriptures saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lu pung mau lai! = tolak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Lu pung mau lai! = tolak suggestion</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Manusia bukan cuma idop dari makanan to'!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;Humans, they don't just live only from food!”&gt;</bt><note reference="4:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 8:3, Mateos 4:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Ais itu, setan dong pung bos bawa sang Dia pi satu tampa tinggi, ju kasi tunju abis sang Dia samua pamarenta di bumi deng dong pung hebat samua. Ais dia kokoe sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua pamarenta deng dong pung kuasa tu, beta pung samua. Bagitu ju deng dia pung hebat samua! Jadi beta ada pung hak mau kasi sapa sa yang beta suka.<bt>After that, the evil spirits boss brought Him to a tall/high place, and showed Him all the governments on earth with all their impressive/amazing.things. Then he coaxed Yesus saying, “All the governments with their power/authority, it's all mine. Like that also with all their impressive/amazing.things! So (consequently), I have the authority to give [it] to whomever I like. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ 5-6 combined Mar 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ 5-6 combined Mar 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Beta mau kasi samua sang Lu. Cuma Lu musti bekin satu hal dolo, baru beta kasi. Gampang sa! Lu cuma sémba sang beta. Itu sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>I'll to give it all to You. Only You must do one thing first, only then I will give [it]. It's easy! You just worship me. Merely that!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Yesus manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Dapa di mana bagitu? Te dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>But Yesus replied in return saying, “Where did you get that from? Cuz (elaboration) in the *Scriptures it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu musti sémba sang Tuhan Allah sa.<bt>&lt;You must worship only the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng lu musti layani ame sang Dia sa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And you-sg must serve only/just Him.”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng Dia tu, yang lu musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Deng Dia tu, yang lu musti layani ame.&gt;&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais itu, setan dong pung bos ame bawa sang Yesus pi kota Yerusalem. Di situ, dia bawa nae sang Yesus pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung tampa paling tinggi. Ais dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Lu memang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, na, Lu buang diri pi bawa su!<bt>After that, the boss of the evil spirits brought Yesus to Yerusalem city. There, he brought Yesus up to the highest place of the Central Worship House. Then he said, “If You truly are the Lord God's Child, then You throw Yourself down [imperative]!</bt><v n="10" />Te ada tulis di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah nanti suru Dia pung ana bua dari sorga,<bt>&lt;Lord God will order His underling/s from heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko jaga ame sang Lu.<bt>to watch.over You.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="should Lu be capitalized here in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">should Lu be capitalized here in a OT quote?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Nanti dong datang tada sang Lu,<bt>Later they will come collect/catch You,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar Lu pung kaki sonde tasonto sadiki ju di batu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so that Your foot does not even touch the rock/s a tiny.bit.’”</bt><note reference="4:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 91:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang maen paricuk deng Beta. Te ada tulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>But Yesus answered, “Don't play dishonestly with Me. Cuz it is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Jang coba Tuhan Allah!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;Don't try/tempt the Lord God!”&gt;</bt><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Setan dong pung bos coba sang Yesus deng jalan macam-macam, ma sonde dapa ontong sang Dia. Ais dia jalan kasi tenga sang Yesus, ko tunggu waktu yang bae.<bt>The evil spirits boss tried Yesus in all sorts of ways, but could not succeed over Him. So he went leaving behind Yesus, to wait for a good time.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi Galilea ko mulai kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan pung Kabar Bae<bt>The Lord Yesus goes to Galilea to start to tell people about the Lord's Good News</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:12-17; Markus 1:14-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais itu, ju Yesus kambali lai pi propinsi Galilea, te Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada kasi kuasa sang Dia. Sonde lama, ju orang di itu da'era dong mulai kanál Dia pung nama.<bt>After that, then Yesus returned again to Galilea province, cuz (elaboration) the Lord's Holy Spirit was giving power to Him. Not long, then people in that area began to recognize/know His name (= he was becoming popular).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulai kanál Dia pung nama ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mulai kanál Dia pung nama = mulai tenar (popular) @@ Example of Gk order</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dia ajar di orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang di mana-mana. Ju orang-orang puji sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus tu, Orang hebat, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>He taught in the Yahudi people's worship houses all.over.the.place. And the people praised Him saying, “That Yesus, is an amazing Person, ó?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong sonde tarima sang Tuhan Yesus di Nasaret<bt>People do not receive/accept the Lord Yesus in Nasaret</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:53-58; Markus 6:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Satu kali, Yesus datang di Dia pung kampong Nasaret. Pas deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang, andia &lt;hari Sabat&gt;, Dia maso pi ruma sambayang, sama ke Dia pung biasa. Ais Dia bangun badiri ko mau baca dari Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>One time, Yesus came to His village Nasaret. Exactly on the Yahudi people's worship day, which is &lt;Sabat day, He entered the worship house, as was His custom/norm. Then He stood up to read from the Scriptures.</bt><v n="17" />Ju dong sorong kasi sang Dia ba'i Yesaya pung tulisan. Tarús Dia buka, ais cari ayat, ju baca bilang,<bt>And they extended gave to Him grandfather Yesaya's writing. Next He opened [it], then looked for verse/passage, and read saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="propheetees?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">propheetees?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00244C.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top">Orang baca Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi dalam orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang<bt>A person reads the Scriptures in a Yahudi worship house</bt></fig>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung Roh pung kuasa ada di Beta.<bt>“The Lord God's Spirit's power is at/on Me. [NOTE to daughter translations: see if team will accept not capitalising 1st pronouns in OT quotes, since interpreting this as Jesus came long after it was written. Several consultants frown on capitalizing pronouns in OT quotes other than for God, unless it is abundantly clear the writer knew he was talking about the Messiah.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko Dia tunju sang Beta,<bt>That.is.why He appoints/chooses Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang orang kasian dong.<bt>to tell the Lord's Good News to poor/unfortunate people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia su utus sang Beta,<bt>He has commissioned Me,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekhrisen me: anointed me = gave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ekhrisen me: anointed me = gave me the commission</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko kasi tau bilang,<bt>to tell saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang di bui dong, nanti bebas;<bt>those who are in jail, will be freed;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang buta dong, nanti bisa lia kambali;<bt>those who are blind, will see again;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang kaná tendes dong, nanti idop bebas.<bt>those who are afflicted with oppression, will live freely. [NOTE: versification in TB is way off for vs.18-19.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="19" />Te sakarang ni, Tuhan pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now, the Lord's time has arrived,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko kasi salamat Dia pung orang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>to save His people.”</bt><note reference="4:18-19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini dua ayat ni iko pas-pas tulisan bahasa Yunani asli. Alkitab bahasa Indonesia (TB) taro angka dari ayat 19 di tampa yang sonde pas.<bt>These two verses follow carefully the original Yunani (Gk) language writings. The Indonesian Bible (TB) places the number for verse 19 in a place that is not precise.</bt></note><note reference="4:18-19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 61:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Baca abis itu tulisan, ju Yesus gulung kambali ko sorong pi pamimpin ibadat, tarús Dia dudu. Samua orang yang ada dalam itu ruma sambayang lia tarús sang Dia.<bt>After finishing reading that writing, then Yesus rolled it up again to hand.over to the leader of the religious.service, then He sat.down. All the people who were in that worship house continued to look at Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypeeretees: assistant, attendant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hypeeretees: assistant, attendant</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Apa yang bosong dengar dari Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi tadi tu, sakarang su jadi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He told them saying, “What you-pl just heard from the Scriptures, has happened now!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ju samua orang yang ada di situ mulai omong angka-angka sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Apa yang Dia omong tadi tu, pung bagus lai! Ma Dia ni, Usu pung Ana, aa? Karmana ko bisa bagini?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then all the people who were there began to speak raising.up (=praising) Yesus saying, “Awii! [+amazement] What He said just then was very good/attractive! But He's Usu's Child, isn't he? How can it be like this?” [NOTE to daughter translations on how to translate /wuang/ as tag question, right? seeking confirmation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ deleted /hebat/ @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ deleted /hebat/ @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tantu bosong samua tau ada bahasa kata, &lt;We, dokter! Bekin bae lu pung diri sandiri dolo!&gt; Bosong ada mau pake itu bahasa ko puku bale sang Beta bilang, &lt;Akurang ko Lu sonde bekin tanda heran satu kasi botong di sini, sama ke yang Lu su bekin di kota Kapernaum sana?&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told them saying, “Surely you all know there is a saying saying, ‘We, [+get attention] doctor! Heal yourself first!&gt; You want to use that saying to hit/knock Me down in return saying, ‘Why don't You do/make an amazing sign for us-exc here, like You did in Kapernaum city over there?&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pepatah = peribahasa, proverb, aphorism ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">pepatah = peribahasa, proverb, aphorism ; bahasa = saying,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Dia pung batúl bagini: orang sonde mau tarima sang Tuhan pung jubir di dia pung kampong sandiri.<bt>The truth is like this: people do not want to accept the Lord's spokesperson in his own village.</bt><note reference="4:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 6:4; Yohanis 4:44</note><v n="25-26" />Ame conto dari Tuhan pung jubir, ba'i Elia. Satu kali, ujan su sonde turun tiga taon satenga. Itu waktu, ada banya janda di Isra'el. Ma Tuhan sonde kirim Elia ko tolong sang dong di Isra'el. Tuhan cuma kirim sang dia pi satu mama janda di kampong Sarfat deka deng kota Sidon. Padahal mamatua tu, bukan orang Yahudi. Ma dia parcaya Tuhan Allah pung kuasa.<bt>Take an example from the Lord's spokesperson, grandfather Elia. One time, rain did not fall for three and a half years. At that time, there were many widows in Israel. But the Lord did not send Elia to help them in Israel. The Lord only sent him to one mother/lady widow in Sarfat village near Sidon city. In.actual.fact that older.lady, was not a Yahudi person. But she believed in the Lord God's power.</bt><note reference="4:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 17:1, 8-16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ame conto laen lai dari Tuhan pung jubir Elisa. Itu waktu, ada banya orang Yahudi yang saki kusta di Isra'el. Ma Tuhan sonde bekin bae sang dong. Tuhan cuma suru Elisa bekin bae satu orang kusta, nama Naaman. Padahal dia tu, orang Siria, bukan orang Yahudi. Ma dia parcaya Tuhan Allah pung kuasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Take another example from the Lord's spokesperson Elisa. At that time, there many Yahudi people who had leprosy illness in Israel. But the Lord did not heal them. The Lord only ordered Elisa to heal one leprosy person, named Naaman. In.actual.fact, that person, was a Siria person, not a Yahudi person. But he believed in the Lord God's power.” [NOTE: Changed to delete rhetorical question from earlier version, UNS's had trouble with it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***deleted clause /tagal dong sonde parcaya./"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***deleted clause /tagal dong sonde parcaya./ (See \ov)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: There were also many lepers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">NRSV: There were also many lepers in Israel in the time of the prophet Elisha, and none of them was cleansed except Naaman the Syrian."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan sonde bekin bae sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma Tuhan sonde bekin bae sang dong, tagal dong sonde parcaya.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 5:1-14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Waktu dong dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju dong samua maruak sang Dia.<bt>When they heard Yesus' speaking like that, then they all got furious with Him.</bt><v n="29" />Ais dong bangun rame-rame, ju usir buang sang Dia dari itu ruma sambayang. Tarús dong hela bawa sang Dia pi kampong pung pinggir, ko mau tola buang sang Dia pi dalam jurang di situ.<bt>Then they all got up with great bustling, and threw Him out of that worship house. Then they dragged brought Him to a the edge of the village, wanting to shove him off into a ravine there. [EXEG: “hill on which the city was built” -- explicit to implicit. Skews information load and focus. Carried by implications of ‘ravine’.]</bt><v n="30" />Ma Dia cuma jalan kaluar lewat itu orang banya dong pung teng-tenga, abis kasi tenga sang dong di situ.<bt>But He just walked out by/via/bypassing the midst of those many people, then left them there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jalan neuk-neuk = stroll casually"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">jalan neuk-neuk = stroll casually</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus usir setan dari satu orang<bt>The Lord Yesus evicts an evil spirit from a person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:21-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, Yesus turun pi kota Kapernaum di dano Galilea pung pinggir. Tiap hari sambayang Dia ajar orang dong dalam ruma sambayang.<bt>After that, Yesus went.down to Kapernaum city on Galilea lake's edge. Every worship day He taught people in the worship house.</bt><v n="32" />Orang dong taheran-heran dengar Dia pung omong, te Dia tau batúl itu ajaran pung isi.<bt>People were amazed hearing His talking, cuz (elaboration) He truly knew/understood the contents of that teaching. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. words for 'amazed' and 'authority' same as in Mk.1:22.]</bt><note reference="4:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:28-29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Satu kali, waktu Yesus ada mangajar di itu ruma sambayang, ada satu orang yang takaná setan mulai batarea ukur kuat pung bilang,<bt>One time, when Yesus was teaching in the worship house, there was a person who was afflicted by an evil spirit who began to shout loudly saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batarea ukur gargantang = shout at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">batarea ukur gargantang = shout at the top of his voice</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akathartos: unclean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">akathartos: unclean</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />&lt;&lt;Woi! Yesus, Orang Nasaret! Lu ada pung urusan apa deng botong! Lu datang ko mau bekin ancor sang botong, ko? Botong kanál sang Lu. Lu ni, itu Orang Barisi yang dolu Tuhan Allah janji ko mau kirim datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>“Woi! [+challenge] Yesus, the Nasaret Person! What business do You-sg have with us-exc! You come because you want to destroy us-exc, don't you? We-exc know/recognise You. You here are that Clean/Holy Person whom long ago God promised to send.” [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk is identical with Mk. 1:24.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ma Yesus masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tutu lu pung mulu! Kaluar dari itu orang!&gt;&gt; Takuju sa, itu setan angka banting itu orang di lante di orang dong pung teng-tenga. Banting abis, ju itu setan kaluar kasi tenga itu orang, deng sonde bekin saki sang dia.<bt>But Yesus rebuked him saying, “Shut your mouth! Come out of that person!” Unexpectedly/suddenly, the evil spirit lifted up threw down that person on the floor in the midst of the people. After throwing him down, then that evil spirit come out leaving that person, and did not hurt him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Orang dong samua tanganga bilang, &lt;&lt;Heran, é! Ini Orang pung omong tu, ada kuasa hebat! Sampe-sampe setan dong ju iko Dia pung parenta ko kaluar dari orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people were open-mouthed (=surprised) saying, “Amazing! This person's speaking has great power! To the point that evil spirits also follow His command to come out of people!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitassei: present tense, generic, not referring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">epitassei: present tense, generic, not referring to just the man in front of them akathartoi: unclean<span class="Italic">(36)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Ais carita so'al Yesus mulai tasiar di itu da'era samua.<bt>Then story/stories about Yesus began to spread throughout that region.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais dong pi kuliling di itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ais dong pi kuliling di itu da'era, ko kasi tau samua orang so'al Yesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae Simon pung mama mantu, deng banya orang lai<bt>The Lord Yesus heals Simon's mother-in-law, and many other people</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added to title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added to title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:14-17; Markus 1:29-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Waktu dong kaluar dari itu ruma sambayang ju, Yesus pi satu orang pung ruma. Itu orang pung nama, Simon.<bt>As they were coming out of that worship house, then Yesus went to a person's house. That person's name was Simon.</bt><note reference="4:38" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Simon tu, andia Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>Simon is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>Simon pung mama mantu ada saki damám, jadi dia pung badan ada panas tinggi. Ais dong minta sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Tolong bekin bae sang mamatua dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon's mother-in-law was sick with fever, so her body was very hot. Then they asked Yesus saying, “Father! Please heal the elder.lady [polite command]!”</bt><v n="39" />Yesus pi badiri di pinggir koi, ais usir kaluar itu damám dari mamatua. Itu sa'at ju, dia pung damám ilang memang. Ais ju dia bangun memang ko pi sadia makan kasi sang dong.<bt>Yesus went to stand a the edge of the bed, then drove away that fever from the elder.lady. At that moment also, her fever disappeared immediately. And then she got up immediately to go prepare food for them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Itu sore, waktu matahari su mulai tanggalám, orang dong bawa datang samua orang saki pi sang Yesus. Dong pung panyaki macam-macam. Ais Dia taro tangan di orang saki dong, ju bekin bae sang dong samua.<bt>That evening, when the sun had begun to sink, people brought all the sick people to Yesus. Their illness were all.sorts. Then He put his hand/s on the sick people, and healed them all. [EXEG: the “all” are in the Greek; it is considered hyperbole.]</bt><v n="41" />Di itu orang saki dong ju, ada barapa yang takaná setan. Ais Yesus parenta sang setan dong ko kaluar dari itu orang dong. Dong kaluar deng batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Tuhan Allah pung Ana!&gt;&gt; Te itu setan dong tau bilang, Dia tu, Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su janji dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Tagal itu, Yesus togor sang dong ko sonde bole ba'omong satu kata ju so'al Dia pung diri.<bt>Among those sick people, there were several who were afflicted by evil spirit/s. Then Yesus ordered those evil spirits to come out of people. They came.out yelling saying, “You here, are the Lord God's Child!” Cuz (elaboration) those evil spirits knew that He was Kristus, whom the Lord God has promised long ago to send. Because of that, Yesus warned them that they were not allowed to speak even one word about Himself.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi kasi tau Kabar Bae di ruma sambayang dong<bt>The Lord Yesus goes to tell Good News in the worship houses</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:35-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Dia pung beso amper siang, ju Yesus bangun ko pi satu tampa sunyi di luar kota. Orang dong cari sang Dia di mana-mana. Waktu katumu, ju dong noki sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa tenga deng botong sa! Sonde usa jalan pi tampa laen!&gt;&gt;<bt>The next day almost light, then Yesus got up to go to a desolate/quite place outside the city. People looked for Him all.over.the.place. When they found him, then they nagged/persisted Him saying, “Father just stay with us! It's not neccessary (=polite don't) to go to another place!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ma Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju musti pi kampong laen dong, ko pi kasi tau Kabar Bae so'al Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Te Tuhan su utus sang Beta ko kasi jalan itu tugas.&gt;&gt;<bt>But he replied saying, “I also must to the other villages, to go tell Good News about the Lord God's rule/governing. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord has commissioned Me to carry out that task/responsibility.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ju Dia jalan dari satu kampong pi kampong laen ko mangajar di ruma-ruma sambayang di propinsi Yudea.<bt>The He travelled from one village to the next village to teach in the worship houses in Yudea province.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong pukat dapa ikan bam-banya<bt>They fish.with.net obtaining many-many fish</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:18-22; Markus 1:16-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, Yesus ajar orang dong di dano Galilea pung pinggir.<bt>One time, Yesus taught people at the edge of Galilea lake.</bt><note reference="5:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani bilang &lt;di dano Genesaret pung pinggir&gt;. Dano Genesaret pung nama laen, andia dano Galilea.<bt>The Yunani language Bible says ‘at the edge of lake Genesaret’. Lake Genesaret's other name is lake Galilea.</bt></note>Banya orang datang ko mau dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata. Sampe-sampe dong baseti makarubu ame sang Yesus.<bt>Many people came to hear the Lord God's Words. To the point that they pushing-and-shoving each other crowding around Yesus.</bt><v n="2" />Deka-deka di situ, ada nalayan yang bekin barisi dong pung pukat di darat. Ju Yesus dapa lia dua parahu kosong ada sandar di situ.<bt>Nearby there, there were fishermen who were cleaning their fishnet/s on the land. And Yesus saw two empty boats that were bow.touching.land there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sandar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sandar</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Satu dari itu parahu dong, andia Simon pung. Ais Yesus nae pi Simon pung parahu, ju minta sang dia ko tola itu parahu pi aer dalam sadiki. Tarús Dia dudu ko ajar itu orang banya dong.<bt>One of those boats, was Simon's. So Yesus got into Simon's boat, and asked him to push that boat out into the deep a bit. Then2 He sat to teach those many people.</bt><note reference="5:1-3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:1-2, Markus 3:9-10, 4:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ajar abis, ju Dia omong sang Simon bilang, &lt;&lt;Mon! Pi tampa yang sadiki dalam ko kasi turun pukat di situ. Te nanti bosong dapa ikan banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>After teaching, then He spoke with Simon saying, “Mon! Go to the place that is a bit deep to let down the net out there. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl will get many fish.” [EXEG: ‘throw’ changed to ‘let down’ better matching Gk and type of net; cf. vs. 6; July 2014.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00212C.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Nalayan pili ame ikan dari pukat<bt>Fishermen select out fish from the net</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Simon manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos lai ju! Botong su karjá banting tulang satu malam anteru, ma satu ekor ju, botong sonde dapa! Ma tagal Bapa su bilang bagitu, na, neu sa! Beta coba kasi turun sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Simon answered saying, “Idiom: Boss that's silly! We-exc have worked flinging our bones (idiom: worked very hard) for an entire night, but we didn't get even a single fish! But because Father has said that, na, ok (=reluctant agreement)! I'll just try to put [it] down.”</bt><note reference="5:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 21:3</note><v n="6" />Ais dong kasi turun pukat. Waktu mau hela kasi nae kambali, tau-tau te itu pukat su ponu deng ikan satu mal'unuk, sampe-sampe pukat su mulai tarobe.<bt>Then they put down the net. When they wanted to pull it back up, that net was already full with a huge.pile of fish, to the point that the net had begun to tear.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ fixed May 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ fixed May 2005</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 21:6</note><v n="7" />Ju Simon batarea pange dia pung kawan dong dari parahu laen ko datang bantu. Ais dong ra'u kasi maso ikan di parahu, sampe itu dua parahu ponu deng ikan ko su amper tanggalám.<bt>Then Simon yelled calling his friends from the other boats to come help. Then they scooped up the fish and put them in the boat, until those two boats were full of fish and almost ready to sink.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metokhois: business partners"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">metokhois: business partners</Message></Annotation><v n="8-10" />Simon pung kawan nalayan, Yakobis deng Yohanis, andia bapa Sabadeus pung ana-ana dong, ju ada. Dong ju heran mau mati, tagal dong dapa ikan bam-banya bagitu. Waktu Simon Petrus lia apa yang su jadi, ju dia langsung tikam lutut di Yesus pung muka bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, satu orang yang su bekin sala talalu banya. Jadi lebe bae Bos jang deka-deka sang beta lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon's fishermen friends, Yakobis and Yohanis, the children of Father Sebedeus, were there as well. They were also very amazed, because they got so many fish like that. When Simon Petrus saw what had happened, then he immediately knelt in front of Yesus saying, “I here, am a person who done/made very many wrongs. So (consequently), it's better that Boss doesn't get near me anymore.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="It what we really want Simon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">It what we really want Simon Petrus here?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koinoonoi: partners"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">koinoonoi: partners</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:8-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Simon, ko Petrus, ko Simon Petrus, itu nama dari satu orang sa.<bt>Simon, or Petrus, or Simon Petrus, those are name from just one person.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mon! Jang talalu bapikir itu so'al, te Beta ada mau pake sang bosong. Bosong ni, biasa cari ikan. Ma sakarang Beta ajar bosong cari orang ko iko sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Mon! Don't think/worry too much about that, cuz (elaboration) I want to use you-pl. You-pl here, usually/habitually hunt for fish. But now I teach you-pl to hunt for people to follow Me.” [EXEG: Why does “fear” go to “worry about” here? It fits the immediate context better. “Fear” can match vs.8, but in KM doesn't transition into the last two sentences, which are the peak of this exchange.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added vocative (suggested at Belu check)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added vocative (suggested at Belu check)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais ju dong langsung hela dong pung parahu ko simpan di darat. Ju dong jalan kasi tenga samua-samua, ko iko sang Yesus.<bt>And then they immediately pulled/dragged their boats to store/put them on land. And they went leaving behind everything, to follow Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang yang kaná panyaki kusta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a person who is afflicted with leprosy illness</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:1-4; Markus 1:40-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Di satu kampong, Yesus dapa katumu sang satu orang yang dia pung badan su ponu deng panyaki kusta. Waktu dia dapa lia sang Yesus, ju dia pi tikam lutut deng tondo dia pung muka sampe di tana. Ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, é! Tolong beta dolo! Te beta tau, Bapa bisa kasi ilang beta pung panyaki ni, ko biar orang jang noju lai sang beta. Asal Bapa mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>In one village, Yesus met a person whose body was covered with leprosy illness. When he saw Yesus, then he went to kneel and bow to the ground in front of him. Then he said, “Father, é! Help me! Cuz (elaboration) I know Father can make this illness of mine disappear, so that people are not repulsed/revolted/disgusted at me anymore. As.long.as Father wants to.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais Yesus sorong tangan ko raba sang dia. Ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau sa! Lu bae su!&gt;&gt; Omong abis, te itu orang pung kusta ilang buang memang.<bt>Then Yesus extended his hand to touch him. And He said, “Of course I want to! You are better!” After speaking, that person's leprosy illness immediately disappeared completely.</bt><v n="14" />Ju Yesus kasi inga sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Lu su bae, ma sonde bole kasi tau sapa-sapa, é! Lu musti iko ba'i Musa pung parenta dolu. Jadi pi di kapala agama, ko dia pareksa lu pung badan, biar dia tau lu pung panyaki su ilang batúl, ko sonde. Ais lu musti kasi persembahan tanda tarima kasi, ko orang samua tau bilang, lu su bae batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus reminded him saying, “Remember this really well! You are now healed, but you may not tell anyone é! You must follow Gf/Ff Musa's command first. So (consequently), go first/now to the head of religion, in order that he examine your body, to see if your illness is really disappeared or not. Then you must give an offering as a sign of thanks, in order that all people know that you are truly healed.” [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. is same as Mk. 1:44.]</bt><note reference="5:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Biar Yesus larang, ma itu carita so'al Dia pung kuasa tu, tasiar dari mulu pi mulu pi mana-mana. Jadi orang dong maen malele datang ko mau dengar Dia ajar sang dong. Ais Dia bekin bae banya orang dari dong pung panyaki macam-macam.<bt>Even though Yesus forbade it, nevertheless that story about that power of His, spread from mouth to mouth all.over.the.place. So (consequently), people habitually/continually flowed/tricked coming to listen to Him teach them. Then He healed many people from their illness of all.sorts.</bt><v n="16" />Ma Yesus ju suka ondor diri dari orang banya, ko pi sambayang di tampa sunyi.<bt>But Yesus also liked to reverse himself (get away) from the many people, to go pray in a quiet/desolate place. [EXEG: Taken as general statement, not one off. See NRSV, NLT, CEV, HCE, NIV, TH "imperfect may be iterative or durative, preferably the former:" TN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang lumpu<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a lame (unable to walk) person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:1-8; Markus 2:1-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Satu kali, Yesus ajar orang di satu ruma. Itu waktu ada orang dari partei agama Farisi deng guru agama barapa orang, datang ko iko dengar sang Dia. Dong datang dari kampong-kampong di propinsi Galilea, dari propinsi Yudea, deng dari kota Yerusalem. Tuhan Allah ada kasi kuasa sang Yesus ko bekin bae orang saki dong.<bt>One time, Yesus taught people at a house. That time there were people from the Farisi religious party and several religion teachers, who came to participate listening to Him. They came from different.villages all around Galilea province, from Yudea province, and from Yerusalem city. The Lord God was giving power to Yesus to heal sick people.</bt><v n="18-19" />Itu waktu, ada barapa orang dorok bawa satu orang lumpu di atas tandu. Dong usaha karás bawa itu orang lumpu, ko Yesus bekin bae sang dia. Ma itu ruma su talalu sesak deng orang, sampe-sampe mau paksa maso ju, sonde bisa. Andia ko dong bawa nae itu orang lumpu pi atas ruma. Ais dong bongkar bekin lobang, ko loos kasi turun itu orang lumpu di atas tandu. Dong kasi turun sang dia di teng-tenga orang banya dong, parsís di Yesus pung muka.<bt>That time, there were several people who carried brought a lame person on top a stretcher. They tried with.great.effort to bring that lame person, so Yesus could heal him. But that house was too crowded with people, to the point that even if they wanted to enter, they couldn't. That's why they carried that lame person up to the top of the house. Then they dismantled made a hole, to lower that lame person down on the stretcher. They lowered him, in the midst of the crowd, exactly in front of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tandu = stretcher genteng = BI"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tandu = stretcher genteng = BI roof tile</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Lia bagitu ju, Yesus tau bilang, dong parcaya Dia bisa bekin bae sang dong pung kawan tu. Ju Dia omong sang itu orang lumpu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Beta su hapus buang lu pung sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing that, Yesus knew they believed He could heal that friend of theirs. Then He spoke to that lame person saying, “Child [+affection]! I have erased away your wrongs.” [EXEG: Trans Notes p.116-117, and following reactions.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dengar Yesus omong bagitu, ju itu orang Farisi deng guru agama dong mulai batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;He'e! Cuma Tuhan Allah sandiri sa yang ada pung hak ko hapus buang orang pung sala dong. Ko dia ni, sapa, sampe bekin diri sama ke Tuhan Allah! Ini ni, hojat barát!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus speak like that, then those Farisi people and the religion teachers began to ask (each other) saying, “What?! The Lord God alone is the only one who has the right to erase away a person's wrongs. Who does he think he is, making himself out to be the same as the Lord God! This here is heavy/serious slander/blasphemy!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="He'e = kaget"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">He'e = kaget</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blaspheemiai: evil speech against God and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">blaspheemiai: evil speech against God and what belongs to him. But here, Jesus isn't saying anything detrimental to God. In the Pharisees' minds, he is insulting God by aping him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung dalam hati. Ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong pikir Beta ni, ada omong hojat?<bt>But Yesus knew their inner livers. So He spoke saying, “Why do you-pl think that I am speaking slander?</bt><v n="23-24" />Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Deng Beta ada pung hak ko kasi ampon orang pung sala. Kalo Beta cuma kasi tau sang ini orang lumpu ni bilang, &lt;Beta su kasi ampon lu pung sala,&gt; bosong sonde lia Beta pung kuasa di ini dunya. Ma kalo Beta bilang, &lt;Bangun suda! Angka lu pung tandu ko pulang.&gt; Kalo dia bangun memang, bosong baru dapa lia Beta pung kuasa. Andia ko Beta mau bekin bae ini orang lumpu ko biar bosong ju tau Beta ada pung hak ko kasi ampon orang pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>I here, am the *Genuine Human. And I have the right/authority to *forgive people's wrongs. If I say to this lame person here saying, ‘I have forgiven your-sg wrong/s,’ you-pl don't see My power/authority here on earth. But if I say, ‘Get.up [imperative]! Pick up your stretcher to go.home!’ If he gets up immediately, only then will you-pl be able to see My power/authority. That's why I will heal this lame person so that you-pl can also know that I have the right/authority to *forgive people's wrongs.” [EXEG: “Which is easier?” implicit in the structure, so as to not force it.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. is almost identical to Mk 2:9-10.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mana lebe gampang? Kalo Beta kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Mana lebe gampang? Kalo Beta kasi tau sang ini orang lumpu ni, bilang, &lt;Beta su kasi ampon lu pung sala,&gt; bosong sonde tau kalo jadi bagitu, ko sonde. Ma kalo Beta bilang, &lt;Bangun suda! Angka lu pung tandu ko pulang.&gt; Kalo dia bangun memang, bosong baru dapa lia bukti, bilang, Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Te Beta ada pung hak ko kasi ampon orang pung sala.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Dia bale ko omong sang itu orang lumpu bilang, &lt;&lt;Badiri su! Angka lu pung tandu, ko jalan pulang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He turned to speak with that lame person saying, “Stand up! Pick up your stretcher, to walk home!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Takuju sa, ju itu orang bangun badiri di orang banya dong pung muka, ais angka ame dia pung tandu. Tarús dia jalan pulang deng angka puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Unexpectedly, then that person stood up in front of the many people, then picked up his stretcher. Then he walked home while lifting.up praises to the Lord God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksazoon: giving full credit to God,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">doksazoon: giving full credit to God, talking up God's reputation</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Lia bagitu ju, samua orang heran. Ais dong angka nae tinggi-tinggi Tuhan Allah pung nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan hebat, ó! Ini hari kotong su lia hal luar biasa deng kotong pung mata kapala sandiri!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then everyone was amazed. Then they lifted up high the Lord God's name saying, “The Lord is amazing! Today we-inc have seen an extraordinary thing with our very own eyes!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange sang Lewi ko iko sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus calls Lewi to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:9-13; Markus 2:13-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Sonde lama ju, Yesus kaluar dari itu ruma, ju Dia dapa lia satu orang tukang tagi bea yang ada dudu di dia pung tampa pajak. Itu orang pung nama, Lewi.<bt>Not long, then Yesus came out of that house, and he saw a tax collector person who was sitting in his tax place. That person's name was Lewi.</bt><note reference="5:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lewi pung nama laen, Mateos.<bt>Lewi's other name, was Mateos.</bt></note>Ais Yesus ajak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari iko sang Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus invited/urged him saying, “Come follow Me!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pungut = BI ; ajak &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">pungut = BI ; ajak &gt; jang pi ba'ajak sang dia = ask s.o. to come with/accompany me , buju jalan sama-sama</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju Lewi bangun memang, ais jalan kasi tenga samua-samua di situ, ko iko sang Yesus.<bt>Hearing like that, then Lewi got up immediately, and walked leaving everything there, to follow Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais itu, Lewi bekin pesta bésar ko undang Yesus datang pi dia pung ruma. Dia ju undang dia pung kawan tukang tagi bea dong, deng tamu laen dong, ko datang makan pesta.<bt>After that, Lewi made a big feast in order to invite Yesus to come to his house. He also invited his tax collector friends, and other guests to come eat the feast.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="undang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">undang</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ma ada barapa orang partei agama Farisi deng guru agama dong, yang mangomel di Yesus pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong dudu makan deng orang tar laku-laku dong, sama ke itu tukang tagi bea deng itu orang tar bae dong? Orang bae jang bacampor deng orang model ke dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were several people of the Farisi religion party, and religion teachers, who grumbled to Yesus' underlings saying, “Why do you-pl sit and eat with people who are nobodies/dispised, like those tax collectors and those not good people? Good people shouldn't mix with that kind/model of people!” [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. same terms as in Mk. 2:16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangomel (frozen \mr); bacibir = despise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mangomel (frozen \mr); bacibir = despise</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 15:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang saki memang parlú dokter. Ma orang su bae, sonde parlú.<bt>But Yesus told them saying, “Sick people really need a doctor. But people who are already well, don't need [a doctor]. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. almost identical to Mk. 2:17.]</bt><v n="32" />Beta datang ko urus orang tar bae dong. Ma sonde datang ko urus orang yang su rasa diri batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>I came to look.after/deal.with people who are not good. But [I] didn't come to look.after/deal.with people who feel/consider themselves to be correct.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Guru agama dong bakanjar deng Tuhan Yesus so'al puasa<bt>Religion teachers debate with the Lord Yesus about fasting</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:14-17; Markus 2:18-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais, itu orang dari partei agama Farisi deng guru agama dong ju mangomel di Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, Bapa! Yohanis tukang sarani pung ana bua dong puasa deng sambayang ulang kali. Orang Farisi pung ana bua dong ju bagitu. Ma akurang ko Bapa pung ana bua dong maen makan-minum tarús? Dong tu, sonde tau puasa, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, those people from the Farisi religion party and the religion teachers also grumbled to Yesus saying, “It's like this, Father! Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer's underlings fasted and prayed repeatedly/often. The Farisi people's underlings also do like that. But why do Father's (=your) underlings continually eat-drink all the time? Don't they know how to fast?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma Yesus balas pake umpama sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang bosong su tau, kalo ada pesta kawin, tamu dong sonde puasa, ma dong makan sampe kinyang. Kalo baroit laki-laki masi ada di situ, tantu dong samua makan rame-rame.<bt>But Yesus responded using an illustration/comparison saying, “Obviously you-pl already know, that if there's a marriage feast, the guests don't fast, but they eat until.satisfied/full. If the groom is still there, of course they all eat together having.a.good.time. [NOTE: Gk only different in one word from Mk. 2:19.]</bt><v n="35" />Ma nanti satu kali, kalo orang laen tangkap bawa itu baroit laki-laki dolo, dia pung tamán dong rasa susa, baru dong puasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But later at some time, if another person/people arrest/kidnap that groom, his friends will feel in.a.state.of.difficulty, and only then will they fast.” [NOTE: Gk same as Mk 2:20, except final phrase "in those days" &gt; "in that day".]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais ju Yesus kasi satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ada orang yang ame kaen baru sapo'ong, ko tempel pi di baju lama yang tarobe. Te nanti kalo cuci itu baju, kaen tempel yang baru tu batakundur, deng itu baju lama tamba tarobe.<bt>Then Yesus told another comparison story saying, “No one takes a piece of new cloth, to attach it on to an old shirt that is ripped. Cuz (elaboration) when that shirt is washed, that attached cloth which is new will shrink, and that old shirt will rip more. [EXEG: undertranslated like CEV; to include “from a new garment” etc. would be overtranslating and make for very heavy information load in these lgs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tisik = sewing, mend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tisik = sewing, mend</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parabolee: this time it isn't really"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">parabolee: this time it isn't really a "story" in Pidgin terms; it's a possible scenario</Message></Annotation><v n="37-38" />Bagitu ju, orang sonde isi tuak baru pi dalam haik yang su lapuk. Te nanti itu haik pica, ju itu tuak malele buang. Jadi tuak baru musti po'a pi dalam haik yang baru.<bt>Similarly, people don't fill new palmwine in a fragile/decayed leaf bucket. Cuz later that pail will break, and that palmwine seep.out wasted. So (consequently), new palmwine must be poured into a pail that is new.</bt><note reference="5:38" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang isi aer anggor yang baru pi dalam tas kulit yang lama, ko jang sampe dia pica ko tarobe.&gt;&gt;<bt>Original Greek language writings say, “Don't fill grape juice that is new in a skin bag that is old, so that it doen't get.to-point-that it breaks and.so tears.”</bt></note>[Deng bagitu, Yesus ajar sang dong bilang, Dia pung ajaran baru, jang kasi campor deng orang Farisi dong pung ajaran lama.]<bt>[In that way, Yesus taught them saying his new teaching shouldn't be mixed with the Farisi people's old teaching.] [EXEG: EXPLICATION: parenthesis info -- following suggestion in Trans. Notes p. 124. ; Gk. vocab is same as Mk. 2:22, with slightly different arrangment, but same meaning.]</bt><v n="39" />Orang yang su parná minum aer anggor yang lama, sonde suka minum yang baru. Te dia tau bilang, &lt;Anggor yang su tasimpan lama tu, yang paling enak na!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>A person who have ever drunk grape juice that is old, doesn't like to drink that which is new. Cuz (elaboration) he/she know that, ‘The wine that is stored long, is obviously the most delicious!”&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: some teams want to go literal, saying “the old is the best”. But old wine = vinegar, so that's why we say “stored for a long time”, suggesting a deliberate process of aging.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang karitik sang Tuhan Yesus dong so'al hari barenti karjá<bt>People criticize the Lord Yesus (collective) about the day of stopping work</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:1-8; Markus 2:23-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, pas deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari barenti karjá, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong ada jalan iko orang pung kabón. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong koru ame padi-gandum pung buler yang ada di dong pung muka idong. Ais dong ma'isi ko makan.<bt>One time, exactly when it was the Yahudi people's day of stopping work, Yesus and His underlings were walking through a person's garden. Then His underlings stripped.seeds off of the grainheads of wheat padi what was right in front of their face nose (ie, they were not stealing it or mass harvesting it). Then they extracted.the.grain to eat it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma'isi = extract contents of grain,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ma'isi = extract contents of grain, kuliti (using fingernail, or teeth to get isi)</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 23:25</note><v n="2" />Di situ, ada barapa orang dari partei agama Farisi yang pegang karás dong pung adat Yahudi. Lia Yesus pung ana bua dong bekin bagitu, ju dong togor sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko Lu pung ana bua dong langgar kotong pung atoran agama? Dong ada karjá pas deng hari barenti karjá! Lia tu! Dong ada koru padi-gandum. Sonde bole bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>There there were several people from the Farisi religious party who held tightly to their Yahudi traditions. Seeing Yesus' underlings do like that, they rebuked Him saying, “Why are your-sg underlings violating our-inc religious regulations? They are working on the day of stopping work! Look! They are picking wheat padi. Can't do like that!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3-4" />Ma Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, ó? Bosong sonde inga ba'i Daud pung carita tu? Ba'i Daud deng dia pung ana bua dong pung parú su karoncong tagal lapar mau mati. Ju dong maso pi dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tenda Sambayang, ko ame itu roti yang kapala agama dong su kasi sang Tuhan, ko dong makan. Padahal cuma kapala agama dong sa yang bole makan itu roti. Orang laen sonde bole. Ais ba'i Daud dong makan, ma sonde ada orang kasi sala sang dong. Bosong tingka ke sonde tau baca Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi sa!<bt>But Yesus responded saying, “How is it? Don't you-pl remember that story about grandfather/ancestor Daud? Gf/Ff Daud and his underlings' stomaches were very hungry. Then they entered into the Lord God's Worship Tent, to take that bread which the religion heads (*priests) had given to the Lord, in order for them to eat it. However.in.actual.fact it was only just the religion heads who could eat that bread. Other people couldn't. Then grandfather Daud (collective) ate [it], but no one accused them. It's as if you just don't know how to read the Lord God's Clean/Holy Writing!</bt><note reference="6:3-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 21:1-6; Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Pasang talinga ko dengar bae-bae! Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Beta ada pung hak ko putus bilang, orang bole bekin apa pas deng hari barenti karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>Attach your ears to listen carefully! I am the Original/Authentic Human. I have the right to decide what people can do on the day of stopping work.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang yang tangan mati sablá<bt>Person with arm dead on one.side (=paralyzed arm)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:9-14; Markus 3:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Satu hari, pas deng hari barenti karjá yang laen ju, Yesus pi ajar di ruma sambayang. Di situ, ada satu laki-laki yang dia pung tangan mati sablá.<bt>One day, on another day of stopping work, Yesus went to teach in the worship house. There, there was male whose arm on one side was dead/paralyzed.</bt><v n="7" />Di situ, ju ada barapa guru agama deng orang dari partei agama Farisi yang ada cari salák ko mau ga'e kasi jato sang Yesus. Ais dong ada tunggu-tunggu kalo Dia mau bekin bae itu orang yang tangan mati sablá, pas deng hari barenti karjá. Deng bagitu, dong bisa tudu sang Dia di muka-muka.<bt>There, there were also several religion teachers and people from the Farisi religion party who were looking for an opportunity to hook/trick Yesus and make him fall. So they were waiting to see if He would heal that person who arm on one.side was dead, on the day of stopping work. In that way, they could accuse Him publically/directly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mama'u = June not know ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mama'u = June not know ; ga'e ; di muka-muka = publicly, directly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Yesus tau parsís dong pung maksud. Andia ko Dia pange itu orang tangan mati sablá bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu, é! Mari badiri di teng-tenga sini doo!&gt;&gt; Ju dia pi badiri memang.<bt>But Yesus knew exactly what their intentions were. That's why He called that person whose arm on one side was dead saying, “Elder.brother, é! Come stand in the middle here!” And he immediately went to stand [there].</bt><v n="9" />Ais Yesus tanya sang itu orang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba Beta tanya sang bosong doo. Iko kotong pung atoran agama, kotong bole bekin apa sa, pas deng hari barenti karjá? Kotong bekin bae ko, bekin jahat? Kotong kasi salamat orang ko, bekin ancor dia pung idop?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked those people saying, “Let Me ask you. According ot our-inc religious regulations, what can we-inc do on the day of stopping work? Do we do good, or do evil? Do we save someone, or destroy his/her life?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cocok ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">cocok =</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Tarús Yesus lia kuliling sang dong, ju Dia omong deng itu orang yang tangan mati sablá tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Sorong datang lu pung tangan!&gt;&gt; Ais dia sorong, ju dia pung tangan bae memang.<bt>Next Yesus looked around at them, and He spoke with that person whose arm was dead on one side saying, “Extend your arm here!” And he extended it, and his arm was immediately well.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Lia bagitu, ju Yesus pung musu-musu dong maruak. Ais dong mulai ator siasat bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong musti cari jalan laen lai, ko mau kasi jato sang Dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then Yesus' enemies were furious. Then they began to plot saying, “We-exc must find yet another way, to make Him fall!” [NOTE to daughter translations: check your lg carefully to avoid a clash with the idea that Jesus is the one who chose to have enemies, rather than people who were at enmity with him. ALT: “then those important people were furious.”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pili ame Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang<bt>The Lord Yesus chooses His twelve underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:1-4; Markus 3:13-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Sonde lama lai, ju Yesus pi satu gunung ko sambayang. Ais Dia sambayang di situ satu malam anteru.<bt>Not much longer, then Yesus went to a mountain to pray. Then He prayed there for an entire night.</bt><v n="13" />Dia pung beso papagi, ju Dia pange ame Dia pung ana bua dong. Ais dari dong samua, Dia pili ame dua blas orang ko jadi Dia pung utusan. Orang yang Dia pili tu, andia:<bt>Early the next morning, then He called/summoned His underlings. Then from among them all, He chose twelve people to become his messengers/emissaries. Those people whom He chose are:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="14" />Simon (yang biasa Yesus pange &lt;Petrus&gt;),<bt>Simon (whom usually Yesus called ‘Petrus’),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Anderias (Simon pung adi),<bt>Anderias (Simon's younger sibling),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis,<bt>Yakobis,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis (Yakobis pung adi),<bt>Yohanis (Yakobis' younger sibling),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Filipus,<bt>Filipus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bartolomeos,<bt>Bartolomeos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="15" />Mateos,<bt>Mateos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tomas,<bt>Tomas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis (Alpius pung ana),<bt>Yakobis (Alpius' child),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (yang iko partei politik Selot),<bt>Simon (who followed the Selot political party),</bt><note reference="6:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Partei Selot ni, ada cari jalan ko dong mardeka dari Roma pung pamarenta. Dong ju kasi nama ini partei bilang, &lt;Patriot&gt;.<bt>This Selot party, was seeking a way for them to be independent of Roma's government. And they also named this party ‘Patriot’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="16" />Yudas (Yakobis pung ana), deng<bt>Yudas (Yakobis' child), and</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yudas Iskariot (yang nanti jual buang sang Yesus).<bt>Yudas Iskariot (who later sold (*betrayed) Yesus away).</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae banya orang<bt>The Lord Yesus heals many people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu turun dari gunung tu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong badiri di tana rata. Di situ ju, ada orang banya bakumpul. Dong tu, datang dari propinsi Yudea, dari kota Yerusalem, dari Tirus deng Sidon, andia dua kota di pinggir laut.<bt>When they came down from that mountain, Yesus and His underlings stood on flat land. There, many people had gathered. They were ones who had come from Yudea province, from Yerusalem city, and Tirus and Sidon, which were two cities on the edge of the sea.</bt><v n="18" />Dong datang ko mau dengar sang Yesus, deng ada yang mau minta Dia bekin bae orang saki. Ju Dia bekin bae sang dong. Dia ju bekin bae orang yang takaná setan, deng usir setan kaluar dari itu orang dong.<bt>They came to hear Yesus, and to request Him to heal sick people. Then/So He healed them. He also healed poeple who were afflicted by evil spirits, and expelled/by expelling evil spirits out of those people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akathartoi: unclean, made them so they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">akathartoi: unclean, made them so they could not associate with God's people or take part in worship</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Samua orang mau sonto ame sang Dia, te kalo dong sonto kaná, na, ada kuasa kaluar dari Dia yang bekin bae sang dong.<bt>All people wanted to touch Him, cuz (elaboration) if they touched him, power came out of Him which healed them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang dapa ontong, deng orang yang dapa calaka<bt>People who obtain good.fortune/blessing, and people who obtain misfortune</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 5:1-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais Yesus bale mangada pi Dia pung ana bua dong, ju ajar bilang,<bt>Then Yesus turned to face His underlings, and taught saying, [NOTE: Lk 6:20-26 most /nanti/ removed to better reflect Gk. Note CEV future for this whole passage really isn't justified. Dallas Willard agrees it is not justified.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Orang kasian dong!<bt>“Poor/pitiful people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong ontong,<bt>You-pl are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan Allah sandiri bosong pung Raja yang bae.<bt>because the Lord God himself is your-pl King who is good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="21" />Orang lapar dong!<bt>Hungry people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong ontong,<bt>You-pl are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan yang nanti bekin bosong jadi kinyang.<bt>because the Lord will later make you become full/satisfied.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang yang manangis deng hati susa dong!<bt>People who cry from distressed livers!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong ontong,<bt>You are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal bosong nanti hati babunga deng katawa sanáng.<bt>because you have joyful/flowered livers and laugh happily.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="22-23" />Orang yang kaná susa tagal iko sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni!<bt>People who are afflicted with difficulty because of following Me, the Orginal Human here! [NOTE to daughter translations: Son of Man here makes heavy info load. But background info, so doesn't work to put it later. Other possibility is to put it as a separate proposition at beginning of 22 “Beta ni, Manusia Tulen.” (See Dhao.)]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong ontong,<bt>You are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan nanti balas sang bosong di sorga.<bt>because the Lord will later reciprocate/reward you in heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Biar orang binci sang bosong,<bt>Even if/though people hate you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, bekin rusak bosong pung nama bae,<bt>or destroy your good name,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, inja-inja sang bosong,<bt>or step.all.over (=oppress) you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, usir kasi iskarobis sang bosong sama ke orang jahat,<bt>or expel evict you out like evil people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong ontong,<bt>you are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan nanti inga sang bosong di sorga.<bt>because the Lord will remember you in heaven. [DISCOURSE: Order following Kupang perceptions of light to heavy.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***q3"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***q3</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekbaloosin to onoma hymoon hoos poneeron:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ekbaloosin to onoma hymoon hoos poneeron: cast out your name as evil</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Petrus 4:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi, kalo orang bekin susa sang bosong bagitu, na, bekin bosong pung hati babunga sa! Deng balompa sanáng! Sonde usa heran, tagal itu orang yang bekin susa sang bosong sakarang ni, dong pung nene-moyang sandiri yang bekin susa sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu dong.<bt>So (consequently), if people cause difficulty for/to you like that, na, just make your livers flower (=joyful)! It's not necessary (=polite 'Don't') to be amazed/surprised, because those people who cause you difficulty now, their very own ancestors are the ones who caused difficulty for the Lord God's spokespersons long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi, kalo bosong dapa susa macam bagitu,<bt>So (consequently), if you encounter difficulty like that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bekin bosong pung hati babunga sa,<bt>just make your livers flower (=be joyful),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan nanti balas sang bosong bam-banya di sorga!<bt>because the Lord will reciprocate/reward you lots.and.lots in heaven!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'e gigi = ketawa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">pe'e gigi = ketawa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoi pateres autoon: The antecedent of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hoi pateres autoon: The antecedent of autoon is the people in Verse 22 who are against you. It's far enough removed from the end of Verse 23 to really complicate things. So we've had to bleach out the meaning to "the people from that time," that is, "long ago," rather than specifically ancestors and descendants. That way we don't lose the train of thought.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 36:16, Utusan dong pung Carita 7:52</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Ma orang kaya dong!<bt>But rich people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong calaka,<bt>You-pl are misfortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal bosong pung idop sanáng, cuma sampe di sini sa.<bt>because your life's happiness, only lasts until now.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Orang kinyang dong!<bt>Full/satisfied people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong calaka,<bt>You are misfortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal musim lapar yang hebat nae kaná sang bosong.<bt>because a horrific hunger season will ascend on you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang kiki-kaka sambarang dong!<bt>People who giggle/show mirth pointlessly/groundlessly!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong calaka,<bt>You are misfortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal sangsara datang bekin bosong manangis makarereu pung.<bt>because suffering comes to make you cry wailing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="26" />Orang gila hormat dong!<bt>People infatuated with honour!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong calaka,<bt>You are misfortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dolu bosong pung nene-moyang dong,<bt>because previously/long ago your ancestors</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ju puji-puji sang jubir tukang omong kosong dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>also praised the nonsense-talking (=deceptive) spokespersons!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="suka makan puji (weaker) ~ orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">suka makan puji (weaker) ~ orang gila hormat (stronger) = selalu cari puji ; seka aer mata = wipe your tears</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoi pateres autoon: same problem as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hoi pateres autoon: same problem as in Verse 23, except that the antecedent of autoon is "everybody," so it's more accessible. Turning Verse 26 around would make the reference of autoon even more jammed up.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong musti sayang bosong pung musu dong<bt>You-pl must love your enemies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 5:38-48, 7:12a)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Yesus sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasang talinga ko dengar bae-bae! Lu musti sayang lu pung musu dong, deng bekin hal bae kasi orang yang binci sang lu.<bt>Then Yesus continued saying, “Attach your ears to listen carefully! You-sg must love your enemies, and do good things for people who hate you. [NOTE: Gk in 2p for whole passage, but Kupang changed to 2s to fit the genre.]</bt><v n="28" />Sambayang ko minta Tuhan Allah ko bekin hal bae kasi orang yang kutuk sang lu. Deng minta Dia bekin hal bae kasi orang yang bekin-bekin sang lu.<bt>Pray requesting the Lord God to do good things for people who curse you. And request Him to do good things for people who make.up.falsehoods/mistreat you.</bt><v n="29" />Kalo ada orang yang tampeleng lu pung pipi sablá, na, kasi loos ko dia tampeleng tamba lai lu pung pipi sablá. Kalo ada yang rampas ame lu pung baju panas, na, kasi tamba lai lu pung baju sang dia.<bt>If a person slaps your cheek on one side, na, allow that s/he also slaps again your other side cheek. If someone snatches/steals your warm shirt, then, give yet another of your shirts to him/her.</bt><v n="30" />Kalo ada orang minta lu pung barang satu, na, kasi pi sa. Deng kalo ada yang angka bawa lu pung barang satu, tenga pi ko dia soa sa. Jang pi minta pulang lai!<bt>If someone requests something of yours, na, go ahead and give it. And if someone picks up carries off something of yours, just let him/her have it. Don't go ask for it back!</bt><v n="31" />Lu musti bekin sang orang laen dong, parsís ke lu mau dong bekin bagitu sang lu.<bt>You must do for/toward other people, exactly like you want them to do for/toward you.</bt><note reference="6:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Lu suka kasi tunju sayang sang lu pung orang sandiri dong. Itu bae. Ma dia pung hebat, apa? Te orang jahat dong ju sayang dong pung orang sandiri!<bt>You like/habitually show love to the your own people. That's good. But what is so amazing/wonderful about that? Cuz evil people also love their own people!</bt><v n="33" />Kalo lu cuma bekin bae sang orang yang bekin bae sang lu, dia pung hebat di mana? Te orang jahat dong ju ada maen babalas bekin bae bagitu.<bt>If you only do good to people who do good to you, where/what is so amazing? Cuz (elaboration) evil people also habitually reciprocate each other doing good like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ yang su bekin bae kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ yang su bekin bae kasi bosong / but kasi sang lu</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Kalo lu cuma kasi pinjam doi sang orang yang bisa bayar kambali, na, dia pung hebat apa? Te orang jahat dong ju tau kasi pinjam doi sang orang laen, asal beso-lusa dong tarima kambali anteru.<bt>If you only loan money to people who can pay it back, na, what is so amazing about that? Cuz (elaboration) evil people also loan money to other people (implies outside their social group), as.long as tomorrow or the next day they get it all back.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ma yang hebat tu, andia bagini: sayang lu pung musu dong! Deng bekin hal bae kasi sang dong. Apa yang dong parlú, na, kasi pinjam sa. Sonde usa pikir bilang, dong bisa kasi kambali, ko sonde. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah nanti balas sang lu. Deng lu jadi Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung ana. Tagal lu idop sama ke lu pung Bapa yang suka bekin hal bae kasi orang jahat. Dia ju bekin hal bae kasi orang yang sonde tau minta tarima kasi.<bt>But what is amazing is this: love your enemies! And do good things for them. What ever they need, na, just give it to them. It's not neccessary (=Don't) think/worry about whether they will give it back or not. [NOTE to daughter translations: #1 “What is amazing is this” is explicating the high-level dynamics of the exchange. If your language does not have a really close match leave it out. Don't force it. #2 If there is not a good match for /pinjam/ or if it evokes only money, then use /kasi pake (tahan)/.] In that way, the Lord God will reciprocate/repay you. And you will become the child of the Very Highest Lord God. Because you live in the same way as your Father who likes to do good things for evil people. He also does good things for people who do not know how to say thankyou.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jadi lu musti kasi tunju rasa kasian sang orang, sama ke lu pung Bapa di sorga ju kasi tunju rasa kasian sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), you must show compassion to people, the same as your Father in heaven also shows compassion to you.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang maen karitik sambarang<bt>Don't heedlessly habitually find.fault/criticize</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 7:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Yesus ajar tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang nilei orang, ko biar orang jang nilei bale sang lu. Jang karitik orang, te nanti orang dong karitik bale sang lu. Lupa buang orang pung sala, ko biar dong ju lupa buang lu pung sala.<bt>Yesus continued teaching saying, “Don't evaluate/judge people, so that people don't evaluate you in return. Don't criticize people, cuz later people will criticize you in return. Completely forget people's wrong/s, so that they also completely forget your wrong/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apolyete, kai apolytheesesthe: pardon, release --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">apolyete, kai apolytheesesthe: pardon, release -- not the ordinary word for forgiving sins.</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Kalo lu kasi orang apa yang dong parlú, nanti lu tarima bale. Te nanti Tuhan ator ko lu tarima bale ponu-ponu. Itu sama ke orang ada po'a kacang bam-banya dalam balék ukur, ais ro'o-ro'o sang dia, tendes kasi turun sang dia, ais isi lai sampe konde ju tapo'a. Yang lu tarima tu, macam ke bagitu. Kalo lu kasi sadiki, lu ju tarima bale sadiki. Ma kalo lu kasi banya, lu ju tarima bale bam-banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you give people what they need, you will receive in return. Cuz (elaboration) later God2 will arrange for you to receive back full-full (abundantly/ overflowing). That is like a person who pours many peanuts in a measuring tin, then shakes it, presses down on it, then fills up more until even the heap/ excessive. amount spills over. That which you will receive, will be like that. If you give a little, you will also receive back a little. But if you give much, you will receive back lots and lots.” [EXEG: “it will be given” by who? Marshall: earn a divine reward; receive from God; TH God is preferable to human agents; TN - God and people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lepeneu = ? konde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Lepeneu = ? konde</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti dong kasi bale sang lu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Nanti dong kasi bale sang lu taponu-ponu. Sama ke orang ada po'a kacang bam-banya dalam balék ukur,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Yesus ju ajar pake umpama. Dia carita bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang buta sonde mungkin kasi tunju jalan kasi orang buta yang laen. Te nanti dong dua rame-rame jato maso pi dalam lobang!<bt>Yesus also taught using a comparison.story. He storied saying, “It's impossible for a blind person to show the way/path for another blind person. Cuz (elaboration) the two of them with great hustle.and.bustle will fall into a hole.</bt><note reference="6:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 15:14</note><v n="40" />Ana murid sonde mungkin lebe hebat dari dia pung guru! Ma kalo dia iko bae-bae dia pung guru pung ajaran, dia bisa jadi sama ke dia pung guru.<bt>It's impossible for a student to be more impressive that his/her teacher. But if s/he carefully follows his/her teacher's teaching, s/he can become like his/her teacher.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari pulang = truant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">lari pulang = truant</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:24-25, Yohanis 13:16, 15:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Lu suka tanda bae-bae orang pung sala kici ana sa. Ma lu pung sala yang bésar, lu anggap ke sonde ada sa. Itu sama ke lu lia abu satu titik di orang pung mata. Padahal ada balok bésar pele lu pung mata, ma lu sonde rasa!<bt>You-sg like.to/habitually take careful note of people's teeny-tiny wrongs. But your wrongs which are big, you consider it as if they just don't exist. That is like you see a dot of dust in someone's eye. But.in.actual.fact there is a big block blocking your eye, but you don't feel it!</bt><v n="42" />Karmana ko lu barani omong bilang, &lt;Konco! Mari ko beta tolong lap kasi kaluar itu abu dari lu pung mata biji dolo.&gt; Padahal lu sandiri sonde bisa lia apa-apa, te ada balok pele lu pung mata na! Woe! Dasar lu tu, orang muka-balakang batúl! Tolong doo! Angka buang itu balok dari lu pung mata sandiri dolo. Baru lu bisa lia, ko tolong lap buang abu sapo'ong ana dari lu pung kawan pung mata.&gt;&gt;<bt>How is it that you dare to speak saying, “Mate! Come let me help wipe that dust out of your eye.” But.in.actual.fact you yourself can't see anything, cuz there is obviously a block blocking your eye! Woe! [+you aren't seeing the point!] Your basic/essential.character is a truly a front-back person (=hypocrite)! Please [+cynical]! Take out and throw away that block from your own eye first. Only.then can you see, to help wipe away that tiny bit of dust from your friend's eye.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tolong do! = +cynical ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Tolong do! = +cynical ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang pung asli kantara dari dia pung bekin<bt>A person's orgin's/true.nature is apparent from his/her deeds</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 7:16-20, 12:33-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Yesus tamba lai satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde mungkin pohon yang bae, kasi kaluar bua yang sonde bae. Deng sonde mungkin pohon yang sonde bae, kasi kaluar bua yang bae.<bt>Yesus added another comparison story saying, “It's not possible for a tree which is good, to produce fruit which is not good. And it's not possible for a tree which is not good, to produce fruit which is good.</bt><v n="44" />Orang bisa tanda, kalo satu pohon tu, bae ko sonde, andia dari itu pohon pung bua dong. Samua orang tau bilang, sonde mungkin orang ketu ame bua jambu, ko bua anggor dari pohon baduri.<bt>People can note/see.a.sign, if one particular tree is good or not, that is from that tree's fruits. All people know that, it is not possible for someone to pick jambu fruit or grape fruit from a thorn tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="duri laus = (like in front"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">duri laus = (like in front of SIL office in Darwin) ; pohon kom = tall, thorny, large round fruit</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, orang sonde ketu ame σῦκον <span class="Italic">(sukon)</span> dari ἀκανθα <span class="Italic">(akantha).</span> Dong ju sonde dapa σταφυλή <span class="Italic">(stafulē)</span> dari βάτος <span class="Italic">(batos).</span> Dia pung arti bilang, dari satu pohon, kotong dapa bua iko dia pung asli.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, people don't pick σῦκον <span class="Italic">(sukon)</span> from ἀκανθα <span class="Italic">(akantha).</span> And they don't get σταφυλή <span class="Italic">(stafulē)</span> from βάτος <span class="Italic">(batos).</span> It means that from one (type of) tree, we-inc get fruit according to its nature.</bt></note><note reference="6:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:33</note><v n="45" />Bagitu ju orang yang hati barisi, bisa bekin hal-hal yang bae. Ma orang yang hati kamomos bekin hal-hal jahat. Te dari orang pung omong, kasi tunju dia pung asli.&gt;&gt;<bt>Similarly a person whose liver is clean/holy, does deeds which are good. But a person whose liver is dirty does evil things. Cuz (elaboration) from a person's speaking, it reveals/shows his true.nature.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asli = true nature"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">asli = true nature</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:34</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang pintar deng orang bodo bangun ruma<bt>A smart person and a stupid person build house</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 7:24-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ais Yesus sambung lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong maen pange tarús sang Beta bilang, &lt;Bos&gt;. Ma akurang ko bosong sonde mau iko Beta pung omong?<bt>Then Yesus connected/continued again saying, “You habitually call Me saying, ‘Boss’. But why do you-pl not want to follow/obey My talking?</bt><v n="47" />Orang yang datang dengar sang Beta, ais bekin iko Beta pung omong, dia tu, sama ke<bt>The person who comes-hears Me, then does according to My speaking, that person is like</bt><v n="48" />orang yang mau kasi badiri ruma yang kuat. Dia gali bae-bae lobang fanderen di tana isi dolo, sampe dapa kaná batu isi. Ais dia bekin fanderen pas di atas itu batu, baru dia bangun ruma. Kalo banjer datang, na, itu ruma sonde tagoyang, tagal dia pung dasar su kuat.<bt>a person who want to/is going to build a house that is strong. S/he carefully digs the foundation hole in the soil first, until s/he hits rock. Then s/he makes the foundation exactly on top of that rock, and.only then does s/he build the house. If/when a flood comes, na, that house does not sway, because it's foundation is strong.</bt><v n="49" />Ma orang yang cuma dengar satenga hati deng sonde iko Beta pung omong, dia tu sama ke orang yang mau bangun ruma deng gampang sa. Dia sonde bekin fanderen, ma dia cuma tempel itu ruma di atas tana isi di kali pung pinggir. Ais waktu banjer datang, ju sapu bekin ancor itu ruma!&gt;&gt;<bt>But the person who only hears half-heartedly and doesn't follow My talking, s/he is like a person wants to build a house easily. S/he doesn make a foundation, but s/he only places that house on top of the soil at the edge of the river. Then when the flood comes, it then sweeps away destroys that house!” [NOTE to daughter translations: Matthew mentions sand; Luke mentions ground.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="talinga sablá, abis kaluar iko talinga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">talinga sablá, abis kaluar iko talinga sablá, dia tu sama ke</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae tantara Roma pung ana karjá<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a Roman army.person's worker</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:5-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ajar abis bagitu, ju Yesus bale pi kota Kapernaum.<bt>After teaching like that, then Yesus returned to Kapernaum city.</bt><v n="2" />Di situ ada satu komandán tantara Roma. Dia ada pung satu ana karjá yang dia parcaya. Itu orang karjá tu, ada jato saki ko amper mati.<bt>There there was a Roman army/military commander. He had a worker whom he trusted. That worker had falled sick and was almost dead.</bt><v n="3" />Waktu itu komandán dapa dengar so'al Yesus, ju dia kirim barapa orang tua Yahudi ko pi minta Yesus datang bekin bae itu ana karjá.<bt>When that commander heard about Yesus, then he sent several elder Yahudi people to go request Yesus to come heal that worker.</bt><v n="4" />Dong noki-noki sang Yesus, ko kalo bisa, na, Dia iko datang deng dong pi bekin bae itu orang. Dong buju sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Ini orang Roma ni, orang bae! Dia tu, pantas Bapa tolong.<bt>They begged Yesus, if possible, He would accompany and come with them to go heal that person. They tried.to.persuade Him saying, “Father! This Roma person, is a good person! He is someone appropriate/worthy for Father to help.</bt><v n="5" />Te dia su bangun satu ruma sambayang kasi sang kotong, ko dia sayang sang kotong orang Yahudi na.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) he has build a worship house for us-inc, because he is obviously happy with us Yahudi people.”</bt><v n="6" />Ju Yesus iko deng dong.<bt>Then Yesus accompanied them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong balóm sampe di ruma, ma itu komandán su kirim dia pung kawan datang bawa pasán sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos sonde usa cape-cape datang lai, te beta sonde pantas tarima Bos di beta pung ruma.<bt>They had not yet arrived at the house, but that commander had already sent his friend to come message/instruct/request2 Yesus saying, “Bos (=you) doesn't need to get all tired.out coming, cuz (elaboration) I am not worthy of recieving Bos (=you) at my house. [NOTE: vs.6-8 are quite complex in their participant orientation, with the friend representing the commander to Jesus using the 1st person. Check it carefully, including the /situ, sini/ below.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** changed kasi tau to pesan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** changed kasi tau to pesan (Helong)</Message></Annotation><v n="7-8" />Deng beta ju sonde pantas datang mangada sang Bos. Su jalás bilang, Bos ada pung kuasa. Jadi asal Bos omong sa dari situ, pasti beta pung ana karjá bae memang. Beta mangarti ini hal, tagal beta pung bos dong ada kuasa ko parenta sang beta. Deng beta ju ada pung kuasa ko parenta beta pung tantara dong. Kalo beta kasi parenta beta pung ana bua bilang, &lt;Pi sana!&gt; pasti dia pi. Kalo beta bilang, &lt;Datang sini!&gt; pasti dia datang. Deng kalo beta suru beta pung orang karjá bilang, &lt;Karjá ini!&gt; pasti dia bekin bagitu. Jadi asal Bos omong sa, pasti beta pung ana karjá ni, bae memang.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I also am not worthy of coming to face.face with Boss. It's already obvious that Boss has power/authority. So (consequently) as.long as Boss just speaks from there, certainly my worker will be immediately healed. I understand these things, because my bosses have power/authority to order me. And I also have power/authority to order my soldiers. If I order my underling saying, ‘Go there!’ surely he goes there. If I say, ‘Come here!’ surely he comes. And if I order my workers saying, ‘Work/Do this!’ surely he does like that. So (consequently) as.long as Boss just says, surely this worker of mine, will be healed right away.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dengar bagitu ju Yesus heran. Dia putar badan ko mangada sang itu orang banya yang ada iko deng Dia. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heran, é! Su bagini lama, ma Beta balóm parná katumu satu orang Yahudi ju yang parcaya sama kuat ke ini orang Roma!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that Yesus was amazed. He turned his body to face those people (crowds) who were following with Him. Then He said, “Amazing! It's been this long, but I have never yet ever met a single Yahudi person who believes as strongly as this Roma person!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Jadi Yesus cuma jalan sampe di situ sa. Ais komandán pung kawan dong bale pulang. Sampe di itu komandán pung ruma, ju dong dapa lia itu ana karjá su bae memang.<bt>Thus Yesus only traveled just to that point. Then the commander's friends returned home. Arriving at that commander's house, then they saw that that worker was indeed already healed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi idop satu janda pung ana<bt>The Lord Yesus makes a widow's child alive</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dia pung beso, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong barangkat pi satu kampong, nama Nain. Ada banya orang yang jalan sama-sama deng dong.<bt>The next day, then Yesus and His underlings left to go a village, named Nain. There were many people who travelled together with them. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk is “travelled with him (sg)”; In this context some lgs will find it more natural to use “with them (pl)” and others “with Him(sg)”.]</bt><v n="12" />Waktu dong su mau deka di itu kampong pung pintu maso, ada satu rombongan orang mau kaluar pi kubur orang mati. Yang mati tu, satu mama janda pung ana laki-laki satu biji sa.<bt>When they were about to come close to that village's entrance door/gate, there was a procession of people wanting to go out to go bury a dead person. The one who had died, was a mama widow's only male child. [NOTE: "carried out" is carried by the KM term "procession of a dead person...going to bury him".]</bt><v n="13" />Waktu Yesus lia itu mama janda, ju Dia jato kasian. Tarús Dia omong deng itu mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama! Suda lai, sonde usa manangis!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw that mama widow, He felt compassion. Then He spoke with that mama,saying, “Mama! Enough, it's not necessary (=don't) cry!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais Yesus pi deka-deka, ju sonto itu tandu orang mati. Ju itu orang yang dorok itu tandu, barenti tahan. Tarús Yesus omong sang itu orang mati bilang, &lt;&lt;Nyong! Bangun su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus went close, and touched that dead person's stretcher. Then the people who carried that stretcher, temporarily stopped. Then2 Yesus spoke to that dead person saying, “Young.male/Lad! Get up!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neaniske: In Pidgin there are terms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">neaniske: In Pidgin there are terms of address for members of one's own family that get up into the neaniskos age range. But for unrelated people, onoly a more general term is appropriate. It spans teen age to elderly, and in some contexts is gender neutral.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ais, itu ana idop kambali, ju dia bangun dudu memang. Tarús dia mulai ba'omong deng orang-orang yang ada badiri kuliling sang dia. Ais Yesus kasi tau sang itu mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama! Ini mama pung ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that child lived again, and he sat up right away. Then he began to speak back.and.forth with the people who were standing around him. Then Yesus said to that mama, “Mama! Here is mama's child.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Samua orang yang ada di situ dong taku mau mati! Ju dong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su utus Dia pung jubir hebat satu kasi kotong!&gt;&gt; Ada laen lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su datang di kotong pung teng-tenga, ko kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae!&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people who were there, were very afraid! And they praised the Lord God saying, “The Lord God has sent one of His amazing spokesperson to us!” There were others who said, “God has come into our midst, to show His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Samua orang yang ada di situ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Samua orang yang ada di situ dong, taku mo mati! Ju dong puji-puji Tuhan Allah, bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su datang di kotong pung teng-tenga! Tuhan Allah su utus Dia pung jubir hebat satu kasi kotong!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ju itu carita tasiar pi mana-mana di propinsi Yudea, sampe di da'era laen ju.<bt>Then that story spread all.over.the.place in Yudea province, even arriving at other regions.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani kirim utusan pi Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer sends a envoy/messenger to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 11:2-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18-20" />Yohanis tukang sarani pung ana bua dong su dengar samua hal yang Yesus bekin. Ais dong pi carita kasi sang Yohanis dalam bui. Ju dia kirim dua orang pi sang Yesus ko tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa ni, batúl-batúl Kristus, yang botong ada tunggu-tunggu, ko? Ko, botong musti tunggu sang orang laen lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer's underlings had heard all the things which Yesus did. So they went to tell them to Yohanis in jail. [EXEG: Prison location (discourse setting needed here) from Lk.3:20, Matt. 11, Trans. Notes p.152, and Marshall p.289.] Then he sent two people to Yesus to ask Him saying, “Is Father here truly Kristus, who we-exc are waiting for [+tag question]? Or must we-exc wait yet again for another person?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dong katumu sang Yesus, ju dong tanya bagitu.<bt>So they met Yesus, and they asked like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Waktu itu utusan ada di situ, Yesus ada bekin bae banya orang dari dong pung panyaki macam-macam. Deng ada usir kaluar setan dari orang yang takaná setan. Deng ada bekin bae orang buta ko dong bisa dapa lia.<bt>When those messengers were there, Yesus was healing many people from all.sorts. of sicknesses. And was expelling out evil spirits from people who were afflicted by evil spirits. And was healing blind people so they could see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang Yohanis pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pulang pi kasi tau sang bu Anis, samua-samua yang bosong su dengar deng su lia sandiri, sama ke Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yesaya ada tulis bilang,<bt>Then Yesus told Yohanis' underlings saying, “You-pl go.home and tell elder.sibling Anis (nickname for Yohanis), everything which you have heard and seen for yourselves, just like the Lord God's spokesperson Yesaya wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Orang buta, dapa lia.<bt>&lt;Blind people, are.able to see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang kaki lumpu, bangun bajalan.<bt>People with crippled foot/feet, get up and walk.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang panyaki kusta, jadi barisi.<bt>People with leprosy illness, become clean.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang tuli, dapa dengar.<bt>Deaf people, are.able to hear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang mati, idop kambali.<bt>Dead people, live again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang kasian, dengar Kabar Bae.&gt;<bt>Poor/pitiful people, hear Good News.’</bt><note reference="7:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 35:5-6, 61:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Pulang pi kasi tau sang bu Anis bilang, &lt;Orang yang sonde malu tarima sang Beta, nanti dong ontong batúl.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Go.home and tell elder.sibling Anis saying, ‘People who are not ashamed to receive/accept Me, they will be truly fortunate.”’ [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK for possible ambiguity “receive Me” vs. “like/similar to Me”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skandalistheei: bent out of shape by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">skandalistheei: bent out of shape by something another person does or says</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu Yohanis pung ana bua dong su pulang, ju Yesus omong deng itu orang banya dong so'al Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu bosong pi cari Yohanis di tampa sunyi sana tu, bosong pikir mau katumu deng manusia model ke apa? Sonde mungkin bosong pi sana ko katumu orang yang noe-noe, sama ke bambu yang tagoyang-goyang iko angin sa!<bt>When Yohanis' underlings had gone home, then Yesus spoke with those many people about Yohanis saying, “When you-pl went looking for Yohanis in that isolated/lonely place over there, what kind of human did you think you were going to meet? It's not possible you went there to met a person who is pliable/bendable (=conforming), like bamboo/cane that sways.to.and.fro merely following the wind!</bt><v n="25" />Sonde mungkin bosong pi ko lia orang yang pake pakean mahal-mahal, te orang macam bagitu cuma tenga di istana sa!<bt>It's not possible you went there to see a person who wears expensive clothing, cuz people/person like that only stay/live in palaces!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malakois himatiois: clothes made from soft"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">malakois himatiois: clothes made from soft fabrics, or for taking it easy en himatismooi endoksooi kai trypheei: with amazing clothing and luxury<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Jadi bosong pi lia sapa di sana? Bosong pikir bosong pi cari Tuhan Allah pung jubir? Batúl! Ma dia tu, jubir yang paling hebat.<bt>So (consequently), who did you go to see over there? Do you think you went to find the Lord God's spokesperson? True/Correct! But this one is the most impressive spokesperson.</bt><v n="27" />Te Tulisan Barisi ada tulis memang so'al Yohanis bilang,<bt>Cuz the Clean/Holy Writing writes beforehand about Yohanis saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dengar! Beta utus Beta pung orang,<bt>'Listen! I am commissioning a person of Mine,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko pi buka jalan kasi sang Lu.&gt;<bt>to go open the way for You.' [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. identical to Mk. 1:2]</bt><note reference="7:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Di ini dunya, sonde ada satu orang ju, yang lebe hebat dari Yohanis. Ma di Tuhan pung karaja'an, orang yang paling kakorek sa su lebe hebat dari Yohanis.&gt;&gt;<bt>In this world, there is not a single person who is more impressive than Yohanis. But in the Lord's kingdom, the person is the very lowest/worthless/least.valued is already more impressive than Yohanis.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Orang yang dengar Yesus pung omong tu, dong su mangarti bilang, Tuhan pung jalan tu, jalan idop yang batúl. Tukang tagi bea dong ju bagitu. Tagal dolu Yohanis su sarani deng ajar sang dong.<bt>The people who heard that speaking of Yesus', they understood that that path of the Lord's, was the true life path. Tax collectors were also like that. Because previously Yohanis had baptised and taught them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="edikaioosan ton theon: They declared (or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">edikaioosan ton theon: They declared (or admitted) that God is just, righteous.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ma orang dari partei agama Farisi deng ahli hukum Yahudi dong su sonde mau iko Tuhan Allah pung mau-mau. Andia ko dong sonde minta Yohanis sarani sang dong.<bt>But the people from the Farisi religious party and the Yahudi law experts did not want to follow the Lord God's will2 (=the things of God). That's why they did not request Yohanis to baptise them. [EXEG: Gk /nomikoi/ “experts in (religious/ Mosaic) law” here, not /grammatewn/ “scribes, writers, teachers of religion”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Key term consistency: use of Yahudi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Key term consistency: use of Yahudi law experts??</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:29-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 21:32, Lukas 3:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais Yesus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau banding orang sakarang ni, deng apa? Manusia macam apa dong ni?<bt>Then/so Yesus asked saying, “What should I compare contemporary people with? What kind of humans are they?</bt><v n="32" />Dong tu, sama ke ana-ana yang ada dudu-dudu di pasar. Dong maen babatarea deng bamangomek bilang,<bt>They are like children who are sitting.around in the market. They are habitually yelling to.each.other and complaining.to.each, saying [EXEG: ‘Complain’ from Gk. context, and NLT; UNS not get high-level connections without it. Could put lexical tie “complain” in 33 and 34, if “cap” doesn't work.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Botong tiop suling rame-rame,<bt>&lt;We-exc blew the flute lively/energetically,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">teng</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde manari sanáng.<bt>but you-pl did not dance happily.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais botong manyanyi lagu mete,<bt>Then we sang funeral.wake songs,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lagu mete = dirge, funeral song"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">lagu mete = dirge, funeral song</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde manangis.&gt;<bt>but you did not cry.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Te Yohanis tukang sarani sonde minum anggor, deng suka puasa, na, bosong cap sang dia bilang, &lt;Dia takaná setan!&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer did not drink wine, and liked to fast, na, you-pl marked/stamped/characterized/branded him saying, ‘He is afflicted by evil spirit/s!’</bt><v n="34" />Ma sakarang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, minum anggor deng makan roti ke biasa. Ju bosong cap sang Beta bilang, &lt;Dia tu, dasar manusia balalas! Pamabok barát lai! Pi bakawan deng tukang tagi bea dong! Satu partei deng orang tar laku-laku dong! Sonde tau diri lai!&gt;<bt>But now I, the Original/Authentic Human, drink wine and eat bread like usual. And you mark/stamp/ characterize Me saying, ‘His nature is fundamentally greedy! And [he's] a heavy drinker! [He] goes and befriends tax collectors! One party (=friend) with the nobodies! [He] doesn't know how to act properly!</bt><v n="35" />Ma bosong tanda sa, Be pung omong, é! Orang yang mangarti batúl, dong iko Tuhan pung mau-mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you-pl just take note of My speaking (=you'll see evidence later)! People who truly/correctly understand, they follow the Lord's will2 (=the things of God).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) Orang mangarti banya hal, tagal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">(al) Orang mangarti banya hal, tagal dong iko Tuhan pung jalan yang batúl. Nanti lia sandiri dia pung bukti dari dong pung cara idop! Ma tanda sa, Be pung omong! = you will find out later.<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus makan pesta di Simon pung ruma<bt>The Lord Yesus eats a feast at Simon's house</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Di itu kota, ada orang Farisi satu, nama Simon. Satu kali, dia undang Yesus dong datang makan di dia pung ruma. Tarima ame itu undangan, ju Yesus dong pi ko mau dudu makan.<bt>In that city, there was a Farisi person, named Simon. One time, he invited Yesus (collective) to come eat at his house. Accepting that invitation, then Yesus (coll) went to sit and eat.</bt><v n="37" />Itu waktu, ada satu parampuan nakal yang dapa dengar bilang, Yesus ada mau makan di situ. Ju dia maso datang, deng pegang bawa satu botol minya wangi yang mahal pung.<bt>At that time, there was a naughty woman (=prostitute) who heard that Yesus was eating there. So she went in, holding a bottle of fragrant oil that was very expensive.</bt><v n="38" />Dia datang deka sang Yesus dari Dia pung balakang. Ais dia pi tikam lutut di Yesus pung kaki. Tarús dia manangis makarereu sampe dia pung aer mata jato kaná Yesus pung kaki. Dia seka Yesus pung kaki pake dia pung rambu sandiri, deng ciom barmaen Yesus pung kaki. Ais ju dia po'a itu minya wangi pi Yesus pung kaki.<bt>She came close to Yesus from behind. Then she went and knelt at Yesus' feet. Next she cried sobbingly until her tears fell onto Yesus' feet. She wiped Yesus' feet using her own hair, and repeatedly kissed Yesus' feet. Then she poured that fragrant oil on Yesus' feet.</bt><note reference="7:37-38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:7, Markus 14:3, Yohanis 12:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Simon tu, kanál itu parampuan pung dudu-badiri. Andia ko dia pikir dalam hati bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini su jadi bukti Yesus ni, bukan Tuhan Allah pung jubir! Kalo batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah yang kirim sang Dia, su tantu Yesus tau bilang, parampuan yang ada sonto sang Dia tu, parampuan nakal. Tuhan Allah pung jubir sonde macam ke Dia tu, te orang barisi sonde bole badeka deng orang kamomos dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>This Simon knew that woman's situation. That's why he thought in his liver saying, “This has become evidence that this person Yesus here, is not the Lord God's spokesperson! If the Lord God had truly sent Him, surely Yesus would know that that woman who is touching Him there, is a naughty woman. The Lord God's spokesperson/s can't be like Him there, cuz clean/holy people can not be near/associate.with dirty/defiled people!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mau-mau sa = be willing to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mau-mau sa = be willing to let it happen</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ma Yesus baca apa yang Simon ada pikir. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu Mon! Bagini, bu. Beta mau kasi tau sang bu satu hal.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus read/knew what Simon was thinking. And He said, “Elder.sibling Mon (Simon nickname)! It's like this, elder.sibling. I want to tell elder.sibling something.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Simon manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu! Bapa Guru, omong sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Simon answered saying, “Ok. Father Teacher, go ahead and talk.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Tarús Yesus buang bahasa sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang yang tukang kasi pinjam doi sang orang laen. Dia parná kasi pinjam doi sang dua orang. Yang satu, dia kasi pinjam 500 doi perak; yang laen, cuma 50 sa.<bt>Then Yesus threw language out at him (=spoke in parables/veiled speech) saying, “There was a person who was a habitual loaner of money to other people. He had (once) loaned money to two people. To one, he loaned 500 silver monies, the other, only just 50.</bt><v n="42" />Ma sampe dia pung waktu kasi pulang itu doi, na, dong dua sonde mampu. Ju itu tukang kasi pinjam doi tu, jato kasian sang dong dua. Andia ko dia kasi bebas itu dua orang pung utang. Naa, kalo iko bu Mon pung pikir, dari itu dua orang yang pinjam doi tu, mana yang lebe sayang sang itu tukang kasi pinjam doi?&gt;&gt;<bt>But when it was time to return that money, na, the two of them were not able/capable. And that habitual money loaner, felt pity/compassion for the two of them. That's why he nullified those two people's debts. So/Now [shift topic], according to elder.sibling Mon's thinking, from those two people who borrowed money, which one loved the habitual money loaner more?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Simon sambar langsung bilang, &lt;&lt;Tantu yang pung utang paling bésar, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon answered straight away saying, “Of course the one who had the bigger debt!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambar = rampas, sambut dgn capat,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sambar = rampas, sambut dgn capat, langsung jawab</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, bu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “True/correct, elder.sibling!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ju Dia bale mangada sang itu parampuan, ko bilang sang Simon, &lt;&lt;Coba bu Mon taro mata di ini parampuan ni. Waktu Beta maso datang di bu pung ruma, bu sonde sadia aer ko cuci Beta pung kaki iko kotong pung adat. Ma ini parampuan kasi basa Beta pung kaki pake dia pung aer mata, abis seka kasi barisi pake dia pung rambu.<bt>Then He turned and faced that woman, to say to Simon, “Elder.sibling Mon have a look at this woman here. When I entered into elder.brother's (=your) house, elder.brother did not prepare water to wash My feet following our custom. But this woman wetted My feet using her tears, then wiped them clean using her hair.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***streamlined by removing “who has been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***streamlined by removing “who has been kneeling here for a while.” Not needed for participant identification.</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Deng tadi waktu sambut sang Beta pi dalam bu Mon pung ruma, bu Mon sonde ciom sang Beta, iko kotong pung biasa. Ma mulai dari Beta maso pi dalam ini ruma, ini parampuan sonde barenti ciom Beta pung kaki.<bt>And earlier, when greeting Me coming into elder.sibling Mon's house, elder.sibling Mon did not kiss Me following our habits. But starting from when I entered this house, this woman has not stopped kissing My feet.</bt><v n="46" />Bu Mon ju lupa itu adat po'a minya di tamu pung kapala, waktu Beta maso tadi. Ma ini parampuan su po'a minya wangi yang mahal mati pung di Beta pung kaki.<bt>Elder.sibling Mon also forgot our custom of pouring oil on the head of a guest, when I entered earlier. But this woman has poured fragrant oil that is very expensive on My feet.</bt><v n="47" />Bu Mon dengar bae-bae doo! Ini parampuan pung sala memang banya. Ma Tuhan su hapus buang samua, tagal dia su kasi tunju dia pung sayang deng rasa sukur bam-banya kasi sang Beta. Ma orang yang rasa diri sonde bekin sala banya, dia ju rasa sonde parlú dapa ampon banya. Andia ko dia sonde tau sayang, deng sonde tau rasa sukur bale kasi sang Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Elder.sibling Mon, listen carefully! The wrongs/sins of this woman are truly many. But the Lord has erased them all away, because she has shown her love and feelings of much thankfulness to Me. But a person who considers him/her.self to not have done many wrongs, s/he also does not feel a need for obtaining much forgiveness. That's why s/he does not know how to love, and does not know how to feel thankfulness in return to the Lord.” [EXEG: Trans. Notes, p.164, bottom].</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ais ju Yesus omong sang itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su hapus buang lu pung sala dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to that woman saying, “I have erased all your wrongs away!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Orang-orang yang ada dudu makan sama-sama, mulai bakusu-kusu bilang, &lt;&lt;Woeh! Dia pikir Dia ni, sapa?! Dia barani kasi ampon orang pung sala, ó! Padahal cuma Tuhan Allah sandiri sa yang ada pung hak ko hapus buang orang pung sala! Cue!&gt;&gt;<bt>People who were sitting eating together, began to whisper to each other saying, “Woeh! [+critical] Who does He think He is? He dares to forgive a person's wrongs! In.actual.fact, only just the Lord God alone is the one who has the right to erase people's wrongs! Cue! [+disgust]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang itu parampuan bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal lu su parcaya sang Beta, andia ko Tuhan su kasi salamat sang lu. Pulang su deng dame!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told that woman saying, “Because you have believed/trusted Me, that's why the Lord has saved you. Go.home in peace!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parampuan dong yang iko sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Women who follow/accompany the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Sonde lama lai, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang, ada jalan kuliling pi kota-kota deng kampong-kampong di situ. Dia jalan kasi tau orang dong so'al Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Itu jadi kabar bae kasi sang dong.<bt>Not long after that, Yesus and His twelve underlings, were walking around going to the cities and villages there. He went to tell people about the Lord God's ruling/governing. That became good news to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabar bae not capitalized???"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kabar bae not capitalized???</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dalam itu rombongan ada barapa parampuan yang iko ju. Ini parampuan dong ni, ada yang parná saki macam-macam, deng ada yang parná takaná setan. Ma Yesus su bekin bae sang dong samua. Macam ke Maria dari kampong Magdala. Dolu Yesus parná usir buang tuju setan kaluar dari dia.<bt>In that travel.group there were several women who also followed. These women, there were those who were once sick with all.sorts. of sickness, and there were those who once were afflicted with evil spirits. But Yesus had healed them all. Like Maria from Magdala village. Previously Yesus had expelled seven evil spirits out of her.</bt><v n="3" />Ada ju Susana, deng mama Yohana. Mama Yohana ni, andia bapa Kusa pung bini. Kusa tu, kapala urusan di raja Herodes pung ruma jabatan. Deng masi ada banya parampuan laen yang jalan sama-sama deng Yesus dong. Ini parampuan dong pake dong pung doi sandiri ko tanggong Yesus dong pung ongkos di jalan.<bt>There was also Susana, and mama Yohana. This mama Yohana, was father Kusa's wife. Kusa was the manager of raja Herodes' official house. And there were still many other women who travelled together with Yesus (collective). These women used their own money to pay.for/be.responsible.for Yesus (collective)'s costs on the road.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="the house manager"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">the house manager</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:2-3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 27:55-56, Markus 15:40-41, Lukas 23:49</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama so'al orang yang tanam bibit di tana macam-macam<bt>Comparison.story about a person who plants seed in various kinds of soil</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:1-9; Markus 4:1-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Satu kali, orang dong kaluar datang dari banya kampong ko cari sang Yesus. Waktu orang banya su bakumpul, ju Dia carita kasi sang dong satu umpama bilang,<bt>One time, people came out from many villages to look for Yesus. When many people/a crowd had gathered, He told them a comparison.stories/parable saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** reworked to match the Gk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** reworked to match the Gk better (Helong)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di mana-mana, kalo orang su bakumpul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Di mana-mana, kalo orang su bakumpul bam-banya, Yesus suka carita kasi sang dong pake umpama. Ini kali Dia carita bagini:</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />&lt;&lt;Ada satu orang tani pi siram bibit di dia pung kabón. Bibit saparu jato di jalan. Waktu orang jalan di situ, dong inja-inja itu bibit dong. Ais burung datang ko toto bekin abis.<bt>“There was a farmer went to scatter/broadcast seed in his/her garden. Some of the seed fell on the path. When people walked there, they stepped all.over those seeds. Then the bird/s came to peck them until completely gone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="para teen hodon: alongside the trail,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">para teen hodon: alongside the trail, right next to the trail</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Bibit saparu lai jato di tana babatu. Itu bibit mulai banupuk, ma dong layu buang, tagal kurang aer.<bt>Some other seeds fell on the rocky soil/land. Those seeds began to sprout, but they wilted away, because of lacking water.</bt><v n="7" />Bibit saparu yang laen jato di tampa baduri. Ma waktu itu bibit dong mulai banupuk, pohon baduri dong gepe kasi mati sang dong.<bt>Some other seeds fell in a thorn place. But when those seeds began to sprout, the thorn plants/trees pressed in killing them.</bt><v n="8" />Ma bibit yang laen lai, jato kaná di tana isi yang subur. Dong banupuk, ais tumbu jadi bésar sampe babua. Itu bibit dong kasi bale hasil saratus kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>But yet other seeds fell on the soil which was fertile. They sprouted, then grew becoming big until they fruit-ed. Those seeds gave back a yield one hundred times.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Carita abis bagitu, ju Yesus konci itu umpama, ais omong deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong yang ada pasang talinga, na, pikir ame bae-bae!&gt;&gt;<bt>After finishing story-ing like that, then Yesus locked/closed that comparison.story, and called/invited saying, “You-pl who are wearing ears (=paying attention), na, think about.this carefully!” [EXEG: KM /pange/ shares 2 senses of Gk word “call, invite”.] [DISCOURSE: Normally in these lgs, a quote margin signals a change of speaker. So here, giving the function of “closing the parable” is needed to allow any quote margin at all.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** tightened up (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** tightened up (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau kanapa Dia suka pake umpama<bt>The Lord Yesus tells why He likes to use comparison.stories</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:10-17; Markus 4:10-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais ju Yesus pung ana bua dong tanya itu umpama pung arti.<bt>After that, Yesus' underlings asked that comparison.stories meaning.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Tagal bosong su iko batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung mau-mau, andia ko Beta buka taráng-taráng ko bosong tau, karmana Tuhan mau parenta Dia pung orang dong. Ma orang laen dong sonde mau toe Tuhan pung mau-mau. Andia ko Beta ajar sang dong pake umpama sa. Te Tuhan pung jubir su tulis memang so'al ini orang dong bilang,<bt>He answered saying, “It's like this! Because you-pl have already truly followed the Lord God's will2 (the things of God), that's why I will clearly reveal so that you know, how the Lord will command/rule His people. But other people don't want to be concerned about the Lord's will2 (the things of God). That's why I teach them using only comparison.stories. Cuz the Lord's spokesperson has already written beforehand about these people saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dong su lia,<bt>&lt;They have seen,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sonde mau mangarti.<bt>but don't want to understand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong su dengar,<bt>They have heard,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sonde mau tau.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>but don't want to know.”&gt;</bt><note reference="8:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau itu umpama bibit pung arti<bt>The Lord Yesus tells the meaning of that comparison.story about seed/s</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:18-23; Markus 4:13-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju Yesus kasi tau itu umpama pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Bibit tu, andia Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata.<bt>Then Yesus told that comparison.story's meaning saying, “That seed, it is the Lord God's Words.</bt><v n="12" />Bibit yang jato di jalan tu, andia orang yang dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata, ma ais setan dong pung bos datang rampas bawa itu Kata-kata dari dong pung hati. Deng bagitu, dong sonde parcaya sang Tuhan, deng sonde dapa salamat.<bt>That seed which fell on the path, that is people who hear the Lord's Words, but then the evil spirit's boss comes and snatches away those Words from their livers. In that way, they don't believe in the Lord, and don't get/obtain salvation.</bt><v n="13" />Bibit yang jato di tana babatu tu, andia orang yang dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata deng sanáng. Ma dong pung akar sonde maso dalam-dalam. Dong mulai parcaya, ma kalo susa su nae kaná sang dong, dong gampang jato.<bt>That seed which fell on the rocky soil, that's people who hear the Lord's Word's happily. But their roots don't go deep inside. They begin to believe, but if/when difficulty arises and afflicts them, they easily fall.</bt><v n="14" />Bibit yang jato pi tampa baduri tu, andia orang yang dengar deng tarima Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Ma sonde lama ju, dong lupa buang itu Kata-kata, te dong lebe barepot deng dong pung urusan sandiri sa, deng dong pung harta macam-macam, deng mau idop sanáng-sanáng sa. Andia ko, dong pung parcaya tu, sonde ada pung hasil apa-apa.<bt>That seed which fell on that thorn place, that is people who hear and receive the Lord's Words. But not long and they completely forget those Words, cuz they are more worried/thinking about their own affairs, and their various kinds of possessions, and they want to just live happily/pleasantly. That's why that faith of theirs, doesn't have any results at all.</bt><v n="15" />Ma bibit yang jato di tana isi yang subur tu, andia orang yang pung hati bae deng hati lurus. Waktu dong dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, ju dong taro bae-bae dalam hati. Deng bagitu, dong parcaya tarús, deng bekin banya hal yang bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the seed which fell on that fertile soil, that is people who have good/kind/generous livers and straight/righteous/honest/just livers. When they hear God's Words, then they put/store them carefully in their livers. In that way, they keep believing, and do many things which are good.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama so'al tutu lampu pake pareu tana<bt>Comparison.story about covering a lamp using a clay pot</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:21-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde mungkin orang kasi manyala lampu te'oek, ais tutu ame deng pareu tana. Deng sonde ada orang yang taro lampu pi kolong koi. Te kalo bekin bagitu, na, orang sonde bisa dapa lia dia pung taráng lai. Lampu yang ada pung guna, andia yang ada taro di tampa tinggi, ko biar dia pung cahaya kasi taráng orang yang maso datang.<bt>Then Yesus spoke again saying, “It's not possible that people light a wick.lantern, then cover it over with a clay pot. And no one puts a lamp under the bed. Cuz if [someone] does like that, na, people cannot see its light anymore. A lamp which has worth/value, is what is put in a high place, so that its radiance/light illuminates the people who come in.</bt><note reference="8:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:15, Lukas 11:33</note><v n="17" />Samua yang tasambunyi sakarang, nanti jadi kantara. Deng samua hal yang orang sonde tau sakarang, nanti orang dapa tau.<bt>Everything that is hidden now, will later become obvious. And everything that people do not know now, later people will know. [NOTE to daughter translations: May want connector linking 16-17 “Itu su sama deng”]</bt><note reference="8:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:26, Lukas 12:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Jadi bosong musti pikir ame bae-bae ini hal dong. Orang yang mau cari tau batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau, dia tamba pintar. Ma orang yang sonde pusing deng Tuhan pung mau, dia tamba bodo.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) you-pl must think carefully about these things. A person who truly wants to know the Lord's will (=the things of the Lord), s/he will increase in skill/cleverness/wisdom. But the person who is not concerned with the Lord's will, he increases in stupidity.” [TEXT: Gk. identical to Mk. 4:25]. [EXEG: context is about wisdom and spiritual understanding (about the Kingdom). TN on this verse, also Gundry on Mark; Marshall on Luke thinks it's about knowledge about teaching.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***note, this rendering explicitly links it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***note, this rendering explicitly links it to God's will, so increasingly ignorant is pretty good. Several other consultants have pushed us in this direction. Literal falls flat. Nobody I've read thinks it's about money.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:29, Markus 4:25, Lukas 19:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung kelu yang batúl dong<bt>The Lord Yesus' true family</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:46-50; Markus 3:31-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Satu kali, Yesus ada sibuk deng orang banya dong. Ju Dia pung mama deng adi-adi dong datang ko mau katumu deng Dia. Ma dong sonde bisa deka-deka deng Dia, tagal orang talalu banya.<bt>One time, Yesus was busy/preoccupied with many people. Then His mama and his younger siblings came to meet with Him. But they could not get close to Him, because there were too many people.</bt><v n="20" />Ju ada orang pi kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa pung mama deng adi-adi dong ada di luar. Dong ada mau katumu deng Bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then a person went and told Yesus saying, “Father! Father's mother and younger siblings are outside. They want to meet with Father.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo! Ma bagini. Beta pung mama deng sodara yang batúl dong, andia orang yang dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, ais bekin iko.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He replied saying, “Yes! But it's like this. My true mother and siblings, are people who hear the Lord God's Words, and then follow them.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(dt) 01/Mar/2006"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">(dt) 01/Mar/2006</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin tadó angin ribut<bt>The Lord Yesus calms the noisy wind (=storm)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:23-27; Markus 4:35-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Satu kali, Yesus ajak Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari kotong nae parahu, ko pi dano pung sablá.&gt;&gt; Ju dong nae parahu satu, ko dong mulai star.<bt>One time, Yesus invited His underlings saying, “Let's us-inc get in the boat, to go to the lake's other side.” And they got in a boat, to begin to start.</bt><v n="23" />Waktu dong ada balayar, Yesus tidor. Sonde lama ju, angin ribut datang. Galombang puku maso dalam parahu. Ju dong su mau calaka.<bt>When they were sailing, Yesus slept. Not long, (=soon) then a noisy wind/storm came. Waves beat entering into the boat. They were about to have a mishap.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Lia bagitu, ju ana bua dong kasi bangun sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Bos, é! Bangun ko tolong dolo! Kotong su mau mati tanggalám ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then the underlings woke Yesus up saying, “Boss! Boss, é! Wake up and help! We are about ready to die drowning here!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus bangun. Ais Dia togor itu angin deng galombang bilang, &lt;&lt;Barenti su!&gt;&gt; Ju galombang deng angin jadi tadó memang.<bt>And Yesus woke.up. Then He scolded the wind and waves saying, “Stop!” And the waves and the wind became calm immediately.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais Dia togor sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong masi balóm parcaya sang Beta ju?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He scolded His underlings saying, “Why do you still not believe in Me?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong taku deng heran. Ju dong batanya satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Yesus ni, sapa? Karmana ko Dia bisa parenta angin deng galombang, ko dong iko Dia pung mau?&gt;&gt;<bt>They were afraid and amazed. Then they asked each.other saying, “Awii! [+impressed] Who is this Yesus? How is it that He can command the wind and waves, so they follow His will?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus usir setan dari orang gila<bt>The Lord Yesus expels evil spirits from a crazy person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:28-34; Markus 5:1-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sonde lama ju dong sampe di da'era Gerasa, di dano Galilea pung sablá.<bt>Not long again, they arrived at Gerasa region, on lake Galilea's other side.</bt><note reference="8:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae tulis bilang, &lt;Gerasa&gt;. Ada tulisan saparu yang tulis bilang, &lt;Gadara&gt;. Deng ada saparu lai yang tulis bilang, &lt;Gergesa&gt;.<bt>The best Yunani language writings write saying, ‘Garasa’. There are some writings which write saying, ‘Gadara’. And there are some others which write saying, ‘Gergesa’.</bt></note><v n="27-29" />Di situ ada satu orang yang su lama takaná setan dong. Dia sonde ada pung ruma, deng dia cuma tenga di kuburan sa. Tiap hari dia pal pi-datang deng talanjang bulat sa. Te setan dong parenta sang dia tarús-tarús. Orang su ika sang dia ulang kali pake rante deng galáng besi, ma dia kasi putus buang sa. Ais setan dong maen paksa dia ko lari pi tampa sunyi.<bt>There, there was a person who had been afflicted for a long time by evil spirits. He did not have a house, and he only lived just in the grave.yard. Everyday he went aimlessly around totally naked. Cuz (elaboration) the evil spirits continually ordered him around. People had tied him over and over with iron chains and bracelets, but he would just break them apart. Then the evil spirits habitually forced him to run to isolated/deserted place/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="use of iron bracelets here different"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">use of iron bracelets here different than in Mark</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Yesus dong turun dari parahu, itu orang gila datang sang Dia. Itu orang batarea, ais buang diri di Yesus pung kaki. Tarús Yesus parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh, setan! Kaluar dari ini orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (collective) got out of the boat, that crazy person came to Him. That person yelled, then threw himself at Yesus' feet. Then Yesus ordered saying, “Weh, [+attention, +rebuke] evil spirit! Come out of this person!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@sense of prostrate here not clear,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@sense of prostrate here not clear, could be seen as attacking ??</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju itu orang gila batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Woi! Jang ganggu sang beta! Te beta tau Lu ni, Yesus, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi pung Ana! Lu jang siksa sang beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that crazy person yelled saying, “Woi! [+challenge] Don't bother me! Cuz (elaboration) I know that You here are Yesus, the Child of the highest Lord God! You don't torture/ill.treat me!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akathartos: unclean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">akathartos: unclean</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung nama sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked him saying, “What is your name?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju itu setan manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Legion</span>, te botong ada banya, tingka ke tantara ribu-ribu.&gt;&gt; Dia bilang bagitu, tagal ada banya setan yang maso tenga di dia pung diri.<bt>Then that/those evil spirit/s answered saying, “<span class="Italic">Legion</span>, cuz we-exc are many, like thousands of soldiers.” He said like that, because there were many evil spirits who entered in and stayed inside him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Itu setan dong maen minta tarús sang Yesus ko jang suru sang dong pi Lobang Siksa, andia tampa tahan kuasa jahat dong.<bt>Those evil spirits continually asked over.and.over to Yesus to not ordered them to go to the Torture Hole, that is the place of detaining the powers of evil. [EXEG: Marshall; CEV also explicates in verse. NOTE to daughter translations: If made direct quote, perhaps explication should be put in ftn, since this is fast-moving narrative.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="andia tampa setan dong kaná siksa."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">andia tampa setan dong kaná siksa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ma deka-deka di situ, ada babi satu kalompok bésar yang ada do'i-do'i tana ko cari makan di gunung pung pinggir. Ju itu setan dong minta sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Suru sa ko botong maso pi dalam itu babi dong!&gt;&gt; Ju Yesus ia bae.<bt>But nearby there, there was a big group of pigs who were rooting around looking for food on the side/slope of the mountain. Then those evil spirits asked Yesus saying, “Just order us-exc to enter into those pigs!” And Yesus was agreeable. [NOTE to daughter translations: if “looking for food” is part of “rooting around” then don't force both to be present.]</bt><v n="33" />Ais, itu setan dong kaluar kasi tenga itu laki-laki, ju dong maso pi dalam itu babi dong. Itu babi dong samua jadi gila, tarús dong lari tabodo-bodo turun dari itu gunung, ko jato pi dalam dano. Ju dong samua mati tanggalám.<bt>Then, those evil spirits come out and left that male, and they entered into those pigs. Those pigs all became crazy, and they ran helter-skelter down that mountain, to fall into the lake. Then they all died drowning. [NOTE to daughter translations: There is no cliff around Galilee, but there are steep banks, so make sure your word matches steep slope /gunung pung pinggir/ or just /pinggir/. /Jurang/ creates too much noise. Match Mark 5:13 (if it's been fixed in your translation).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, itu setan dong kaluar kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ais, itu setan dong kaluar kasi tenga itu laki-laki, ju dong maso pi dalam itu babi dong. Itu babi dong samua jadi gila, tarús dong lari tabodo-bodo turun dari itu gunung, ko malompa iko pinggir jurang maso pi dalam dano. Ju dong samua mati tanggalám.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Lia bagitu ju, tukang jaga babi dong lari pi kuliling kampong-kampong di situ, ju dong carita samua-samua.<bt>Seeing like that, then the habitual guarders of the pigs ran to all the villages around there, and they told everything.</bt><v n="35" />Dengar dong pung carita bagitu, orang banya dong kaluar pi itu tampa. Dong mau lia sandiri apa yang su jadi. Sampe di situ, ju dong dapa lia itu orang yang takaná setan ada dudu tanáng-tanáng deka Yesus pung kaki. Dia su pake pakean, deng dia su sonde gila lai. Lia bagitu, ju dong samua jadi taku.<bt>Hearing their story like that, many people come out to that place. They wanted to see what had happened. Arriving there, they saw that person who was/had.been afflicted by evil spirits/s was sitting quietly near Yesus' feet. He had clothes on, and his craziness was gone/disappeared. Seeing like that, then they all became afraid.</bt><v n="36" />Ais orang-orang yang tadi dapa lia itu parkara, kasi tau orang yang baru datang dong karmana ko itu orang gila su jadi bae kambali.<bt>Then the people who had seen that event, told the people who had just come how it happened that that crazy person had become well again.</bt><v n="37" />Ju orang Gerasa samua yang tenga di itu da'era dong, minta sang Yesus ko Dia jalan kasi tenga sang dong, te dong samua ada taku mau mati.<bt>Then all the Gerasa people who lived in that area, requested Yesus that He go leaving them, cuz they all were very afraid.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus dong pi nae dalam parahu, ko mau pulang kambali pi dano Galilea pung sablá.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) went into the boat, to go back again to the other side of Galilea lake.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ma itu orang yang tadi takaná setan tu, maen noki-noki sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Biar ko beta iko deng Bapa ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that person who previously been afflicted by evil spirits, repeatedly begged/insisted Yesus saying, “Father! Allow that I also go with Father!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus balas bilang,<bt>But Yesus replied saying,</bt><v n="39" />&lt;&lt;Bagini sa! Lebe bae lu pulang pi lu pung kelu dong, ko carita sang dong so'al Tuhan Allah pung bae, yang Dia su bekin kasi sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>“It's like this! It's better (=polite imperative) you go.home to your family, to tell them about the Lord God's goodness, which He has done for you.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu orang pi kuliling itu kota, ju dia carita kasi samua orang so'al Yesus bekin bae sang dia.<bt>Then, that person went all around that city, and he told all the people about Yesus healing him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi idop kambali Yairus pung ana nona, deng bekin bae parampuan yang saki dara loos<bt>The Lord Yesus causes Yairus' young.girl child to live again, and heals a woman who was ill of unrestrained blood</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:18-26; Markus 5:21-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ais ju Yesus dong balayar pulang pi dano Galilea pung sablá. Waktu dong turun dari parahu, orang banya dong su tunggu-tunggu sang Dia. Dong datang makarubu ko mau sambut sang Dia.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) sailed back to lake Galilea's other side. When they got out of the boat, many people were already waiting for Him. They came crowding around to welcome Him.</bt><v n="41-42" />Di situ ju, ada satu orang, nama Yairus. Dia tu, kapala ruma sambayang di itu kota. Dia pung ana, cuma satu biji sa; ana nona, umur dua blas taon. Sakarang itu nona ada saki karás amper mati. Waktu Yairus lia Yesus pung datang, dia pi tikam lutut di Yesus pung muka. Dia minta ko Yesus datang di dia pung ruma, ko tolong sang dia pung ana nona.<bt>There also, was a person, named Yairus. He was the head of the worship house in that city. His child, was only one single child, a young.girl child, twelve years old. Now that young.girl was very sick almost dead. When Yairus saw Yesus' coming, he went and knelt in front of Yesus. He requested that Yesus come to his house, to help his young.girl child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Yesus manyao ia sang dia, ju dong jalan pi Yairus pung ruma. Ma orang banya dong ju tar sampat ko mau iko ju. Andia ko dong jalan baseti-baseti.<bt>When Yesus answered yes to him, then they walked to Yairus' house. But many people were also eager to follow (idiom). That's why they walked pushing.and.shoving.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tar sampat ko iko = eager"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tar sampat ko iko = eager to follow</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ada satu parampuan ju yang jalan iko deng dong. Dia pung datang bulan sonde tau barenti batúl su dua blas taon. Dia su kasi abis dia pung doi deng harta dong, ko pake bayar kasi dokter dong. Ma sonde ada yang bisa bekin bae sang dia. Dia pung panyaki tu, maen foe tarús.<bt>There was also a woman who walked following them. Her menstrual period had not stopped correctly for twelve years. She had already spent all here money and possessions, to pay the doctors. But there was not one who could heal her. That illness of her's, continued to relapse continually. [EXEG: Last sentence implied from “no one could cure her”; NOTE to daughter tranlations: Gk TEXT: UBS 4th edition, AGNT, NRSV, NLT, CEV has info on physicians in text. TB2 has info on physicians in brackets. Some Gk manuscripts do not have it at all. NIV puts it in a ftn. Marshall notes “which is sufficiently different in wording from Mk. to suggest that it may be an original part of Luke's text”. FTN added.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** ftn added (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** ftn added (Helong)</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:43" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu sonde tulis &lt;&lt;Dia su kasi abis dia pung doi deng harta dong, ko pake bayar kasi dokter dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Some Yunani writings don't write “She had already spent all her money and possessions, to pay the doctors.”</bt></note><v n="44" />Ju dia datang deka-deka sang Yesus dari Dia pung balakang. Ais dia sonto ame Yesus pung ujung baju. Waktu dia sonto abis, ju dia pung dara loos barenti memang.<bt>Then she came close to Yesus from His back. Then she touched the edge of Yesus' clothing. When she had touched [him], then her unrestrained blood stopped immediately.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Takuju Yesus badiri, ais Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang ada sonto sang Beta ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>Unexpectedly Yesus stopped walking (lit: stood), then He asked saying, “Who was it who touched Me?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Takuju Yesus barenti jalan, abis Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Takuju Yesus barenti jalan, abis Dia tanya, bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang ada sonto sang Beta ni?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma sonde ada satu orang yang mangaku ju. Ais Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos lai, ju! Ko orang banya ada jalan baseti bagini! Dong su, yang maen batola dari balakang.&gt;&gt;<bt>But not a single person acknowledged/confessed. Then Petrus said, “Come on, Boss! (+slight exasperation) So many people are walking pushing.and.shoving like this! They are the ones who keep shoving from behind.” [DISCOURSE: helps carry speaker attitude]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bos lai, ju! ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Bos lai, ju! =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ma Yesus bilang sang dia, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Tadi Beta rasa ada kuasa yang kaluar dari Beta. Jadi Beta tau ada satu orang yang sangaja sonto sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke to him, “No! I recently/just felt power which went out of Me. So (consequently), I know there was a person who purposefully touched Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="quote margin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">quote margin</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Waktu itu parampuan sadar kalo dia sonde bisa sambunyi, ju dia taku mau mati. Dia gamatar, ko tikam lutut di Yesus. Ais dia carita dia pung akar masala di muka orang dong samua. Tarús dia kasi tau bilang, pas dia sonto sang Yesus, ju dia bae memang.<bt>When that woman was aware that she could not hide, then she was very afraid. She trembled, and knelt at Yesus. Then she storied in from of many people the root of her problem. Then she told that, exactly when she touched Yesus, she was healed immediately.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ais Yesus omong sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Susi! Lu su jadi bae, tagal lu parcaya sang Beta. Pulang ruma deng dame su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to her saying, “Elder.sister! You are healed, because you believed in Me. Go home in peace!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong deng itu parampuan, ju Yairus pung orang satu datang kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu, Bapa, é! Bapa pung ana su sonde ada lai! Dia su mati, jadi sonde usa bekin repot lai sang Bapa Guru.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus was still speaking with that woman, then one of Yairus' people came and told him saying, “Oh, dear, Father! Father's child is no more (=is dead)! She has died, so it's not neccessary to bother Father Teacher anymore.” [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure /kasi tau sang dia/ traces to Yairus, not Jesus (who is grammatically in focus). If read beyond quote margin it's almost impossible to link to anyone except Yairus.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ma waktu Yesus dapa dengar itu orang pung laporan, ju Dia bilang sang Yairus, &lt;&lt;Bu! Tanáng sa! Jang kawatir! Parcaya sang Tuhan Allah sa. Dia yang kasi salamat sang bu pung ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>But when Yesus heard that person's report, then He said to Yairus, “Elder.brother! Be calm! Don't worry! Just believe in the Lord God. He is the one who saves elder.brother's child.” [EXEG: Gk. is the word for ‘saved’ here, although Eng. trans have ‘healed’, but ‘healed’ doesn't collocate in KM with a dead person--‘saved’ does.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51-53" />Waktu dong sampe di Yairus pung ruma, orang dong su ponu di situ. Dong ada manangis makarereu. Ju Yesus togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong barenti manangis su! Ini ana sonde mati. Dia cuma tidor sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived at Yairus' house, people where already full/crowded.in there. They were crying sobbingly. Then Yesus scolded them saying, “You-pl stop crying! This child is not dead. She is only just sleeping!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma orang dong cuma katawa bengko mulu sang Dia sa, te dong yang su lia sandiri itu ana pung putus napas. Ais ju Yesus minta itu ana nona pung mama-bapa, Petrus, Yohanis, deng Yakobis, maso pi dalam sama-sama deng Dia. Yang laen dong Dia suru tunggu di luar sa.<bt>But they only just laughed with a crooked mouth at Him (cynically), cuz (elaboration) they were the ones who had seen for themselves that child's last breath. Then Yesus requested that young.girl child's mother-father, Petrus, Yohanis and Yakobis to go in together with Him. The others He told to just stay outside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu ana pung tarek nafas terahir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">itu ana pung tarek nafas terahir &gt; kamus ; katawa bengko mulu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kategeloon (imperfect): they were laughing him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">kategeloon (imperfect): they were laughing him down, ridiculing him. Not mockery ("make fun"), just reacting to how he could be so dumb. While they were doing that, Jesus went ahead and brought her back to life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Dong maso, ju Yesus pegang itu ana pung tangan, deng pange bilang, &lt;&lt;Nona! Bangun suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>They entered, then Yesus held that child's hand, and called saying, “Young.girl! Get up!”</bt><v n="55" />Takuju sa, itu ana idop kambali, abis dia bangun memang. Ais Yesus suru itu nona pung mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi ini ana makan doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Unexpectedly/suddenly that child lived again, and she got/woke up immediately. Then Yesus ordered that young.girl's mother saying, “Give this child food!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneuma: in this case, &quot;her life&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">pneuma: in this case, "her life"</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Itu nona pung mama-bapa heran mau mati. Ma Yesus kasi inga sang dong, ko jang kasi tasiar itu kabar pi orang dong.<bt>That young.girl's mother-father were very surprised. But Yesus reminded/warned them, to not spread that news around to people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus utus Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang<bt>The Lord Yesus commissions His twelve underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:5-15; Markus 6:7-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, Yesus kumpul Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang. Ais Dia kasi sang dong kuasa ko bisa usir setan, deng bisa bekin bae orang saki dari dong pung panyaki macam-macam.<bt>One time, Yesus gathered his twelve underlings. Then He gave them power/authority to be able to expel evil spirits, and to heal sick people from all sorts of their illnesses.</bt><v n="2" />Dia utus sang dong, ko jalan kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta. Dia ju utus sang dong ko bekin bae orang saki dong di mana-mana.<bt>He commissioned them, to go tell people about the Lord God holding power/authority. He also commissioned them to heal sick people everywhere.</bt><v n="3" />Ma Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Bosong sonde usa bawa apa-apa di jalan. Jalan deng baju di badan sa. Sonde usa bawa tongkat, ko tas, ko bakál, ko doi. Baju ganti ju, sonde usa bawa!<bt>But (contrary to expectation) He told them saying, “Remember! You do not need to take anything on the road. Travel just with a shirt/dress on your body. It's not neccessary to bring a walking.stick, or a bag, or travel.food, or money. Even a change of clothes, it's not neccessary to take!</bt><v n="4" />Kalo bosong maso di satu kampong, ko ada orang yang mau tarima sang bosong, na, pi tenga di dong pung ruma sa. Jang bapili-pili ruma. Tenga di situ tarús, sampe bosong barangkat kasi tenga itu kampong.<bt>If/when you-pl enter into a village, so there are people who want to accept you, na, just go stay at their house. Don't be picky.selecting a house. Keep staying there, until you leave that village.</bt><v n="5" />Kalo bosong maso pi satu kampong, ais orang di situ sonde mau tarima deng sonde mau dengar sang bosong, na, angka kaki kasi tenga sang dong sa. Kalo bosong kaluar dari situ, bekin iko adat ko kabás buang abu dari bosong pung kaki. Kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;Bosong sonde mau dengar, na, biar ko bosong pikol tanggong-jawab sandiri!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>If/when you enter into a village, and the people there do not want to receive and don't want to hear you, na, just pick up your feet and leave them behind. If/when you leave there, do according to the custom of brushing off the dust from your feet. Tell them saying, ‘You don't want to hear, so, may it be that you carry the responsibility/consequences yourselves!”’</bt><note reference="9:3-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:4-11; Utusan dong pung Carita 13:51</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais ju itu ana bua dong jalan dari kampong pi kampong. Dong kasi tau orang dong so'al Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae. Ais dong ju bekin bae orang saki dong.<bt>Afterwards then, those underlings went traveling from village to village. They told people about the Lord God's Good News. Then they also healed sick people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Herodes bingung so'al Tuhan Yesus<bt>Raja Herodes is confused about the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:1-12; Markus 6:14-29)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Itu waktu, carita macam-macam so'al Yesus su sampe di raja Herodes Antipas<bt>That time, all sorts of stories about Yesus had arrived at raja Herodes Antipas'</bt><note reference="9:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Herodes Antipas tu, Herodes Bésar pung ana. Herodes Bésar tu, yang parenta bunu bekin mati ana-ana kici di Betlehem pas Tuhan Yesus pung lahir. Lia Mateos 2:16-18.<bt>That Herodes Antipas, was the Big Herodes' child. That Big Herodes, was the one who ordered to murder kill the small children in Bethlehem at the Lord Yesus' birth. See Mateos 2:16-18.</bt></note>pung talinga. Dengar itu carita dong, ju dia bingung, tagal ada barapa orang yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus tu, andia Yohanis tukang sarani yang su idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>ears. Hearing those stories, he became confused, because there were several people who said, “That Yesus, is Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer who has lived again.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ada saparu lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, ba'i Elia yang su idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>There were some others who said, “He's Gf Elia who has lived again.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added \p"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added \p</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ada laen lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, satu dari Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu yang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>And there were still others who said, “He is one of the Lord's other spokespersons from long ago.” [DISCOURSE: paragraph added for change of speaker; July 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ada lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, ba'i Elia yang su idop kambali. Kalo bukan, na, satu dari Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu yang laen dong.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:14, Markus 8:28, Lukas 9:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma Herodes inga bilang, &lt;&lt;Tempo hari, beta su suru potong bekin putus Yohanis pung kapala. Dia su idop kambali, ko apa? Ais ini satu ni, sapa lai?&gt;&gt; Ju dia usaha ko mau katumu muka deng Yesus.<bt>But Herodes remembered saying, “A while ago, I gave the order to cut off Yohanis' head. Is he now alive again, or what? Then this one here, who else is he?” And so he tried to meet Yesus in person.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan lima ribu orang<bt>The Lord Yesus feeds five thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:13-21; Markus 6:30-44; Yohanis 6:1-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Satu waktu, ana bua yang Yesus su utus tu, dong pulang ko bakumpul ulang lai deng Dia. Dong kasi tau sang Dia samua yang dong su bekin ame. Ais Yesus dong jalan diam-diam pi satu tampa deka deng kampong Betsaida, ko dong pi barenti cape di situ.<bt>One time, those underlings which Yesus had commissioned, they returned to gather again with Him. They told Him everything which they had done. Then Yesus (collective) went quietly to a place near Betsaida village, so that they could rest there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="retrét = (spiritual) retreat, get away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">retrét = (spiritual) retreat, get away from distractions of daily life, implies in a group ; = ko dong bisa sandiri di situ</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma orang banya dong dapa ciom Yesus dong mau pi mana, ais dong ba'ekor sang Dia pi. Jadi Yesus tarima bae sang dong, tarús Dia bekin bae orang saki dong samua, deng Dia carita sang dong so'al Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta.<bt>But many people were able to smell (=ascertain) where Yesus (collective) were going, so they tailed along after Him. So (consequently), Yesus accepted them, and He healed all the sick people, and He told them about the Lord God's holding rule. [DISCOURSE: reversed order because of grammatical clash of complement clauses.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu su sore, ju Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang dong, bawa usul sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae Bapa suru ini orang dong pi kampong-kampong yang badeka di sini, ko bisa cari dong pung makanan sandiri. Deng biar dong pi cari tampa ko dong manumpang tidor. Te tampa sunyi bagini, karmana ko dong bisa dapa makan?&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was late.afternoon, then His twelve underlings, brought a suggestion to Yesus saying, “It's better Father (=you) tell these people to go to the villages near here, so they can find their own food. And let them go look for a place to sleep overnight. Cuz (elaboration) in a desolate/deserted place like this, how are they able to eat?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13-14" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Biar bosong sa yang kasi makan sang dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Like.this! You-pl be the ones who give them food!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe', Bapa lai! Mana bisa bagitu? Ini orang dong ni, ada lima ribu lebe! Itu cuma laki-laki sa, balóm itong parampuan deng ana-ana lai! Ais kotong pung roti cuma lima bua, deng ikan dua ekor sa. Kalo Bapa mau botong yang kasi makan ini orang banya dong, na, karmana ko botong bisa béli makan bam-banya kasi sang dong?!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they protested saying, “Good grief, Father! How can we do like that? These people here, there's more than five thousand of them! That only just the men, not yet counting the women and children! And our-inc bread is only five pieces, and just two tails (counter) of fish. If Father wants us to feed these many people, na, how is it that we can buy lots.and.lots of food for them?!”</bt><note reference="9:13-14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ator ini orang dong dudu bakumpul lima-lima pulu, satu kalompok.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered them saying, “Arrange these people to sit gathered in fifty per one group.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais dong pi ator bagitu.<bt>So they went to arrange like that.</bt><v n="16" />Waktu dong su dudu, ju Yesus ame itu roti lima bua deng ikan dua ekor. Ais Dia mangada pi langit, ko sambayang minta tarima kasi. Ais Dia kasi pica-pica itu roti deng ikan, ju Dia sorong kasi ana bua dong ko pi bagi-bagi kasi itu orang dong.<bt>When they had sat.down, then Yesus took those five pieces of bread and two tails of fish. Then He looked up to the sky, to pray reciprocating thankyou. Then He broke up that bread and fish, and He extended them to his underling to go divide out to those people.</bt><v n="17" />Dong samua makan sampe kinyang. Ais dong kumpul ame itu makanan sisa dong, sampe ponu dua blas bakul.<bt>They all ate until they were full. Then they gathered that leftover food, to the point that there were twelve baskets full.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takinyang-kinyang = stuffed to the gills,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">takinyang-kinyang = stuffed to the gills, carries sense of glutton</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus mulai sadar bilang, Tuhan Yesus tu, Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu<bt>Petrus starts to be aware that the Lord Yesus is Kristus, that is, the Person whom the Lord God had promised beforehand from long ago</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:13-19; Markus 8:27-29)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Satu kali, Yesus ada sandiri ko sambayang di satu tampa. Ais Dia pung ana bua dong bakumpul deng Dia. Sambayang abis, ju Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar-dengar orang omong bilang, Beta ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, Yesus was alone praying at a place. Then His underlings gathered together with Him. After praying, then He asked them saying, “You-pl hear people talking about me, who are they saying I am?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada yang bilang Bapa ni, Yohanis tukang sarani. Laen lai bilang, mangkali Bapa ni, ba'i Elia. Kalo sonde, na, satu dari Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu yang su idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, “There are those who say Father here is Yohanis the Habitual Baptiser. Others yet again say, probably Father here, is grandfather Elia. If not, na, one of the Lord God's spokespersons from long ago who has lived again.”</bt><note reference="9:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:1-2, Markus 6:14-15, Lukas 9:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Tarús Yesus tanya lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo iko bosong sandiri, na, bosong anggap Beta ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked them again saying, “According to you-pl yourselves, na, who do you consider I am?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais ju Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa ni, Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus replied saying, “Father here is Kristus, that is the Person whom the Lord God appointed/designated beforehand long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho khriston tou theou: only here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ho khriston tou theou: only here</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 6:68-69</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais Yesus larang sang dong ko jang kasi tau sapa-sapa bilang, Dia tu, Kristus.<bt>Then Yesus forbade them to not tell anyone that He was the one who was Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong so'al Dia pung mati, deng Dia pung idop kambali<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks about His death, and His living again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:21-28; Markus 8:31--9:1)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais ju Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Beta musti pikol sangsara barát macam-macam. Nanti orang Yahudi pung tua-tua adat, kapala agama pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong sonde mau tarima bilang, Beta ni, Kristus. Ais nanti dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta. Memang Beta mati, ma dia pung lusa, beta idop kambali!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus spoke further saying, “I here am the Original/Authentic Human. I must bear all.sorts of heavy suffering. Later the traditional Yahudi elders, the bosses of the religious heads, and the religion teachers will not accept that I here am Kristus. Then later they will murder kill Me. Certainly I will die, but on the day.after.the.tomorrow, I will live again!” [EXEG: UBS HB says /te trete heimera/ = on third day after this one = day after tomorrow].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed FTN to get rid of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed FTN to get rid of BI bangkit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodokimastheenai: be rejected, repudiated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">apodokimastheenai: be rejected, repudiated</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani pung cara itong hari, andia, ini hari = hari partama; beso = hari kadua; lusa = hari katiga. Jadi Tuhan Yesus pung mati, itong hari partama (Jumat Agung), deng Dia pung idop kambali, itong hari katiga, andia dia pung lusa (Minggu Paska).<bt>The Yunani language way of counting days, is, today = the first day; tomorrow = the second day; the day.after.tomorrow = the third day. So (consequently) the Lord Yesus' death, count it on the first day (Good Friday), and His living again, count it the third day, which was the day.after.tomorrow (Easter Sunday).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais ju Dia kasi tau orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau iko sang Beta, na, dia musti batahan iko tarús tiap hari. Dia musti lapás buang dia pung mau-mau sandiri. Dia musti iko tarús, biar orang ada mau bunu sang dia, sama ke orang pikol dia pung kayu palang ko pi di dia pung tampa mati.<bt>Then He told the many people saying, “The person who wants to follow Me, na, s/he must endure and follow continually every day. S/he must throw away his/her own desires. S/he must follow continually, even if/though someone wants to murder him/her, like a person carrying his/her cross to go to his/her place of death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sapa to Orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Sapa to Orang</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:38, Lukas 14:27</note><v n="24" />Te orang yang sadia mati tagal dia iko sang Beta, nanti dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan. Ma orang yang cuma mau idop buat dia pung diri sandiri sa, nanti dia tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who is prepared to die because s/he follows Me, later s/he will be able to live continually with the Lord. But the person who only wants to live just for him/herself, later s/he will be separated off/cut off from God. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. almost identical with Mk. 8:35; Gk here is the ‘perish’ term, so KT].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed last sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed last sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma orang yang cuma mau idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma orang yang cuma mau idop buat dia pung diri sandiri sa, nanti dia pung idop tu, ilang bagitu sa!</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, Lukas 17:33, Yohanis 12:25</note><v n="25" />Kalo orang dapa dunya pung isi samua, ma Tuhan Allah tola buang sang dia, na, dia dapa ontong apa?<bt>If a person obtains the world's entire contents, but the Lord God throws him/her away, na, what has s/he gained?</bt><v n="26" />Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Jadi orang yang malu iko sang Beta, deng malu pegang Beta pung ajaran, Beta ju nanti malu mangaku sang dia di Tuhan Allah pung muka waktu Beta kambali dari sorga. Te nanti Beta turun datang deng Bapa pung kuasa yang hebat, sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dari sorga.<bt>I here, am the Authentic Human. So (consequently) the person who is ashamed to follow Me, and ashamed to hold on to My teaching, I also will later be ashamed to acknowledge him/her in front of the Lord God when I return from heaven. Cuz (elaboration) later I will come down with Father power which is amazing, together with His underlings from heaven (*angels). [EXEG: Gk: glory here x2] [NOTE: ‘holy’ angels undertranslated so as not to make heavy information load and skew the focus.] [NOTE to daughter translations: In one lg the “glorious/radiant/flashing power” was taken from the context of the previous sentence to reflect the flashing anger of judgement, not positive majesty. We restructured it positively to say “power which is majestically good”. CHECK.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sapa</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Beta kasi tau batúl-batúl sang bosong. Ada barapa dari bosong yang ada di sini ni, yang nanti dapa lia sandiri Tuhan pung pegang parenta, ais baru dong bisa mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>I'm telling you correctly. There are several of you who are here now, who later will be able to see for themselves the Lord's ruling, and only then they can die.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jadi laen di atas gunung<bt>The Lord Yesus becomes different on top of the mountain</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***Title changed to reflect Mark and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***Title changed to reflect Mark and so readers can tell this is transfiguration</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:1-8; Markus 9:2-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Abis dia pung dalapan hari, ju Yesus ame bawa sang Petrus, Yohanis deng Yakobis pi nae di satu gunung ko mau sambayang.<bt>After eight days, then Yesus took Petrus, Yohanis and Yakobis up a mountain to pray.</bt><v n="29" />Waktu Yesus ada sambayang, ju Dia pung rupa ba'oba, deng Dia pung pakean jadi puti mangkilat.<bt>When Yesus was praying, then His shape/form/face changed, and His clothing became shiny white. [EXEG: Gk. “appearance of His face”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Takuju sa, dua orang muncul datang. Dong dua tu, andia ba'i Musa deng ba'i Elia. Ju dong ada ba'omong deng Yesus.<bt>Unexpectedly/suddenly two people appeared. Those two were grandfather Musa and grandfather Elia. Then they were speaking (recip) with Yesus.</bt><v n="31" />Dong ju kantara hebat luar biasa. Dong tiga ba'omong so'al Yesus pung mati nanti di Yerusalem.<bt>They also appeared/were.visible extraordinarily amazing. The three of them spoke about Yesus' death later in Yerusalem. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Itu waktu, Petrus deng dia pung kawan dua orang manganto sonde bisa-bisa, sampe dong tatidor. Waktu dong bangun, ju dong dapa lia Yesus ada badiri deng dua orang. Dong ju lia Yesus bacaya taráng.<bt>At that time, Petrus and his two friends were so drowsy they couldn't endure, to the point that they fell asleep. When they woke up, then they saw Yesus standing with two people. And they saw Yesus shining bright. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Waktu ba'i Musa deng ba'i Elia su mau kasi tenga sang Yesus, ju Petrus bingung, sonde tau dia mau bekin apa. Ju dia omong sambarang sa bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Botong rasa enak di sini, é! Jadi lebe bae botong kasi bangun tiga laak. Satu kasi sang Bos, satu kasi ba'i Musa, deng satu lai kasi ba'i Elia.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Gf Musa and Gf Elia were about to leave Yesus, Petrus was confused and didn't know what to do. Then he spoke thoughtlessly/unthinkingly saying, “Bos! We-exc feel great here! So it's better/good (=suggestion) if we-exc build three shelters. One for Boss, one for grandfather Musa, and one more for grandfather Elia.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="laak = Rote lalaak = memayungi,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">laak = Rote lalaak = memayungi, asal buat (shelter), (some [mesolectal?, non-Rote?] speakers don't know this term); laak = pondok daun-daun; gubuk</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ma waktu dia masi ba'omong bagitu, ada satu awan turun datang ko tutu sang dong. Ais Petrus dong jadi taku.<bt>But when he was still speaking like that, a cloud came down and covered them. Then Petrus (collective) became afraid.</bt><v n="35" />Ju dong dapa dengar suara dari dalam itu awan bilang,<bt>And they heard a voice from inside that cloud saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini, Beta pung Ana yang Beta su pili memang!<bt>“This, is My Child whom I have choose beforehand!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia omong, na, dengar bae-bae sang Dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>When He speaks, listen carefully to Him!”</bt><note reference="9:28-35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Petrus 1:17-18; Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 3:17, 12:18, Markus 1:11, Lukas 3:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Omong abis, ju Petrus dong cuma lia Yesus sandiri sa. Dong tiga tutu mulu ko sonde carita kasi sapa-sapa ju, apa yang dong dapa lia tu. Lama-lama baru dong buka mulu ko carita kasi orang laen.<bt>After talking, then Petrus (collective) only saw just Yesus alone. The three of them shut their mouths to not tell anyone at all what that had seen there. Eventually, only then did they open their mouths to tell other people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae ana yang takaná setan jahat<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a child who is afflicted by evil spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:14-18; Markus 9:14-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dia pung beso, waktu Yesus deng Petrus dong turun dari itu gunung, orang banya dong datang katumu sang Yesus.<bt>The next day, when Yesus and Petrus (collective) came down from that mountain, many people came to meet Yesus.</bt><v n="38" />Ju ada satu orang batarea sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru, é! Tolong lia beta pung ana laki-laki satu biji doo!<bt>Then a person called out to Him saying, “Father Teacher! Help my one and only male child!</bt><v n="39" />Te ada setan yang maen pegang ame sang dia, ko bekin dia batarea takuju, deng ro'o-ro'o sang dia sampe busa fafudik kaluar dari dia pung mulu. Itu setan ju maen pok-pak pok-pak sang dia, deng maen ganggu sang dia tarús-tarús.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there is evil spirit who continually grabs him, to make him suddenly yell, and shake him until foam comes out of his mouth. That evil spirit also keeps slapping/hitting him, and keeps bother him all the time.</bt><v n="40" />Beta su minta tolong sang Bapa pung ana bua ko usir kasi kaluar itu setan, ma dong sonde ontong sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>I have requested assistance from Father's underlings to expel that evil spirit, but they could not overcome it!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus masparak sang dong samua bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong sonde parcaya kalo Tuhan bisa bekin bae orang, ko? Bosong tu, dasar manusia yang sonde tau idop iko jalan lurus! Beta musti sama-sama deng bosong barapa lama, baru bosong mau parcaya sang Beta? Beta musti sabar sang bosong sampe kapan lai!?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, Yesus rebuked them all saying, “Huh! Don't you-pl believe the Lord can heal people? You are basically/fundamentally humans who don't know how to live following the straight path! How long must I be with you-pl before you believe in Me? How much longer must I be patient with you?” [EXEG: Gk two propositions at end of verse “stay with you” and “put up with you” were conflated into one in earlier KM version. Restored to better convey Jesus' exasperation. All versions. Explication following TN. Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added “hearing that” at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) added “hearing that” at beginning ; restored two separate propositions from Gk at end of verse to better convey Jesus' exasperation ; Revised &amp; Note added.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong tu, dasar manusia yang sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Bosong tu, dasar manusia yang sonde tau idop iko jalan lurus! Beta musti sabar sang bosong sampe kapan lai!?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Dia bale omong deng itu bapa bilang, &lt;&lt;Bawa lu pung ana datang sini su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he turned.back to speak with that father saying, “Bring your child here!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Waktu dong bawa itu ana pi Yesus, ju itu setan banting itu ana di tana, ro'o-ro'o barmaen sang dia. Ma Yesus parenta itu setan ko kaluar kasi tenga itu ana, ju itu ana bae memang. Ais Yesus sarakan itu ana pi dia pung bapa.<bt>When they brought that child to Yesus, then that evil spirit threw that child on the ground, repeatedly shook him. But Yesus ordered that evil spirit to come out and leave that child, then that child was immediately well. Then Yesus handed.over that child to his father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akathartos: unclean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">akathartos: unclean</Message></Annotation><v n="43a" />Orang yang dapa lia Tuhan pung kuasa yang hebat tu, dong samua jadi taheran-heran.<bt>People who saw that amazing power of the Lord's, they all became amazed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong ulang lai so'al Dia pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks again about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:22-23; Markus 9:30-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43b" />Waktu orang dong samua masi ba'omong so'al tanda-tanda heran yang Yesus ada bekin, Dia kasi tau sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang,<bt>When all the people were still talking.to.each.other about lthe amazing signs which Yesus was doing, He told His underlings saying,</bt><v n="44" />&lt;&lt;Bosong tanda bae-bae Beta pung omong ni! Sonde lama lai, te orang mau jual buang sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Ais dong sarakan Beta pi orang luar dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>“You-pl mark this speaking of mine well! Not much longer, (elaboration) people/person will sell Me off (*betray), the Original Human here. Then they will surrender Me to outsiders.”</bt><v n="45" />Ma Dia pung ana bua dong tabingung-bingung. Dong sonde mangarti dia pung maksud. Dong ju taku tanya dia pung arti apa.<bt>But His underlings were totally confused. They did not understand the intention. They also were afraid to ask the meaning.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sapa yang jadi orang nomer satu<bt>Who becomes the number one person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:1-5; Markus 9:33-37)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Satu kali, Yesus pung ana bua dong mulai bakanjar so'al sapa dari dong yang nanti jadi orang nomer satu.<bt>One time, Yesus' underlings started to argue about who among them would later become the number one person.</bt><note reference="9:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:24</note><v n="47" />Ma Yesus tau apa yang dong bakanjar. Ju Dia pange satu ana kici, ais kasi badiri sang itu ana di Dia pung sablá.<bt>But Yesus knew what they were arguing about. And He called a small child, then stood that child at His side.</bt><v n="48" />Ais Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Orang yang iko Beta ko layani orang kici sama ke ini ana, dia pung arti, itu orang ju ada layani sang Beta. Deng dia ju ada layani sang Beta pung Bapa di sorga yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya. Ada banya orang yang suka pandang enteng sang dong. Macam ke orang kasian, orang susa, orang tar bae, orang sial, deng orang kici dong. Naa! Orang yang suka layani orang macam bagitu yang Tuhan Allah anggap paling hebat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He told them saying, “Listen well! The person who follows Me in order to serve little people (=unimportant people) like this child, that means, that person also serves Me. And He also serves My Father in heaven who commissioned Me to come to this world. There are many people who like to look.down.on/ belittle them. Like poor people, people in trouble, people not considered good, bad luck people, and small/unimportant people. So! Whoever likes to serve people like those is the one who the Lord God considers to be the most impressive.” [EXEG: explication from TN p.211; NOTE to daughter translations: compare wording in Mrk 9:37.].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang sial = bad luck people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">orang sial = bad luck people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Manusia dong pandang enteng atau pandang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Manusia dong pandang enteng atau pandang barát sang bosong, tagantong dari bosong pung kasi sayang sang dong.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:40, Lukas 10:16, Yohanis 13:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang sonde malawan, dia tu kotong pung kawan<bt>A person who doesn't oppose, s/he is our-inc friend</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:38-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ais Yohanis kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Satu kali, botong lia satu orang usir kaluar setan deng subu Bapa pung nama. Jadi botong larang sang dia ko jang subu-subu pake Bapa pung nama, tagal dia tu bukan kotong pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yohanis told Yesus saying, “Father/sir! One time, we-exc saw a person expelling evil spirit/s by using/mentioning Father's name. So (consequently) we forbade him to not use Father's name, because he is not our-inc person.” [EXEG: Gk vocative translated ‘master’ in English here is not /kurios/.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa! Te orang yang sonde malawan sang kotong, dia pung arti, dia tu kotong pung kawan sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “It's not necessary (=polite rebuke)! Cuz (elaboration) a person who does not oppose us-inc, that means, he is our own friend.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang di satu kampong di Samaria sonde mau tarima sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>People in a village in Samaria do not want to accept the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Yesus tau bilang, Dia pung hari nae pi sorga su deka-deka. Ais Dia putus ko barangkat pi kota Yerusalem.<bt>Yesus knew that His day of going up to heaven was near. So He decided to leave to go to Yerusalem city.</bt><v n="52" />Dia utus orang ko jalan kamuka dari dong, ko biar dong bisa ator makan-minum. Ju dong maso pi satu kampong di propinsi Samaria ko mau urus tampa manumpang.<bt>He sent person/people to go in front of them, so that they could arrange food-drink (=all logistics, can include lodging). Then they entered into a village in Samaria province to try to arrange a place to stay.overnight/ temporarily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ator makan-minum = covers all logistics,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ator makan-minum = covers all logistics, including lodging</Message></Annotation><v n="53" />Ma itu orang Samaria dong sonde mau tarima sang Yesus dong, tagal Dia ada mau jalan pi sémba sang Tuhan Allah di kota Yerusalem.<bt>But those Samaria people did not want to receive Yesus (collective), because He wanted to go worship the Lord God in Yerusalem city.</bt><note reference="9:53" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Samaria pung tampa sémba sang Tuhan ada di gunung Gerisim di dong pung da'era. Dong su lama baparkara deng orang Yahudi yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah di kota Yerusalem.<bt>The Samaria people's place of worshiping God is on Gerisim mountain, in their region. For a long them they had had a dispute with Yahudi people who worship the Lord God in Yerusalem city.</bt></note><v n="54" />Waktu Yakobis deng Yohanis dapa dengar itu orang Samaria dong pung bekin-bekin, ju dong babuju sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Karmana kalo kotong minta Tuhan Allah kirim api datang dari langit ko bakar abis sang dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yakobis and Yohanis heard what those Samaria people had done, then they tried to persuade Yesus saying, “Boss! How about it if we request the Lord God to send fire from the sky to burn them up?”</bt><note reference="9:54" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 1:9-16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Ma Yesus mangada sang dong dua, ju togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa pikir bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus faced the two of them, and scolded saying, “It's not necessary to think like that.”</bt><v n="56" />Ais dong jalan tarús pi kampong laen.<bt>So they travelled on going to another village.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sarat iko sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Requirements for following the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:19-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Waktu dong ada jalan, ada satu orang omong sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa pi mana sa, na, beta mau iko tarús deng Bapa!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were walking, one person spoke to Yesus saying, “Father! Where ever Father goes, na, I want to always go with Father!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="58" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae, ju! Ma inga bagini. Samua orang deng binatang ada dong pung tampa tenga sandiri. Anjing utan kambali pi dia pung lobang. Burung kambali pi dia pung sarang. Ma Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, sonde ada pung ruma sandiri ko pulang di situ. Tampa alas kapala, ju sonde ada.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “OK! But remember this. All people and animals have their own place to stay. A wild dog returns to his hole. A bird returns to its nest. But I, the Authentic Human, do not have my own house to return to. Not even a place for laying/supporting the head.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Satu kali, Yesus pange satu orang laen bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari iko sang Beta, ko jadi Beta pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, Yesus called another person saying, “Come follow Me, to become My person.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu! Ma bagini, Bos. Biar beta pulang ko urus orang tua dong dolo. Kalo beta pung bapa su mati, na, baru beta iko.&gt;&gt;<bt>That person replied saying, “Alright (reluctant agreement)! But it's like this, Bos. Let me go home to take care of my parents first. If/When my father has died, only then will I follow.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Kasi tenga ko orang yang sonde ada pung parcaya sang Tuhan dong, urus dong pung orang mati. Ma bosong yang parcaya sang Tuhan, bosong pung tugas pi jalan kasi tau so'al Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told him saying, “It's like this! Allow people who do not have faith/belief in the Lord arrange their dead people. But you-pl who believe in the Lord, your work/task is to go tell about the Lord God's reign.” [EXEG: NLT; NOTE: Gk is singular in last sentence. But here we have seen a pattern that they won't broaden the application to themselves unless it is plural. So plural for genre (instruction) reasons. If changed to singular, would have to delete first clause in last sentence, which is then too broad for local audiences. So implication here of /bosong/ is “you-sg and people like you”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***This is fine 59 urus, 60a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***This is fine 59 urus, 60a urus, 60b tugas</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But Jesus said to him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">NRSV: But Jesus said to him, “Let the dead bury their own dead; but as for you, go and proclaim the kingdom of God.”</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Ada satu orang lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae ju, Bos! Beta mau iko sang Bos tarús. Ma kasi isin ko beta pi ciom bapisa deng beta pung kelu dong dolo, baru beta kambali iko sang Bos.&gt;&gt;<bt>There was yet another person saying, “Ok, Boss! I want to follow Boss continually. But give permission for me to go kiss goodbye my family first, only then I will come back and follow Boss.” [DISCOURSE: added last clause for higher level context/ implicature.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ added last clause for higher"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ added last clause for higher level context</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:61" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 19:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Kalo orang mulai bale tana, ais batasibu deng urusan laen sampe lupa tanam, na, dia pung kabón sonde jadi. Bagitu ju deng orang yang putus mau iko sang Beta, ma maen inga tarús dia pung idop dolo. Orang macam bagitu sonde ada guna jadi orang karjá di Tuhan Allah pung parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told him saying, “Like.this! If a person begins to turn the soil, then gets preoccupied with other matters to the point that he forgets to plant, well.then his garden won't happen. It's like that also with a person who decides to follow Me, but continually keeps remembering his former life. A person like that does not have any value in becoming a worker in the Lord God's rule/governance.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus utus ana bua tuju pulu dua orang<bt>The Lord Yesus commissions seventy two underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus pili ame ana bua laen, 72 orang.<bt>After that, Yesus chose other underlings, 72 people.</bt><note reference="10:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan Bahasa Yunani saparu ada tulis bilang, &lt;ana bua 72 orang&gt;. Saparu lai bilang, &lt;ana bua 70 orang&gt;. Terjemahan moderen dong, banya yang pili &lt;72&gt;.<bt>Some Yunani language writings have written saying, ‘72 underlings’. Some others, say, ‘70 underlings’. The modern translations, many have chosen ‘72’.</bt></note>Ais Dia bagi-bagi sang dong dua-dua orang, ko dong pi lebe dolo dari Dia di tampa-tampa yang nanti Dia mau datang.<bt>Then He divided them into pairs, for them to go ahead of Him to places which He would come to later. [EXEG: Marshall p.414-415, Ex.Summ. &amp; Trans Notes p.216 discuss 70 vs. 72; most recent translations go with 72, (NLT, CEV, TNIV, ESV, REB, NET, NCV); team favours 72.]</bt><v n="2" />Dia utus sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada orang bam-banya yang sama ke padi yang su kuning. Tenga tuan kabón kirim dia pung orang karjá ko datang koru sa. Jadi bosong musti sambayang minta Tuhan Allah kirim tamba Dia pung orang karjá ko kumpul ame orang-orang yang mau iko sang Beta. Tagal orang yang mau iko sang Beta tu, banya. Ma orang karjá dong cuma sadiki sa.<bt>He commissioned them saying, “There are many people who are like padi that is already yellow. The only thing lacking is just for the garden owner to send his workers to come harvest. So (consequently) you must pray request the Lord God to sent extra of His workers to collect people who want to follow Me. Because, those people who want to follow Me, are many. But the workers are only just a few. [EXEG: Explication modifying Trans. Notes].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Helong couldn't collocate yellow to indicate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Helong couldn't collocate yellow to indicate "ripe padi", so used agricultural term "ripe"; see if this is a problem in other lgs, and in KM itself</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:37-38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Sakarang bosong barangkat suda! Beta utus sang bosong ko pi di orang banya dong. Ma inga bagini. Bosong sama ke domba ana yang hati manis, yang pi teng-tenga anjing utan yang jahat dong.<bt>Now you-pl must leave! I commission you to go to many people. But remember this. You are like sheep offspring whose livers are sweet, who go into the midst of wild dogs that are evil.</bt><note reference="10:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Bosong sonde usa bawa doi, ko tas pakean, ko sandal lebe di jalan. Jang buang-buang waktu parcuma deng maen batogor orang di jalan.<bt>You don't need to bring money, or clothes bag, or extra sandals on the road. Don't waste time needlessly by greeting everybody on the road/journey.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-8" />Kalo bosong maso pi dalam satu kampong, bosong sonde usa pinda-pinda dari satu ruma pi ruma laen. Kalo orang tarima bae sang bosong di satu ruma, na, tenga di situ sa, sampe bosong barangkat dari itu kampong. Kalo bosong maso pi satu ruma, bosong musti minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang orang di itu ruma. Kalo tuan ruma di situ tarima bae sang bosong, tantu Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang itu isi ruma dong. Ma kalo dong sonde mau tarima sang bosong, na, biar ko Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong sandiri sa. Kalo bosong maso di satu ruma ko, satu kampong ko, makan-minum apa sa yang dong kasi. Tarima deng sanáng hati, te pantas kalo dong kasi bosong bagitu ko ganti bosong pung karingat.<bt>If/when you enter into a village, you don't need to move around from one house to another house. If a person accepts you graciously in one house, na, just stay there, until you leave that village. If you enter into a house, you must request that the Lord God give blessing to the people in that house. If the house master there accepts you graciously, surely the Lord will show his good liver (=grace) to that household. But if they don't want to accept you, na, let the Lord show His good liver just to you yourselves. If you enter a house or, a village or [where ever], eat-drink whatever they give. Accept it with a happy liver, cuz (elaboration) it's appropriate that they give to you like that, to replace your sweat (=reciprocate for your work).</bt><note reference="10:5-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 9:14, 1 Timotius 5:18</note><v n="9" />Bekin bae dong pung orang saki. Deng kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah pung parenta su ada di muka idong!&gt;<bt>Heal their sick people. And tell them saying, ‘The Lord God's ruling/governing is already in front of your nose!&gt; [EXEG: Dallas Willard. We take this here as a condensed flag representing the nature of the topic, not the details of what is to be communicated.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ma ada kampong ju yang dia pung orang dong sonde mau tarima sang bosong. Kalo dong bekin bagitu sang bosong, na, pi badiri di kampong pung jalan ko angka omong bilang,<bt>But there will also be villages whose people don't want to receive you. If they do like that to you, na, go stand at that village's road and start talking saying,</bt><v n="11" />&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Botong su datang bawa Tuhan pung Kata-kata kasi sang bosong, ma bosong sonde toe sadiki ju. Jadi botong sakarang kabás buang ini kampong pung abu dari botong pung kaki, ko jadi tanda bilang, nanti bosong tanggong risiko sandiri! Ma inga bae-bae! Tuhan Allah pung parenta su ada di muka idong!&gt;<bt>&lt;Listen carefully! We-exc have come bring the Lord's Words to you, but you do not care even a little bit. So (consequently) we now brush.off this village's dust from our feet, to become a sign that, later you yourselves are responsible for the risk! But remember well! The Lord God's ruling/governing is right in front of your nose.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@changed city &gt; village (vs. 10)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@changed city &gt; village (vs. 10) How does this compare with Mark?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah pung Parenta su mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Tuhan Allah pung Parenta su mau deka-deka datang!</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:4-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:7-14, Markus 6:8-11, Lukas 9:3-5; Utusan dong pung Carita 13:51</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bosong tau kota Sodom pung jahat, aa? Beta kasi tau, é! Nanti pas di hari kiamat, Tuhan kasi hukum orang yang tola buang sang bosong tu, jao lebe barát dari orang Sodom dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>You know Sodom city's evil, right? I'm telling you! Later at the end of the world, the Lord will send down a judgement to those people who reject you, far heavier than the Sodom people!”</bt><note reference="10:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 19:24-28, Mateos 10:15, 11:24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang sonde mau tarima sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>People who do not want to receive the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 11:20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Yesus omong tamba lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong yang ada di kampong Korasin<bt>Yesus spoke adding again saying, “Watch out you-pl who are in Korasin village</bt><note reference="10:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Indonesia tulis &lt;Khorazim&gt;. Yang asli pung, dari bahasa Yunani tulis Χοραζίν &lt;Choradzin&gt;.<bt>Indonesian writes &lt;Khorazim&gt;. The original, from the Yunani language writes Χοραζίν &lt;Choradzin&gt;.</bt></note>deng kampong Betsaida! Awas, é! Calaka kaná sang bosong! Beta su bekin tanda heran macam-macam di bosong pung batang idong, ma bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Tuhan. Padahal bosong ni, orang Yahudi yang mangaku kanál sang Dia. Ma andekata itu tanda-tanda heran yang Beta bekin di bosong pung kampong jadi kaná di kota Tirus deng kota Sidon, tantu bagini lama orang di situ dong su tobat memang, deng su kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala ko bale iko sang Tuhan. Deng dong ju tantu pake pakean duka, deng taro abu di atas kapala ko jadi tanda bilang, dong ada manyasal deng dong pung sala-sala dong. Padahal orang Tirus deng orang Sidon dong ni, bukan orang Yahudi yang mangaku kanál sang Tuhan.<bt>and Betsaida village! Misfortune afflicts you! I have done all sorts of miracles right in front of your face, but you do not want to believe the Lord. But.in.actual.fact, you here are Yahudi people who acknowledge knowing Him. But if for.instance those miracles which I did in your villages happened in Tirus city and Sidon city, surely after this long people there would have repented and they would have left their wrongs to turn and follow the Lord. And they also surely would have put on mourning clothes, and put ashes on their heads to be a sign that they are regretting their wrongs. But.in.actual.fact these Tirus people and Sidon people, aren't Yahudi people who acknowledge knowing the Lord. [EXEG: in unpacking “repent” we introduce “believe” which opens the question “believe in God” vs. “believe in me (Jesus)”. This question is only touched on indirectly in the commentaries and there are good arguments in both directions--both with contextual support. Broader passage has high-level themes. Words like “cities” “repent”, “sackcloth and ashes” (w/ “judgment” in 14; “heaven and hell” in 15) make us lean toward God evoking OT stories like Job (but people in the Jewish cities would think they already believed in God, it was Jesus they were rejecting). Direct support for God from CEV, and indirect from Green. Made ambiguous to “Lord”, to keep open both possibilities.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ contrary to fact construction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ contrary to fact construction</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 23:1-18, Yeskial 26:1--28:26, Yoel 3:4-8, Amos 1:9-10, Sakaria 9:2-4</note><v n="14" />Batúl! Bosong lia sa! Nanti kalo Tuhan putus samua orang dong pung parkara, orang Tirus deng orang Sidon pung hukuman masi jao lebe ringan dari bosong pung hukuman.<bt>It's true! You-pl just look/watch! Later when the Lord decides all people's cases/disputes, the punishment of Tirus people and Sidon people will still be far more light than your punishment.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Bosong orang kampong Kapernaum! Awas! Bosong jang pikir bilang, nanti Tuhan angka nae sang bosong maso pi sorga. Sonde! Nanti Tuhan lempar buang sang bosong maso pi naraka!<bt>Be careful you people from Kapernaum village! You shouldn't think that the Lord will lift you up to enter heaven. No! Later the Lord will throw you away into hell!</bt><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 14:13-15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Inga bae-bae! Te orang yang dengar sang bosong, sama sa deng dengar sang Beta. Deng orang yang sonde mau dengar sang bosong, sama sa deng sonde mau dengar sang Beta. Tamba lai, orang yang sonde mau dengar sang Beta tu, sama sa deng dia sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan Allah, yang su utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya.&gt;&gt;<bt>Think about this! Cuz (elaboration) a person who listens to/obeys you-pl, it's just like he listens to/obeys Me. And a person who will not listen to/obey you-pl, it's just like he will not listen to/obey Me. Furthermore, that person who will not listen to/obey Me, it's just like he will not listen to/obey the Lord God, who sent/commissioned Me to come to this world.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[DISCOURSE: shift of audience made explicit,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">[DISCOURSE: shift of audience made explicit, see NLT, CEV.]</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:40, Markus 9:37, Lukas 9:48, Yohanis 13:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuju pulu dua utusan dong kambali<bt>Seventy two commissioned ones/*apostles returned</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu itu 72 orang utusan datang kambali,<bt>When those 72 commissioned people/*apostles came back,</bt><note reference="10:17" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu ada tulis bilang, &lt;ana bua 72 orang&gt;. Saparu lai bilang, &lt;ana bua 70 orang&gt;. Terjemahan moderen dong, banya yang pili &lt;72&gt;.<bt>Some of the Yunani language writing write saying, ‘72 underlings&gt;. Some others sayi, ‘70 underlings&gt;. Modern translations, many have chosen &lt;72&gt;.</bt></note>dong pung hati ada babunga-bunga. Ju dong lapor sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Pung hebat lai! Waktu botong pake Bos pung nama ko usir setan dong, itu setan dong dengar sang botong, ais ju dong kaluar memang! Talalu!&gt;&gt;<bt>their livers were joyful. And they reported to Yesus saying, “Awii! [+impressed] Amazing! When we-exc used Bos' name to expel the evil spirits. Those evil spirits heard/obeyed us, and they came out immediately! Super!” [NOTE to daughter translations: built up here to convey excitement / speaker attitude. CHECK to see if your language can carry this more succinctly.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ju Yesus manyao sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Waktu bosong bekin bagitu, Beta ada lia Tuhan Allah lempar buang sang setan deng dong pung bos dari langit, sama ke kilat yang kaluar kiri-kanan dari langit!<bt>Then Yesus answered them saying, “True! When you-pl did like that, I saw the Lord God throw the evil spirit's boss from the sky, just like lightening when came out left-right from the sky!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaan: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Satanaan: da Devil</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Inga, é! Setan dong pung bos tu, kotong pung musu. Deng dia ada pung kuasa ju! Ma Beta su kasi kuasa sang bosong ko kasi pata dia pung kuasa. Deng andekata bosong ada inja kaná ular babisa, ko, kalajingking, na, bosong sonde kaná apa-apa. Sonde ada yang bisa bekin calaka sang bosong.<bt>Remember! That boss of the evil spirit's is our enemy. And he has power also! But I have given power to you to break/sever his power. And if.for.example you step on a poisonous snake, or a scorpion, na, you won't be harmed at all. There is nothing that can cause misfortune/harm to you.</bt><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 91:13</note><v n="20" />Bosong pung hati babunga, tagal setan dong dengar sang bosong. Bae ju, ma itu hal kici sa! Lebe bae bosong pung hati babunga, tagal Tuhan su tulis ame bosong pung nama ko jadi Dia pung warga yang maso sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Your livers are joyful, because the evil spirits listen.to/obeyed you. That's ok, but that is just a small matter! It's better that your livers be joyful because the Lord has written your names to become His citizens who enter heaven.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung hati babunga [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus' liver is joyful [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 11:25-27, 13:16-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Itu waktu, Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi bekin Yesus pung hati babunga. Ais Dia puji Tuhan bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa yang pegang hak parenta samua di langit deng bumi. Beta minta tarima kasi bam-banya, tagal Bapa tutu ame ini hal dong dari orang yang anggap diri pintar deng yang tinggi hati dong. Ma Bapa buka ini hal samua kasi ana-ana kici dong, deng orang yang randá hati dong. Batúl, Bapa! Te itu yang bekin Bapa pung hati sanáng!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, the Lord's Holy Spirit made Yesus' liver joyful. Then He praised the Lord saying, “Father! Father is the one who has the say-so/ordering rights for everything in the sky and on earth. I give many thanks, because Father covers/hides these things from people who consider themselves to be smart and those who have high liver (=pride). But Father opens all these things to the small children and the people who have low livers (=humility). True, Father! Cuz (elaboration) that is what makes Father's liver happy!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar ó! Beta pung Bapa di sorga su kasi samua kuasa sang Beta. Yang tau batúl bilang, Beta ni, sapa, andia cuma Bapa sa. Deng yang tau batúl bilang, Bapa tu, sapa, cuma Bapa pung Ana sa, andia Beta. Deng Beta pili orang laen, ko kasi tau sang dong, ko biar dong ju kanál sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told those many people saying, “Listen! My Father in heaven has given all power/authority to Me. Those who truly know who I am, it's only just Father. And those who truly know who Father is, is only just the Father's Child, which is Me. And I choose other people, to tell them, so that they also know Him.” [NOTE: shift from 2nd person to 3rd person in Gk. taken as a shift in audience, as per Marshall and Trans. Notes p.226-227; EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***ov fine from NLT &amp; CEV,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***ov fine from NLT &amp; CEV, but Gk is not about "knowing the Son", but "knowing who the son is"; fixed with adjustments throughout verse</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: All things have been handed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">NRSV: All things have been handed over to me by my Father; and no one knows who the Son is except the Father, or who the Father is except the Son and anyone to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yang kanál bae sang Beta tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Yang kanál bae sang Beta tu, andia cuma Bapa sa. Deng yang kanál bae sang Bapa, cuma Bapa pung Ana sa, andia Beta. Deng Beta pili orang-orang laen, ko kasi tau sang dong, ko biar dong ju kanál bae sang Dia.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 3:35, 10:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais Yesus bale mangada sang Dia pung ana bua dong, deng kasi tau sang dong sandiri bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ontong batúl, tagal bosong su lia Tuhan pung kuasa.<bt>Then Yesus turned facing His underlings, and told them alone saying, “You-pl are very fortunate, because you have seen the Lord's power.</bt><v n="24" />Raja-raja deng jubir dolu-dolu dong rindu mau lia apa yang bosong su dapa lia, ma dong sonde bisa. Dong ju rindu mau dengar apa yang bosong su dapa dengar, ma dong sonde bisa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Rajas and spokespersons of long ago yearned to see what you have seen, but they couldn't. They also yearned to hear what you have heard, but they couldn't.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Samaria yang hati mas<bt>The Samaria person with the golden liver (=extremely good/upright/generous)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Satu kali, ada satu ahli hukum Yahudi badiri ko mau hiki sang Yesus. Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Tolong kasi tau doo! Beta musti bekin apa, ko biar beta tau beta bisa dapa idop tarús sama-sama deng Tuhan di sorga?&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, a Yahudi law expert stood up to try to trap Yesus. He asked saying, “Father Teacher! Please tell/explain! What must I do, so that I can know I will live continually together with the Lord in heaven?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check use of ahli hukum here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">check use of ahli hukum here for keyterm consistency</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ba'i Musa tulis apa so'al ini hal? Lu pung mangarti karmana sang dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “What did Gf/Ff Musa write about this matter? What is your understanding about it?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu orang kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ada tulis bilang:<bt>That person told [Him] saying, “He wrote saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu musti sayang sang Tuhan Allah <span class="Italic">lebe</span> dari samua, te Dia yang hak parenta sang lu.<bt>&lt;You-sg must love the Lord God, <span class="Italic">more</span> than everything else, for (elaboration) He is the one who has the say-so/ordering rights over you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal itu, lu musti salalu rindu sang Dia,<bt>Because of that we must always yearn affectionately for Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">karjá karás ko iko Dia pung mau,<bt>work hard to follow His will,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng mangarti sang Dia.&gt;<bt>and understand Him,&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju ada tulis bilang, &lt;Lu musti sayang lu pung sodara, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>It is also written saying, ‘You-sg must love your sibling/cousin/same.generation.or.rank.individual, the same as you love your own self.”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang badeka = people close in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">orang badeka = people close in relationships</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pleesion: not just the person next"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">pleesion: not just the person next door</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Kalo lu bekin iko bagitu, lu idop deng Tuhan tarús-tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “True! If you do like that, you will live continually with the Lord.”</bt><note reference="10:25-28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:35-40, Markus 12:28-34; Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 18:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma itu orang ada mau bekin diri ke orang alim sa. Ais dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma beta pung &lt;sodara&gt; tu, yang mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>But that person wanted to make himself out to be like a religious/pious person. So he asked Yesus saying, “But what/which &lt;sibling&gt; do you mean there?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin diri ke tau-tau = sok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bekin diri ke tau-tau = sok tahu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Beta mau kasi satu umpama. Nanti lu kasi tau, mana yang batúl-batúl &lt;sodara&gt;. Dia pung carita bagini: Ada satu orang Yahudi barangkat dari kota Yerusalem, jalan turun pi Yeriko. Ma takuju sa, ada tukang rampok dong datang korfei barmaen sang dia. Dong papoko sang dia, ais rampas ame dia pung doi deng dia pung pakean samua. Tarús dong lempar buang sang dia di pinggir jalan, ais jalan kasi tenga sang dia. Itu orang su amper mau mati sa.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “Like.this! I will give a comparison.story. Then you will know, who/which.one is truly &lt;sibling&gt;. The story is like this: A Yahudi person left from Yerusalem city, walking down to Yeriko. But suddenly, robbers came and messed.him up. They beat him, then snatched his money and all his clothes. Then they threw him off to the side of the road, and went leaving him behind. That person was about to die.</bt></p>
    <fig path="Wade\gw086.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Satu kapala agama lewat di jalan<bt>A priest passes by on the road</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma sonde sangka-sangka, te ada satu kapala agama Yahudi yang jalan turun lewat di situ ju. Ma waktu dia dapa lia ada orang luka-luka yang malenggang di pinggir jalan, dia sonde barenti ko tolong sang dia. Dia serong pi sablá ko jalan tarús sa.<bt>But by chance, (elaboration) a head of Yahudi religion who was walking down also passed by there. But when he saw there was a wounded person laying face up on the side of the road, he didn't stop to help him. He diverged over to the other side to just keep going. [NOTE: Greek doesn't say how the person is laying, but this is how he is in picture and how people would tend to talk about it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde sangka-sangka = by chance, by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Sonde sangka-sangka = by chance, by coincidence ; @@NOTE; early version said matono, but picture shows malenggang. Gk doesn't matter, so follow picture. @@</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Sonde lama, ju ada satu orang laen yang lewat di situ. Dia tu, orang dari suku Lewi yang biasa bantu di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Waktu dia dapa lia itu orang talempar di pinggir jalan, dia pi lia deka-deka sa, ma sonde tolong sang dia. Tarús dia serong pi sablá ko jalan tarús.<bt>Not long, (=soon) then another person passed by there. He was a person from the Lewi tribe who usually helped in the Lord God's Central Worship House. When he saw that person thrown on the side of the road, he only went close to have a look, but didn't help him. Then he diverged to the other side to continue walking.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33-34" />Sonde lama lai, ada satu orang dari da'era Samaria lewat di situ deng dia pung binatang keledai. Kotong samua tau bilang, orang Yahudi biasa lia deng sablá mata sang orang Samaria dong. Naa, waktu ini orang Samaria lia itu orang yang kaná rampok tu, ju dia jato kasian sang dia. Dia datang deka-deka ko mau tolong itu orang. Dia po'a anggor ko kasi barisi itu orang pung luka-luka dong, ais dia taro minya pi. Tarús farbán bae-bae sang dia, ju angka kasi nae pi atas dia pung keledai. Ais dia bawa itu orang pi sampe di kota. Tarús dia kasi manumpang itu orang di losmen, deng urus bae-bae sang dia.<bt>Not long again, another person from the Samaria region passed by there with his donkey animal. We-inc all know that Yahudi people usually look sideways (=disparagingly) at the Samaria people. Naa, when this Samaria person saw that person who had been robbed, he felt pity on him. He came close to help that person. He poured wine to clean that person's wounds, then he put oil on them. Next he bandaged him well, and put him on his donkey. Then he brought that person to the city. Then he arranged for that person to stay.temporarily at a guest.house, and arranged things well for him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lia deng sablá mata = anggap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">lia deng sablá mata = anggap remeh, pandang enteng, look down their noses at would Jesus really have said when talking to a bunch of Jews: Orang Yahudi biasa lia deng sablá mata sang orang Samaria dong.<span class="Italic">(33) (33) </span>inconsistent use of anggor and aer anggor farbán ~ ferbán ~ verban = bandage (large winds) &lt; Du. ; totobi = tend to the wounds</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:33-34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 28:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia pung beso, itu orang Samaria pi kasi panjar doi, dua perak<bt>The next day, that Samaria person went to give an advance of money, two silvers</bt><note reference="10:35" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;dua denari&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Yunani language writes saying, “two dinari&gt;&gt;.</bt></note>di tuan losmen, deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;Pake ini doi ko urus bae-bae itu orang saki sampe bae. Kalo sonde cukup, na, tolong pake tahan bapa pung doi doo. Waktu beta bale lai, nanti beta ganti bapa pung doi samua.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>to that guesthouse owner, and told him saying, ‘Use this money to take care of that sick person until he is well. If it's not enough, na, please use father's (=your) own money temporarily. When I come back again, then I will replace all of father's money.”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="panjar = ; pake tahan ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">panjar = ; pake tahan = pakai sementara</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Yesus pung umpama sampe di situ sa. Ais Dia tanya sang itu ahli hukum bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko lu, mana yang batúl-batúl &lt;sodara&gt; buat itu orang yang kaná rampok tadi tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus' comparison.story concluded there. Then He asked that law expert saying, “According to you, which.one was truly a &lt;sibling&gt; for that person who was robbed there?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tantu sa, itu orang yang jato kasian sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>That person replied saying, “Of course it was that person who had pity on him.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, bu! Pi su, ko bekin iko.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus said, “True, elder.brother. Go, to do accordingly.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus, Ma'a deng Mia<bt>The Lord Yesus, Ma'a (Martha nickname) and Mia (Mary nickname)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38-40" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong jalan tarús pi Yerusalem. Ju dong singga di satu kampong. Di situ ada dua basodara, nama Marta deng Maria. Marta minta ko Yesus dong manumpang di dia pung ruma. Ais dong tenga tahan di situ.<bt>After that, Yesus and His underlings traveled on to Yerusalem. They stopped at a village. There there were two siblings, named Marta and Maria. Marta requested that Yesus (collective) spend the night at her house. So they stayed temporarily there. [EXEG: Did Martha invite Jesus to spend the night, or merely eat a meal? TN says of vs.40 “all the preparations that had to be made: She was probably preparing a meal for Jesus and getting a place ready for him to sleep.” The Gk vb. glossed “welcome” in vs.38 is the same one Luke uses in 19:6, where Jesus explicitly tells Zaccheus he will “stay” in his house that day (night?). Green associates this “with extending or refusing hospitality to those on the road,” continuing a theme from the previous story (of the good Samaritan). In contrast, Luke uses very different Gk vocabulary in Luke 7:36,39, when Simon the Pharisee invites Jesus for a meal.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***(2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***(2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Yesus dudu ko ajar orang dong, Marta batasibu urus makan-minum di dapur. Ma dia pung adi Maria, ada dudu deka-deka di Yesus pung kaki, ko dengar Dia pung omong. Sonde lama, ju Marta maso datang ko mangomel di Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, é! Karmana, ó! Beta ada batasibu satenga mati urus makan-minum, baru beta pung adi dudu ena-ena di sini sa. Tolong doo! Suru sang dia bantu beta sadiki di dapur!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus sat to teach people, Marta was busy arranging the food-drink in the kitchen. But her younger sibling Maria, was sitting near Yesus' feet, in order to hear His talking. Not long (=soon) then Marta came in to complain to Yesus saying, “Father! How is it? ["Karmana, ó!" + complaint = "don't you care?"] I am very busy taking care of the food-drink, while my younger sibling just sits pleasantly here. Please/Help! Tell her to help me a bit in the kitchen!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ deleted &quot;sandiri&quot; so as not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ deleted "sandiri" so as not to skew FT mangomek di Yesus = complain to Y ; mangomek sang Y. = complain about ; Urus do! = not known by all UNS's</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:38-39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 11:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ma Tuhan Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma'a. Lu ni, batasibu deng pikir macam-macam.<bt>But the Lord Yesus replied saying, “Ma'a. Ma'a. You are the one very busy with all sorts of thoughts/worries.</bt><v n="42" />Bae, ma ada satu hal yang lebe pantíng sakarang. Deng dia dudu dengar Beta pung Kata-kata, Mia su pili yang paling bae. Orang sonde bisa rampas buang itu Kata-kata dari dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's ok, but there is one thing that is more important now. By sitting and hearing My Words, Mia has chosen was is the best. People cannot snatch those Words away from her.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Ajar sang botong sambayang&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Teach us-exc to pray&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 6:9-13, 7:7-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, Yesus pi sambayang. Sambayang abis, ju Dia pung ana bua satu datang ko minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Yohanis tukang sarani su ajar dia pung ana bua dong, ko dong tau sambayang. Botong minta ko Bapa ju ajar sang botong sambayang dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, Yesus went to pray. After praying, then one of His underlings came and requested saying, “Father! Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer also taught his underlings, so that they would know how to pray. We-exc request that Father (=you) teach us to pray too [polite imperative]!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ais Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae ju! Sambayang pake conto bagini:<bt>Then Yesus said, “Ok! Pray using an example like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bilang without other speach word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bilang without other speach word</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bapa! Bapa pung nama paling barisi.<bt>‘Father! Father's name/reputation is the most clean/holy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar samua orang angka nae tinggi-tinggi Bapa pung nama yang hebat.<bt>May.it.be that all people lift up high that amazing name of Father's.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar Bapa jadi Raja kasi samua orang.<bt>May.it.be.that Father become Raja for all people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Botong minta Bapa kasi turun Bapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Botong minta Bapa kasi turun Bapa pung parenta kasi samua orang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Bapa tolong kasi botong makanan yang cukup tiap hari.<bt>Father help/please give us food that is enough each day.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Botong minta Bapa lupa buang botong pung sala-sala dong,<bt>We request that Father thoroughly forget our wrongs,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke botong ju lupa buang orang pung sala yang dong bekin-bekin sang botong.<bt>the same as we also thoroughly forget people's wrongs which they do to/against us.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bapa jaga ko botong sonde bekin jahat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Father guard us so that we don't do evil.” [EXEG: cf. Wierzbicka explication, focusing on the desired result of the request. NRSV note points out some minor Gk texts have “rescue us from evil/'the evil one”. On the surface, it looks like we're following the minor textual reading, but we're actually unpacking the meaning of the goal of the main textual reading. Q: In this context, should we lean the meaning of the Gk word towards sense 1) testing (of character), or 2) temptation (to do sin)? We favour the latter. Among other things, the first would be a request pretty inconsistent with much of scripture, whereas the second wouldn't. Marshall summarizes it as meaning “cause us not to succumb to temptation” (to sin). Or NLT nicely puts it “don't let us yield to temptation” (to sin). LN describe this Gk word as “to endeavor or attempt to cause someone to sin”. BADG “enticement to sin”. An earlier KM rendering (which was more literal), was ambiguous in several respects and only went in the direction of #1, not #2. “If/when we-exc get testing (of character), Father don't let us-exc fall (socially).”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) note added;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo botong dapa coba'an, Bapa jang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Kalo botong dapa coba'an, Bapa jang kasi biar ko botong jato.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai gar autoi aphiomen: &quot;let go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">kai gar autoi aphiomen: "let go ... an no stay huhu" is the way people do it: "let go ... an hemo da shame" is the way God does it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Ais Yesus ajar tamba sang dong so'al sambayang. Dia pake umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Andekata tenga malam, ada kawan datang dari jao, ko manumpang di lu pung ruma. Ma lu sonde ada apa-apa ko kasi dia makan. Ais lu pi di lu pung kawan laen pung ruma, ko noki-noki dari luar bilang, &lt;Bu, é! Kasi tahan beta roti tiga balok doo! Te beta ada tamu di ruma, ma botong ada karíng-karíng sa, ni! Bu, tolong doo! Tiga balok sa! Nanti be ganti!&gt;<bt>Then Yesus taught them further about prayer. He used a comparison.story saying, “Suppose.that it's the middle of night, a friend comes from far, to overnight at your-sg house. But you don't have anything to give him to eat. So you go to your other friend's house, to beg/insist from outside saying, “Elder.brother! Loan me three loaves of bread! Cuz (elaboration) I have guests at the house, but we-exc are completely dry (=no food in house)! Elder.brother, help! Just three loaves! I'll replace them!’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">balok</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Kira-kira nanti lu pung kawan manyao bale bilang, &lt;Ko bu lai, ju! Orang ada tidor sonu, ma bu datang ganggu lai! Pintu dong su takonci mati ni! Ana-ana dong su tidor sonu. Jang mara, é! Ma laen kali sa, bu!&gt;<bt>Probably your friend will reply back saying, ‘This is riduculous elder.brother! People are sleeping soundly, but elder.brother  (=you) come and bother us! The doors are locked now! The kids are sound asleep. Don't get angry =sorry! But come back another time, elder.brother!&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaná salót kiri-kanan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kaná salót kiri-kanan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Biar bagitu ju, ma inga bae-bae. Biar itu orang sonde bangun ko kasi sang lu tagal lu dia pung kawan, ma kalo lu maen noki-noki tarús, tantu dia bangun ko kasi.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless remember this well. Even if/though that person does not get.up to give you [anything], because you are his friend, nevertheless if you repeatedly keep on insisting and insisting, surely he will get.up to give it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ tagal lu dia pung kawan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ tagal lu dia pung kawan ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Bagitu ju, deng sambayang.<bt>It's like that also, with prayer.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Minta tarús sang Tuhan;<bt>[If you] Continually request from the Lord;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nanti Dia kasi.<bt>He will give.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Cari tarús;<bt>Continually seek;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nanti Dia kasi tunju jalan.<bt>He will reveal the path/way.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Eki tarús;<bt>Continually call.out;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nanti Dia buka pintu.<bt>He will open the door.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Te samua orang yang minta tarús sang Tuhan Allah, nanti tarima. Yang cari tarús, nanti dapa. Yang eki tarús, nanti Dia buka pintu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) all people who continually request of the Lord God, will receive. Those who continually seek, will find. Those who continually call.out, He will open the door [for them].</bt><v n="11" />Bosong pikir coba! Dapa di mana, ada bapa, yang kalo dia pung ana minta ikan, na, dia kasi ular?<bt>Think about it! Where is there a father, if his child requests fish, then he gives snake?</bt><v n="12" />Ko, kalo ana minta talór, dia kasi kalajingking? Sonde mungkin, to?<bt>Or, if a child requests egg, then he gives a scorpion? Impossible, right?</bt><v n="13" />Manusia pung dasar memang jahat. Ma bosong pung Bapa di sorga tu, Dia pung dasar bae batúl. Jadi, kalo manusia yang jahat macam bosong sa, suka kasi barang yang bae sang bosong pung ana-ana dong, apalai Bapa! Dia bukan cuma kasi apa yang bosong parlú sa, ma lebe dari itu, Dia kasi Dia pung Roh yang Barisi sang orang yang minta sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Humans essential.character is truly evil. But that Father of yours in heaven, His essential.character is very good. So (consequently), if humans who are evil like you-pl, like to give things which are good to your children, even.more.so Father! He not only gives just what you-pl need, but more than that, He gives His Holy Spirit to people who request [it] from Him.” [EXEG: "how much more" is built implicitly into the syntax of the last two sentences.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sonde pake kuasa dari setan dong pung bos<bt>The Lord Yesus doesn't use power from the evil spirits' boss</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:22-30; Markus 3:20-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Satu kali, Yesus usir kasi kaluar setan dari orang bisu satu. Ais, itu orang mulai omong kambali. Orang dong di situ taheran-heran.<bt>One time, Yesus expelled evil spirit/s out of a dumb/mute person. Then that person began to speak again. The people there were amazed.</bt><v n="15" />Ma ada ju yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang sa, Dia bisa usir setan! Ko Dia dapa kuasa dari setan dong pung bos, andia Balsebul na.&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were also some who said, “Of course He can expel evil spirit/s! Obviously He gets power from the boss of the evil spirits, who is Balsebul.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Memang sa, = of course, obviously"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Memang sa, = of course, obviously</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:34, 10:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Orang laen dong mau coba sang Yesus. Ais dong minta ko Dia bekin satu tanda heran lai ko kasi tunju sang dong bilang, Dia pung kuasa memang dari Tuhan.<bt>Other people wanted to test (character of) Yesus. So they requested Him to do another miracle to show them that His power truly was from the Lord.</bt><note reference="11:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:38, 16:1, Markus 8:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma Yesus tau memang dong pung otak kotor. Ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo dalam satu negara, dia pung rakyat dong bamusu, tantu itu negara jadi ancor-ancor. Bagitu ju, kalo dalam satu ruma, dia pung isi ruma dong ada maen idop bakanjar satu deng laen, na, tantu itu ruma tangga su sonde jadi doi lai!<bt>But Yesus knew beforehand those dirty brains of theirs. So He spoke saying, “If a country, its populace is mutual.enemies, surely that country will break apart. Like that also, if in a household, it's members habitually live fighting each other, na, surely that household won't become money anymore (idiom: = won't amount to anything)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde jadi doi = Idiom @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sonde jadi doi = Idiom @@</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Jadi, kalo setan dong maen bamusu deng maen ba'usir satu deng satu, na, dong pung bos su sonde bisa pegang parenta lama-lama lai! Jadi sonde maso di otak, kalo bosong bilang Beta ada pake setan pung kuasa ko usir setan sandiri!<bt>So (consequently), if evil spirits continually are mutual.enemies and continually mutually.expel each other, na, their boss is not capable of holding authority/ruling much longer! So (consequently) it doesn't make any sense if you-pl say I am using evil spirits' power/authority to expel evil spirits themselves!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde lama-lama lai = not very"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sonde lama-lama lai = not very much longer ; mati kutu (BI) = tidak berkutik, no way to respond</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil hee basileia autou:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil hee basileia autou: his kingdom<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Inga, é! Bosong pung orang dong ju tau usir setan. Dong pake kuasa dari setan, ko? Sonde, to! Jadi bosong jang omong sambarang bilang, Beta ada pake setan pung kuasa ko usir setan. Nanti bosong pung orang sandiri yang putus bilang, apa yang bosong tudu tu, sala.<bt>Remember! Your-pl people also know how to expel evil spirit/s. Do they use power from evil spirit/s? No, right? So (consequently) you shouldn't speak thoughtlessly saying, I am using evil spirit's power/authority to expel evil spirits. Later your own people will decide/resolve that that which you are accusing there, is false.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beelzeboul: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Beelzeboul: da Devil</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma kalo Beta batúl-batúl usir setan pake Tuhan Allah pung kuasa, itu kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan pung parenta su ada di bosong pung muka idong. Ada, ma tingka ke bosong sonde tau.<bt>But if I truly expel evil spirit/s using power from the Lord God, that shows that the Lord's rule/reigning is right in front of your noses. It's there, but it's as if you don't know. [EXEG: last clause from implicature of Gk. See HCE and UBS TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Kalo geng satu ada pake sanjata kiri-kanan, ko jaga bae-bae dia pung ruma, tantu dia pung barang samua aman-aman sa.<bt>If a gang leader uses weapons left-right, to protect his house, surely all his things will be safe.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="denjer = geng = orang barani"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">denjer = geng = orang barani (gangster)</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ma nanti, ada yang lebe kuat dari dia, datang kasi kala deng rampas ame itu orang pung sanjata dong. Ais itu, dia ju ra'u bawa itu orang pung harta dong ko bagi-bagi kasi dia pung ana bua dong. Su bagini lama itu geng partama parcaya dia pung sanjata. Ma sakarang dia su sonde bisa harap itu sanjata dong lai.<bt>But later, someone stronger than him comes defeating [him], and snatching away that person's weapons. After that, he then scoops up and takes away that person's possessions to go divide out to his underlings. For a long time that first gangster believed in his weapons. But now he cannot hope in those weapons anymore. [EXEG: TH, TN and Marshall all take "the stronger man" to be Jesus, so /geng/ carries inappropriate baggage --deleted.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma nanti, ada geng yang lebe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma nanti, ada geng yang lebe kuat dari dia, datang bekin kala,</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:21-22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab, “geng” di sini, andia setan dong pung bos. Deng “yang lebe kuat dari dia”, andia Tuhan Yesus.<bt>According to people who are knowledgable about the Bible, “gangster” here is the bos of the evil spirits. And “someone stronger than him” is the Lord Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Inga bae-bae! Orang yang sonde bapartei deng Beta, dia tu, Beta pung musu. Deng orang yang sonde babantu deng Beta pung karjá, na, dia tu, bekin kaco sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember well! A person is not mutually.one.party with Me, he/she is My enemy. And the person doesn't mutually.help with My work, he/she is just causing chaos.”</bt><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 9:40</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Setan mau pulang pi dia pung tampa lama<bt>Evil.spirit wants to return to his old place</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:43-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Yesus omong tamba lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo kotong usir setan kaluar dari satu orang, dia pi tampa sunyi ko cari tampa barenti cape. Tagal dia sonde dapa tampa yang cocok, ju dia pikir bilang, &lt;Ee! Sonde dapa tampa bagini, lebe bae beta pulang pi tenga kambali di itu orang yang dolu tu.&gt;<bt>Yesus continued speaking saying, “If we-inc expel an evil spirit out of a person. he goes to a deserted place to look for a place to rest. Because he does not find a place that is suitable, then he thinks saying, ‘Hee! Not finding a place like this, it's better I return and go stay again in that previous person.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akathartos: unclean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">akathartos: unclean</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ais dia kambali, ju dia katumu itu tampa tu, su sapu barisi deng ta'ator bae-bae.<bt>So he returns, and he encounters that place is already swept clean and rearranged well. [EXEG: Gk does not have ‘clean’ as in NLT and CEV. It has ‘swept’ and ‘put in order’. MTTs had theological problem with ‘clean’ by itself as a resulting state, implying the person was already made holy/pure/sanctified, and then the demons took over again. That skews the point of the picture. The problem doesn't seem to arise with ‘swept clean’. June 2014.]</bt><v n="26" />Ju itu setan pi pange dia pung kawan tuju setan, yang lebe jahat lai dari dia. Ais dong samua pi tenga di itu orang, ju karoyok sang dia. Jadi sakarang itu orang pung idop lebe calaka lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>So that evil spirit goes and calls his seven friends, who are more evil than he. Then they all go stay at that person, and gang.up.on him. So (consequently), now that person's life is even more misfortunate.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[sakarang = relative to time in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">[sakarang = relative to time in locus]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yang paling ontong<bt>Those who are the most fortunate</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong deng orang banya tu, ada satu parampuan di situ batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak pung mama ontong bésar, tagal dia yang dapa barana sang Pak, deng dapa kasi susu sang Pak!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus was still speaking with those many people, a woman there called out saying, “Sir/Your-sg mother is very fortunate, because she is the one who gave.birth to You/Sir, and nursed You/Sir!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, mama! Ma yang lebe ontong lai, andia orang yang pasang talinga ko dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, deng bekin iko!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “True, mama! But those who are even more fortunate, are the people who fasten their ears [pay attention] to hear the Lord God's Words, and follow/obey them!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang minta Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju bukti doo!<bt>People request the Lord Yesus to show evidence [+ impatience/imperative]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong, orang banya dong makarubu kuliling sang Dia. Ju Dia angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang sakarang dong ni, cuma tau bekin jahat sa. Dong maen minta tarús ko Beta bekin tanda heran kasi sang dong, ko dong tau Beta ni, batúl-batúl Tuhan pung orang. Padahal dolu Tuhan su kasi tanda heran sang dong pake Dia pung jubir Yunus. Itu su cukup!<bt>When Yesus was still talking, many people came crowding around Him. Then He began to speak [formally] saying, “People nowadays, only know how to do evil. They continually request that I do miracles for them, so that they can know that I here, am truly the Lord's person. But.in.actual.fact the Lord has already given miracle to them previously using His spokesperson Yunus. That is enough!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ changed intro so it doesn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ changed intro so it doesn't hang out in nothing</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dolu-dolu, Yunus kasi tau orang kota Niniwe bilang, dong musti tobat dolo. Naa, apa yang jadi di Yunus dolu, jadi tanda kasi sang dong bilang, Tuhan Allah yang utus sang dia. Bagitu ju deng Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Beta datang kasi tau sang bosong, ko bosong musti tobat dolo. Deng apa yang nanti jadi di Beta, ju jadi tanda kasi orang sakarang bilang, memang Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta.<bt>Long ago, Yunus told the people of the city of Niniwe, that they must repent. Naa [+shift], what happened with Yunus previously, became a sign for them, that the Lord God was the one who had sent/commissioned him. It's like that also with Me, the Orginal/Authentic Human. I (have) come telling you-pl that you must repent. And what will happen to Me, will also be a sign for people nowadays that, the Lord God really is the one who has sent/commissioned Me. [EXEG: HCE and TN. UNS's not making the parallel link without this explication. This also sets up vs.31 nicely. Marshall also discusses the “preaching” parallel between Jonah &amp; Jesus. Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised significantly; note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) revised significantly; note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Apa yang jadi di Yunus dolu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Apa yang jadi di Yunus dolu, jadi tanda kasi orang di kota Niniwe, bilang, Tuhan Allah yang utus sang dia. Bagitu ju deng Manusia Tulen. Apa yang jadi di Beta, nanti jadi tanda kasi orang sakarang, bilang, memang Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:29-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:4, Markus 8:12; Yunus 3:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Nanti di hari kiamat, kalo Tuhan badiri jadi Hakim, nanti ratu dari salatan sana idop kambali, ju badiri jadi saksi. Dia tunju jari ko tudu sang bosong samua yang idop sakarang ni bilang, &lt;Bosong samua ni, bodo, é!&gt; Te dolu itu ratu datang dari jao-jao ko lia deng mata kapala sandiri raja Soleman pung pintar. Padahal sakarang ada Orang di bosong pung teng-tenga yang lebe hebat dari raja Soleman. Ma bosong sonde mau ame pusing sadiki ju sang Dia!<bt>Later at the end.of.the.world, if/when the Lord stands as Judge, later the queen from the south over.there will live again and also stand and become a witness. She will point her finger to accuse you-pl all who live nowadays saying, ‘All of you here are stupid!’ Cuz (elaboration) previously that queen came from far.away to see with her very own eyes the wisdom/skill of raja Soleman. But.in.actual.fact, now there is a Person in your midst who is more impressive than raja Soleman. But you don't want to care even a little bit about Him! [EXEG vs.31-32: “You're all stupid/ignorant,” or “You're all guilty”? Context is about reading the signs, connecting the dots. In Kupang and surrounding lgs, chiding people for not reading the signs is “You're stupid!” = failing to discern. To use a phrase like “You're guilty” is highly restricted to a formal court decision. Doesn't fit the RL here. Sense of accuse/condemn is carried by the symbolic action of finger pointing. See also HCE. TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** EXEG note added (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** EXEG note added (Helong)</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 10:1-10, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 9:1-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Deng bukan dia sandiri sa! Nanti orang dari Niniwe dong ju bangun badiri ko tunju jari sang bosong yang idop sakarang ni bilang, &lt;Bosong samua, bodo!&gt; Dong omong bagitu, tagal tempo hari, waktu Yunus pi kasi tau Tuhan pung mau sang dong, ju dong tobat memang. Padahal sakarang Orang yang lebe hebat dari Yunus ada di bosong pung teng-tenga, ma bosong sonde mau tobat sadiki ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>And it won't be just her alone! Later people from Niniwe will also stand up and point their fingers at you who live nowadays saying, ‘All of you here are stupid!&gt; They will speak like that, because long ago when Yunus went to tell the Lord's will to them, they repented straight away. But.in.actual.fact, now there is a Person who is more impressive than Yunus in your midst, but you don't want to repent even a little bit! [EXEG: Last clause implied by context/purpose of 29-32, and following NLT]</bt><note reference="11:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yunus 3:5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Idop taráng<bt>Clear/Bright living</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 5:15, 6:22-23)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Yesus sambung lai Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang kasi manyala lampu te'oek, ais taro di tampa yang tinggi, ko biar dia bekin taráng itu kamar kasi samua orang yang maso di situ. Sonde ada orang yang kasi manyala lampu, ais tutu ame deng bakul, ko, sambunyi mati sang dia.<bt>Yesus continued again His speaking saying, “People light a wick.lantern, then put it on a high place, so that it makes that room bright for all the people who enter there. No one lights a wick.lantern, then covers it over with a basket, or hides it!</bt><note reference="11:33" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu sonde tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;ais tutu ame deng bakul&gt;&gt;.<bt>Some Yunani language writings, don't write “then cover it with a basket”.</bt></note>Itu sonde ada guna apa-apa!<bt>That has no worth/value at all! [EXEG: LEX: Gk secret place/cellar (TB di kolong rumah); but in eastern Indonesia it actually is quite common to put a lamp under a pile house, so this is not recommended. NLT = basket]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ example of queries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ example of queries</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:15, Markus 4:21, Lukas 8:16</note><v n="34" />Bosong pung mata ju sama ke lampu. Dia bekin taráng bosong pung dalam hati. Kalo mata galáp, orang lia samua-samua deng hati jahat. Ma kalo mata taráng, orang lia samua-samua deng hati bae.<bt>Your eye is like a lamp. It makes your inner liver bright. If the eye is dark, people see everything with evil livers. But if the eye is bright, people see everything with good livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***@@look at HCE, Message, NLT; for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***@@look at HCE, Message, NLT; for revising 33-36; for the moment, it's as good as any other translation, BUT if we can verify "give with a good eye" is a Hebrew idiom meaning "give generously" then we can revise accordingly (al) Bosong pung mata sama ke lampu yang kasi taráng bosong pung dalam hati. Kalo mata yang bae, orang pung dalam hati taráng. Ma kalo mata sonde bae, orang pung dalam hati galáp.<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong pung mata pung sinar kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Bosong pung mata pung sinar kasi tunju apa yang ada di dalam bosong pung hati. Mata yang bakilat, yang dia pung cahaya barisi tantu kasi maso apa yang bae pi dalam bosong pung hati. Ma mata jahat bekin halangan kasi cahaya ko maso pi dalam hati, deng itu orang idop dalam galáp.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Usaha ko taráng yang ada di bosong pung hati tu, jadi taráng sakali, sama ke matahari pung taráng. Taráng di bosong pung hati tu, jang sama ke bulan pung taráng, yang cuma kasi lia bayang-bayang sa.<bt>Make.an.effort so that that light which is in your liver, becomes very bright, like the sun's brightness. That brightness in your livers, shouldn't be like the moon's brightness, which only shows/reveals just shadows. [COMMENT (Chuck): I can't find the source or justification for this apparent overtranslation. But I assume it's there for a reason--I just can't reconstruct it.]</bt><v n="36" />Kalo bosong pung hati taráng, sampe sonde ada satu nat ju yang galáp, tantu bosong pung idop samua ju taráng, sama ke ada lampu bésar yang kasi taráng bosong pung idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>If your livers are bright, to the point that there is not a single gap that is dark, surely all [parts of] your lives will also be bright, as if there is a big lantern which illuminates your lives.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">nat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus togor orang Yahudi pung kapala agama dong<bt>The Lord Yesus scolds the Yahudi people's heads of religion</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 23:1-36; Markus 12:38-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Yesus omong abis, ju ada satu orang dari partei agama Farisi undang sang Dia ko datang makan di dia pung ruma. Sampe di sana, ju Yesus maso pi dalam ruma ko dudu di meja makan.<bt>After Yesus finished speaking, then a person from the Farisi religious party invited Him to come eat at his house. Arriving there, then Yesus entered into the house to sit down at the eating table.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="is the dudu memang exegetically correct."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">is the dudu memang exegetically correct. Implied went straight in at sat at table -- culturally not good to Tetun people (deleted, not necessary)</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Ma tuan ruma jadi heran lia Yesus dudu makan deng sonde pake cuci tangan lebe dolo, iko orang Farisi pung atoran.<bt>But the house owner became amazed seeing Yesus sitting eating without handwashing first, according to the Farisi people's regulation.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong orang Farisi dong hebat! Bosong pegang karás bosong pung atoran agama! Bosong inga kasi barisi piring deng galás pung luar sampe mangkilat, ma bosong sonde inga ko kasi barisi bosong pung dalam hati yang kamomos tu, yang jahat deng rakus mati pung!<bt>Then Yesus told him saying, “You-pl Farisi people are impressive! You hold on tight to your religious regulations! You remember to clean the outside of the plates and glasses until they are shiny, but you don't remember to clean those filthy inner livers of yours which are evil and exceedingly greedy!</bt><v n="40" />Ngali, é! Jang lupa. Tuhan Allah yang bekin bagian luar. Dia ju yang bekin bagian dalam.<bt>Stupid! Don't forget. The Lord God is the one who made the outside. He is also the one who made the inside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dasar kelo' &lt; Timorese ; ngali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Dasar kelo' &lt; Timorese ; ngali = bodo, é</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Ma ada lebe bae, bosong kasi sang orang kasian dong dari apa yang bosong punya, ko biar bosong bisa barisi di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>But it's better [=you should], you give to the poor people from what you own, so that you be clean in front of the Lord. [NOTE to daughter translations: the ‘but’ reflects a Gk word that is not the normal word for ‘but’. Here is reflects a contrary to expecation, so if it is not natural to put a ‘but’ here in your language, leave it out.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Bosong orang Farisi dong! Bosong nanti dapa calaka! So'al kasi Tuhan satu bagian dari sapulu bagian, bosong maen ba'itong samua-samua, kici-bésar. Sampe bosong pung bumbu kici ana dari kabón ju, bosong ba'itong mati! Ma bosong sonde toe hal yang pantíng dong. So'al parkara sayang sang Tuhan Allah, deng parkara adil, bosong lupa buang sang dong sa! Memang kotong musti tatáp kasi sang Tuhan Dia pung bagian, ma jang lupa hal-hal yang lebe pantíng dong.<bt>You-pl Farisi people! You will obtain misfortune! In.regards to giving the Lord one part out of ten, you habitually count everything, small-big. Even your tiny little spices from the garden, you count every last one! But you don't care about important things. In.regards to loving the Lord God, and matters of justice, you just completely forget about them! Certainly we must continue to give the Lord His share, but don't forget about the things which are more important.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="satu bagian dari sapulu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">satu bagian dari sapulu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal bosong sonde adil buang parkara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Tagal bosong sonde adil buang parkara adil deng parkara sayang, yang sama ke Tuhan pung maksud! Memang kotong musti tatáp kasi sang Tuhan, Dia pung bagian, ma jang lupa hal-hal yang lebe pantíng dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:42" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 27:30</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Bosong nanti dapa calaka! Te bosong suka cari tampa yang paling bae dalam ruma sambayang, deng suka cari hormat di tampa-tampa umum.<bt>You will obtain misfortune! Cuz (elaboration) you like to find the best place in the worship house, and like to seek honour in the public places. [NOTE to daughter translations: Try /di muka banya orang/ “in front of many people.”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Bosong nanti dapa calaka! Te bosong sama ke kubur yang dia pung tana su rata. Orang jalan di situ, ma dong sonde tau bilang, di situ ada kubur, tagal kubur pung tana di atas barisi, ma dia pung dalam busuk. Padahal iko kotong pung adat, orang yang inja kubur bekin kotor dia pung diri, jadi sonde pantas maso pi ruma sambayang. Bosong orang Farisi dong sama ke itu kubur! Di luar-luar bosong conto ke barisi mati pung. Ma bosong pung dalam hati ada ponu deng hal busuk.&gt;&gt;<bt>You will obtain misfortune! Cuz (elaboration) you are like a grave whose dirt is already flat. People walk there, but they don't know that there is a grave there, because the dirt on top of the grave is clean, but inside it is rotten. In.actual.fact, according to our-inc tradition, a person who steps on a grave makes him/herself dirty/defiled, and thus no appropriate to enter the worship house. You Farisi people are like that grave. On the outside you are very clean. But your livers are full of rotten things.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@What is the basis for the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@What is the basis for the last clause?? (Removed Sept 2008) Orang yang deka-deka deng bosong ju iko jadi kamomos.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kira-kira hukuman macam apa yang ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Kira-kira hukuman macam apa yang ada tunggu sang bosong, é? Te bosong ini sama ke kuburan pung isi yang sonde kantara. Orang yang lewat di bosong pung kubur sonde tau, bilang, di dalam situ ada mayat bobo puruk. Itu dia bosong pung hati yang puruk itu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ada satu ahli hukum Yahudi di situ, sambar sang Yesus pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Bapa pung kata-kata tadi tu, puku kaná sang botong ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>There was a Yahudi law expert there (who) retorted to what Yesus said saying, “Father Teacher! Those words of Father's, hit at us-exc!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="need quote margin to End Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">need quote margin to End Yesus talk sambar = 1) strike out at, 2) retort, respond accusingly<span class="Italic">(45)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ais Yesus balas sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Bosong ahli hukum Yahudi dong, biar ko bosong ju dapa calaka! Bosong bukan bantu orang deng bekin ringan dong pung idop, ma bosong bekin tamba susa sang dong deng bekin-bekin bosong pung atoran agama yang barát. Ais bosong kasi pikol orang deng bosong pung atoran macam-macam dong. Ma bosong sandiri sonde bantu pikol coba itu babán deng satu jari ju!<bt>Then Yesus answered him saying, “True! You Yahudi law experts, may.it.be that you also obtain misfortune! You don't help people by making their lives light/unburdened, but you make their difficulty increase by making up your heavy religious regulations. Then you make people carry all.kinds.of regulations of yours. But you yourselves don't even lift a finger to try to help carry that burden!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Bosong nanti dapa calaka! Te bosong batasibu bangun batu-batu tugu kasi Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu ko kasi hormat sang dong. Padahal bosong pung nene-moyang sandiri yang bunu bekin mati sang itu jubir dong!<bt>You will get/experience/obtain misfortune! Cuz (elaboration) you are busy building pillar/monument rocks for the Lord's spokespersons from long ago to give honor to them. But.in.actual.fact, your own ancestors are the ones who killed those spokespersons.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prasasti = (BI) plaque commemorating inauguration"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">prasasti = (BI) plaque commemorating inauguration of building</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Bosong ju satu kaki deng bosong pung nene-moyang. Dong tola buang Tuhan pung jubir, deng bunu bekin mati sang dong. Ais bosong bangun batu kubur kasi itu jubir dong, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong ju ia bae deng bosong pung nene-moyang.<bt>You are one foot (=intimate/loyal.to) with those ancestors of yours. They rejected the Lord's spokespersons, and murdered killed them. Then you-pl build grave stones for those spokespersons, to become a sign that you also agree with those ancestors of yours.</bt><v n="49" />Tagal itu, Tuhan Allah yang tau samua, parná omong bilang, &lt;Beta nanti utus Beta pung jubir deng utusan laen dong, ko datang di orang Isra'el dong. Ais, itu orang dong siksa barmaen saparu, deng bunu bekin mati saparu.&gt;<bt>Because of that, the Lord God who knows everything, once spoke saying, ‘I will commission my spokesperson and other commissioned.ones to come to the people of Isra'el. Then those people will habitually torture some, and murder kill some.’ [EXEG: Send them to who? Context, TN, TH, Green explicitly say ‘Israel’, and this is also clearly assumed by Marshall.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50-51" />Orang yang idop sakarang ni, musti pikol tanggong-jawab dari orang yang su bunu bekin mati Tuhan pung jubir dong. Itu itong dari Tuhan bekin ini dunya, mulai deng Habel pung mati, sampe yang paling ahir, Sakaria. Dia tu, yang kaná bunu di teng-tenga meja korban deng Kamar Barisi di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Bosong ju pikol ame dong pung hukuman!<bt>People who live nowadays, must carry the responsibility for people who have murdered killed the Lord's spokespersons. That counts/calculates from when the Lord made this world, starting with Habel's death, until the lastest, Sakaria. He was the one who was murdered in between the sacrifice table and the the Holy Room in the Lord God's Central Worship House. You also bear/carry that punishment of theirs.</bt><note reference="11:51" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 4:8, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 24:20-21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Bosong ahli hukum Yahudi dong! Nanti bosong dapa calaka! Te bosong pegang konci yang bisa buka pintu ko orang dapa mangarti bae-bae Tuhan Allah pung mau. Ma bosong sandiri sonde maso pi situ. Lebe jahat lai, bosong pele ame orang, ko dong jang maso pi situ!&gt;&gt;<bt>You Yahudi law experts! You will obtain misfortune! Cuz you hold the key that can open the door so people can understand well the Lord God's will. But you yourselves don't/won't enter there. And even more evil, you block people, so that they can't enter there!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53-54" />Waktu Yesus omong abis, ju itu guru agama deng orang Farisi dong maruak sang Dia. Mulai itu waktu, dong maen tanya macam-macam ko mau hiki kasi jato sang Dia. Dong ator siasat tarús ko cari-cari hal deng Dia.<bt>When Yesus finished speaking, then those religion teachers and Farisi people were furious at Him. Starting from that time, they continually asked all sorts of.things to attempt to trap and make Him fall. They continually made plans to look for issues/disputes with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jaga diri ko jang iko orang Farisi dong pung pura-pura<bt>Watch yourself in order to not follow the Farisi people's pretending</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:26-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, ada barapa ribu orang datang ko mau dengar sang Yesus. Dong jalan baseti deng makarubu ame sang Dia. Ju Dia omong lebe dolo deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jaga diri ko jang iko orang Farisi dong pung pura-pura. Te dong suka omong laen, ma dong bekin laen.<bt>At that time, several thousand people came to listen to Yesus. They walked shoving/elbowing each other and crowding around Him. Then He spoke first with His underlings saying, “Watch yourselves so you don't follow the Farisi people's pretending. Cuz (elaboration) they like to say one.thing, but they do another (=hypocricy).</bt><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:6, Markus 8:15</note><v n="2" />Dong pura-pura bae, ma dong pung pura-pura tu nanti kantara. Te samua yang tasambunyi sakarang, nanti dapa lia.<bt>They pretend to be good, but that pretending of their's will become visible. Cuz (elaboration) everything that is hidden now, will be seen.</bt><note reference="12:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:22, Lukas 8:17</note><v n="3" />Apa yang bosong omong sambunyi-sambunyi sakarang, nanti orang dapa dengar taráng-taráng. Apa yang bosong kusu-kusu dalam kamar, nanti orang omong karás-karás di muka banya orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>What you-pl speak hiddenly now, later people will hear it clearly/openly. What you whisper in the room, later people will speak loudly in front of many people.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***close quote"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***close quote</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Manusia pung nilei di muka Tuhan Allah<bt>The value of humans in front of the Lord</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:28-31)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana dong! Sonde usa taku kalo orang mau bunu sang bosong. Te dong cuma bisa bunu bosong pung badan sa, ma sonde bisa bekin apa-apa deng bosong pung jiwa.<bt>Yesus continued speaking saying, “Children! It's not neccessary (=don't) be afraid if people want to murder you. Cuz (elaboration) they only can murder just your body, but they can't do anything with your *soul.</bt><v n="5" />Beta mau kasi tau bilang, bosong musti taku sang sapa. Bosong musti taku sang Tuhan Allah. Te Dia yang bisa bunu sang bosong, ais itu lempar kasi maso bosong pi dalam naraka. Jadi Dia ni, yang bosong musti taku batúl-batúl.<bt>I want to tell who you should/must be afraid of. You must be afraid of the Lord God. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who can murder you, and then throw you away into hell. So (consequently) He is the one, whom you must truly fear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Bosong pikir coba, burung pipit pung harga barapa? Paling mura, to?! Lima ekor dua sen, aa? Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan Allah sonde lupa buang satu ekor ju.<bt>You try to think, what is the price of a pipit (sparrow-like) bird? The very cheapest, right? Five tails (=bird counter) for two cents, right? Even though that's the case, nevertheless the Lord God does not forget even one tail.</bt><v n="7" />Bagitu ju Tuhan taro hati sang bosong. Dia tau parsís barapa banya rambu di bosong pung kapala. Jadi bosong sonde usa taku, te Tuhan nilei bosong lebe dari burung pipit bam-banya dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Similarly, the Lord also pays attention to you-pl. He knows exactly how many hairs on your-pl heads. So (consequently) you-pl don't need to be afraid, cuz (elaboration) the Lord values you more than those many pipit birds.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(dt) 14/Mar/2006"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">(dt) 14/Mar/2006</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang malu mangaku sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Don't be ashamed to acknowledge the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:32-33, 12:32, 10:19-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais Yesus omong lai deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasang talinga bae-bae! Kalo ada orang yang barani mangaku sang Beta di muka orang banya di ini dunya, nanti Beta ju mangaku sang dia di muka Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga bilang, dia tu Beta pung orang.<bt>Then Yesus spoke again with His underlings saying, “Attach your ears well (=pay attention)! If someone is brave to acknowledge Me in front of many people in this world, later I will acknowledge her/him in front of the Lord God's underlings in heaven (*angels), saying that s/he is My person.</bt><v n="9" />Ma kalo ada orang yang omong di muka manusia bilang, dia sonde kanál sang Beta, nanti Beta ju omong di muka Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga bilang, Beta sonde kanál sang dia.<bt>But if someone speaks in front of humans saying that s/he does not know Me, later I also will speak in front of the Lord God's underlings in heaven saying that I don't know him/her.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Kalo ada orang omong bekin busuk Beta pung nama bae, na, Tuhan Allah masi sadia lupa buang dia pung sala tu. Ma kalo dia omong bekin busuk Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi pung nama bae, Tuhan Allah sonde lupa dia pung sala.<bt>I here, am the Authentic Human. If someone speaking making My good name rotten, na, the Lord God is still prepared to completely forget that wrong. But if s/he speaks making rotten the good name of the Lord's Holy Spirit, the Lord God will not forget his/her wrong. [EXEG: 'speak against' parallels 'blaspheme against', cf. TH]</bt><note reference="12:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:32, Markus 3:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Nanti kalo orang hela bawa sang bosong pi tampa urus parkara agama, ko, pi orang pegang parenta dong, tagal bosong parcaya sang Beta, bosong sonde usa taku mau bela diri karmana.<bt>Later if people drag you-pl off to the place of settling religious disputes, or, to the people who hold rule/govern, because you-pl believe in Me, you don't need to be afraid about how you will defend yourselves.</bt><v n="12" />Te nanti itu waktu ju, Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi ajar kata-kata yang pas ko bosong manyao sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later at that time, the Lord God's Holy Spirit will teach words which are exact/precise so that you-pl can answer/respond to them.”</bt><note reference="12:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:19-20, Markus 13:11, Lukas 21:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Carita orang kaya yang bodo<bt>Story of the rich person who was stupid</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, satu dari itu orang banya dong tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Tolong suru beta pung kaka ko babagi deng beta botong pung bapa pung pusaka.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, one of those many people asked Yesus saying, “Father Teacher! Please tell my elder.sibling to divide our father's inheritance with me.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma Yesus manyao sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Sapa yang angka sang Beta jadi Hakim ko putus bosong dua pung parkara macam bagitu?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus answered him saying, “Weh! [+exasperation] Who raised me up to be Judge to decide the two of you's disputes like that?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais Yesus omong sang itu orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti ati-ati ko jang saraka. Te harta yang banya sonde jamin idop yang aman.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to those many people saying, “You-pl must be careful to not be greedy. Cuz (elaboration) lots of inheritance/wealth doesn't guarantee/promise a safe life.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais ju Dia carita satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang kaya, yang dia pung kabón kasi hasil bam-banya.<bt>Then He story-ed a comparison story saying, “There was a rich person, whose gardens/fields had lots of harvest.</bt><v n="17" />Sampe-sampe dia pung gudang dong su sesak, deng dia sonde tau mau bekin karmana lai.<bt>To the point that his storage.houses were tight/crowded, and he did not know what else to do.</bt><v n="18" />Ais ju dia putus bilang, &lt;Beta mau bekin bagini sa! Beta bongkar buang ini gudang lama dong, ko kasi bangun yang lebe bésar, ais simpan beta pung kabón pung hasil deng samua harta milik laen di situ.<bt>So he decided saying, “I'll just do like this! I'll knock down this old storage house, to build a bigger one, then I'll store my garden/field's harvest and all other possession there.</bt><v n="19" />Kalo su bagitu, nanti beta omong deng beta pung diri sandiri bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Gudang su ponu! Makanan su cukup ko makan sampe taon-taon. Jadi makan-minum ena-ena deng goyang kaki sanáng-sanáng suda!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>When it's like that, then I'll speak to myself saying, ‘We! [+get attention] The storage house is full! There is enough food to eat for years and years. So (consequently) let's eat-drink pleasantly and sway our feet happily!&gt;</bt><v n="20" />Ma Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;Woi! Lu bodo, é! Ini malam ju, lu mati. Ais sapa yang dapa lu pung gudang pung isi samua?&gt;<bt>But the Lord God told him saying, ‘Woi! [+challenge] You are stupid! This night you die. Then who will get all the contents of your storage house?’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jadi bagini! Orang bisa sa kumpul harta bam-banya di ini dunya kasi dia pung diri sandiri, ma di Tuhan Allah pung pikiran, dia tu, miskin, tagal sonde babae deng Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>So it's like! A person can gather lots of inheritance in this world for him/herself, but in the Lord God's thinking, he/she is poor, because he/she is not in a good relationship with the Lord. [EXEG: spiritual poverty following NLT]”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parcaya sa sang Tuhan Allah<bt>Just believe in the Lord God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 6:25-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais Yesus ajar tamba sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa barepot deng bosong pung idop hari-hari so'al mau makan apa, ko, mau pake apa.<bt>Then Yesus taught His underlings further saying, “You-pl don't need to be overly preoccupied/busy with your every.day lives, about what to eat or what to wear.</bt><v n="23" />Te kotong pung idop ni, lebe dari apa yang kotong makan, deng apa yang kotong bapake.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) these lives of ours-inc, are more than what we-inc eat, and what we wear.</bt><v n="24" />Lia coba burung gagak itam dong! Dong sonde tanam, sonde koru, sonde ada pung gudang ko simpan makanan, ma Tuhan Allah piara sang dong. Kalo bagitu, tantu Dia ju bisa piara sang bosong, tagal Dia nilei bosong lebe dari itu burung dong.<bt>Have a look at the black gagak birds! They don't plant, don't harvest, don't have a storage.house to store food, but the Lord God takes.care of them. If/Since that's the case, surely He also can take.care of you, because He values you more than those birds.</bt><v n="25" />Kalo orang badiri di muka carmín, ais barepot deng dia pung diri, kira-kira dia bisa bekin tamba panjang dia pung umur idop, ko? Sonde bisa!<bt>If a person stands in front of a mirror, then busies him/herself with him/herself, (do you think) s/he can make the age of his/her life any longer? [He/she] Can't (=impossible)! [EXEG: Message has “mirror”. Is first clause required to set a thinking context for the rest? People reflect on their lives when standing in front of mirrors -- associated context. Otherwise phrasing seems to imply busy-ness, not worry. Has had input from several consultants (one objecting as addition).]</bt><v n="26" />Jadi, kalo barepot deng hal kici bagitu sonde bawa hasil apa-apa, akurang ko bosong masi mau barepot lai deng hal yang bésar dong? Dia pung ontong apa?<bt>So (consequently), if busy-ing one's.self with small things like that don't produce any effect, why do you-pl still want to busy your self with big things? What is the gain/benefit?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Lia coba bunga utan. Dong sonde karjá kabón, deng sonde tanún kaen. Ma raja Soleman pung pakean paling mewa ju, sonde bisa lawan bunga utan pung bagus.<bt>Have a look at the jungle/wild flowers. They don't work gardens/fields, and don't weave cloth. But even the most fancy clothes of raja Soleman, cannot compete with the beauty of those wild/jungle flowers. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: wildflower as per BAGD and Louw &amp; Nida; work field (male) nor spin/weave cloth (female) following TH.]</bt><note reference="12:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 10:4-7, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 9:3-6</note><v n="28" />Te Tuhan Allah piara rumput kici yang sonde ada pung arti, yang cuma idop ini hari, ais beso mati, ko orang buang pi dalam api. Kalo bagitu, na, Dia ju bisa piara bosong yang pung harga lebe dari itu rumput. Jadi akurang ko bosong sonde batúl-batúl bagantong sang Dia?<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Lord God takes.care of the small grasses which don't have any meaning, which only live today, then die tomorrow, so that people throw them into the fire. If/Since that's the case, na, He also can take care of you-pl whose worth is more than that grass. So (consequently), why do you-pl not truly hang/depend on Him?</bt><v n="29" />Bagitu ju, bosong sonde usa barepot so'al makan-minum. Te nanti Tuhan urus.<bt>Similarly, you-pl don't need to be busy-ing yourselves about eating-drinking. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord will handle/arrange it. [EXEG: /barepot/ covers both the effort of ‘striving for’ and the emotion of ‘worrying about’ from the Gk. Last sentence from context, needed for naturalness.]</bt><v n="30" />Orang yang sonde bagantong sang Tuhan, dong banting tulang ko urus itu hal dong samua. Ma bosong ni jang bagitu, te bosong pung Bapa di sorga su tau samua yang bosong parlú.<bt>People who don't depend on the Lord, they strive very hard to arrange all those things. But you-pl here don't do like that, cuz (elaboration) your Father in heaven already knows everything which you need.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ethnee: da peopo dat donno God,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ethnee: da peopo dat donno God, da odda peopos all ova da world? He's talking about everybody who isn't part of God's Kingdom.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Kalo bosong kasi jalan Tuhan Allah pung karjá dolo, nanti Dia ju urus ini hal dong kasi bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you-pl carry out the Lord God's work first, [NOTE: “work” is fairly broad, approx equiv of “the things of God”] He will arrange/take.care.of these things for you.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Simpan harta di sorga<bt>Store possessions in heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 6:19-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais Yesus sambung lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sama ke domba satu kumpul kici yang sonde ada pung kuat apa-apa. Ma sonde usa taku! Te bosong pung Bapa di sorga tu, Raja Bésar. Apa yang Dia pung, Dia sanáng kasi sang Dia pung ana sayang dong.<bt>Then Yesus continued again saying, “You-pl are like a small group of sheep who have no strength at all. But it's not neccessary (=don't) be afraid! Cuz that Father of yours-pl in Heaven, is the Big Raja. What He owns, He is happy to give to His beloved children. [EXEG: leaves open 1. share in blessings of Kingdom, and/or 2. share in rule of Kingdom, see Marshall. EXEG: Vocative “little flock”, affection carried by last sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added /sayang/ in last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) added /sayang/ in last sentence; NOTE added</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Jadi pi jual buang bosong pung barang dong, abis dia pung doi pi bagi kasi orang miskin dong. Deng bagitu bosong simpan harta di sorga di tampa yang aman deng batahan tarús. Pancuri sonde bisa pi mancuri ame sang dia. Kakarlák ju sonde bisa makan bekin rusak sang dia.<bt>So (consequently) go sell off your-pl things, then go divide out the money to the poor people. In that way you store possessions in heaven in a place that is safe and keep enduring/lasting. Thieves cannot go steal it. Even cockroaches cannot eat destroy it. [EXEG: “purses...that will not wear out/grow old” TN: not talking about stronger earthly purses. Invest in eternal enduring treasure that is important to God. See also similar discussion in Marshall.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="This is not just future; this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">This is not just future; this is an investment we are making every day now.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Inga bae-bae! Bosong pung harta di mana, na, bosong pung hati ju ada di situ.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember well! Where your-pl possession are, na, your livers are also there.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tukang suru-suru yang siap layani siang-malam<bt>Low.ranking.servant who is ready to serve day-night (=all the time)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35-36" />Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Siang-malam bosong musti siap sadia ko layani sang Tuhan. Sama ke tukang suru-suru yang mete tunggu dia pung tuan ruma pulang dari pesta kawin. Kalo bos toki pintu, na, dia bisa buka deng capát.<bt>Yesus spoke again saying, “Day-night you-pl must be ready to serve the Lord. Like a servant who stays.awake.at.night waiting for the house owner to come home from a wedding feast. If the boss knocks on the door, na, he can open it quickly. [EXEG: prepare to serve God? prepare for the Lord's return? NLT, Marshall seem to go with the former. TN the latter. Many evade the issue and just say "gird up your loins" is an idiom meaning "be prepared for action"]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added note</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:35-36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:1-13; Markus 13:34-36</note><v n="37" />Kalo bos datang dapa dia pung orang karjá dong ada batunggu bagitu, tantu dong barontong. Te nanti bos sandiri yang kasi tunju dia pung hati bae sang dong. Dia pake pakean orang karjá, ais pi layani itu orang karjá dong deng makanan ena-ena.<bt>If the bos comes and finds his workers are waiting like that, surely they will benefit/profit. Cuz later the bos himself will show his good liver to them. He will put on slave clothes, then go serve those servants with delicious food.</bt><v n="38" />Itu orang karjá dong memang barontong tagal dong layani bos deng bae. Biar bos datang jam barapa sa, tenga malam ko, amper siang, dong salalu siap.<bt>Those servant truly benefit because they served their boss well. No matter what time the boss comes, middle of the night or almost dawn, they are/were always prepared.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Pikir bae-bae! Kalo ada tuan ruma yang tau parsís jam barapa pancuri mau datang, su tantu dia sonde kasi sampat ko itu pancuri bongkar dia pung ruma.<bt>Think carefully! If there is a house owner who knows exactly what time a thief comes, surely he will not allow an opportunity for that thief to dismantle/destroy his house.</bt><v n="40" />Jadi bosong musti siap salalu, te sonde ada satu orang ju yang tau parsís kapan Manusia Tulen mau datang kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must always be prepared, cuz (elaboration) there is not a single person who knows exactly when the Authentic Human will come back.”</bt><note reference="12:39-40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:43-44</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana bua yang satia, deng ana bua yang sonde satia<bt>Underlings who are faithful, and underlings who are not faithful</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rethink satia for daughter translations"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">rethink satia for daughter translations</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:45-51)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais Petrus tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Bapa pung umpama tadi tu, cuma kaná sang kotong sandiri sa, ko, kaná samua orang?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus asked Yesus saying, “Father Teacher! That comparison.story of Father's earlier, is it only about us-inc ourselves or about all people?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-44" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu umpama kaná di samua orang yang bekin sama ke kapala urusan yang pintar urus deng satia kasi dia pung bos. Te nanti dia pung bos angka sang dia ko bagi makanan kasi orang karjá laen dong. Kalo dia rajin bekin iko dia pung tugas bagitu, biar dia pung bos datang kapan sa, ma dia salalu ada bekin yang batúl. Ais dia barontong, tagal dia pung bos nanti angka sang dia ko urus dia pung harta milik samua.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “That comparison.story is about all people who do like a manager who is skilled in arranging.matters and faithful to his boss. Cuz (elaboration) later his boss will lift him up (appoint him) to divide food for the other workers. [EXEG: Gk here is /oikonomos/ ‘kapala urusan (supervisor)’, not ‘hamba (servant/slave)’.] If he is diligent in following his work like that, no matter what time his boss comes, but [+contrary to expectation] he is always doing things correctly. So then he profits, because his boss will appoint him to take care of all his belongings-possessions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistos: trustworthy oikonomos: person in charge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">pistos: trustworthy oikonomos: person in charge of managing a household or an estate.<span class="Italic">(42)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ma calaka kalo itu kapala urusan mulai pikir bilang, &lt;Eh! Tantu bapatua masi lama baru pulang.&gt; Tarús dia mulai papoko orang karjá laen dong, laki-laki deng parampuan. Ais dia dudu makan-minum sanáng-sanáng sampe mabo.<bt>But misfortune if that manager starts to think saying, ‘Eh! [+realisation] Surely it will be a long time before the old.man comes home.’ Then he begins to beat up the other servants, male and female. Then he sits eating-drinking happily until drunk. [EXEG: LEX: Gk shifts from /oikonomos/ to /doulos/ here, but it has the anaphoric article, so for our NTT lgs need to keep ‘kapala urusan’ for referent tracking.]</bt><v n="46" />Ma satu hari, waktu itu kapala urusan sonde sangka apa-apa, takuju sa bos pulang. Waktu bos dapa tau itu hal dong, ju itu bos langsung papoko sang dia, ais usir buang sang dia, ko dapa dia pung bagian di luar sama-sama deng orang yang sonde satia bekin iko bos pung mau.<bt>But one day, when that servant is not suspecting anything, unexpectedly the boss comes.home. When the boss found out about these things, then he immediately beats him up, then expels him, to find his portion (Fig: just desserts) outside together with the people who are not faithful in following the boss' will. [EXEG: Gk “cut up” taken as severe punishment LN, CEV.] [DISCOURSE: “When the boss found out about these things...” added as RL discourse required missing step. Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised, note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) revised, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju bos langsung papoko sang dia,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ju bos langsung papoko sang dia, ais usir buang sang dia, ko dapa dia pung bagian di luar sama-sama deng orang yang sonde satia bekin iko bos pung mau.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Te orang karjá yang tau dia pung bos pung mau, ma sonde siap bekin iko, ko, sonde mau bekin iko, nanti kaná hukuman barát.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the worker who knows his boss' will, but is not ready to follow it, or does not want to follow/obey it, will be afflicted with heavy/severe punishment.</bt><v n="48" />Ma orang karjá yang karjá sala tagal dia sonde tau bos pung mau, nanti dia kaná hukuman yang sonde barát. Te orang yang su tarima banya, dia pung tuntutan ju banya. Orang yang tarima karjá bésar, dia pung tanggong-jawab ju bésar.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the worker who works wrong because he did/does not know his boss' will, he will be afflicted with punishment that is not heavy. Cuz (elaboration) a person who receives much, the demands on him are also much. A person who receives big/important work, his responsibility is also big/important.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ajaran bisa bekin orang bamalawan<bt>The Lord Yesus' teaching can cause people to be at odds with each other</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** new title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** new title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Yesus sambung Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta datang ko kasi pisa Beta pung orang dari orang laen di ini dunya. Itu sama ke orang pake api ko bakar buang kotoran. Beta pung suka kalo itu api su mulai manyala di mana-mana.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “I've come to separate out My people from other people in this world. That is like people use fire to burn off the crud/filth/rubbish. I would like it if that fire was beginning to burn everywhere. [EXEG: Marshall says in context of Luke ‘fire’ here should be taken as judgment (broad sense). He says interpretation as representing “power of the Spirit” has no contextual support here. Green agrees. TN favours “division” in context of 12:49-53. UNS's at one check took fire literally, hence unpacking the metaphor. Western Bukidnon Manobo BT.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk word here is “kindled, ignite, start fire, cause process of burning to begin” so try to reflect inceptive phase of fires starting everywhere, rather than end phase of fires burning things up and consuming everything in their path everywhere. But don't overtranslate.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** unpack the metaphor (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** unpack the metaphor (Helong)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus sambung Dia pung omong, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Yesus sambung Dia pung omong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta datang ni ko bawa api pi ini dunya. Beta mau ko itu api su manyala pi mana-mana.</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Ma Beta musti pikol sangsara yang barát lebe dolo. Beta nanti sangsara batúl sampe Beta pung tugas su abis.<bt>But I must carry heavy suffering first. I will truly suffer until My mission/task/responsibilities are over/complete. [EXEG: until the time is over? or until my work is completed? NLT in 49 “that my task were already completed, 50 until it (burden) is accomplished”; Marshall in 50 “a destiny to be fulfilled” Green “within the … framework of his mission”]</bt><note reference="12:50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 10:38</note><v n="51" />Bosong pikir Beta datang bawa dame di ini dunya, ko? Sonde! Beta datang ko bekin orang dong bakanjar deng bekin orang dong tapica-pica tagal Beta pung ajaran.<bt>You-pl think I come/came to bring peace to this world, right? No! I come/came to make people argue with each other, and make people break apart/divide because of My teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="May be secondary result, but not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">May be secondary result, but not primary purpose</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Mulai sakarang orang basodara dong tapica-pica. Dalam satu kelu, tiga lawan dua, dua lawan tiga.<bt>Starting now people who are mutually.siblings will break.apart. In one family, three will oppose two, two will oppose three.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="53" />Papa lawan ana;<bt>Papa will oppose child;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ana lawan papa.<bt>child will oppose papa.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mama lawan ana;<bt>Mama will oppose child;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ana lawan mama.<bt>child will oppose mama.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mama mantu lawan ana mantu;<bt>Mother in law will oppose child in law</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ana mantu lawan mama mantu.&gt;&gt;<bt>child in law will oppose mother in law.”</bt><note reference="12:53" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mika 7:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kanál bae-bae hari susa pung tanda-tanda dong<bt>Know well the signs of difficult days</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:2-3)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Tarús Yesus omong deng itu orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong lia awan tabal muncul di sablá barat, bosong omong, &lt;Ini tanda bilang, hujan su mau turun.&gt; Memang batúl bagitu.<bt>Then Yesus spoke with those many people saying, “If/when you-pl see thick clouds appearing on the west side, you say, ‘This sign says that rain will come.’ Certainly that's true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="On different parts of the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">On different parts of the same island, a storm normally comes in from different directions. It also depends on the wind pattern and whether there is a hurricane. "Black cloud" matches ombros 'rain storm, thunderstorm,' though thunderstorms are not very frequent.</Message></Annotation><v n="55" />Kalo angin salatan fuu datang, bosong omong, &lt;Ini tanda bilang, ini hari panas mati pung!&gt; Memang batúl bagitu.<bt>If/when the south wind blows comes, you say, “This sign says today will be very hot.’ Certainly that's true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="notos: south, southwest; the &quot;kona&quot; direction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">notos: south, southwest; the "kona" direction is from what is normally the leeward side, and on all islands it is southwest to west southwest. It brings hot, muggy weather. LN: "All get asthma."</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Woi! Bosong manusia muka-balakang yang omong laen bekin laen! Bosong pintar kasi mangarti ini bumi deng dia pung cuaca pung mau-mau. Ma akurang ko bosong sonde mau mangarti Tuhan pung mau-mau di ini jaman?&gt;&gt;<bt>Woi! [+challenge] You-pl hypocritical people who speak one thing, do another! You are skilled in understand the ways of this earth and it's weather. But why do you not want to understand the ways of the Lord in this age?” [EXEG: 'unwilling to understand' from Marshall and LB. “interpret the present time” God's power in the miracles Jesus does (too narrow); the significance of what I do (TN-OK); Marshall and Oz Guiness argue that it is quite broad, including political developments, and this is the broad sense we are aiming for.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Badame deng bosong pung musu dong<bt>(Make) mutual.peace with your-pl enemies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 5:25-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57-58" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong baparkara, akurang ko bosong sonde bisa putus sandiri mana yang batúl! Lebe bae urus dame dolo! Jang sampe bosong su sampe di muka hakim, ais dia putus ko kasi maso sang bosong pi bui.<bt>Yesus spoke again saying, “If you-pl have a dispute, why don't you decide yourselves what is correctf! It's better to arrange/make peace first! May it not be that you-pl have arrived in front of the judge, then he decides to put you in jail.</bt><v n="59" />Te kalo bagitu, tantu bosong sonde bisa kaluar sampe bosong bayar bekin abis bosong pung utang yang hakim putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz if that's the case, surely you will not get out until you have completely paid off that debt/fine of yours which the judge decides.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arkhon: magistrate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">arkhon: magistrate</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kasi tenga idop yang jahat, ko bale iko Tuhan pung mau-mau<bt>Leave behind life which is evil, to turn and follow God2's will2 (=things of God2)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, ada orang kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, gubernor Pilatus su bunu barapa orang Yahudi dari Galilea waktu dong ada bawa korban di Ruma Sambayang Pusat di Yerusalem.<bt>At that time, people told Yesus that gubernur Pilatus had murdered several Yahudi people from Galilea, when they were bringing sacrifices to the Central Worship House in Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed to get simultaneity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed to get simultaneity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mignymi: Hebraism, does not imply mixing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">mignymi: Hebraism, does not imply mixing of bloods, but simultaneity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu ada orang kasi tau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Itu waktu ada orang kasi tau sang Yesus, bilang, Gubernor Pilatus su bunu barapa orang Yahudi dari Galilea, yang datang di Yerusalem ko bawa korban di Ruma Sambayang Pusat.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko bosong, kira-kira itu orang yang kaná bunu tu, dong pung sala ada lebe bésar dari samua orang Galilea yang laen? Andia ko dong kaná hukum mati, ko?<bt>Hearing that, then Yesus asked saying, “According to you-pl, (do you think that perhaps) those people who were murdered, their wrongs were bigger than all the other Galilea people? Is that why they were afflicted with the death penalty, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tightened up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***tightened up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus tanya, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus tanya, bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Itu orang Galilea yang kaná bunu tu, dong pung sala ada lebe bésar dari samua orang laen, andia hukum mati sang dong, ko?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Sonde! Ma kalo bosong sonde kasi tenga bosong pung idop yang jahat, ko bale iko Tuhan pung mau-mau, bosong ju nanti kaná ancor buang sama ke dong.<bt>No! But if you don't leave behind your lives which are evil, to return and follow the God2's will2 (=things of God), you also will be destroyed like them. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure focus is on end result, not living bad lives along the way. Also in vs.5.]</bt><v n="4" />Ais karmana lai deng itu dalapan blas orang yang mati kaná tendes manara yang rubu di Siloam tempo hari tu? Dong pung sala lebe bésar dari samua orang laen di Yerusalem, ko?<bt>Then how.about those eighteen people who died being smashed by the tower which fell.down at Siloam a while ago? Their wrongs were bigger than all other people in Yerusalem, right?</bt><v n="5" />Sonde! Ma kalo bosong sonde kasi tenga bosong pung idop yang pakane'o, ko bale iko Tuhan pung jalan lurus, bosong ju nanti kaná ancor buang sama ke dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>No! But if you don't leave behind your lives which are twisted, to return and follow the Lord's straight path, you also will be destroyed like them.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pohon yang sonde babua, sama ke Tuhan pung orang yang sonde ada pung hasil<bt>Tree/s which don't bear fruit are like the Lord's people which don't yield results (bear fruit2-collocation)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE on structure (from Chuck): One"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">NOTE on structure (from Chuck): One consultant wanted vs 1-9 combined into a single section. NIV is the only translation I looked at that does this. NRSV, NLT, CEV, and TB all treat them separately. UBS-TH and CONNOT do not address the higher level structure issue. TN treats them as separate sections, but notes that both are addressing the issue of the need for repentance, but from different angles. Marshall discusses the two in one section, but notes that while both address the need for repentance, "the lesson of the parable (e.g. vs.6-9) is different from the lesson of the intro (vs.1-5)." In my words, the intro is saying "If your theology leads you to think that all bad things that happen to people are God's punishment for evil (which they aren't), then you had better get serious and repent." The lesson of the parable is, "The window of opportunity for getting right with God and becoming productive for Him is limited, so you'd better repent NOW, and get on with it." The suggestion that both these passages are teaching that we should not quickly jump to conclusions in judging others has 1) no support from within the text itself, and as far as I can see, 2) not a hint of support from the commentaries. With the TB treating them separately, and the connection not being tight, by treating the two separately, their proximity talking about repentance is adequate. I think we lose by combining them under one title.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais ju Yesus kasi satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang yang ada pung pohon bua<bt>Then Yesus gave a comparison.story saying, “There was a person who had a fruit</bt><note reference="13:6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Indonesia pake kata &lt;pohon ara&gt; dari istila bahasa Yunani <span class="Italic">sukē.</span> Ma Alkitab kasi tunju satu pohon di sana yang orang biasa makan dia pung bua. Di Indonesia sablá timur, orang sonde makan &lt;pohon ara&gt; pung bua. Jadi &lt;pohon ara&gt; di Alkitab bahasa Indonesia, sonde sama ke kotong pung pohon ara di sini.<bt>Indonesian language uses the word &lt;ara tree&gt; from the Yunani language term <span class="Italic">sukei</span>. But the Bible indicates a tree there which people often ate its fruit. In eastern Indonesia, people do not eat &lt;ara tree&gt; fruit. So &lt;ara tree&gt; in the Indonesian Bible, is not the same as our-inc ara trees here.</bt></note>di dia pung kabón. Dia maen datang ko maloi coba mau cari tau itu pohon su babua, ko balóm. Ma itu pohon balóm babua.<bt>tree in his garden. He habitually came to inspect it wanting to know if that tree had fruit already, or not yet. But that tree had not yet born fruit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="use of Alkitab here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">use of Alkitab here</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais ju dia suru dia pung tukang kabón bilang, &lt;Su tiga taon ni, beta datang ulang kali ko cari ini pohon pung bua, ma beta sonde dapa apa-apa. Jadi potong buang sang dia, te ini pohon cuma makan tampa sa.&gt;<bt>Then he told his garden worker saying, “For three years now, I have come over and over to seek this tree's fruit, but I have not gotten anything. So chop it down, cuz this tree is just taking up space.’ [EXEG: Is Gk “using up the soil” 1) taking up space, or 2) using up nutrition (so needs fertiliser)? NLT, CEV and TN favour #1; Marshall and TH mention both.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma itu tukang kabón manyao bilang, &lt;Bapa jang mara. Kasi tempo ini pohon satu taon lai. Biar ko beta pacol kuliling sang dia, ais taro pupuk ko bekin subur sang dia.<bt>But that garden worker replied saying, ‘Father don't get angry. Allow time for this tree one more year. Let me hoe around it, then put fertilizer to make it fertile.</bt><v n="9" />Kalo taon datang ini pohon babua, na, bae. Ma kalo sonde, na neu, potong buang sang dia sa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>If next year this tree gives.fruit, na, good. But if not, well alright, just chop it down.”&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae parampuan balakang bongko, kaná deng hari sambayang<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a woman with a bent back, on the worship day</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Satu kali, pas deng orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang, Yesus pi ajar di ruma sambayang.<bt>One time, exactly on the Yahudi people's worship day, Yesus went to teach at the worship house.</bt><v n="11" />Di situ ada satu parampuan yang dia pung balakang su bongko dalapan blas taon, tagal setan pung bekin. Dia sonde bisa badiri lurus.<bt>There there was a woman whose back was bent already eighteen years, because of evil spirit's doing. She could not stand straight.</bt><v n="12" />Yesus dapa lia itu parampuan ju, Dia pange ame sang dia, ais omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama! Sakarang mama su bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus saw that woman, then He called/summoned her, then spoke saying, “Mama! Now mama is healed.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ you have been freed from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ you have been freed from your ailment/suffering &gt; God has freed you from your suffering</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ju Yesus taro tangan di itu parampuan. Takuju, dia pung balakang bongko tu lurus memang. Ju dia minta tarima kasi, deng puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then Yesus put his hand on that woman. Unexpectedly that bent back of hers was straight right.way. And she reciprocated thankyou, and praised the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma itu kapala ruma sambayang mara, tagal Yesus bekin bae orang kaná deng hari sambayang. Ju dia kasi tau orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Satu minggu ada anam hari karjá. Jadi lebe bae orang saki dong datang di itu hari-hari karjá sa, ko cari orang bekin bae sang dong. Jang datang di hari sambayang!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that worship house's head got angry, because Yesus healed that woman on the worship day. And he told the crowd saying, “One week has six work days. So (consequently) it would be better for sick people to come just on those work days, to seek someone to heal them. Don't come on the worship day!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** changed to “come to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** changed to “come to be healed” (Helong) Problem: who would be the subject?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa! Lebe bae bekin bae orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Naa! Lebe bae bekin bae orang saki di itu hari-hari karjá sa, jang di hari sambayang!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:9-10, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:13-14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Yesus manyao sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Orang muka-balakang. Di hari sambayang bosong ju karjá, to?! Te bosong pi kasi lapás bosong pung sapi deng keledai ko kasi minum sang dong, aa?!<bt>But Yesus replied to him saying, ‘Heh! [+rebuke] Hypocrite! On the worship day you-pl also work, right?! Cuz (elaboration) you-pl go to free your cows and donkeys to give them drink, right?!</bt><v n="16" />Ini mama ni, ba'i Abraham pung turunan, sama ke kotong. Setan dong pung bos su ika sang dia 18 taon. Kalo Beta lapás sang dia kaná deng hari sambayang, na, sala ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>This mother here, is ancestor Abraham's descendant, just like us-inc. The bos of the evil spirits has tied her for 18 years. If I free her on the worship day, na, is that wrong?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="na sala ko? @@GRAMMAR"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">na sala ko? @@GRAMMAR</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus pung musu dong malu. Ma itu orang banya dong sanáng deng Dia pung karjá yang bagus dong.<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus' enemies were embarrassed. But those many people were happy with His good deeds.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al biji yang paling kici<bt>The Lord Yesus gives a comparison.story about seed that very small</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:31-32; Markus 4:30-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ju Yesus sambung Dia pung omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira Beta banding Tuhan pung orang dong sama ke apa, é?<bt>Then Yesus connected His speaking again saying, “What should I compare the Lord's people with? [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that “the Lord's people” is taken narrowly as “believers”, and not broadly as “humanity”. If problem, change to “believers”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Mula-mula dong cuma sadiki sa, ma lama-lama dong tamba banya. Dong tu mulai sama ke biji yang kici ana sa. Orang tanam sang dia di kabón. Ais ju dia idop ko jadi pohon bésar. Tarús burung dong datang basarang di dia pung cabang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>At the beginning they are only just a few, but eventually they increase. They start like a seed that is very tiny. A person plants it in his garden. Then it lives to become a big tree. Then the birds come nest in it's branches.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al ragi<bt>The Lord Yesus gives a comparison.story about yeast</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira Beta banding Tuhan pung orang dong deng apa lai, é?<bt>Then Yesus spoke again saying, “What else should I compare the Lord's people with?</bt><v n="21" />Dia sama ke ragi yang parampuan ame ko campor deng tarigu dua sak,<bt>It's like yeast which a woman takes to mix with two sacks of flour</bt><note reference="13:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani bilang tarigu 3 <span class="Italic">sata</span>. Satu sata, kira-kira 12 liter. Jadi 3 sata, 36 liter tarigu.<bt>The Yunani langauge says 3 <span class="Italic">sata</span> of flour. One sata, is about 12 liters. So (consequently) 3 sata, 36 liters of flour.</bt></note>ko bekin banya roti. Ju itu tarigu samua reis sampe bésar, tagal itu ragi yang sadiki ana. Tuhan pung orang dong ju pangaru tamba luas bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>to make lots of bread. Then that flour all raises until it's big, because of that tiny bit of yeast. The Lord's people also increase in influence like that.” [EXEG: increase in number? or, increase in influence? (Marshall, TH, CONNOT, TN, NLT all favour the latter.); added last sentence from Belu Cons. Check UNS responses to explicate topic.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="reis = raise; ***added last sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">reis = raise; ***added last sentence from Belu Cons. Check UNS responses to explicate topic check the first Dia Is this = orang dong<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="3 sata: around 55 pounds, a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">3 sata: around 55 pounds, a little more than a standard flour sack. ezymoothee holon: People know the difference in taste between flour tortillas from Taco Bell, made with flour, water, and a little oil, and pita bread, sold in the supermarkets. It's not the size of the risen dough that is at issue (it gets punched down anyway), but the different quality. But LN didn't realize that the yeast at that time was kept moist, like sourdough; she's used to powdered yeast in a sealed envelope.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sorga pung pintu kici ana<bt>Heaven's door is teeny tiny</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 7:13-14, 21-23)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais itu, Yesus dong mulai jalan pi kota Yerusalem. Iko-iko jalan, Dia singga-singga di kota deng kampong ko ajar orang.<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) began to walk to Yerusalem city. On the way, He stopped at cities and villages to teach people.</bt><v n="23" />Di satu tampa, ada satu orang tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Kira-kira cuma sadiki orang sa yang bisa dapa salamat, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>At one place, a person asked Him saying, “Father Teacher! Probably it's only just a very few people who can be saved, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sorga pung pintu maso tu, kici. Jadi pasang kaki ko bosong bisa maso iko situ. Te ada banya orang yang mau coba maso, ma sonde bisa.<bt>He answered saying, “That door of heaven is small. So strive/make effort (Idiom: fasten feet) so that you-pl can enter in there. Cuz (elaboration) there are many people who want to try to enter, but can't.</bt><v n="25" />Kalo tuan ruma su konci pintu, nanti bosong badiri di luar ko toki-toki pintu, deng ba'eki minta tolong bilang, &lt;Bos! Buka pintu dolo!&gt;<bt>If the house owner has already locked the door, then you-pl stand outside to knock and knock on the door, and yell out requesting help saying, ‘Boss! Open the door!’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma nanti dia manyao bilang, &lt;Bosong tu, sapa? Beta sonde kanál sang bosong!&gt;<bt>But later he will reply saying, ‘Who are you-pl? I don't know you!&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egertheei: gets up, not from bed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">egertheei: gets up, not from bed, but from eating a late dinner, gets up from the table, locks up the house, and then goes to bed. apokleiseei: shut with a lock<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Tarús bosong bilang, &lt;Mana bisa bos sonde kanál sang botong? Botong yang biasa dudu makan-minum deng bos. Bos ju biasa ajar sang botong di botong pung istraat dong.&gt;<bt>Then you will say, ‘How can it be that boss doesn't know us? We are the ones who habitually ate-drank with boss. Boss also habitually taught us in our streets/avenues/boulevards.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju nanti dia manyao bilang, &lt;Beta su bilang tadi, beta sonde kanál sang bosong! Bosong ni, manusia tukang bekin jahat sa. Iskarobis dari sini!&gt;<bt>Then He will reply saying, ‘I've already said, I don't know you! You are just humans who habitually do evil. Get out of here!’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iskarobis = menjauhlah = mundur jauh-jauh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">iskarobis = menjauhlah = mundur jauh-jauh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikia: unrighteousness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">adikia: unrighteousness</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais nanti kalo Tuhan Allah putus samua orang pung parkara, bosong manangis makarereu deng makan gigi sa. Te bosong dapa lia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, ba'i Yakob deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir samua su maso dudu di dalam sorga. Ma bosong kaná usir buang pi luar sa.<bt>Then later when the Lord God decides every one's cases, you-pl will just cry sobbingly and grind your teeth. Cuz you got to see grandfather Abraham, grandfather Isak, grandfather Yakob and all the Lord God's spokesperson having already entered and are sitting in heaven. But you have been expelled outside. [EXEG: sitting forshadowing reclining at banquet from vs. 29]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="brygmos: sign of rage and futility"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">brygmos: sign of rage and futility -- don't like it but can't do a thing about it.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:13, 25:30</note><v n="29" />Nanti manusia datang dari dunya pung ujung-ujung, dari matahari nae sampe matahari turun; dari utara sampe salatan, ko dudu makan rame-rame di Tuhan Allah pung istana.<bt>Later humans will come from the ends of the world, from the east to the west; from the north to the south, to sit and eat festively at the Lord God's palace. [EXEG: kingdom — palace: part-whole as appropriate context and imagery for feast.]</bt><note reference="13:28-29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 8:11-12</note><v n="30" />Tanda bae-bae ini hal: nanti kalo Tuhan putus samua orang pung parkara, ada yang orang dolu sangka dia orang kici sa, ma dia dapa hormat bésar. Deng ada yang orang dolu bilang, dia orang bésar, padahal Tuhan anggap dia orang kici sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Take good note of this: later when the Lord decides everyone's cases, there will be those who previously people considered a small/unimportant person, but he will get great honour. And those whom people previously said he was a big/important person, in.actual.fact the Lord just considers him a small/unimportant person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idou: call attention to what he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">idou: call attention to what he is going to say</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Taro kira bae-bae ini hal: Orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Taro kira bae-bae ini hal: Orang yang dolu dong sangka dia orang kici, nanti dia dapa hormat bésar. Deng orang yang dolu dong bilang dia orang bésar, nanti orang su sonde toe sang dia lai.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 19:30, 20:16, Markus 10:31</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jato kasian sang kota Yerusalem pung isi<bt>The Lord Yesus has pity on the inhabitants of Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 23:37-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Itu waktu, ada barapa orang Farisi datang mangada sang Yesus, ais kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae, Bapa Guru ondor jao-jao pi tampa laen, te raja Herodes mau bunu sang Bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, several Farisi people come to see Yesus, then told saying, “It's better Father Teacher retreats far to another place, cuz raja Herodes wants to murder Father.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32-33" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bapatua tu, sama ke musang licik! Bosong pi kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;Beta ada usir setan deng bekin bae orang saki dong ini hari deng beso. Dia pung lusa, baru Beta pung karjá su abis.&gt; Biar karmana ju, Beta masi mau karjá sadiki lai dalam Beta pung jalan pi Yerusalem. Te orang Yerusalem dong yang suka bunu Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, ‘Heh! [+rebuke] That old.man is like a crafty civet cat! You-pl go tell him saying, ‘I am expelling evil spirit/s and healing people today and tomorrow. On the day after tomorrow, only then will that work of Mine be finished.’ No matter what, I still want to work a bit more on My way to Yerusalem. Cuz those Yerusalem people, are the ones who like to murder the Lord God's spokespersons. [NOTE to daughter translations: Commentaries note Jesus uses irony here. So if UNS's can't get that he's saying He expects them to zap Him in Jerusalem, I suggest adding “like Me” at the end, or something similar.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haloopeki: not &quot;sly&quot;, which is how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">haloopeki: not "sly", which is how the fox is cast in French, German, and English folk tales, but lightweight, no consequence, a pest (Buth). Like the little foxes that spoil the vines in Canticles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Aduu, orang Yerusalem dong, é! Bosong ni yang maen bunu Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong, deng lempar bekin mati utusan yang mau datang tunju Tuhan pung jalan sang bosong. Su ulang kali Beta mau kumpul jaga bosong ko pele ame sang bosong dari jahat, sama ke ayam mai yang mau tutu ame dia pung ana dong di bawa dia pung sayap. Ma bosong sonde mau.<bt>Aduu, Yerusalem people! You-pl are the ones who habitually murder the Lord God's spokesperson, and throw kill the commissioned ones who want to come point out the path for you. Already many times I have wanted to gather protect you to block/defend you from evil, like a female chicken who wants to cover up her children under her wings. But you don't want it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tightened up, reduced metonomy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***tightened up, reduced metonomy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Aduu, orang Yerusalem di kota Yerusalem,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Aduu, orang Yerusalem di kota Yerusalem, é! Bosong ni satu kota yang maen bunu Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong, deng lempar bekin mati utusan yang mau datang tunju jalan sang lu. Su ulang kali Beta mau kumpul jaga lu pung isi ko pele ame sang dong dari jahat, sama ke ayam mai yang mau tutu ame dia pung ana dong di bawa dia pung sayap. Ma lu sonde mau.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Sakarang Tuhan su sonde toe lai bosong pung ruma sambayang. Ais beso-lusa dia su kosong. Nanti bosong sonde akan lia sang Beta lai, sampe bosong mangaku bilang,<bt>Now the Lord no longer cares about your worship houses. So tomorrow or the next day they will be empty. Later you will not see Me again, until you acknowledge that [EXEG: Take Gk. house = temple (TN, and mentioned as possibility in TH), since carries imagery in RL of loss of blessing, not carried by house (by itself), or house = city in RL.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tightened up, reduced metonomy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***tightened up, reduced metonomy</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang orang yang datang bawa Tuhan pung nama,<bt>&lt;The Lord God gives blessing to person who comes bearing the Lord's name,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan su utus sang Dia!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>because the Lord has commissioned Him!”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Capital Dia?? in ot quote?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Capital Dia?? in ot quote?</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang, kaná deng hari sambayang<bt>The Lord Yesus heals people on the worship day</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, kaná deng hari sambayang, orang partei agama Farisi pung kapala satu undang sang Yesus ko datang makan di dia pung ruma. Dia dudu makan, ma ada orang yang mama'u sang Dia ko mau lia Dia mau bekin apa kaná deng hari sambayang.<bt>One time, on the worship day, one head of the Farisi religion party invited Yesus to come eat at his house. He sat to eat, but there were people who spied on him to see if He would do anything on the worship day.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mama'u = intip (not known by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mama'u = intip (not known by all)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Itu waktu, ada satu orang saki bere-bere yang ada iko dudu di situ.<bt>At that time, there was a person sick with "bere-bere" who was also sitting there. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hydroopikos: accumulation of body fluids. Like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hydroopikos: accumulation of body fluids. Like diabetes and other things.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais Yesus tanya sang ahli hukum Yahudi deng orang Farisi yang ada iko dudu makan di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko ba'i Musa pung atoran, bole bekin bae orang saki, kaná deng hari sambayang, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked the Yahudi lawyers and Farisi people who were sitting eating there saying, “According to grandfather Musa's regulation, is it permissible to heal people on the worship day, or not?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="He knew that they knew."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">He knew that they knew.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma sonde ada satu orang yang buka mulu. Ju Yesus sonto itu orang saki, ais dia bae memang. Tarús Yesus suru sang dia ko pulang.<bt>But not a single person opened his mouth. Then Yesus touched that sick person, and he was healed immediately. Then Yesus told him to go home.</bt><v n="5" />Ais itu, Yesus tanya sang dong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada ana yang jato maso pi dalam parigi, kaná deng hari sambayang, bosong pi hela kasi kaluar sang dia, ko sonde? Kalo sapi yang jato, bosong kasi tenga, ko, hela kasi kaluar? Tantu bosong hela kasi kaluar. Naa, itu dia pung arti bilang, bosong su karjá, to!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, Yesus asked them again saying, “If a child falls into a well, on the worship day, do you-pl go pull him out, or not? If its a cow that falls, do you leave it, or pull it out? Surely you pull it out. Naa [+shift to implication], that means you-pl have done work, right!”</bt><note reference="14:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dengar Yesus omong bagitu, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa manyao sang Dia.<bt>Hearing Yesus speak like that, there was not a single person who could answer Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang cari-cari muka<bt>Don't seek face (=seek praise/honour)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Itu waktu, Yesus ada lia-lia orang yang datang makan pesta di itu ruma. Ada banya orang yang pili tampa di muka, ko pi dudu di situ. Lia bagitu, ju Dia omong bilang,<bt>At that time, Yesus was watching people who came to eat the feast at that house. There were many people who chose places in front, to go sit there. Seeing like that, He spoke saying,</bt><v n="8" />&lt;&lt;Ati-ati, ó! Kalo orang undang sang bosong pi pesta kawin, na, jang pi cari tampa dudu di orang bésar dong. Te jang sampe tuan pesta ada undang tamu yang lebe pantíng.<bt>“Becareful! If someone invites you-pl to a wedding feast, na, don't go seek to sit in the places for the big/important people. Lest the feast master has invited more important guests.</bt><v n="9" />Kalo bagitu, tuan pesta nanti datang omong sang lu bilang, &lt;Jang mara, é! Bapa tolong pinda pi balakang dolo, te beta su sadia ini korsi kasi ini orang bésar ni.&gt; Ju lu bangun kasi tenga itu korsi deng malu, ko pi dudu di balakang.<bt>If so, the feast master will come talk to you-sg saying, “Don't get angry (=I'm sorry)! Father  (=you) please move to the back, cuz (elaboration) I have prepared these chairs for these big/important people here.’ Then you stand up and leave that chair embarrassed, to go sit in the back.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eskhaton: most humble"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eskhaton: most humble</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi, kalo lu dapa undangan, na, pi dudu sa di korsi paling balakang. Nanti kalo tuan pesta dapa lia sang lu, ju dia datang bilang, &lt;Eh, Pak! Mari ko dudu di muka sini sa.&gt; Deng bagitu bosong dapa hormat di muka tamu samua.<bt>So (consequently), if you get an invitation, na, just go sit in the chairs in the very back. Later if the feast master sees you, and he comes saying, ‘Eh, Mr! Come sit in the front here.’ In that way you will receive respect in front of all the guests.</bt><note reference="14:8-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 25:6-7</note><v n="11" />Te orang yang angka-angka diri, nanti Tuhan kasi jato sang dia. Ma orang yang bekin diri sama ke orang kici, nanti Tuhan angka nae sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who lifts himself up, the Lord will drop/humble him. But the person who makes himself like a small/unimportant person, the Lord will raise him up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eskhaton: least important"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eskhaton: least important</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:12, Lukas 18:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, Yesus omong deng itu tuan ruma bilang, &lt;&lt;Laen kali, kalo pak bekin pesta, na, jang undang pak pung kelu deng tamán orang kaya dong sa! Te dong pasti bisa undang balas sang pak.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke with that house master saying, “Another time, if Mr makes a feast, na, don't just invite Mr's family and rich friends! Cuz (elaboration) they certainly can reciprocate the invitation to Mr.</bt><v n="13" />Ma kalo pak bekin pesta, na, undang orang miskin, orang kaki hela, orang yang sonde bisa jalan, deng orang buta dong.<bt>But if Mr makes a feast, na, invite the poor people, the dragging-feet people, the people who cannot walk, and the blind people.</bt><v n="14" />Tantu dong sonde bisa balas sang pak. Ma kalo pak undang sang dong, Tuhan Allah yang balas. Nanti kalo Dia kasi idop kambali orang parcaya yang su mati dong, Dia sonde lupa pak pung bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Surely they cannot reciprocate Mr. But if Mr invites them, the Lord God will be the one who reciprocates/rewards. If/when he makes the believers who have died live again, He will not forget Mr's goodness.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama so'al pesta bésar<bt>Comparison story about a big feast</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***fleshed out title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***fleshed out title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Dengar bagitu ju, ada orang yang dudu satu meja deng Yesus angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Paling ontong tu, andia orang yang iko makan rame-rame di Tuhan Allah pung istana, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then a person who was sitting at the same table with Yesus began to talk [formally] saying, “The one who is the most fortunate, is the person who participates eating festively in the Lord God's palace!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Yesus manyao sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta carita kasi umpama bagini: ada satu orang bekin pesta bésar. Ju dia undang orang bam-banya.<bt>Yesus answered him saying, “I'll tell a story like this: there was a person who made a big feast. Then he invited many people.</bt><v n="17" />Waktu pesta su siap, ju dia suru dia pung tukang suru-suru ko pi pange orang-orang yang kaná undang dong bilang, &lt;Mari, te acara su mau mulai.&gt;<bt>When the feast was ready, he ordered his servant to go call people who were invited saying, ‘Come, cuz (elaboration) the activity is about to begin.’</bt><v n="18" />Ma dong samua bekin alasan macam-macam ko biar dong sonde bisa datang. Satu kasi alasan bilang, &lt;Waa! Beta baru béli ame satu kabón, jadi beta musti pi lia coba dolo. Jang mara ó! Te beta sonde bisa datang.&gt;<bt>But they all made all sorts of excuses why they could not come. One gave an excuse saying, ‘Oh dear! I have just bought a garden, so I must go have a look at it. Don't get angry! Cuz I am unable to come.’</bt><v n="19" />Ada laen yang kasi alasan bilang, &lt;Beta baru béli ame sapi bajak lima pasang. Beta ada mau pi coba sang dong ni, jadi ma'af, ó!&gt;<bt>There was another who gave an excuse saying, ‘I have just bought five pairs of plow cows. I need to go try them out, so sorry!&gt;</bt><v n="20" />Yang laen lai bilang, &lt;Beta baru kawin, jadi sonde bisa.&gt;<bt>Yet another said, ‘I just married, so I am unable.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais, itu tukang suru-suru pulang ko lapor dia pung tuan. Dengar bagitu ju, itu tuan mara mau mati. Ais dia parenta itu tukang suru-suru bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, lu kaluar ko pi capát-capát! Lu pi di samua istraat deng lorong di ini kota, ko undang bawa orang kasian, orang kaki hela, orang buta, deng orang lumpu dong.&gt;<bt>Then, that servant went home to report to his master. Hearing like that, that master got very angry. Then he ordered that servant saying, ‘If that's the case, you go out quickly! Go to all the main.streets and corridors/alleyways in this city, to invite the poor people, the dragging-foot people, the blind people and the lame people.’ [EXEG: vs. 21 is in city, vs. 23 in country outside city. NLT, Marshall.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** vs. 21 &amp; 23 tightened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** vs. 21 &amp; 23 tightened up (Helong)</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dengar bagitu ju, itu tukang suru-suru pi undang itu orang dong. Ais dia pulang ko lapor bilang, &lt;Bapa! Dong su datang samua, ma tampa kosong masi banya.&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, that servant went to invite those people. Then he came.home and reported saying, ‘Father! They have all come, but there are still many empty places.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju itu tuan bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, na, lu pi lai di kampong-kampong di luar kota, sampe di kabón-kabón. Buju-buju sang sapa sa, ko bawa datang sang dong, asal bekin ponu ini tampa pesta.<bt>Then that master said, ‘If that's the case, na, you go again to the villages outside the city, to the point of (going) to the gardens/fields. Persuade anyone and bring them, so.long.as this feast place is made full. [EXEG: see note at vs. 21. “roads” here is taken as leading to surrounding villages; Gk here is lit. ‘fences’ which in RL worldview is taken as going to the fields, with support from LN sense #1.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** vs. 21 &amp; 23 tightened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** vs. 21 &amp; 23 tightened up (Helong)</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Dengar, é! Itu orang yang su tola beta pung undangan tu, dong sonde dapa rasa ini pesta pung enak sadiki ju!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen! Those people who rejected that invitation of mine, they will not get to taste even a tiny bit of this feast's tastiness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bareken bae-bae dolo, baru iko sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Count carefully first, only then follow the Lord Yesus</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:37-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús pi Yerusalem. Orang banya ada iko sang Dia. Ais Dia mangada sang dong, ju Dia omong bilang,<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) travelled on to Yerusalem. Many people were following Him. Then He faced them, and He spoke saying,</bt><v n="26" />&lt;&lt;Orang yang batúl-batúl mau iko sang Beta, dia musti sayang sang Beta <span class="Italic">lebe</span> dari samua: lebe dari dia pung mama-papa, lebe dari dia pung bini-ana, lebe dari dia pung adi-kaka, malahan lebe dari dia pung diri sandiri. Kalo sonde, itu orang sonde pantas jadi Beta pung ana bua.<bt>“The person who truly wants to follow Me, s/he must love Me <span class="Italic">more</span> than everything: more than his mama-papa, more than his wife-children, more than his younger-elder siblings, and even more than his own self. If not, that person is not worthy of being My underling. [DISCOURSE: follows RL pattern for pairs.]</bt><note reference="14:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:37</note><v n="27" />Te orang yang sonde mau pikol sangsara tagal dia iko sang Beta, dia sonde pantas jadi Beta pung orang. Orang yang mau jadi Beta pung orang, biar orang mau bunu bekin mati sang dia ju, ma dia pikol tarús dia pung sangsara.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who does not want to carry/endure suffering because he follows Me, he is not worthy of being My person. A person who wants to be My person, even if/though people want to kill him, nevertheless s/he continually bears his/her suffering, [NOTE to daughter translations: check if “endure” has to be transitive. If so, add object “that/his suffering”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** restructured Feb 2008 because of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** restructured Feb 2008 because of 2 problems. 1) s/he dies of natural causes whereas “cross” evokes someone killing or threatening to kill them, and 2) keep bearing their suffering after they have died.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar dia mati ju, dia musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Biar dia mati ju, dia musti pikol tarús.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:38, 16:24, Markus 8:34, Lukas 9:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jadi kalo mau iko sang Beta, na, bareken bae-bae dolo. Conto ke orang yang mau bangun ruma batingkat. Dia musti itong lebe dolo dia pung ongkos sampe alus-alus. Jang sampe doi sonde cukup.<bt>So (consequently) if [you] want to follow Me, na, count carefully first. For example like a person building a high/multi-storied house. He must count first the cost to the finest details. Lest the money be lacking.</bt><v n="29" />Kalo sonde itong alus-alus, mangkali dia baru bekin ruma pung fanderen, te doi su abis. Ais orang dong katawa bekin malu sang dia,<bt>If [he] doesn't count it in detail, probably he will only have made the house's foundation, and the money runs out. The people laugh and make him ashamed,</bt><v n="30" />bilang, &lt;Bosong lia coba itu orang dolo! Dia baru bekin fanderen, ma balóm apa-apa, te doi su abis.&gt;<bt>saying, ‘You-pl have a look at that person! He just made the foundation, but nothing has happened yet and the money is already all.gone.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Conto laen, andia so'al baparáng. Raja yang mau baparáng musti dudu ba'itong lebe dolo deng dia pung konco dong. Kalo dia cuma ada pung tantara 10.000 orang, kira-kira dia bisa manáng lawan musu 20.000 orang, ko sonde?<bt>Another example is in regards to war. The raja that wants to go to war must sit and first count his cronies/underlings. If he only has an army of 10.000 people, is it possible to win against an enemy of 20.000, or not?</bt><v n="32" />Kalo su itong-itong abis, ma nanti dia kala paráng, na, lebe bae, waktu musu masi jao, dia kirim memang utusan ko ba'urus dame sa.<bt>If/when he has finished counting, but he would lost in war, na, it's better, when the enemy is still far, he just immediately sends an envoy to go arrange peace.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@changed order of last clause May"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@changed order of last clause May 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Bagitu ju orang yang mau iko sang Beta. Dia musti itong pi-datang bilang, dia su siap kasi tenga samua-samua, ko sonde? Te kalo sonde, itu orang sonde pantas jadi Beta pung ana bua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also the person who wants to follow Me. He must count back and forth whether he is ready to leave everything or not? Cuz (elaboration) if not, that person is not worthy/appropriate to be/become My *disciple.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check final ?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">check final ?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang sonde pantas iko sang Tuhan Yesus, sama ke garam yang sonde ada pung guna lai<bt>The person who is not worthy to follow the Lord Yesus, is like salt that has no more use</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***expanded title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***expanded title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 5:13; Markus 9:50)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34-35" />Yesus sambung Dia pung omong deng conto laen lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Garam tu, bae. Kotong pake ko bekin enak makanan. Ma kalo garam sonde asin lai, dia pung guna apa? Sonde bisa pake sang dia lai ko bekin enak makanan. Mau bekin pupuk ju, sonde bisa. Kotong angka buang sa. Jadi bosong ju musti jadi sama ke garam, ko idop basayang deng samua orang. Sapa ada talinga, na, dengar bae-bae, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus continued His speaking with another example again saying, “Salt, is good. We-inc use it to make food delicious. But if that salt is not longer salty, what is its worth? Can't use it anymore to make food delicious. We can't use it even to make fertilizer. We just throw it away. So (consequently), you-pl must also be like salt, to live in mutual love with all people. Whoever has ears, na, listen carefully!” [EXEG: From Gk &amp; NRSV ftn; NOTE to daughter translations: if "sonde asin lai" is problematic, try "su tawar". Explication of purpose modelled on explication Mark version. UNS's off in outer space without it. Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sapa ; *** (2009) added explication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Sapa ; *** (2009) added explication from Mark to narrow purpose. UNS's all over the map otherwise</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Domba yang ilang<bt>The sheep which disappeared</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:12-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, orang tukang tagi bea deng orang tar laku-laku laen dong, maen datang sang Yesus ko mau dengar sang Dia. Ma orang Yahudi anggap sang dong tu, orang sonde bae.<bt>At that time, the tax collectors and the people considered ‘down.and.outers’ kept coming to Yesus to listen to Him. But the Yahudi people considered them, people who were not good. [NOTE: last sentence clarifies cultural knowledge, that both categories are “bad”, and sets the background info for the social dynamics of rest of the chapter.]</bt><v n="2" />Lia bagitu, ju ada orang Farisi deng guru agama Yahudi dong yang mangomek bilang, &lt;&lt;Cue! Ini orang batamán deng orang tar laku-laku dong. Malahan Dia dudu makan deng dong lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, the Farisi people and the Yahudi religion teachers complained saying, “Cue! [+disgust] This person is mutual.friends with the down.and.outers. He even sits and eats with them!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malahan = Cnj"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">malahan = Cnj</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:1-2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:29-30</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dengar bagitu ju, Yesus carita kasi sang dong ini umpama bilang,<bt>Hearing like that, Yesus told them this comparison.story saying,</bt><v n="4" />&lt;&lt;Andekata dari bosong ada satu orang pung domba saratus ekor. Tarús ada satu ekor yang ilang. Sakarang itu orang musti bekin apa? Tantu dia kasi tenga itu domba yang sambilan pulu sambilan ekor di tampa yang aman, ais dia pi cari sampe katumu itu domba yang ilang tu.<bt>“Suppose that one of you had one hundred tails (animal counter) of sheep. Then one tail disappeared. Now what should that person do? Surely he would leave those sheep who were ninety nine tails in a safe place, then he would go hunt for that sheep that disappeared until he found it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tarús ada ilang satu ekor."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Tarús ada ilang satu ekor.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kalo dia su katumu itu domba, ju dia masa'a bawa pulang deng sanáng.<bt>If/when he encounters that sheep, then he happily shoulder.carrys it and brings it home.</bt><v n="6" />Sampe di ruma, tarús dia pange dia pung kawan dong, ais kasi tau bilang, &lt;We! Bosong datang ko sanáng-sanáng deng beta dolo! Te beta su katumu be pung domba yang ilang.&gt;<bt>Arriving home, then he calls his friends, [NOTE: friends is RL category conflating friends and neighbours] then tells saying, ‘We! [+get attention] You-pl come to be happy/pleased along with me! Cuz (elaboration) I have found that sheep of mine that disappeared.’</bt><v n="7" />Naa, di sorga ju bagitu. Kalo ada satu orang sala yang tobat, ais kambali pi Tuhan, sorga pung isi samua sanáng. Dong lebe sanáng tagal ini satu orang yang kambali pi Tuhan, dari sambilan pulu sambilan orang yang idop lurus, deng sonde ilang jalan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to implications], in heaven it is also like that. If/when one sinner repents, then returns to the Lord, all the contents/inhabitants of heaven are happy. They are happier because of this one person who has returned to the Lord, than [because of] ninety nine people who live straight and haven't lost their way (physically, morally, spiritually).” [NOTE: last clause reinforces the point (=beautiful style), brings lexical cohesion to the whole pericope, and lexical ties with following pericopes.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Doi perak yang ilang<bt>The silver money which disappeared</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais Yesus carita satu umpama laen lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu mama pung doi perak sapulu biji.<bt>Then Yesus told yet another comparision.story saying, “There was a mama who had ten silver coins.</bt><note reference="15:8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang 10 <span class="Italic">drakma</span>. Satu drakma, andia tukang pung gaji satu hari.<bt>The Yunani language says 10 <span class="Italic">drakma</span>. One drakma, is one craftsman/workers wage for one day.</bt></note>Tau-tau, te ada satu biji ilang. Sakarang dia mau bekin apa? Tantu dia pi bakar lampu ais loti di mana-mana, deng sapu itu ruma sampe di huk-huk, ko cari bae-bae itu doi.<bt>It.turns.out that one coin disappeared. Now what should she do? Surely she will go light a lamp and inspect all over, and sweep that house even to the corners, to carefully look for that money.</bt><v n="9" />Waktu dia dapa katumu itu doi ju, dia pi pange orang sablá ruma dong, ais kasi tau bilang, &lt;We! Bosong datang ko sanáng rame-rame deng beta dolo! Te beta su dapa kambali beta pung doi yang ilang tu!&gt;<bt>When she finds that money, then she calls people from the next house, and tells them saying, ‘We! [+get attention] You-pl come to be lively happy with me! Cuz (elaboration) I have found again that money of mine that disappeared!’ [EXEG: Gk. “friends and neighbours” is grammatically feminine, but in most lgs in this region forcing it would make it a highly marked construction that is not natural. Would skew the focus.]</bt><v n="10" />Di sorga ju bagitu. Kalo ada satu orang sala yang tobat, ais kambali pi Tuhan, tantu samua ana bua di sorga dong sanáng mau mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>In heaven it's also like that. If there is one sinner who repents, then returns to the Lord, certainly all the angels in heaven are very happy.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana yang ilang<bt>The child which disappeared</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais Yesus sambung Dia pung carita deng satu umpama laen lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu bapa deng dia pung ana laki-laki dua orang.<bt>Then Yesus continued/connected His story with yet another comparison.story saying, “There was a father and his two male children.</bt><v n="12" />Satu kali, itu ana bungsu kasi tau dia pung bapa bilang, &lt;Papa! Bagi kasi beta pung harta pusaka sakarang su!&gt; Ju dia pung bapa bagi itu harta kasi dia pung ana dua-dua.<bt>One time, that youngest child told his father saying, ‘Papa! Divide out my inheritance possessions now! [+insistence like a 2-year-old]’ So his father divided those possessions to both his children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="In Near Eastern culture, this is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">In Near Eastern culture, this is like saying 'Father, I wish you were dead!'</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Sonde lama ju, itu ana bungsu jual dia pung bagian. Ais dia bungkus dia pung pakean, ju dia barangkat pi negrí yang jao. Di situ, dia ambur-ambur dia pung doi deng idop foya-foya.<bt>Not long then, that youngest child sold his portion. Then he wrapped his clothes, and he left to go to a country that was far. There, he scattered/wasted his money with extravagant living. [NOTE to daughter translations: /idop foya-foya/ was difficult for a couple teams. Try “live according to his own desires” or “to please himself”, but check as there should be a conventionalised or idiomatic way of talking about this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ambur-ambur ~ hambor-hambor (CHECK); idop foya-foya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ambur-ambur ~ hambor-hambor (CHECK); idop foya-foya = live extravegantly ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="synagagoon panta: the father's assets were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">synagagoon panta: the father's assets were varied, including land, which the boy couldn't take with him. He converted everything into cash. asootoos: dissolutely, profligately = he just couldn't hold on to his money, he spent it like it was never going to run out. He was stupid about money and ran up a lot of debts (like some people who go to Las Vegas). It doesn't say he was immoral in other ways: that was the assumption his older brother made.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Waktu dia pung doi abis ju, itu negrí kaná musim lapar yang hebat, sampe dia ju idop malarat.<bt>When his money was all.gone, then that country was afflicted with a severe hunger season, to the point.that he also lived impoverished.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The family money had gone to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">The family money had gone to Gentiles. This was a deep insult to family and community.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Tarús dia pi cari-cari karjá. Ais satu orang di itu negrí tarima sang dia ko suru dia karjá kasi makan babi.<bt>Then he went to hunt for work. So one person from that country accepted him in order to order him to work feeding pigs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekolleethee: attached himself to. It wasn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ekolleethee: attached himself to. It wasn't a real job. He had a chance to scrounge food, but no pay.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Tagal itu ana tar tahan lapar lai, ju dia kapingin makan itu babi dong pung makanan. Te sonde ada orang yang mau kasi makan sang dia na.<bt>Because that child couldn't endure hunger anymore, he desired to eat those pigs' food. Cuz (elaboration) there was no one to give him food [+obviously]. [NOTE to daughter translations: (alternate) /Tagal itu ana su sonde bisa tahan dia pung lapar lai,/.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Lama-lama dia mulai pikir pi-datang bilang, &lt;Di beta pung papa pung ruma, samua orang karjá dong dapa makan sampe kinyang. Padahal beta di sini su mau mati lapar sa.<bt>Eventually he began to think over.and.over saying, ‘In my papa's house, all the workers get to eat until they are satisfied. Whereas I here am just about ready to die of hunger. [EXEG: “came to himself / his senses” implied by the process of thinking it through plus what he says to himself. Forcing it would be overtranslation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** if issues, see Dhao for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** if issues, see Dhao for alternate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eis heauton elthoon: not repentance, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eis heauton elthoon: not repentance, but "he got smart."</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Lebe bae, beta pulang sa pi di beta pung papa. Ais kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Beta su bekin sala bésar sang Tuhan deng papa.<bt>It's better I just go.home to my papa. Then tell him saying, “Papa! I have done big wrongs toward the Lord and papa.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What the boy wants to tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">What the boy wants to tell his father is almost word for word what Pharaoh says to Moses to get him off his back in Exodus 10:16: "I wen do bad ting to yoa God da Boss# Above, an to you guys." This is not repentance, it's a deal to keep from being thrown out by the community for what he had done to his family.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Beta su sonde pantas jadi papa pung ana lai. Biar papa tarima sang beta jadi kuli sa di papa pung ruma, ju bae!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>I am not worthy of being papa's (=your) child anymore. Allow papa to accept me to just be a kuli (lowest level of worker) in papa's house, that's ok.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="If the son has the status"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">If the son has the status of a hired laborer, that would neutralize some of the shame for the family.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais pikir bagitu, ju dia bangun ko pulang pi dia pung bapa pung ruma. Dari jao bapatua su dapa lia sang dia, ju jato kasian sang dia. Dia turun dari ruma ko lari-lari pi sambut dia pung ana yang su pulang tu. Ais bapatua paló-ciom sang dia.<bt>After thinking like that then he got up and went.home to his father's house. From afar the old.man already saw him, and felt pity on him. He went down from the house to run to greet that child of his who had come.home. Then the old.man hugged-kissed him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju itu ana omong deng dia pung bapa bilang, &lt;Papa! Beta su bekin sala bésar sang Tuhan deng papa. Beta su sonde pantas lai jadi papa pung ana.&gt;<bt>Then that child spoke with his father saying, ‘Papa! I have done big wrongs towards the Lord and papa. I am not worthy of being papa's child anymore.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma dia pung bapa langsung parenta dia pung orang karjá dong bilang, &lt;We! Capát, é! Pi ame bawa baju yang paling bagus ko kasi pake sang dia. Taro cincin di dia pung jari, deng sapatu di dia pung kaki.<bt>But his father immediately ordered his workers saying, ‘We [+get attention]! Hurry! Go get the very best clothes/shirt for him to wear. Put rings on his fingers, and shoes on his feet.</bt><v n="23" />Pi hela ame itu sapi paron ko horo, te kotong mau bekin pesta rame-rame.<bt>Go drag/pull that carefully.handfed/fatten cow in order to cut/slaughter it, cuz (elaboration) we-inc are going to make a lively feast.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapi paron = (implied male) piara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sapi paron = (implied male) piara dgn perhatian khusus, tinggi, kasi makan, kasi minum secara teratur dan lebe banya</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Tagal beta pung ana ni sama ke dia su mati, ma sakarang dia su idop kambali. Dia ilang, ma sakarang beta su dapa kambali sang dia.&gt; Omong abis bagitu ju, dong mulai bapesta rame-rame.<bt>Because this child of mine was as if he had died, but now he lives again. He disappeared, but now I have him again.’ After speaking like that, they begain to feast festively. [NOTE: made 1st sentence into simile, cohesion with vs 32.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Itu waktu, ana sulung sonde ada di ruma, te dia ada karjá di kabón. Waktu dia pulang, dari jao dia dengar orang maen musik deng bafoti baronggeng.<bt>At that time, the eldest child was not at home, cuz (elaboration) he was working in the garden. When he returned.home, from far.off he heard people playing music and male.dancing and female.dancing.</bt><v n="26" />Ju dia pange ame satu orang karjá, ais tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;We! Ada bekin rame apa ni?&gt;<bt>Then he called a worker and asked him saying, ‘We! [+get attention] What are they celebrating here?’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hena toon paidoon: more probably &quot;one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">hena toon paidoon: more probably "one of the village kids," not "worker." The workers were busy putting on the party. Bailey points out this this village kid acts like the chorus in a Greek drama.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu orang karjá manyao bilang, &lt;Bos pung adi su datang. Jadi bapa suru horo sapi ko bekin pesta bésar, te dia pung ana su pulang deng salamat.&gt;<bt>That worker answered saying, ‘Bos' younger sibling has come. So (consequently), father ordered to slice/slaughter the cow to make a big feast, cuz (elaboration) he child has come.home safely.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apelaben: accepted him. The father didn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">apelaben: accepted him. The father didn't give the boy a chance to propose his deal. He forgave the boy publicly and took the loss of half his assets. This is a picture of Jesus forgiving us, and paying a high price to do it. hygiainonta: shalom, everything okay<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu ana sulung mara. Dia su sonde mau maso pi dalam ruma lai. Tarús dia pung bapa pi kokoe sang dia ko maso pi dalam.<bt>Hearing that, that eldest child got angry. He no longer wanted to enter the house. Then his father went to coax him to come inside.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma dia maruak bilang, &lt;Papa! Coba pikir dolo! Bagini lama ni beta banting tulang karjá satenga mati sama ke kuli kasar kasi sang papa. Beta sonde tau langgar papa pung mau. Biar bagitu ju, ma papa balóm parná kasi kambing ana satu ekor ko beta bekin pesta sanáng-sanáng deng beta pung kawan dong.<bt>But he burst.out.angrily saying, ‘Papa! Think about it! All this time I have worked very hard like the lowest kuli for papa. I do not know how (=have never) to oppose papa's will/wishes. Even though that's the case, nevertheless papa has not yet ever given one goat offspring so that I can make a happy feast with my friends.</bt><v n="30" />Ma tau-tau te papa pung ana tukang royal ni, pi maen parampuan bekin abis papa pung doi. Sakarang dia pulang datang, ju papa horo sapi yang paling bagus ko bekin pesta bésar kasi sang dia.&gt;<bt>But wouldn't you know it, this royal tradesman child (=cynical) of father's, went and played around with women using up father's money. Now he comes.home, and papa slaughters the very best cow to make a big feast for him.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana tukang royal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ana tukang royal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma dia pung papa manyao bilang, &lt;Ana sayang, é! Dengar bae-bae! Bagini lama lu tenga sama-sama deng papa. Samua yang papa pung, itu samua ju lu pung.<bt>But his father replied saying, ‘Beloved child! Listen carefully! For all this time you have stayed together with papa. Everything which papa owns, it all is also yours.</bt><v n="32" />Ma sakarang kotong musti bapesta sanáng-sanáng, tagal lu pung adi satu ni. Dolu, sama ke dia su mati, ma sakarang dia su idop kambali. Dia ilang, ma sakarang su dapa kambali.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But now we-inc must happily feast, because of this one younger sibling of yours. Previously, it was as if he had died, but now he lives again. He disappeared, but now has been found again.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added /ma/ at beginning of sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added /ma/ at beginning of sentence to 1) better reflect Gk, and 2) better reflect the contrast of the context</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="edei: fitting, proper, we just have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">edei: fitting, proper, we just have to do this -- inner compulsion, impossible not to. hoti ho adelphos sou houtos: this brother of yours -- a direct comeback to ho hyios sou houtos in 30 "this son of yours"<span class="Italic">(32) (32) </span>If the father hadn't taken the initiative and forgiven the boy publicly, the townspeople would have insisted on a ceremony (still used) that would result in everybody treating him as dead, no longer part of the community, because he had taken money for town lands and thrown it away to the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapala urusan yang lihai<bt>The manager who is astute</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Ais Yesus carita tamba satu umpama lai kasi Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang kaya yang kasi karjá satu orang jadi dia pung kapala urusan. Ma lama-lama bos dengar isu bilang, itu kapala urusan mulai pakane'o ko bekin rugi sang dia.<bt>Then Yesus told another comparision story to His underlings saying, “There was a rich person who gave work to a person to become his manager. But eventually the boss heard rumours that that manager had begun to be crooked making him suffer.financial.loss.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lihai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">lihai</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi dia pange itu kapala urusan, ko kasi tau bilang, &lt;Lu ni, karmana? Beta dengar lu maen pakane'o beta pung harta. Sakarang lu pi bekin laporan karjá ko beta pareksa dolo. Te abis itu, beta mau lapás buang sang lu.&gt;<bt>So (consequently), he called that manager, to tell him saying, ‘How is it with you-sg? I have heard that you are being crooked with my possessions. Now you go make a work report so that I can examine it. Cuz after that, I am getting rid of you.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu kapala urusan pikir pi-datang bilang, &lt;Beta su paya ni, ma! Beta mau bekin apa sakarang? Cangkul tana, beta sonde kuat. Jadi tukang minta-minta ju, beta malu.<bt>Hearing like that, that manager thought/mulled.over.it saying, ‘I'm really in trouble here! What am I going to do now? To hoe soil, I'm not strong. Even to become a beggar, I'm ashamed.</bt><v n="4" />Kalo beta su sonde bisa karjá di sini lai, beta musti cari akal, ko biar orang laen dong masi mau tolong tarima sang beta.&gt;<bt>If I cannot work here anymore, I must find a way so that other people still want to help me.’ [EXEG: Gk has word-play /oikonomias/ ‘stewardship, kapala urusan, house/business management, manage household affairs’ and /oikos/ ‘house’; so “receive me into their house” could be taken as “accept me to work for them”. Remember he's looking for a means of livlihood in the context of the story. See LN on the first word. Broader phrasing like the Kupang is better.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tagal itu, dia mulai pange ame samua orang yang ada utang sang dia pung bos. Dia tanya orang nomer satu bilang, &lt;We! Lu ada utang barapa sang beta pung bos?&gt;<bt>Because of that, he began to call all the people who were endebted to his boss. He asked person number one saying, ‘We! [+get attention] How much do you owe my boss?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;Beta ada utang minya saitun 4.000 liter.&gt;<bt>That person answered saying, “I have a debt of 4000 liters of olive oil.’</bt><note reference="16:6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang &lt;100 <span class="Italic">batos</span>&gt;. Satu batos, andia 35-40 liter.<bt>The Yunani language writing says &lt;100 <span class="Italic">batos</span>&gt;. One batos is 35-40 liters.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju itu kapala urusan bilang, &lt;Batúl. Ini lu pung surat utang. Sakarang robe buang su, ais dudu ko capát-capát tulis surat utang baru bilang, lu ada utang 2.000 liter sa.&gt;<bt>So that manager said, ‘True. This is your debt letter. Now tear it up throw it away, then sit down and quickly write a new debt letter, saying you only owe 2000 liters.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais dia pi tanya orang nomer dua bilang, &lt;Ko lu lai ada utang barapa?&gt;<bt>Then he went and asked person number two saying, ‘So how much do you owe?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;Beta utang 1.000 karong padi.&gt;<bt>He answered saying, ‘I owe 1000 sacks of padi.’ [EXEG: Note that TB ‘100 pikul gandum’ is off by a factor of ten.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TB is off here."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">TB is off here.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang &lt;100 <span class="Italic">koros</span>&gt;. Satu koros, andia 390 liter.<bt>The Yunani language writing says &lt;100 <span class="Italic">koros</span>&gt;. One koros, is 390 liters.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu kapala urusan kasi tau bilang, &lt;Robe buang lu pung surat utang lama tu, abis tulis yang baru bilang, 800 karong sa.&gt;<bt>That manager told him saying, ‘Rip up and throw away that debt letter of yous, then write a new one, saying just 800 sacks.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dia bekin bagitu, sampe dia pung bos dapa tau dia pung akal. Ma itu bos musti mangaku bilang, itu kapala urusan yang jahat tu, memang lihai.<bt>He did like that, until his boss found out about his idea/plan. But that boss had to acknowledge that, that manager who was evil, was certainly astute.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Beta kasi tau ini umpama ko bosong mangarti bilang, kalo banding deng orang parcaya, orang yang sonde parcaya memang lebe lihai idop di rakyat sakarang pung teng-tenga.<bt>So! I tell this comparison.story so that you-pl understand that, if compared with believers, people who don't believe certainly are more astute living in the midst of the current.day populace. [NOTE: reworked modelling on NLT, because 1) KM /orang dunya/ would translate literally into many vernaculars with their term for 'human', but here it should be 'people who don't believe'; and 2) /su pintar cari jalan ko bekin ontong dia pung diri sandiri./ misread by Belu team as "clever obtaining profit", rather than "clever finding ways to advantage themselves".]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@Orang parcaya ju musti cari jalan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@Orang parcaya ju musti cari jalan ko maso pi di Tuhan Allah pung @@kerajaan. Naa! Beta kasi tau ini umpama ko bosong mangarti, bilang, orang dunya sa su pintar cari jalan ko bekin ontong dia pung diri sandiri. Orang parcaya yang idop di taráng sonde lihai di ini dunya bagitu.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikia: unrighteousness, unjust"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">adikia: unrighteousness, unjust</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Jadi bosong pikir coba. Biar orang dunya maen kotor pake dong pung harta, ma lebe bae bosong pake harta dunya ko tolong orang. Deng bagitu, bosong ju dapa tamán bam-banya. Biar itu harta abis, ma nanti Tuhan sadia tampa kasi bosong di sorga.<bt>So (consequently) have a think about it. Regardless of the fact that people of the world play dirty using their possessions, but it's better you-pl use the world's possession to help people. In that way, you will obtain many friends. Even if those possessions get used.up/finished, but the Lord will prepare a place for you in heaven. [See NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mamoona adikias: money may be associated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">mamoona adikias: money may be associated with or gained by unjust means (UBS). Used in the Targums and the Talmud.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Kalo orang jujur deng hal kici dong, tantu dia ju jujur deng hal bésar. Ma kalo orang pakane'o deng hal kici dong, tantu dia ju pakane'o deng hal bésar.<bt>If a person is honest with small matters, surely he will also be honest with big matters. But if a person is crooked with small matters, surely he will also be crooked with big matters.</bt><v n="11" />Kalo orang sonde bisa parcaya sang bosong ko urus harta biasa deng hal-hal kici di ini dunya, karmana ko Tuhan bisa parcaya sang bosong deng hal-hal bésar?<bt>If people cannot trust you-pl to take care of/manage normal possessions and small matters in this world, how can the Lord trust you with big/important matters? [EXEG: NLT. Marshall points out that “mammon” here must mean ‘worldly wealth’ (a la NLT) rather than ‘wealth dishonestly acquired or used’ (a la NRSV and CEV). And that it is something entrusted, rather than owned.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistoi: trustworthy, faithful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">pistoi: trustworthy, faithful</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Kalo bosong sonde bisa urus orang laen pung harta, na, sapa yang barani mau kasi harta sang bosong?<bt>If you-pl cannot take.care of other people's possessions, na, who will dare give possessions to you?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Satu tukang suru-suru sonde bisa dengar dua tuan. Te nanti dia binci satu, deng sayang satu. Ko, dia satia deng satu, ma sonde toe deng satu. Bagitu ju deng bosong, te orang sonde bisa sayang Tuhan Allah sama-sama deng doi.&gt;&gt;<bt>One low.rank.worker cannot hear/obey two masters. Cuz he will hate one, and love one. Or, he will be faithful to one, but not care about the other. It's also like that with you-pl, cuz people cannot love the Lord God together with money. [EXEG: why sayang ‘love’? because ‘serve’ doesn't collocate with money; neither do several other candidates that were considered.] [NOTE to daughter translations: consider making last clause “sama-sama deng sayang doi”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tweaked last sentence to make more"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***tweaked last sentence to make more general</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oiketeis: household servant, personal servant (not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">oiketeis: household servant, personal servant (not doulos here)</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 6:24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong so'al doi, so'al Tuhan pung Kabar Bae, deng so'al kawin-cere<bt>The Lord Yesus talks about money, about the Lord's Good News, and about marriage-divorce</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***expanded title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***expanded title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 11:12-13, 5:31-32; Markus 10:11-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu waktu, ada barapa orang Farisi yang iko dengar Yesus pung omong tadi tu. Ju dong olok-olok sang Dia, tagal dong ada rakus doi.<bt>At that time, there were several Farisi people who were also participating in listening to that speaking of Yesus' earlier. Then they ridiculed Him, because they were greedy for money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rakus doi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">rakus doi</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Biar bosong bekin barisi diri di muka orang, ma Tuhan Allah kanál bosong pung hati tu, jahat. Ada banya hal yang manusia angka tinggi-tinggi, padahal Tuhan Allah anggap itu hal jahat, deng noju sang dong.<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Weh! [+attention, + rebuke] Even though you-pl make yourselves out to be holy in front of people, but the Lord God knows that those livers of yours are evil. There are many things with humans regard highly, while the Lord God considers those things evil, and is appalled/disgusted by them. [NOTE to daughter translations: The Gk has a parallel proverb-type of structure in the last sentence, "for what is prized by human beings is an abomination in the sight of God." KM can't do that easily because of the problems with mesolectal speakers not knowing /noju/. If possible, mirror the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***NOTE added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***NOTE added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Sampe deng Yohanis tukang sarani pung datang, kotong orang Yahudi idop iko ba'i Musa deng Tuhan pung jubir dong pung atoran. Ma sakarang Tuhan pung Kabar Bae su tasiar pi mana-mana. Banya orang ada usaha karás ko biar dong idop iko Tuhan pung mau-mau.<bt>Until Yohanis the Habitual Baptiser coming, we-inc Yahudi people lived according to Gf/Ff Musa and the Lord's spokespersons' regulations. But now the Lord's Good News has spread everywhere. Many people are trying hard so that they can live following God2's will2 (=the things of God). [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: “Beginning from forefather Musa and the spokespersons' getting God's regulations, until the time of Yohanis the Baptiser coming, we-inc Yahudi people lived according to those regulations.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="consider more natural; kotong o.Y idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">consider more natural; kotong o.Y idop iko atoran yang turun dari Ba'i Musa deng Tuhan pung jubir dong. *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 11:12-13</note><v n="17" />Biar langit deng bumi ilang, ma Tuhan Allah pung atoran sadiki ju sonde akan ilang. Satu titi-koma ju sonde ilang!<bt>Even if the sky and earth disappear, nevertheless the Lord God's regulations even a little bit won't disappear. Not even a full.stop-comma will disappear!</bt><note reference="16:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Orang yang cere buang dia pung bini, ais kawin lai deng parampuan laen, dia barsina. Ais orang yang kawin deng bini buang, dia ju barsina.&gt;&gt;<bt>A person who divorces his wife, then marrys again with another woman, he is adulterous. And then the person who marries that thrown away wife, he also is adulterous.” [NOTE to daughter translations: (alternate) /Abis laki-laki yang kawin deng parampuan yang dia pung laki su cere buang,/]</bt><note reference="16:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:32, 1 Korintus 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Carita orang kaya deng Lasarus<bt>Story of the rich person and Lasarus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Yesus carita tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang kaya. Dia suka pake pakean bagus-bagus yang bekin dari kaen alus. Siang-malam dia makan-minum ena-ena, deng salalu foya-foya.<bt>Yesus story-ed further saying, “There was a rich person. He liked to use fancy clothes that were made out of fine cloth. Day-night he ate-drank enjoyably, and was always extravagant.</bt><v n="20" />Di situ ju ada satu orang malarat. Dia pung nama Lasarus. Dia pung badan ponu deng luka puruk. Tiap hari dia pung tamán dong bawa sang dia ko taro di muka itu orang kaya pung pintu maso.<bt>There there was also an impoverished person. His name was Lasarus. His body was full of smelly wounds. Every day his friends brought him to place him in front of that rich person's outer gate.</bt><v n="21" />Dia kapingin dapa makan dari itu orang kaya pung makanan sisa dong, ma dia sonde dapa apa-apa. Cuma anjing dong datang ko lambe-lambe dia pung luka pung nanak.<bt>He desired to get food from that rich person's left over food, but he didn't get anything. Only the dogs came to like his wounds' pus. [EXEG: Marshall “unfulfilled wish”, TN “he did not get anything to satisfy his hunger”, which is also probable reading of NRSV, NLT, GW, and Green; CEV assumes it was fulfilled, without any support that I can see. Result of neglect was Lazarus died. Most thorough discussion in Marshall.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lambe = lick ; nanak ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">lambe = lick ; nanak = pus ; CEV misses it here</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais ju Lasarus mati. Ju Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga datang ame bawa sang dia, ko kasi dudu di ba'i Abraham pung sablá.<bt>And then Lasarus died. Then the Lord God's underlings from heaven came and took him, to sit him at grandfather Abraham's side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sonde lama te itu orang kaya ju mati, ais orang dong kubur sang dia.<bt>Not long and that rich person also died, and people buried him.</bt><v n="23" />Ma dia sonde maso sorga. Dia maso pi naraka, sama-sama deng banya orang mati. Di situ dia kaná siksa deng sangsara tarús. Ais satu kali, dia angka muka ju dapa lia Lasarus ada dudu sanáng-sanáng di ba'i Abraham pung sablá.<bt>But he didn't enter heaven. He entered hell, together with many dead people. There he was afflicted with torture and misery continually. Then one time, he lifted his head then he could see Lasarus sitting happily at grandfather Abraham's side. [EXEG &amp; NOTE to daughter translations: because of the TB “sitting in his lap” expect your teams to query KM “at his side”. See NRSV, NLT, CEV, Marshall, LN (1.16) for meaning of Gk idiom “in his bosom” = closely associated with, place of honour, at his side, next to”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ example of queries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ example of queries</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ju dia batarea bilang, &lt;Ba'i Abraham, é! Kasian ame sang beta dolo! Suru sang Lasarus calóp dia pung ujung jari pi dalam aer, ko datang bekin basa beta pung ujung lida sa ju bae. Te beta sangsara satenga mati di api naraka ni!&gt;<bt>Then he yelled out saying, ‘Gf/Ff Abraham! Have pity on me! Tell Lasarus to dip the tip of his finger in water, in order to come wet even just the edge of my tongue would be good. Cuz (elaboration) I am very miserable in hell fire here!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma Abraham manyao bilang, &lt;Naa! Ana, é! Inga bae-bae dolo. Tempo hari, waktu lu masi idop di dunya, lu dapa samua yang bae. Ma Lasarus cuma dapa susa sa. Jadi sakarang Tuhan hibur sang dia di sini, ma lu sangsara.<bt>But Abraham replied saying, ‘Well! Child! Think carefully. Earlier when you still lived on earth, you had everything that was good. But Lasarus only had just suffering. So now the Lord comforts/consoles him here, but you suffer.</bt><v n="26" />Lebe-lebe lai, antara lu deng botong, Tuhan ada taro jurang lebar. Jadi orang dari sini sonde bisa pi situ, deng orang dari situ sonde bisa datang di sini.&gt;<bt>And even more, between you and us-exc, There is a ravine that is broad and high. So (consequently) people from here cannot go there, and people from there cannot come here.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jurang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">jurang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Tarús itu orang kaya minta bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, na, ba'i tolong suru Lasarus pi beta pung papa pung ruma dolo.<bt>Then that rich person requested saying, ‘If that's the case, na, grandfather please order Lasarus to go to my father's house.</bt><v n="28" />Te beta masi ada adi laki-laki lima orang di sana. Suru sang Lasarus pi kasi inga, ko dong kambali suda pi Tuhan. Biar dong mati, na, dong jang maso di ini tampa sangsara ni.&gt;<bt>Cuz I still have five male younger siblings there. Tell Lasarus to go remind them, so they return to the Lord. Even if they died, na, they wouldn't enter this horrible/miserable place here.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma Abraham manyao bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah su kasi sang dong ba'i Musa deng jubir dong pung tulisan. Lu pung adi dong bisa baca ulang-ulang, ko dong mangarti Tuhan pung mau.&gt;<bt>But Abraham replied saying, ‘The Lord God has given them grandfather Musa and the spokespersons' writings. Your younger siblings can read them over.and.over, so they understand the Lord's will.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ma itu orang kaya protes bilang, &lt;Ba'i Abraham, é! Itu balóm cukup. Dong sonde toe Tuhan pung Kata-kata! Musti ada orang mati kaluar dari kubur ko pi kasi tau sang dong, baru dong tobat, ais mau dengar.&gt;<bt>But that rich person protested saying, ‘Gf/Ff Abraham! That not enough. They don't pay attention to the Lord's Words. There must be a dead person coming out of the grave who goes to tell them, only then will they repent and want to listen/obey.’</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** yelled changed to protested (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** yelled changed to protested (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma Abraham manyao bilang, &lt;Kalo dong sonde mau dengar ba'i Musa deng Tuhan pung jubir dong pung kata-kata, biar orang mati kaluar dari kubur ko pi omong deng dong ju, dong sonde akan dengar.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But Abraham responded saying, ‘If they don't want to listen to/obey Gf Musa and God2's spokespeople's words/sayings, even if the dead people were to come out from the graves to go speak to them, (nevertheless) they would not listen.’”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al orang yang jato sala, deng yang minta ampon<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about people who fall into sin, and those who request forgiveness</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:6-7, 21-22; Markus 9:42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="17" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Banya kali ada orang yang jato sala, tagal orang laen pung gara-gara. Ma orang yang bekin gara-gara tu, yang paling calaka.<bt>Yesus told His underlings saying, “Many time there are people who fall into sin, because of other people's reasons/basis/excuses. But the person who makes those reasons/basis/excuses, is the one who is most misfortune/in.trouble.</bt><v n="2" />Kalo orang bekin gara-gara sampe ada ana kici yang sonde parcaya sang Beta, Tuhan Allah nanti kasi hukum barát sang dia. Lebe ringan ika batu bésar satu di dia pung leher, ais angka buang sang dia pi dalam laut.<bt>If a person does s.t. that causes to the point that there is a small child who doesn't believe in Me, the Lord God will heavily punish him. It's lighter to tie a big stone on his neck, then pick him up and throw him into the sea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See Gilles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">See Gilles</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jadi jaga diri bae-bae ko bosong ju jang bekin orang jato sala! Ma kalo lu pung sodara bekin sala, na, togor sang dia. Kalo dia tobat, ais datang minta ampon, na, lupa buang dia pung sala.<bt>So (consequently), watch yourselves carefully so you-pl don't also make people fall into sin! But if your-sg sibling sins, na, scold/rebuke him. If he repents, then come and asks forgiveness, na, completely forget that sin of his.</bt><note reference="17:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kalo lu pung sodara bekin sala tuju kali dalam satu hari, tarús dia tobat, ais dia datang tuju kali ko minta ampon, na, lu musti lupa buang sang dia pung sala tuju kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>If your-sg sibling sins seven time in one day, then he repents, then he comes seven time to request forgiveness, na, you must completely forget his sin seven times.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang musti parcaya Tuhan Allah pung kuasa<bt>People must believe in the Lord God's power</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Satu hari, Yesus pung ana bua dong<bt>One day, Yesus' underlings</bt><note reference="17:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;utusan&gt;&gt;. Lukas suka tulis &lt;&lt;utusan&gt;&gt; kasi Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua 12 orang dong.<bt>The Yunani language writings here write, “*apostle”. Lukas likes to/often writes “apostle” for the Lord Yesus' 12 *disciples.</bt></note>datang mangada sang Dia ko minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong pung parcaya sonde kuat. Tolong bekin kuat tamba botong pung parcaya dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>came and met Him to request saying, “Father Teacher! Our-exc faith is not strong. Please help make our faith stronger.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong ada pung parcaya sang Tuhan Allah pung kuasa, biar sadiki ana sa, ma bosong bisa parenta ini pohon bésar bilang, &lt;Tacabu, ko pinda pi laut!&gt; Nanti itu pohon iko bosong pung parenta memang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “If you have faith in the Lord's power, even just a little bit, then you can order this big tree saying, “Get.uprooted and move to the sea!&gt; Later that tree will follow your command right away .” [EXEG: 1st sent. is faith in God's power; KM is awkward on 1st reading] [NOTE: to follow TN suggestion on process would be severely overtranslating this well known verse. TN seems to be the only source that reads it this way.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang karjá yang bae iko dia pung bos pung mau<bt>A worker who is good, follows his boss' will</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed title; changed hamba &gt; orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed title; changed hamba &gt; orang karjá</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ame conto. Ada budak yang pacol tana di kabón, ko, jaga domba di padang. Karjá abis ju, itu budak pulang pi ruma. Sonde mungkin dia pung tuan omong sang dia bilang, &lt;Mari ko kotong dua dudu makan sama-sama suda!&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;Take an example. There was/is a slave who hoes dirt/soil in the garden, or watches sheep in the field. After working, then that slave returns home. It's impossible his master will tell him saying, &lt;Come let's the two of us eat together!&gt;</bt><v n="8" />Sonde! Yang wajar tu, dia pung tuan parenta sang dia bilang, &lt;Pi ator meja kasi beta dolo. Ais, baru lu makan-minum di balakang.&gt;<bt>No! What is natural is for his master to order him saying, &lt;Go arrange the table for me. Afterwards, then you-sg eat-drink later.&gt;</bt><v n="9" />Kalo itu budak su bekin iko dia pung tuan pung mau, bosong kira itu tuan nanti minta tarima kasi sang dia, ko? Sonde!<bt>If that slave has done according to his master's will, do you-pl think that master will later say thank you to him, [+tag question]? No!</bt><v n="10" />Bosong ju bagitu. Kalo bosong su karjá abis samua yang Tuhan su parenta, na, bosong omong bilang, &lt;Botong cuma tukang suru-suru sa, yang sonde pantas tarima apa-apa. Botong sonde cari-cari puji. Botong cuma kasi jalan tugas sa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl are also like that. If/when you have finished doing everything God2 has commanded, na, you speak saying, &lt;We are only just low level workers, unworthy to receive anything. We do not seek praise. We only just carried out our duty/work.&gt;&gt;&gt; [EXEG: ‘unworthy’ undertranslated in earlier versions. July 2014.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae sapulu orang kusta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals ten leprosy people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu Yesus dong ada jalan pi Yerusalem, dong sampe di propinsi Galilea deng propinsi Samaria pung batas.<bt>When Yesus (collective) was walking/going to Yerusalem, they arrived at the boundary of Galilea province and Samaria province.</bt><v n="12" />Waktu dong mau maso pi satu kampong di situ, ada sapulu orang kusta datang ko mau katumu deng Yesus. Dong badiri dari jao.<bt>When they were about to enter into a village there, ten leprosy people came wanting to meet with Yesus. The stood far off.</bt><v n="13" />Ais dong batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Tuan! Kasian sang botong dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they yelled enthusiastically saying, “Yesus! Master! Have pity/mercy on us-exc!” [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk word for ‘master’ here is different from /kurios/ which we normally translate as ‘bos’. So /tuan/ is a way to reflect there is a difference.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ama Guru deleted before Yesus, May"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ama Guru deleted before Yesus, May 2005, Overtranslation.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu Yesus dapa lia sang dong, ju Dia suru bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi kasi tunju bosong pung badan di kapala agama dolo, ko biar dong pareksa bilang, bosong pung kusta tu su ilang, ko balóm.&gt;&gt; Dengar bagitu ju, dong pi. Ma di tenga jalan, takuju sa, dong samua bae memang.<bt>When Yesus saw them, then He ordered saying, “You-pl go show your bodies to the heads of religion first, so that they can examine whether that leprosy of yours have disappeared or not.yet.” Hearing like that, they went. But in the middle of the road/journey, suddenly, they were all healed immediately.</bt><note reference="17:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Dong jalan tarús sanáng-sanáng. Ma ada satu yang kambali pi Yesus. Dia batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Puji Tuhan! Te beta su bae!&gt;&gt;<bt>They travelled on happily. But there was one who returned to Yesus. He yelled saying, “Praise the Lord! Cuz I am well!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Added Te"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Added Te</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ju dia tikam lutut ko minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Yesus. (Tau-tau te dia tu, bukan orang Yahudi. Dia orang Samaria yang baparkara tarús deng orang Yahudi dong.)<bt>Then he knelt to say much thankyou to Yesus. ( As it turns out, that person wasn't even a Yahudi person. He was a Samaria person who continually have disputes with the Yahudi people.)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju Yesus tanya orang dong yang iko sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, é? Tadi Beta ada bekin bae sapulu orang, to? Yang sambilan dong di mana?<bt>Then Yesus asked the people who were following Him saying, “How is it? Earlier I healed ten people, right? Where are the nine? [DISCOURSE: note there are possible shifts of addressee between 17 and 18 and 19. Most (all?) AN lgs in eastern Indonesia do not (cannot) put a quote margin in for a continuation of same speaker.] [EXEG: Most translations and commentators are vague or do not address this. Marshall points out the obvious, that 19 is addressed to the just-healed leper. 18 is fairly clearly including His followers (from vs. 5). So the exegetical question focuses on 17. It could be read as addressed to a) the leper, or b) to include His followers. In the Gk. there is a quote margin in 17, and another in 19. This could suggest 17 + 18 = general RQ's for the benefit of His followers, followed by 19 = to the leper. But a number of people reading various translations in various lgs see 17 as addressed to the leper. Green appears to imply 17 is directed at (b) and adds “By keeping Jesus’ companions offstage, however, or at least in the background, Luke allows Jesus’ queries to be aimed more pointedly at Luke’s audience.” TH doesn't address the issue at all. TN recognises the problem but does not lobby for either (a) or (b), and says, in effect, because the issue is not clear, the safer solution is to be broad “Jesus asked those who were with Him”. A better solution which preserves the ambiguity of the Gk (in which both possible options are acceptable) if the language allows it is just a vague “Jesus asked”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus tanya sang dia, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ju Yesus tanya sang dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Adi, é!</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Akurang ko cuma ini orang asing sa yang datang kambali ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, deng angka puji sang Dia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Why is it that it is only just this foreign person who come to say thankyou to the Lord God, and lift up praises to Him?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Tarús Dia kasi tau itu orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu su jadi bae tagal lu parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta. Jadi bangun ko pulang deng salamat su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He told that person saying, “You-sg are healed because you truly believe in Me. So (consequently), get up and go.home in safety!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus carita so'al hari kiamat, deng Dia pung datang kambali<bt>The Lord Yesus story-s about the end.of.the.world, and His coming back</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:23-28, 37-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Satu hari, ada barapa orang Farisi yang datang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Coba kasi tau dolo! Kapan Tuhan Allah mulai kasi jalan Dia pung parenta?&gt;&gt;<bt>One day, there were several Farisi people who came asking Yesus saying, “Father Teacher! Please tell us! When will the Lord God begin to carry out His rule?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk ... meta parateereeseoos: not just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ouk ... meta parateereeseoos: not just a thing you go to gawk at, like a public spectacle. Predictable by signs, as with the Wise Men?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Jang sangka Tuhan kasi jalan Dia pung parenta deng tanda macam-macam di ini dunya yang orang bisa pareksa deng mata biji. Orang sonde dapa bukti ko bilang, &lt;Coba lia sini! Te Tuhan Allah ada kasi jalan Dia pung parenta di sini!&gt;, ko, &lt;Ada di sana!&gt; Sonde! Te Dia kasi jalan Dia pung parenta di bosong pung teng-tenga dalam orang dong pung hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, “It's like this! Don't assume the Lord will carry out His rule with all sorts of signs in this world which people can examine with their own eyes. People will not obtain the evidence to say, ‘Look here! Cuz the Lord God is carrying out His rule here!&gt;, or, ‘It's over there!&gt; No! Cuz He carries out His rule in the midst of you-pl in people livers.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ sonde ada dasar ko bilang..."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ sonde ada dasar ko bilang... Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;So'al Tuhan pung parenta tu, lu bisa pareksa alus-alus di Dia pung buku. Tuhan pung parenta tu sonde ada tanda-tanda yang orang bisa lia deng mata.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai te Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, su sonde sama-sama deng bosong lai. Nanti deng hari-hari susa dong, bosong rindu mau lia Beta pung datang kambali. Ma Beta balóm datang.<bt>Then Yesus told His underlings saying, “Not much longer (=soon) I, this Authentic Human, will not be together with you anymore. Later when its the days of difficulty, you will yearn to see My return. But I will not yet come. [EXEG: see extensive discussion in Marshall on 6 different interpretations of “the days of the Son of Man”. This rendering following HCE, &amp; Western Bukidnon Manobo BT.]</bt><v n="23" />Ais kalo orang dong datang kasi tau bilang, &lt;Kristus ada di sini!&gt; ko, &lt;Kristus ada di sana!&gt; na, bosong sonde usa barepot ko, bacari pi-datang, te dong pung omong tu, putar-balek.<bt>Then if people come telling saying, ‘Kristus is here!&gt; or, ‘Kristus is there!&gt; na, you don't need to worry or go hunt all around, cuz that speaking of this is twisted (=deceitful). [EXEG: Messiah, as in Marshall &amp; TN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added last clause from Belu UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added last clause from Belu UNS responses. Avoids interpretation of "he's really coming, but it's not necessary for you to go see him"</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te nanti kalo Manusia Tulen batúl-batúl datang kambali, dia pung tanda talalu jalás, sama ke kilat yang bacaya ko bekin langit jadi taráng dari ujung pi ujung.<bt>Cuz when the Authentic Human truly returns, the signs will be very clear, the same as lightening which shines to make the sky become clear from one end to the other.</bt><v n="25" />Ma Dia ju musti tanggong sangsara macam-macam dolo. Deng manusia generasi sakarang ni, sonde mau dengar deng mau tola buang sang Dia.<bt>But He also must bear all sorts of suffering first. And humans in this generasi, don't want to listen/obey and will reject him. [EXEG: vs.25-29, UNS's were not getting the parallels between when Jesus returns, Noah's time, and Lot's time. Restructured to make parallels with more obvious lexical ties. Problem: Luke assumes two things: 1) everyone knows the stories of Noah and Lot, and that the people were punished for their evil lifestyles, and 2) everyone knows these people were given fair warning and chose to ignore them, continuing on unchanged. UNS &amp; team pointed out that without making these explicit, it's hard to understand what the problem is to follow what's supposed to be parallel.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check generasi, not often used ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">check generasi, not often used ; *** 25-29 restructured Feb 2008</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma nanti, kalo Dia mau datang kambali, orang dong cuma idop jahat sama ke biasa sa, sama ke di Noh pung jaman.<bt>But later, when He comes back, people will be living evil as they normally do, the same as in Noh's age.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[Check: is it clear that they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">[Check: is it clear that they are ignoring the warnings of disaster?]</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 6:5-8</note><v n="27" />Itu waktu, dong ada makan-minum, bekin pesta kawin, sampe deng hari Noh maso pi dalam dia pung kapal. Ma itu orang dong ju sonde mau dengar. Ais takuju sa, banjer bésar datang ju bekin ancor sang dong samua.<bt>At that time they ate-drank, made wedding feasts, until the day Noh entered his boat. But those people also did not want to hear/obey. Then suddenly, the big flood came and destroyed all of them.</bt><note reference="17:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 7:6-24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Itu ju sama ke orang-orang yang idop jahat di Lot pung jaman. Itu waktu, dong makan-minum, badagang, karjá kabón, deng kasi bangun ruma, deng idop jahat sama ke biasa sa.<bt>That is also the same as people who lived evilly in Lot's age. At that time, they ate-drank, traded, made gardens, and build houses, living evil just like normal.</bt><v n="29" />Ma orang dong ju sonde mau dengar. Ais, itu pagi, waktu Lot lari kasi tenga kota Sodom, takuju sa, ujan api deng balerang jato datang dari langit ko bakar buang sang dong samua.<bt>But those people also did not want to hear/obey. Then, that (particular) morning [that we know about], when Lot ran leaving behind Sodom city, suddenly, fire rain and sulfer fell from the sky to burn them all up.</bt><note reference="17:28-29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:20--19:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Jadi bosong ati-ati, ó! Jang sampe nanti kalo Manusia Tulen mau datang kambali, orang dong ju cuma idop biasa-biasa sa. Ma takuju sa te Dia muncul datang.<bt>So (consequently) you all watch out! Lest when the Authentic Human comes back, people are living just like normal. But suddenly [+contrary to expectation] He will appear.</bt><v n="31" />Itu hari, orang yang ada di ruma pung teras, jang maso lai pi dalam ruma ko manyimpan. Orang yang ada karjá di kabón, jang pulang ruma lai ko ame barang.<bt>That day, people who are on a house's porch, shouldn't enter again inside the house to put.stuff.away. People who are working in the garden, shouldn't go.home again to get stuff.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teras"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">teras</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:17-18, Markus 13:15-16</note><v n="32" />Inga apa yang su jadi deng Lot pung bini dolu. Dia mati, tagal dia inga dia pung barang di ruma.<bt>Remember what happened with Lot's wife long ago. She died, because she remember her stuff at home.</bt><note reference="17:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 19:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Orang yang sonde mau iko sang Beta tagal sayang dia pung diri, nanti dia pung idop parcuma sa. Ma orang yang mau iko sang Beta sampe sarakan dia pung idop tagal sayang sang Beta, nanti dia dapa salamat, deng idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>The person who does not want to follow Me because he loves his own self, later his life will just be useless/ineffectual. But the person who follows Me to.the.point.of handing over his life because he loves Me, he will obtain salvation, and live continually with the Lord God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***reworked for parallel structure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***reworked for parallel structure</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, 16:25, Markus 8:35, Lukas 9:24, Yohanis 12:25</note><v n="34" />Beta kasi tau memang! Waktu Manusia Tulen datang kambali, kalo ada dua orang tidor di satu tampa tidor, takuju Tuhan angka nae yang satu, deng kasi tenga yang satu.<bt>I'm telling = mark my words! When the Authentic Human comes back, if there are two people sleeping in one bed, suddenly the Lord will pick up one, and leave the other. [DISCOURSE: 34-36, In contrast to the other synoptics, Luke's phrasing is a confident “there will be two...” Nevertheless we take these as an open series of “for instances”, rather than “in every case where there are two people doing routine activity x, one will be taken...” Green says Jesus uses them “for illustrative purposes”. TN says “this kind of thing will happen all over the world when he returns”.]</bt><v n="35" />Kalo ada dua parampuan mol padi sama-sama, nanti Tuhan angka nae yang satu, ma kasi tenga yang laen.<bt>If there are two women milling padi together, the Lord will pick up one, but leave the other. [NOTE to daughter translations: in some cultures in the regions, milling/grinding grain is not known or is the work of men; pounding grain is the work of women. If necessary say /tumbu padi/. See also LN, which suggests the same solution.]</bt><v n="36" />[Kalo ada dua orang karjá sama-sama di kabón, nanti Tuhan angka nae yang satu, deng kasi tenga yang laen.]&gt;&gt;<bt>[If there are two people working together in the garden, the Lord will lift up one, and leave the other.]&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="final connector in last 3 verses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">final connector in last 3 verses alternates ma and deng</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:36" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ayat 36 sonde ada dalam tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae dong.<bt>Verse 36 is not in the best Yunani writings.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus pung ana bua dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Nanti itu samua jadi di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus' underlings asked Him saying, “Father Teacher! Where will all that happen?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus buang bahasa bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo bosong lia burung tukang makan bangke dong tarbáng bakumpul pi mana, bosong su tau itu jadi tanda bilang, pasti dong ada makan bangke di itu tampa.&gt;&gt; [Deng maksud tasambunyi, nanti kalo Kristus datang kambali, dia pung tanda dong talalu jalás, kalo orang tau baca.]<bt>Then Yesus threw out language (=spoke figuratively) saying, “It's like this. Whereever you-pl see the birds who habitually eat corpses flying gathering, you know that is a sign that surely they are eating corpse/s at that place.” [With a hidden meaning, later when Kristus comes back, the signs will be very clear, if people know how to read them.] [EXEG: Pattern from Mrk 7:27-28; explication following Marshall, NLT and TN.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Proverb in quote may be able to be more succinct in some lgs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added NOTE explication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added NOTE explication</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Carita so'al janda satu, deng hakim yang sonde bae<bt>Story about a widow, and a judge who is not good</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***expanded title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***expanded title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="18" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, Yesus ajar Dia pung ana bua dong pake umpama, ko dong sambayang sonde putus-putus, deng sonde ilang samangat. Dong musti parcaya tarús sang Tuhan.<bt>One time, Yesus taught His underlings using a comparison.story, so they would pray unendingly, and not lose enthusiasm. They must continually believe in the Lord. [literal + explication]</bt><v n="2" />Dia pung carita bagini: &lt;&lt;Di satu kota ada satu hakim yang sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah. Dia sonde nodek sang sapa-sapa ju.<bt>The story is like this: “In one city there was a judge who didn't care about the Lord God. He didn't even pay.attention.to/care.about anyone.</bt><v n="3" />Di situ ju ada satu mama janda yang maen datang di itu hakim ko minta bilang, &lt;Bapa hakim! Putus dolo beta pung parkara deng batúl, ó!&gt;<bt>There there was also a mama widow who kept coming to that judge to request saying, “Father judge! Decide my case correctly!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Mula-mula itu hakim sonde paduli deng itu janda. Ma lama-lama dia bosan dengar sang dia. Ais dia dudu pikir bilang, &lt;Memang beta ni sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah, lebe-lebe deng manusia.<bt>Initially that judge didn't pay any attention to that widow. But eventually he got fed.up hearing her. So he sat and thought saying, ‘It's very true that I don't care about the Lord God, and even less about humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bosan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">bosan</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma ini janda su bekin pusing sang beta. Tagal itu, lebe bae beta putus dia pung parkara deng fer dolo. Kalo sonde, nanti dia maen datang bekin cape sang beta tarús.&gt;<bt>But this widow has made me worried/frustrated. Because of that, it's better that I fairly decide her case. If not, she will keep coming and continually make me worn.out.”&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Naa, bosong pikir coba itu hakim jahat pung omong tu.<bt>Naa [+shift], you-pl think about the words of that evil judge. [DISCOURSE: Gk has “And the Lord /kurios/ said”; but AN lgs in eastern Indonesia do not (cannot) have quote margin in continuation of same speaker talking, so it's removed here. Naa, indicates shift.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikias: unrighteousness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">adikias: unrighteousness</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Kalo lama-lama dia su tolong itu janda, tantu Tuhan Allah ju mau tolong Dia pung orang yang sambayang siang-malam ko minta tolong sang Dia. Ma Tuhan sonde tunda-tunda.<bt>If eventually he helped that widow, surely the Lord God also want to help His people who pray day-night requesting help from Him. But the Lord doesn't delay. [EXEG: /chosen/ explicit &gt; implicit in /his people/; would skew the focus to force it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***wait changed to delay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***wait changed to delay</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te Dia urus dong pung parkara deng capát. Naa, Beta mau tanya bagini: kalo Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, su datang kambali, kira-kira Beta masi bisa katumu deng orang parcaya di bumi, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz He takes.care of their cases quickly. Naa, I want to ask like this: when I, the Authentic Human here, return again, do you think I will still be able to meet believers on the earth, or not?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi satu deng tukang tagi bea satu pi sambayang<bt>A Farisi person and a tax collector go pray</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Yesus carita tamba satu umpama so'al orang yang pung parcaya diri tinggi, deng suka pandang enteng orang laen. Dia carita bilang,<bt>Yesus told another comparison.story, about people who believe/confidence in themselves is high, and they like to look disparagingly at other people. He story-ed saying,</bt><v n="10" />&lt;&lt;Ada dua bapa pi sambayang di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Yang satu, orang dari partei agama Farisi; yang satu lai, tukang tagi bea. [Orang Yahudi dong anggap orang Farisi dong, orang suci. Ma dong anggap tukang tagi bea dong, orang sonde bae.]<bt>“There were two fathers/men who went to pray at the *Temple. One was a person from the Farisi religious party; the other one a tax collector. [The Yahudi people consider the Farisi people, holy people. But they consider tax collectors, not good people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[ ] are called kurung kurawal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">[ ] are called kurung kurawal in BI</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Sampe di ruma sambayang ju, itu orang Farisi badiri sandiri ko sambayang bilang, &lt;Tarima kasi Tuhan, te beta ni, orang bae. Beta sonde jahat ke orang laen dong. Beta sonde jadi pancuri. Beta sonde parakus. Beta sonde maen serong. Tarima kasi, Tuhan, te beta ju sonde jahat ke ini tukang tagi bea ni.<bt>Arriving at the worship house, that Farisi person stood off by himself to pray saying, ‘Thank you Lord, cuz I here am a good person. I am not evil like other people. I have not become a robber. I am not greedy. I am not adulterous. Thankyou Lord, cuz I also am not evil like this tax collector here. [NOTE: Sentence broken up to emphasize self-praise.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikoi: unrighteous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">adikoi: unrighteous</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta lebe bae dari orang parakus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Beta lebe bae dari orang parakus deng orang putar-balek dong. Beta sonde selingku sama ke orang laen. Tarima kasi, Tuhan, te beta ju masi lebe bae dari ini tukang tagi bea ni.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta rajin puasa satu minggu dua kali. Deng beta salalu kasi perpuluhan dari samua yang beta dapa.&gt; Itu orang Farisi sambayang bagitu.<bt>I diligently fast two times a week. And I always give a tenth from everything I obtain.’ That Farisi person prayed like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perpuluhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">perpuluhan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma itu tukang tagi bea badiri jao-jao di balakang. Dia sonde barani angka muka ko lia pi langit. Dia cuma sambayang tondo kapala deng hati ancor bilang, &lt;Ee! Tuhan Allah. Kasian sang beta, manusia bardosa ni! Kasi ampon sang beta!&gt;<bt>But that tax collector stood far in the back. He did not dare lift his face to look at the sky. He only prayed bowing his head with his liver crushed (=broken.hearted) saying, ‘Ee! Lord God. Have pity on me, this sinful human! Forgive me!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Naa, waktu itu dua orang pulang pi dong pung ruma, kira-kira sapa yang babae deng Tuhan Allah? Itu orang Farisi yang sombong, ko, itu orang tagi bea? Pasti Dia tarima bae itu tukang tagi bea yang randá hati. Ma Dia sonde toe sang itu orang Farisi. Te Tuhan Allah kasi jato orang sombong, ma Dia angka nae orang yang randá hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to implications], when those two people returned home, which one (do you think) was in a good.relationship with the Lord God? That proud Farisi person, or that tax collector? Surely He accepted that tax collector who was low-livered (=humble). But He didn't care about that Farisi person. Cuz the Lord God causes proud people to fall (morally, socially), but He lifts up people who are *humble (lit: low-livered).”</bt><note reference="18:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:12, Lukas 14:11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong kasi berkat sang ana-ana<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks giving blessing to the children</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:13-15; Markus 10:13-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Satu kali, orang dong ada koko bawa dong pung ana mea pi Yesus, ko biar Dia taro tangan deng omong kasi berkat sang dong. Lia bagitu, ju Yesus pung ana bua dong togor sang itu orang dong.<bt>One time, people were carrying bringing their newborns to Yesus, so that He would put his hands and speak giving blessing to them. Seeing like that, Yesus' underlings scolded those people. [EXEG: NRSV, LN, Marshall; NOTE to daughter translations: the Gk word here is “infant” in vs.15; because this is different from the Matthew and Mark versions, don't be surprised if your team queries this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ example of queries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ example of queries</Message></Annotation><v n="16-17" />Ma Yesus sambut ame itu ana-ana dong datang sang Dia. Ais Dia togor Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi tenga ko itu ana kici dong datang sang Beta. Bosong jang palang sang dong. Inga bae-bae! Te orang yang mau jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang, dia musti bagantong sang Tuhan Allah, sama ke ana kici bagantong sang dong pung mama deng papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus invited those children to come to Him. Then He scolded his underlings saying, “Allow those small children to come to Me. Don't you-pl block them. Remember well! Cuz the person who wants to become the Lord God's person, he must depend/hang on the Lord God, just like small children depend on the mama and papa.” [DISCOURSE: order following RL norms.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palang vb"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">palang vb</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang kaya yang kapingin maso sorga<bt>Rich person who desires to enter heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:16-30; Markus 10:17-31)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Satu kali, ada orang Yahudi pung orang bésar satu datang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru yang terhormat! Beta musti bekin karmana ko biar beta tau parsís bilang, beta bisa maso sorga ko idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah?&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, there was an important person of the Yahudi people who asked Yesus saying, “Father Teacher who is most.respected! What must I do so that I know for sure that I can enter heaven to live continually with the Lord God?” [EXEG: Gk ‘ruler, important person’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** fixed ‘priest’ to ‘leader/ruler’"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** fixed ‘priest’ to ‘leader/ruler’</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satu kali, ada satu kapala agama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Satu kali, ada satu kapala agama Yahudi datang tanya sang Yesus,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu sapa sang Beta bilang, &lt;yang terhormat&gt;? Cuma satu sa yang terhormat, andia Tuhan Allah sa.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “Why do you-sg address Me saying &lt;who is most.respected&gt;? There is only just one who is most.respected, that the Lord God alone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapa - is that mesolectal; whould"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">sapa - is that mesolectal; whould subu be better?</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Naa! Lu su tau, to, Tuhan Allah pung atoran dari dolu bilang:<bt>So! You know, right?, the Lord God's regulations from long ago, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang barsina;<bt>Don't commit adultery;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang bunu orang;<bt>don't murder people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang pancuri;<bt>don't steal;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang jadi saksi putar-balek;<bt>don't be a twisted (=deceitful) witness;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kasi hormat sang lu pung mama deng papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>and give respect to you-sg papa and mama.”</bt><note reference="18:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:12-16, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:16-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, Bapa! Beta su iko itu atoran dong mulai dari beta masi kici.&gt;&gt;<bt>That person answered saying, “True, Father! I have followed those regulations beginning from when I was still small.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae! Ma lu masi kurang satu hal. Andia, sakarang lu pulang ko jual lu pung harta samua. Ais itu, pi bagi-bagi itu doi kasi orang malarat dong. Ais itu, baru lu datang kambali ko iko sang Beta. Te nanti Tuhan Allah balas kasi lu harta di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus said, “Good! But you-sg are still lacking one thing. Which is, now you go.home and sell all your possessions. After that, go divide out the money to the destitute people. After that, only then you come back to follow Me. Cuz the Lord God will reciprocate giving you possessions in heaven.”</bt><v n="23" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang pung hati susa, te dia kaya mau mati.<bt>Hearing like that, then that person's liver was distressed, cuz he was very rich.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Lia dia pi deng hati ancor, ju Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang kaya memang paling susa maso sorga.<bt>Seeing him go with a destroyed liver (=broken.hearted), Yesus told His underlings saying, “It's truly difficulty for rich people to enter heaven. [EXEG: following NLT and TN.]</bt><v n="25" />Kotong banding deng hal laen. Memang sonde mungkin binatang onta yang bésar bisa maso pi dia pung kandang lewat lobang jarom. Bagitu ju orang yang cuma harap dia pung harta, ma sonde harap sang Tuhan, sonde mungkin dia bisa maso sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc can compare it with a different thing. Truly it's impossible for a camel animal which is big to enter his pen through the hole of a needle. It's like that also for the person who only hopes in his possessions, but doesn't hope in the Lord, it's not possible he can enter heaven.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Orang yang dengar Yesus omong bagitu dong, tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo memang susa kasi orang kaya bagitu, na, orang macam karmana bisa dapa salamat?&gt;&gt;<bt>The people who heard Yesus speaking like that, asked Him saying, “If it's truly difficult for rich people like that, then what kind (categories) of people can be saved?” [NOTE: CEV focuses on how, whereas Gk focuses on who.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV focuses on how, whereas Gk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">CEV focuses on how, whereas Gk focuses on who</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang-orang yang dengar Yesus omong bagitu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Orang-orang yang dengar Yesus omong bagitu, tanya sang Dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo memang susa kasi orang kaya bagitu, na karmana orang bisa dapa salamat?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Buat manusia, memang banya hal sonde mungkin. Ma buat Tuhan Allah samua bisa jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “For humans, it's true many things are not possible. But for the Lord God everything can happen.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ju Petrus sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Botong su jalan kasi tenga botong pung harta samua, ko iko sang Papa. Ma botong nanti dapa apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus connected.his.speach saying, “Papa! We-exc have gone leaving behind all our possessions to follow Papa. But what will we get?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u! Dengar bae-bae! Orang yang kasi tenga dia pung ruma, dia pung bini, dia pung adi-kaka, dia pung orang tua, ko, dia pung ana-ana, tagal dia kasi jalan tugas dari Tuhan Allah,<bt>Yesus replied saying, “Pe'u (nickname)! Listen carefully! The person who leaves behind his house, his wife, his elder.younger siblings, his parents, or his children, because he carries out work/tasks from the Lord God,</bt><v n="30" />pasti dia tarima kambali lebe banya di ini dunya. Ais kalo ini dunya su kiamat, dia ju dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>surely he will receive back more in this world. Then when this world ends, he will also get to live continually with the Lord God.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ added close quotes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">@@ added close quotes</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Su tiga kali Tuhan Yesus omong Dia pung mati<bt>For the third time the Lord Yesus talks about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:17-19; Markus 10:32-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Yesus bawa Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang ko pi omong sandiri deng dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong samua su tau bilang, sakarang kotong ada jalan pi kota Yerusalem. Sampe di sana, samua hal yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis dolu so'al Manusia Tulen tu, nanti jadi parsís ke apa yang dong su tulis.<bt>Yesus brought His twelve underlings to go speak alone with them saying, “You all know that, now we-inc are travelling to Yerusalem city. Arriving there, everything which the Lord's spokesperson wrote about that Authentic Human, will happen exactly like what they wrote.</bt><v n="32" />Nanti dong sarakan sang Beta pi orang asing dong yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Ais dong olok-olok sang Beta, bekin hina macam-macam sang Beta, buang luda sang Beta,<bt>They will hand Me over to foreigners who don't believe in the Lord God. Then they will mock Me, do all sorts of offensive things to Me, spit at Me,</bt><v n="33" />firuk sang Beta, abis bunu bekin mati sang Beta. Ma dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>whip Me, then murder kill Me. But on the day.after.the.tomorrow, I will live again.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, Dia pung ana bua dong bingung, tagal dong balóm bisa tangkap itu kata-kata pung arti.<bt>Hearing Yesus' speaking like that, His underlings were confused, because they could not yet grasp the meaning of those words.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang buta satu<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a blind person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:29-34; Markus 10:46-52)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Waktu Yesus dong su mau maso pi kota Yeriko, ada satu orang buta yang ada dudu minta-minta di jalan pung pinggir.<bt>When Yesus (collective) were about to enter into Yeriko city, there was a blind person who sitting begging on the side of the road. [NOTE to daughter translations: earlier version had “met/encounter” which to some UNS's set up clash with direct meeting with Jesus not happening until vs.40. So this change to “there was a” is both tighter to the Gk and avoids the mixed signals.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Waktu dia dengar orang banya dong lewat di situ ju, dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Ada apa ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard many people passing.by there, he asked saying, “We! [+get attention] What's happening here?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ju orang kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus, dari Nasaret, ada lewat di sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then people told him saying, “Yesus, from Nasaret, is passing by here.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang buta batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Raja Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian ame sang beta dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then that blind person yelled.out loudly saying, “Yesus! Raja Daud's descendant! Have pity on me!”</bt><note reference="18:38" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada pung banya pangkat yang tunju sang Mesias, ko, Kristus. Conto ke: Manusia Tulen, Tuhan Allah pung Ana, deng laen-laen. &lt;Raja Daud pung turunan&gt; ju satu pangkat kasi &lt;Kristus&gt;. Deng bagitu, ini orang buta mangaku bilang, Yesus tu, Kristus.<bt>There are many ranks/title which point to/designate Mesias or Kristus. For example: the Ideal/Prototype Human, Child of God, etc. &lt;Raja Daud's descendant&gt;, is one rank/title for &lt;Kristus&gt;. In that.way, this blind person acknowledged that Yesus there, was Kristus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Orang yang jalan di muka Yesus togor sang dia ko suru diam. Ma dia ba'eki-eki tamba kuat lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Raja Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian sang beta dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>People who were walking in front of Yesus scolded him to be quiet. But he yelled out even louder saying, “Raja Daud's descendant! Have pity on me!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Waktu Yesus dengar bagitu, ju Dia badiri. Ais Dia suru orang pi hela bawa itu orang buta. Sampe di Dia pung muka ju, Yesus tanya sang dia bilang,<bt>When Yesus heard that, He stood (=stopped walking). Then he ordered people to go pull bring that blind person. Arriving in front of Him, thenYesus asked him saying,</bt><v n="41" />&lt;&lt;Lu mau Beta bekin apa kasi sang lu?&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;What do you-sg want Me to do for you?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Beta minta ko beta bisa dapa lia.&gt;&gt;<bt>He replied saying, “Father! I'm requesting to be able to see.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Yesus manyao sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae. Tagal lu parcaya bilang, Beta bisa bekin bae sang lu, jadi sakarang lu su bisa dapa lia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied to him saying, “Ok. Because you believe that I can heal you, now you can see.”</bt><v n="43" />Takuju sa, itu orang pung mata buta su bae memang. Ju dia iko sang Yesus deng puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah. Samua orang yang lia bagitu, ju angka nae puji sang Tuhan.<bt>Suddenly, that person's blind eye/s were healed right away. Then he followed Yesus and praised the Lord God. Everyone who saw like that, then lifted up praises to the Lord.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus katumu satu tukang tagi bea, nama Sakeos<bt>The Lord Yesus meets a tax collector, named Sakeos</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***title expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***title expanded</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="19" />
      <v n="1" />Ais Yesus dong maso iko kota Yeriko, ko dong mau jalan tarús.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) entered into Yeriko city, so they could continue travelling.</bt><v n="2" />Di situ ada satu kapala tukang tagi bea kasi pamarenta Roma. Dia pung nama Sakeos, deng dia orang kaya.<bt>There there was a head tax collector for the Roma government. His name was Sakeos, and he was a rich person.</bt><v n="3" />Waktu dia dengar Yesus ada mau lewat, ju dia kapingin lia sang Yesus. Ma dia sonde bisa dapa lia deng bae, tagal orang talalu banya makarubu sang Yesus, deng dia pung badan talalu pende.<bt>When he heard Yesus was about to passby, then he desired to see Yesus. But he was not able to see [him] well, because too many people were crowding around Yesus, and his body was too short.</bt><v n="4" />Andia ko dia lari-lari lebe dolo, ais nae pi atas satu pohon di jalan pung pinggir, yang Yesus mau lewat.<bt>That's why he ran on ahead, then climbed up into a tree on the side of the road which Yesus wanted to pass.by.</bt><note reference="19:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang ini pohon <span class="Italic">sukomorea</span>. Jenis pohon itu sonde ada di Indonesia sablá timur.<bt>The Yunani language writing says this tree is <span class="Italic">sukomorea</span>. This type of tree does not exist in eastern Indonesia.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Sampe di bawa itu pohon, ju Yesus lia pi atas. Ais Dia pange sang Sakeos bilang, &lt;&lt;Sakeos! Mari, turun su! Capát, te ini hari beta mau manumpang di lu pung ruma.&gt;&gt;<bt>Arriving at the bottom of that tree, Yesus looked up. Then He called Sakeos saying, “Sakeos! Come, get down! Quickly, cuz today I want to stay.over.night at your house.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sakeos taheran-heran. Ju dia turun capát-capát, ais bawa sang Yesus pi dia pung ruma. Dia pung hati sanáng mau mati.<bt>Sakeos was surprised. Then he came down quickly, and brought Yesus to his hoouse. His liver was very happy.</bt><v n="7" />Ma ada banya orang mangomek bilang, &lt;&lt;Cue! Sakeos ni, orang tar bae! Akurang ko Yesus maso pi manumpang di dia pung ruma?! Samua orang su tau na!&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were many people who grumbled saying, “Huh! This Sakeos here, isn't a good person! Why is Yesus entering to go stay at his house?! Everyone knows that [+obviously]!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sampe di ruma ju, Sakeos badiri di Yesus pung muka, ais omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Mulai ini hari beta bagi dua beta pung harta samua, ko kasi satu bagian pi orang malarat dong. Kalo beta parná tagi pajak lebe-lebe, beta bayar kambali sang dong ampa kali lipat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Arriving at the house, Sakeos stood in front of Yesus, and spoke saying, “Father Teacher! Starting from today I will divide all my possessions in two, to give one part to the poor people. If I ever collected excessive tax, I will pay it back to them four times over.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae. Ini hari Tuhan Allah su kasi salamat sang lu deng lu pung kelu samua, tagal lu parcaya sang Tuhan sama ke ba'i Abraham.<bt>Yesus replied saying, “Good. This day the Lord God has saved you-sg and all your family, because you believe in the Lord like grandfather Abraham.</bt><v n="10" />Te Tuhan Allah utus sang Beta jadi Manusia Tulen di ini dunya. Beta datang ko cari orang yang su serong dari Tuhan pung jalan, ko kasi salamat sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz the Lord God is the one who commissioned Me to become the Authentic Human in this world. I came to seek people who have strayed/deviated from the Lord's path, in order to save them.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***ilang changed to serong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***ilang changed to serong</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Carita so'al budak yang ator bae-bae dia pung tuan pung doi<bt>Story about the slave who carefully manages his master's money</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***title changed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***title changed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 25:14-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu waktu, ada banya orang yang iko dengar sang Yesus. Dong su mau deka-deka deng kota Yerusalem. Dong ju sangka Dia su mau kasi jalan Tuhan Allah pung parenta di situ, sama ke satu raja. Ais Yesus carita kasi sang dong satu umpama lai,<bt>At that time, there were many people who were following listening to Yesus. They were about to get near Yerusalem city. They also supposed He wanted to carry out the Lord God's rule there, like a raja. So Yesus told them another comparison.story, [EXEG: note Gk “immediately” carried by KM “su”. Make sure the element comes through in your language.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***pikir changed to sangka to better"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***pikir changed to sangka to better match Gk "suppose" (which implies wrongly) ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang bésar. Dia mau barangkat pi luar negrí, ko dong lantik sang dia jadi raja. Ais itu, baru dia mau kambali lai jadi raja di dia pung negrí sandiri.<bt>saying, “There was a big/important person. He wanted/was.about.to leave to go out of the country, so they could install him to be a raja. After that, then he would come back again to be king in his country. [EXEG: Is he king only in the far country? Or does he go to the far country to get crowned king their over his own (first) country? Marshall, Green, TN, LB (also implied by the run of the story as a whole) point out it was common for aspirants to regional kingships to travel to Rome to be installed (and legitimized) there, then return to their domain.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***raja muda &gt; orang besar; di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***raja muda &gt; orang besar; di sana deleted--pelantikan is done elsewhere, but he becomes ruler over both countries ; *** adjusted further Feb 2008</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eugeneis: high status, important, possibly of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eugeneis: high status, important, possibly of noble birth</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Waktu dia su siap mau jalan, dia pange dia pung orang karjá sapulu orang, ais kasi sang dong satu orang satu doi mas.<bt>When he was ready to travel, he called his ten workers, and gave each one of them one gold money.</bt><note reference="19:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang dia kasi dong, &lt;10 <span class="Italic">mina</span>&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">mina</span>, andia 100 <span class="Italic">denari</span>, ko, satu tukang pung gaji 100 hari karjá.<bt>The Yunani language writing says he gave them, ‘10 <span class="Italic">mina</span>&gt;. One mina is 100 <span class="Italic">dinari</span>, or one workers wage for 100 days.</bt></note>Dia parenta bilang, &lt;Bosong pake ini doi jadi modal. Te nanti kalo beta pulang, bosong lapor bosong su ontong barapa.&gt; Ais ju dia barangkat.<bt>He ordered saying, “You-pl use this money as seed.money. Cuz later when I come.home, you report how much you have gained.’ Then he left. [NOTE to daughter translations: it needs to be clear that the ten mina are one to each servant (see vs.16)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** paragraph added Feb 2008"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** paragraph added Feb 2008</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma dia pung rakyat dong binci sang dia. Jadi dong kirim utusan pi sana ko kasi tau bilang, &lt;Botong sonde mau ini orang pegang parenta kasi botong.&gt;<bt>But his populace/people hated him. So they sent a envoy over there to tell saying, ‘We don't want to person to rule us.’ [NOTE to daughter translations: This is probably not the whole populace, but part of them. If UNS's say “all”, say /saparu/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rakyat ; *** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">rakyat ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Biar bagitu ju, ma dong lantik sang dia di sana. Ais ju dia pulang. Sampe di dia pung ruma, ju dia pange ame itu orang karjá sapulu orang dong, ais tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;Bosong su ontong barapa dari itu doi mas yang beta kasi sang bosong tu?&gt;<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless they installed him there. Then he came.home. Arriving at his house, then he called those ten workers, and asked them saying, ‘How much have you gained from that gold money which I gave to you?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Orang karjá partama lapor bilang, &lt;Bapa raja! Beta su dapa ontong sapulu kali dari modal yang beta tarima!&gt;<bt>The first worker reported saying, “Father raja! I have profited ten times from that seed.money which I received!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju raja kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;Bagus! Lu ni, orang karjá yang bae. Tagal beta bisa parcaya sang lu deng hal kici dong, andia ko sakarang beta angka sang lu ko parenta sapulu kota.&gt;<bt>Then the raja told him saying, ‘Great! You here a re a good worker. Because I can trust you with small things, that's why now I am raising you up to rule ten cities.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tarús, orang karjá nomer dua lapor bilang, &lt;Bapa raja! Beta dapa ontong lima doi mas dari modal yang beta tarima.&gt;<bt>Next, worker number two reported saying, ‘Father raja! I have profited five gold coins from that seed.money which I received.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais, itu raja puji sang dia bilang, &lt;Bagus! Kalo bagitu, beta angka sang lu ko parenta lima kota.&gt;<bt>So that raja praised him saying, ‘Great! If that the case, I raise you up to rule five cities.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma orang karjá nomer tiga bawa pulang dia pung doi mas. Ais dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;Ini bos pung doi! Beta bungkus, ais sambunyi sang dia bae-bae ko jang ilang.<bt>But worker number three brought back his gold money. Then he told saying, ‘Here is boss' money! I wrapped itu, then hid it carefully so it wouldn't disappear.</bt><v n="21" />Beta bekin bagitu, tagal beta taku. Beta tau bapa ni orang karás. Te bapa suka ame apa yang bukan bapa pung, deng ketu ame apa yang bapa sonde tanam.&gt;<bt>I did like that, because I am afraid. I know that father here is a hard person. Cuz father likes to take what is not father's and pick/harvest what father did not plant.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju raja masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;Lu ni, kurang ajar! Lu pung omong su hukum lu pung diri sandiri. Lu kira beta ni orang karás, yang ame apa yang bukan beta pung, deng ketu apa yang beta sonde tanam.<bt>Hearing like that the raja got.angry with him saying, ‘You here don't know manners! Your own words have judged/punished you yourself. You think (implied wrongly) that I here am a hard person, who takes what is not mine, and harvests what I have not planted. [EXEG: Is he 1) really a hard man, or 2) is this just the servant's view? “Judge you by your own words” seems to imply the second. TN says “The king’s words here seem to imply that he did not agree with what the evil servant thought of him.” So counterfactual signals “if that's what you thought, then you should have...” need to be built in to the translation. Previous KM version “You knew...” changed to “You thought (lexical choice implies: thought wrongly)...” Also implied by CONNOT. Green reads it differently, saying “the nobleman seems to accept this assessment of himself.” Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) lu su tau --&gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) lu su tau --&gt; lu kira ; Note added</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Kalo bagitu, na, akurang ko lu sonde pi simpan ini doi di bank? Ko biar waktu beta pulang, beta bisa dapa dia pung bunga. Biar sadiki ju bae.&gt;<bt>If that's the case, na, why didn't you go store this money in the bank? So that when I came home, I could get the interest. Even a little.bit would be ok.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Tarús, itu raja suru orang laen dong di situ bilang, &lt;Ame dia pung doi tu, ko sarakan kasi orang karjá yang dapa ontong sapulu tadi.&gt;<bt>Then that raja ordered other people there saying, ‘Take that money of his, and hand it over to that earlier worker who got ten profit.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma dong protes bilang, &lt;Pak! Itu orang su dapa cukup. Akurang ko mau ame dari orang yang pung sadiki, ko kasi tamba sang dia lai?&gt;<bt>But they protested saying, ‘Mr! That person has enough. Why do you want to take it from a person who has only a little.bit, to give even more to him?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ma itu raja manyao bilang, &lt;Pikir bae-bae! Te orang yang pintar urus apa yang orang su parcaya kasi dia, nanti dia dapa tamba lai. Ma orang yang malas urus, nanti dong ame bekin abis apa yang dia pung.<bt>But that raja answered saying, ‘Think well! Cuz the person who is skilled in managing what people have entrusted to him, later he will obtain even more. But the person who is lazy in managing, later they will come and deplete/finish.off what he has.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: /nanti dong ame.../ is problematic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">NOTE: /nanti dong ame.../ is problematic for FT, it preserves active "what he has will be taken away" but non-referential /dong/ is awkward</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:12, Markus 4:25, Lukas 8:18</note><v n="27" />Naa! Sakarang bosong pi tangkap beta pung musu dong yang sonde suka beta jadi raja di sini. Bawa sang dong datang di sini, ais bunu sang dong samua di beta pung muka. Pi su!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa! Now you-pl go capture my enemies who don't like me being raja here. Bring them here, then kill all of them in front of me. Go now!”&gt;</bt><note reference="19:11-27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:14-30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso pi kota Yerusalem<bt>The Lord Yesus enters into Yerusalem city</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:1-11; Markus 11:1-11; Yohanis 12:12-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus carita abis ju, dong jalan tarús pi Yerusalem. Yesus ada jalan di muka.<bt>After Yesus finished telling the story, then they travelled on to Yerusalem. Yesus was walking in front.</bt><v n="29" />Waktu su mau deka-deka deng dua kampong, andia Betfage deng Betania, yang ada di gunung Saitun pung pinggir, ju Dia suru Dia pung ana bua dua orang ko jalan lebe dolo.<bt>When about to get close to two villages, which were Betfage and Betania, which were on the edge/slope of Saitun Mountain, then He ordered two of His underlings to go on ahead.</bt><v n="30" />Dia suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua pi kampong yang di muka tu. Nanti bosong dapa lia satu keledai ana ada ta'ika di situ. Orang balóm parná nae sang dia. Bosong buka dia pung tali ko hela bawa datang di sini.<bt>He commanded them saying, “You two go to that village in front there. You will see a donkey offspring is tied there. A person has not yet ridden it. You open/untie it's rope to pull bring it here.</bt><v n="31" />Ma kalo ada yang tanya bilang, &lt;Akurang ko bosong buka itu keledai pung tali?&gt; na, kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;Botong pung Bos ada mau pake sang dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But if anyone asks saying, ‘Why are you untying that donkey's rope?&gt;, well tell them saying, ‘Our-exc Boss wants to use it.”&gt; [NOTE: KM likes /bos/ to be possessed--it is always someone's boss.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais dong dua pi, ju katumu itu keledai ana, sama ke Yesus pung omong.<bt>So then the two of them went, and encountered that donkey offspring, just like Yesus' speaking.</bt><v n="33" />Waktu dong ada lapás itu keledai ana pung tali, ju dia pung tuan tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong lapás ini binatang?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were free-ing/releasing that donkey offspring's rope, his master asked them saying, “Why are you free-ing this animal?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong pung Bos ada mau pake.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, “Our-exc Boss wants to use it.”</bt><v n="35" />Itu tuan tarima bae, ais dong dua hela bawa itu keledai ana pi sang Yesus. Dong buka dong pung salimut di itu keledai ana pung balakang. Ju dong kasi nae Yesus pi atas.<bt>That master agreed, then the two of them dragged brought that donkey offspring to Yesus. They opened their blankets/male.sarongs on that donkey offspring's back. Then they put Yesus on top.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do we have to keep saying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">do we have to keep saying keledai ana - would just keledai work? @@ Deleted last sentence, May 2005 "Padahal, cuma orang kici sa yang biasa nae keledai." Shouldn't be in the text.<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="19:35" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di sana, orang bésar nae kuda, ma orang kici nae keledai. Tuhan Yesus nae keledai tu, jadi tanda Dia pung randá hati. Di <span class="Italic">Sakaria</span> 9:9, ju ada satu janji yang bilang orang Isra'el pung raja nanti mau datang nae keledai.<bt>There, big/important people ride horses, but small/unimportant people ride donkeys. The Lord Yesus getting on that donkey, became a sign that he was low livered (=humble). In <span class="Italic">Sakarias</span> 9:9 there is also a promise that says the king of the Isra'el people was going to come (riding) on a donkey.</bt></note><v n="36" />Orang banya ju ame dong pung salimut deng salendang, ais buka di jalan, ko sambut sang Yesus sama ke tarima orang bésar.<bt>Many people also took their blankets/male.clothes and their shawls, and opened them on the road, to welcome Yesus like they were recieving a big/important person.</bt><v n="37" />Waktu Dia mulai jalan turun dari gunung Saitun, ju itu orang banya deng Dia pung ana bua dong mulai ba'eki puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah, tagal samua tanda kuasa yang dong su lia tu.<bt>When He started to go down Saitun mountain, then those many people and his underlings began to yell out praises to the Lord God, because of all those signs of power which they had seen. [EXEG: ‘signs of power’, not miracles.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eerksanto ... khairontes ainein: this is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">eerksanto ... khairontes ainein: this is outward behavior manifested by yelling and whooping it up</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Dong ba'eki bilang,<bt>They yelled out saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dia ni, Raja yang Tuhan Allah utus datang!<bt>He here, is the Raja whom the Lord God commissioned to come!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang Dia!<bt>The Lord God blesses Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Sakarang manusia su bisa badame deng Tuhan di sorga.<bt>Now humans can be in relational peace (reconciled) with the Lord in heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Puji sang Tuhan yang dudu parenta di langit yang paling tinggi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Praise the Lord who sits ruling in the very highest sky.” [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="19:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ma ada orang Farisi di itu orang banya dong pung teng-tenga. Dong lapor sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Togor ko dong jang batarea bagitu, te ini su talalu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were Farisi people in the midst of the crowd. They reported to Yesus saying, “Father Teacher! Scold/Rebuke them so they don't yell like that, cuz this is just too much!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee! Beta kasi tau memang! Kalo ini orang dong tutu mulu, nanti batu dong yang puji sang Tuhan!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Hee! [+exasperated] I'm telling you! If these people shut their mouths, then the rocks will be the ones who praise the Lord!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus manangis kasi Yerusalem<bt>The Lord Yesus crys for Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Waktu dong su deka-deka maso Yerusalem, Yesus dapa lia itu kota, ju Dia manangis<bt>When they were close to entering Yerusalem, Yesus saw that city, and He cried/wept,</bt><v n="42" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu, orang Yerusalem, é! Beta mau ko ini hari bosong tarima dame yang Beta bawa. Ma tagal bosong sonde toe sang Tuhan, jadi sakarang su talambat. Itu dame su jao dari bosong.<bt>saying, “Adoo, Yerusalem people! I want so that today you receive the peace which I bring. But because you don't care about the Lord, now it's too late. That is already far from you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***depersonified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***depersonified</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="if: There's no &quot;then&quot; clause, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">if: There's no "then" clause, and the implication is a wish that cannot be fulfulled. ta pros eireeneen: the things that bring about peace (inner peace? freedom from strife? peace with God?) NEB "the way that leads to peace", TEV "what is needed for peace." UBS prefers reconciliation to God; in commenting on 1:79 negative as lack of strife between persons and absence of war, positive as fulness of well-being resting on confidence in God. There's also outward peace (from war, peace with God) and inner peace (like John 14:1, which doesn't use the word) to choose here. Stick with "stay good wit God".<span class="Italic">(42)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Nanti bosong pung musu dong timbun tana kuliling kota pung tembok, ais dong maso saráng sang bosong.<bt>Later your enemies will heap up dirt around your city's walls, then they will enter and attack you. [EXEG: Gk. dirt embankment. LN, Also “rampart” sense #1; HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="timbun = heap, pile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">timbun = heap, pile</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Dong kasi rubu sang bosong pung kota rata deng tana, ais bunu bosong deng bosong pung ana-ana dong samua. Dong sonde kasi tenga satu batu badiri, tagal Tuhan su datang ko mau kasi salamat sang bosong, ma bosong sonde kanál sang Dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>They will knock.down your city flat to the ground, then murder you-pl and all your children. They will not leave one stone standing, because the Lord has come wanting to save you, but you did not know/recognize Him!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat<bt>The Lord Yesus enters into the Central Worship House</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:12-17; Markus 11:15-19; Yohanis 2:13-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais ju Yesus maso pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Di itu ruma pung kintal, orang su bekin jadi pasar ko jual binatang korban. Lia bagitu ju, Yesus mulai usir kasi kaluar sang dong dari situ.<bt>Then Yesus entered into the Central Worship House. In that house's yard, people had made a market in order to sell sacrifice animals. See like that then Yesus began to expel out those people from there.</bt><v n="46" />Dia masparak bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung jubir su tulis memang bilang,<bt>He got.angry saying, “The Lord's spokesperson has written in.advance saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Beta kasi bangun ini Ruma,<bt>&lt;I built this House,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko samua orang bisa datang sambayang di sini.&gt;<bt>so that all people can come worship here.’</bt><note reference="19:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 56:7, Yeremia 7:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma bosong su bekin sang dia jadi parampok dong pung tampa bakumpul.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you have made it become a robbers' gathering place.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Ais itu, tiap hari Yesus pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat ko ajar di situ. Ma kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama deng tua-tua adat Yahudi dong cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu sang Dia.<bt>After that, every day Yesus went to the Central Worship House to teach there. But the *chief priests, the religion teachers and the traditional Yahudi elders kept looking for a way to murder Him.</bt><note reference="19:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 21:37</note><v n="48" />Ma dong sonde dapa jalan, tagal itu orang banya dong talalu sanáng dengar Yesus pung omong.<bt>But they did not find a way, because many people were very happy listening to Yesus' speaking.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong baso'al Tuhan Yesus pung hak deng kuasa<bt>They debate the Lord Yesus' authority and power</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:23-27; Markus 11:27-33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="20" />
      <v n="1" />Satu hari, Yesus pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ais ajar Tuhan pung Kabar Bae di dia pung kintal. Ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat dong datang baso'al deng Dia.<bt>One day, Yesus went to the Central Worship House then taught the Lord's Good New in it's yard. Then the *chief priests, the teachers of religion, and the traditional elders came and debated with Him.</bt><v n="2" />Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa kasi hak sang Lu ko bekin kaco di sini kamaren? Coba kasi tau dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked saying, “Who gave authority to You make everything chaotic here yesterday/the other day? Tell us! [NOTE to daughter translations: /kemarin/ here is in the broad sense, not the narrow sense.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju mau tanya satu hal, ais baru Beta manyao sang bosong.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “I also want to ask one thing, afterwards then I will answer you-pl.</bt><v n="4" />Bagini: bosong kanál sang Yohanis tukang sarani, to? Sapa kasi kuasa ko dia sarani orang? Tuhan Allah ko, manusia?&gt;&gt;<bt>It's like this: you know Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer, right? Who gave him power to baptise women? The Lord God, or humans?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju dong barunding pi-datang, deng ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Kotong su kaná ni ma. Kalo kotong bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah yang suru&gt;, nanti Dia balas bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, akurang ko bosong sonde parcaya sang Yohanis?&gt;<bt>Then they discussed it over.and.over, and spoke to each other saying, “Oh no! We-inc are caught now. If we say &lt;The Lord God is the one who told.him.to.do it&gt;, later He will reply saying, ‘If that's the case, why don't you believe in Yohanis then?&gt;</bt><v n="6" />Ma kotong ju sonde bisa bilang, &lt;manusia yang suru&gt;, te nanti ini orang dong angka batu ko lempar bekin mati sang kotong. Te dong parcaya bilang, Yohanis tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.&gt;&gt;<bt>But we also can't say, ‘humans who told.him.to.do it&gt;, cuz then these people will pick up stone to throw killing us. Cuz they believe that Yohanis there, was the Lord God's spokesperson.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais dong manyao sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde tau.&gt;&gt;<bt>So the replied to Yesus saying, “We-exc don't know.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, Beta ju sonde mau bilang sapa yang suru sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus reciprocated saying, “If that's the case, I also don't want to say who it was that ordered/told Me.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Carita tukang garap kabón anggor<bt>Story of the grape garden workers</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:33-46; Markus 12:1-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais ju Yesus carita itu orang banya dong, satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang yang tanam kabón anggor. Dia kasi sewa itu kabón di tukang garap, ko dong babagi hasil. Tarús dia pinda pi luar negrí ko tenga lama di sana.<bt>Then Yesus told those many people, another comparison story saying, “There was a person who planted a grape garden. He rented that garden out to workers so that they could divide the harvest. Then he moved outside the country to stay there for a long time. [NOTE to daughter translations: In some languages/cultures in the region, there is a clash here. If it is a share cropping system (using /tukang garap/), then one cannot /kasi sewa/ ‘rent out’ the land. CHECK for collocational clash.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang garap -- share croppers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tukang garap -- share croppers</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 5:1</note><v n="10" />Sampe musim ketu bua anggor ju, itu tuan kabón suru dia pung orang karjá satu ko pi tarima dia pung bagian dari itu tukang garap dong. Ma itu tukang garap dong papoko itu orang karjá, ais dong usir buang sang dia pulang deng tangan kosong.<bt>When it came time for harvest the grape fruits, that garden master ordered one of his workers to go accept his share from those workers. But those workers beat up that worker, then they chased him out to go home with empty hands.</bt><v n="11" />Ais, itu tuan kabón kirim dia pung orang karjá satu pi. Ma itu tukang garap dong papoko sang dia, deng bekin malu sang dia. Ais dong usir pulang sang dia deng tangan kosong.<bt>Then that garden master sent one of his workers to go. But those workers beat him up, and embarrased him. Then they chased him away to go.home with empty hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Is first sentence ok?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Is first sentence ok?</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ju itu tuan kabón kirim lai dia pung orang karjá nomer tiga pi, ma dong papoko bekin luka sang dia, ais dong buang kaluar sang dia.<bt>Then that garden master sent again his third worker to go, but they beat him up wounding him, then they threw him outside.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu tuan kabón dudu pikir-pikir bilang, &lt;Beta musti bekin karmana lai? Lebe bae beta kirim beta pung ana sayang sa. Tantu dong hormat deng tarima sang dia deng bae-bae.&gt; Jadi dia kirim dia pung ana barana pi sana.<bt>That garden master sat and thought about it saying, ‘What else should I do? It's better I just send my beloved child. Surely they will respect and accept him well.’ So he sent his own child there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma waktu itu tukang garap dong lia sang dia, ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;We, bosong lia dolo! Te bapatua su kirim datang dia pung ana sandiri. Dia yang nanti tarima bapatua pung pusaka samua. Jadi mari ko kotong bunu sang dia su! Biar ko kotong yang soa ini kabón.&gt;<bt>But when those workers saw him, then they spoke.with.each.other saying, ‘We, [+get attention] look at that! Cuz the old.man has sent his own child. He is the one who will receive all the old.man's inheritance. So (consequently), let's murder him! Just let us become the ones who possess this garden.’</bt><v n="15" />Waktu itu ana sampe ju, dong hela raroso bawa sang dia kaluar dari itu kabón, ais dong bunu bekin mati sang dia.<bt>When that child arrived, then they dragged him along.the.ground out of that garden, then they murder killed him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Beta mau tanya bagini: bosong pikir itu tuan kabón mau bekin karmana deng itu tukang garap dong?<bt>Naa [+shift to implications]! I want to ask like this: What do you think that garden master should do with those workers? [NOTE to daughter translations: if the target language has no equivalent of Naa! which indicates a big shift here, consider putting in a quote margin saying, /Carita abis, Yesus tanya itu orang di situ dong, bilang, “Iko bosong, itu tuan kabon.../ -- but most lgs cannot have a quote margin if the same speaker is continuing. Quote margins always imply change of speaker.]</bt><v n="16" />Iko Beta, pasti dia datang ko bunu sang dong samua, ais dia kasi sewa itu kabón pi orang laen.&gt;&gt;<bt>According to Me, surely he will come and murder them all, then rent that garden to other people.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu itu orang dong dengar Yesus omong bagitu, ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bisa, na, Tuhan Allah jang kasi hukum sang botong bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>When those people heard Yesus speak like that, then they responded saying, “If possible/Hopefully the Lord God won't send down punishment like that to us!” [EXEG: explication of “heaven forbid”. Most complete discussion in TN. Marshall points out “The remark may be taken as expressing horror at the reaction of the owner or at the whole course of events; in either case the application of the story to the Jewish leaders is in mind.” Realisation is in vs. 19. Green says “the answer is self-evident. Surely the destruction of Jerusalem marks the obliteration of Israel as well! But this misses the careful distinction drawn in the parable between vineyard and tenants, and thus between Israel and its leaders.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="can 2nd Yesus become a pronoun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">can 2nd Yesus become a pronoun ; *** restructured to remove addition that belonged in vs. 19 (Feb 2008)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu itu orang dong dengar Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Waktu itu orang dong dengar Yesus omong bagitu, ju dong tau, bilang, Yesus ada omong ser sang dong. Ais dong manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bisa, na, Tuhan Allah jang kasi hukum sang botong bagitu!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Yesus lia karás-karás sang dong, ju tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo sonde jadi kasi hukum bagitu, na, akurang ko Tuhan pung jubir su tulis bilang,<bt>Then Yesus looked sternly at them, and asked saying, “If it doesn't happen that [He] sends punishment like that, then why did the Lord's spokesperson write saying like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added kasi hukum, because of UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***added kasi hukum, because of UNS confusion in Belu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ada satu batu yang tukang dong su angka buang,<bt>&lt;There was a stone which the workers threw away,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sakarang su jadi tiang induk pung batu alas.&gt;<bt>but now it has become the main pole's foundation stone?&gt;</bt><note reference="20:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Orang yang ta'antok di itu batu, pasti ancor, tagal kaná hukum. Deng kalo itu batu jato kaná orang, dia ju ancor abis, tagal kaná hukum.&gt;&gt;<bt>The person who trips.over that stone, surely will destroyed, because of obtaining punishment. And if that stone falls on a person, he also will be completely destroyed, because of obtaining punishment.” [EXEG: punishment from Marshall, MC]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'antuk = stub foot on s.t.,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">ta'antuk = stub foot on s.t., terantuk ***added punishment clauses (Marge)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Waktu guru agama deng kapala agama pung bos-bos dengar itu carita, dong tau bilang, Yesus ada ser sang dong pake itu umpama. Dong parsís sama ke itu tukang garap kabón tu. Jadi dong mara mau mati. Ju dong ator siasat ko mau tangkap sang Dia. Ma dong ada eleng sang orang banya yang suka Yesus pung ajaran. Jadi dong jalan kasi tenga sang Dia sa.<bt>When the religion teachers and the chief priests heard that story, they knew that Yesus was targeting them using that comparison.story. They were exactly like those garden workers. So they got very angry. So they looked for a way to arrest Him. But they were hesitant/afraid of the many people who liked Yesus' teaching. So (consequently), they just went off leaving Yesus behind.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">&lt;&lt;Kasi sang Tuhan Allah apa yang Tuhan Allah pung hak&gt;&gt;<bt>“Give the Lord God what is the Lord God's right&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:15-22; Markus 12:13-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais itu, Yesus pung musu dong ada mama'u sang Dia. Dong cari mata-mata yang bisa bekin diri tingka ke orang alim, ko pi hiki coba sang Yesus. Dong harap Yesus bisa omong lawan pamarenta Roma, ais dong mau pi lapor di gubernor, ko biar dong suru orang pi tangkap sang Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus' enemies were angry (?mama'u) at Him. They sought spies who could make themselves like devout people, to go try to trick Yesus. They hoped Yesus could speak against the Roma government, and.then they wanted to go report to the governor so that they would order people to go capture Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mama'u ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">mama'u =</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ju dong kirim itu mata-mata ko pi baso'al deng Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong tau Bapa pung hati lurus. Bapa sonde tau putar-balek, deng sonde pili muka. Bapa salalu ajar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata deng batúl.<bt>So they sent those spies to go debate with Yesus saying, “Father Teacher! We-exc know that Father's liver is straight (=righteous). Father doesn't twist-turn (=decieve), and doesn't choose faces (=discriminate). Father always teaches the Lord God's Words correctly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pili muka = pandang muka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">pili muka = pandang muka</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Sakarang botong mau tanya satu hal: iko kotong pung atoran agama Yahudi, kira-kira kotong bole bayar pajak kasi pamarenta Roma pung raja bésar, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>Now we-exc want to ask one thing: according to our Yahudi religious regulations, do you think we-inc may pay tax to the Roma government's big raja, or not?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma Yesus su tau dong pung maksud jahat ko mau hiki sang Dia. Ju Dia manyao bilang,<bt>But Yesus knew their evil intent to try and trap Him. So He replied saying,</bt><v n="24" />&lt;&lt;Coba kasi tunju sang Beta doi perak satu dolo.&gt;&gt; Ju dong kasi tunju itu doi sang Dia. Ais Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini, sapa pung gambar ni? Deng ini, sapa pung nama?&gt;&gt;<bt>“Show Me a silver money.” Then they showed that money to Him. And He asked saying, “This here, whose picture is this? And this here, whose name?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu raja bésar, keser.&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, “That is the big raja, Keser.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ju Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, kasi sang pamarenta apa yang pamarenta pung hak. Deng kasi sang Tuhan Allah apa yang Tuhan Allah pung hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus said, “If that the case, na, give to the government what the government has rights.to. And give to the Lord God what the Lord God has rights.to.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong taheran-heran, tagal dong sonde bisa hiki ame sang Dia di muka orang banya. Ju dong tutu mulu su.<bt>Hearing like that, they were amazed because they could not trap Him (successfully) in front of many people. So they shut their mouths.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al idop kambali dari mati<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about living again from death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:23-33; Markus 12:18-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu, ada barapa orang dari partei agama Saduki datang ko mau hiki sang Yesus. Orang Saduki dong ajar bilang, orang mati sonde idop kambali lai di hari kiamat. Dong datang baso'al deng Yesus bilang,<bt>After that, there were several people from the Saduki religious party who wanted to trap Yesus. Saduki people teach that, dead people don't live again at the end of the world. They came to debate with Yesus saying,</bt><note reference="20:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:8</note><v n="28" />&lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Ba'i Musa su tulis kasi tenga sang kotong atoran bilang: kalo ada laki-laki mati, ma sonde kasi tenga ana, na, itu orang pung adi musti kawin ame dia pung janda, ko biar kasi turunan sang dia pung kaka yang su mati tu.<bt>“Father Teacher! Gf/Ff Musa has written leaving behind for us-inc regulation/s saying: if a male dies, but doesn't leave behind a child, na, that person's younger sibling must marry his widow, in order to give a descendant to that elder.brother of his who is dead.</bt><note reference="20:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Memang dolu ba'i Musa ajar bagitu. Ma sakarang botong ada mau tanya bagini: ada tuju laki-laki basodara. Yang sulung kawin, ma dia mati deng sonde kasi tenga ana.<bt>Certainly Gf/Ff Musa taught like that previously. But now we-exc want to ask like this: there were seven male siblings. The eldest married, but he died and did not leave behind a child.</bt><v n="30" />Ais dia pung adi yang iko sang dia kawin ame itu janda. Sonde lama, te dia mati, ma sonde kasi tenga ana.<bt>Then the younger sibling who followed him married that widow. Not long, and he died, but didn't leave behind a child.</bt><v n="31" />Bagitu ju deng ana nomer tiga. Dia kawin deng itu janda, ma dia ju mati deng sonde kasi tenga ana. Bagitu tarús-tarús sampe adi bungsu ju mati.<bt>Simarly with child number three. He married that widow, but he died without leaving behind a child. Like that over and over until the youngest sibling also died.</bt><v n="32" />Tarús itu janda ju mati.<bt>Then that widow also died.</bt><v n="33" />Naa! Sakarang botong mau tanya bagini: itu parampuan su parná kawin deng tuju laki-laki. Nanti kalo dunya kiamat, ais Tuhan kasi idop kambali orang mati dong, na, itu parampuan jadi sapa pung bini?&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Now we want to ask like this: that woman had married those seven males. When the world ends, and the Lords makes the dead people live again, na, that woman will be whose wife?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Manusia bakawin di ini dunya sa.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “Humans mutually.marry only on this earth.</bt><v n="35-36" />Ma nanti di sorga orang su sonde bakawin lai. Deng di sana dong su sonde mati lai. Dong su sama ke Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga. Te waktu Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali orang mati, Dia pili ame sang dong ko jadi Dia pung ana-ana.<bt>But later in heaven people will no longer mutually.marry. And there they will no longer die. They will be like the Lord God's underlings in heaven. Cuz when the Lord God makes the dead people live again, He choose them to become HIs children.</bt><v n="37" />Dalam ba'i Musa pung tulisan ada carita pohon kici yang tabakar ma sonde angus. Dari itu carita kotong dapa tau bilang, orang mati bisa idop kambali. Di situ Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang ba'i Musa bilang, &lt;Beta ni, lu pung ba'i-ba'i pung Tuhan Allah. Andia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob. Dong samua sémba tarús sang Beta sampe sakarang.&gt;<bt>In Gf/Ff Musa's writing there is a story about a little tree that was on.fire but didn't get burn.up. From that story we-inc know that dead people can live again. There the Lord God told grandfather Musa saying, “I here, am your-sg grandfathers' Lord God. That is grandfather Abraham, grandfather Isak, and grandfather Yakob. They all continually worship Me until now.’</bt><note reference="20:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:6</note><v n="38" />Padahal itu ba'i dong su mati dari dolu. Ma tagal Tuhan Allah su bilang Dia masi jadi dong pung Tuhan, andia ko kotong tau bilang, dong ada idop. Jadi biar orang su mati ju, dong idop kambali. Te cuma orang idop yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah, bukan orang mati, to?!&gt;&gt;<bt>In actual.fact those grandfathers had already been dead a long time. But because the Lord God said He was still their Lord, that's why we know that they were living. So even though people die, they live again. Cuz only living people are the ones who worship the Lord God, not dead people, right?!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pantes gar autooi zoosin: in relationship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">pantes gar autooi zoosin: in relationship to God they are all alive</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Dengar Yesus manyao bagitu ju, ada guru agama yang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru pung jawab tu, talalu batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus answer like that, then a religon teacher spoke saying, “Father Teacher's answer there, is very true.”</bt><v n="40" />Mulai dari itu waktu ju, sonde ada satu orang yang barani tanya lai sang Yesus, te sonde ada yang bisa hiki ame sang Dia na.<bt>Starting from that time then there was not one person who dared ask anything more to Yesus, cuz there was [+obviously] no one who could trap/trick Him (successfully).</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus tu, memang raja Daud pung turunan, deng dia pung Bos ju<bt>The Kristus is truly Raja Daud's descendant, and also his Bos</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:41-46; Markus 12:35-37)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais itu, Yesus masi ajar itu orang dong di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ju Dia so'al bale sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko bosong pung pikiran, karmana? Guru agama dong ajar bilang, Kristus tu, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju dari dolu-kala. Iko dong, Dia cuma jadi raja Daud pung turunan sa. Ma itu balóm cukup.<bt>After that, Yesus was teaching those people at the Central Worship House. Then he debated in.return to them saying, “According to your thinking, how.is.it? The religion teachers teach that the Kristus, is the Person whom the Lord God had appointed from long ago. According to them, He only just became raja Daud's descendant. But that is not enough.</bt><v n="42" />Tagal dolu raja Daud sandiri yang tulis dalam buku Lagu Puji dong bilang,<bt>Because long ago raja Daud himself is the one who wrote in the book of Praise Songs saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah su kasi tau sang beta pung bos bilang,<bt>&lt;The Lord God has told my bos saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Mari ko dudu di ini tampa terhormat di Beta pung sablá kanan.<bt>“Come to sit in this most.honoured place at My right side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="43" />Te nanti Beta bekin lu pung musu dong,<bt>Cuz I will make/bother your-sg enemies</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="captial Lu in OT quote?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">captial Lu in OT quote?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe dong ta'alok sang lu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>to the point that they subjugate.themselves to you.”&gt;</bt><note reference="20:42-43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Naa! Dari itu tulisan, kotong dapa tau bilang, raja Daud sandiri pange sang Kristus tu bilang, &lt;Bos&gt;. Dia pung arti, kalo orang bilang Kristus tu, cuma raja Daud pung turunan sa, itu balóm cukup! Tagal Dia ju jadi raja Daud pung Bos yang hak parenta sang dia na!&gt;&gt;<bt>So! From that writing, we-inc know that raja Daud himself called the Kristus, saying &lt;Bos&gt;. That means, if people say the Kristus is only just raja Daud's descendant, that is not enough! Because he also is [+obviously] raja Daud's Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over him [+emphatic]!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ati-ati deng guru agama yang tutu dong pung sala<bt>Be careful with the religion teachers who cover their sins</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 23:1-36; Markus 12:38-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Waktu samua orang ada pasang talinga ko dengar sang Yesus, ju Dia omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang,<bt>When all the people were paying attention to listen to Yesus, then He spoke with His underlings saying,</bt><v n="46" />&lt;&lt;Bosong musti ati-ati deng guru agama dong. Te dong suka pasiar pake baju panjang raroso, pi katumu banya orang, ko biar orang lia sang dong bilang, &lt;Awii! Dong tu, orang bésar, ó!&gt; Dong suka cari tampa yang paling terhormat di ruma-ruma sambayang, di pesta, deng di tampa banya orang suka bakumpul.<bt>“You-pl must becareful about the religion teachers. Cuz they like to go.out long draping to the ground robes, and go meet many people, so that people see them and say, ‘Awii! [+impressed] They there are big/important people!&gt; They like to find the most respected place in the worship houses, at feasts, and the place many people like to meet. [NOTE to daughter translations: some mesolectal speakers try to take /suka/ in its primary sense. /Suka/ here is only aspectual 'often'; it is not 'desire to'.]</bt><v n="47" />Ma ati-ati, te dong maen putar-balek sang janda dong ko rampas ame dong pung ruma. Ma di muka banya orang, dong tutu dong pung jahat deng badiri sambayang lama-lama. Dong mau ko orang bilang dong tu, orang alim. Ma Tuhan tau dong pung sala, jadi nanti Dia kasi hukum yang lebe barát sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But becareful, cuz they keep decieving widows in order to snatch away their house/s. But in front of many people, they cover over that evil of theirs and stand praying for a long time. They want people to say that they are pios people. But the Lord knows their wrongs, so He will give punishment that is heavier/more severe to them.” [NOTE to daughter translations: some mesolectal speakers try to take /maen/ in its primary sense. /Maen/ here is only aspectual 'often, kept'; it is not 'play'.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Janda miskin kasi kolekte yang paling bésar<bt>A poor widow gives the biggest offering</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:41-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="21" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus ajar di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, Dia dapa lia orang kaya dong datang kasi maso kolekte di peti derma.<bt>When Yesus taught in the Central Worship House, He saw rich people come putting offering in the collection box.</bt><v n="2" />Dia ju dapa lia satu janda kasian datang iko sambayang. Dia kasi maso doi dua sen di itu peti. Itu doi pung harga paling kici.<bt>He also saw a poor widow come to participate in praying. She put two cents of money in that box. The value of that money/coin is the very smallest.</bt><v n="3" />Ais Yesus omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Ini janda kasian ni cuma kasi maso doi dua sen sa, ma dia su kasi lebe dari samua orang.<bt>Then Yesus spoke with His underlings saying, “Listen well! This poor widow here only put in just two cents of money, but she has given more than all people.</bt><v n="4" />Itu orang laen dong kasi maso kolekte dari dong pung doi sisa sa. Ma ini janda ni, dia su kasi abis dia pung doi samua-samua. Padahal itu dia pung doi ko idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>Those other people just put in collection money from their excess/leftover money. But this widow here, she has completely given all her money. In fact, that was her money for living. [EXEG: Last clause explicating Gk /bios/]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung rubu<bt>The Lord Yesus tells about the Central Worship House's destruction</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:1-2; Markus 13:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Itu waktu, Yesus pung ana bua dong omong puji-puji itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Lia coba ini Ruma pung bagus lai! Dong bekin sang dia pake batu-batu potong yang paling bésar, ais dong susun deng rapi. Deng ada orang yang su kasi barang mahal ko bekin hias Tuhan pung Ruma ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus' underlings spoke praising that Central Worship House saying, “Papa! Look at the beauty of this House! They made it using cut stones which were very big, and.then they stacked/compiled them very neatly. And there were people who gave expensive things to decorate this House of the Lord's!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus manyao bilang,<bt>But Yesus replied saying,</bt><v n="6" />&lt;&lt;Ini ruma memang bagus. Ma sonde lama lai, te orang dong kasi rubu abis ini batu samua, sampe rata.&gt;&gt;<bt>“This house is truly great. But soon people will completely knock.over all these stone, until they are flat/even.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hari-hari susa deng sangsara<bt>Days of difficulty and suffering</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:3-14; Markus 13:3-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Yesus pung ana bua dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Apa yang Bapa omong tadi tu, kira-kira nanti jadi kapan? Kalo dia pung waktu su deka, nanti dia pung tanda-tanda karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus' underlings asked saying, “Father Teacher! That which Father spoke about earlier, approximately when will it happen? If the time is near, how will the signs be?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal bosong jaga bae-bae ko jang kaná tipu. Te nanti ada macam-macam orang datang puku dada bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Kristus.&gt; Ada ju yang bilang, &lt;Hari kiamat su deka-deka datang!&gt; Ma jang parcaya!<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “As.long.as you-pl guard carefully so you don't get decieved. Cuz there will be all.sorts of people coming beating their chest saying, “I here am Kristus.’ There will also be (those) who say, ‘The end of the world is nearly come!&gt; But don't believe it! [EXEG: "the time has drawn near" = the End is near, see Marshall, TN; Gk either implies or leaves open the possibility that it could be the same group that says both quotes, so restructured to not insist they are said by different groups of people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed last quote and added note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***changed last quote and added note ; *** adjusted to leave open possibility that both things are said by the same group</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Kalo bosong dengar kabar bilang, orang dong bakaco deng baparáng di mana-mana, na, sonde usa taku. Memang, itu samua musti jadi lebe dolo. Ma hari kiamat balóm sampe.<bt>If you hear news that people are mutually.making. chaos and mutually.warring everywhere, well.then it's not neccessary to be afraid. True, all that must happen first. But the end of the world is not yet arrived.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Nanti satu suku baparáng lawan suku laen. Satu negara baparáng lawan negara laen.<bt>One clan will war against another clan. One nation will war against another nation. [DISCOURSE: Gk has quote margin here, but local languages can't have a quote margin where the same speaker is continuing, since a quote margin indicates “change of speaker”.]</bt><v n="11" />Nanti ada tana tagoyang yang hebat mati pung. Di mana-mana ada musim lapar yang hebat, deng panyaki bahaya marajalela. Nanti orang ju lia ame hal yang bekin bulu badan badiri, deng tanda-tanda hebat di langit.<bt>There will be very big earthquakes. In many/various places there will be severe hunger seasons, and dangerous illnesses spreading. Later people will see things which make the body hair stand up, and unusual/incredible signs in the sky.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="marajalela = semua takana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">marajalela = semua takana</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti ada tana goyang bésar-bésar, deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Nanti ada tana goyang bésar-bésar, deng musim lapar yang hebat. Panyaki bahaya marajalela, deng muncul di mana-mana. Nanti orang ju lia ame hal yang bekin bulu badan badiri, deng tanda-tanda hebat di langit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ini hal dong samua balóm jadi abis, ma nanti orang dong tangkap sang bosong, deng siksa sang bosong, tagal bosong parcaya sang Beta. Ais dong sarakan sang bosong pi ko orang dong urus bosong pung parkara di ruma-ruma sambayang, deng tahan sang bosong dalam bui. Dong ju suru sang bosong pi mangada sang raja deng orang pamarenta laen dong. Samua ni, tagal bosong iko sang Beta.<bt>All these thing will not yet have finished (=before all this has happened), but people will capture you and torture you because you believe in Me. Then they will hand you over so they can handle your case in the worship houses, and restrain you in jail. They will also order you to report.to rajas and other government people. All of this, because you follow Me.</bt><v n="13" />Ma bosong musti pake itu sampat ko kasi tau sang dong Beta pung Kabar Bae.<bt>But you must use that opportunity to tell them My Good News.</bt><v n="14" />Jadi sonde usa pikir-pikir lebe dolo bilang, bosong mau bela diri karmana.<bt>So it's not necessary to keep thinking/worrying first about how you will defend yourselves.</bt><v n="15" />Te nanti Beta kasi kata-kata yang pas ko bosong bela diri. Deng bagitu, bosong pung musu dong sonde tau mau bilang apa lai.<bt>Cuz I will give words which are fitting/exact for you to defend yourselves. In that way, your enemies won't know what else to say.</bt><note reference="21:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:11-12</note><v n="16-17" />Nanti banya orang binci mati sang bosong, tagal bosong iko sang Beta. Ada dari bosong pung kelu sandiri, tingka ke mama-papa, adi-kaka, sodara-sodara, deng tamán-tamán dong. Nanti ada dari dong yang cari jalan ko jual buang sang bosong, sampe ada bosong saparu yang kaná bunu.<bt>Later many people will hate you, because you follow Me. There will be those from your own families, like mama-papa, elder-younger siblings, siblings/cousins, and friends. Later there will be those from them who seek ways to betray/sell you off, to.the.point that there are some of you who are killed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thanatoosousin: probably the ones to whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">thanatoosousin: probably the ones to whom the others were betrayed</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma bosong jang taku, te nanti Tuhan sonde lupa sang bosong. Rambu satu urat ju sonde bisa gugur dari bosong pung kapala, kalo bukan Dia pung mau.<bt>But you don't be afraid, cuz later the Lord will not forget you. Not even one hair can drop from your-pl heads, if it is not His will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai thriks ...: probably means that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">kai thriks ...: probably means that the community as a whole won't be harmed or wiped out, even though a few people get killed.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kalo bosong batahan tarús-tarús, tantu Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you keep on enduring, surely the Lord God will save you.” [EXEG: LN “Gk = idiom: save yourselves from grave danger”; QUESTION: does this clash with 16, where “some of you will die”? NRSV “gain your souls” and NLT “win your souls” may not be recognising the idiom. See TN, but don't overtranslate to try and get the “not die spiritually” sense.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yerusalem pung jato<bt>Yerusalem's fall</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:15-21; Markus 13:14-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong lia musu dong su kepung ame kota Yerusalem, bosong tau bilang, dia su mau ancor tu.<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, “If/when you-pl see enemies have encircled Yerusalem city, you will know that it is about to be destroyed. [EXEG: Gk literally “armies”, but carried in KM by combination of /musu/ with military term /kepung ame/ “surround, encircle, besiege”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kepung = surround, encricle, besiege Is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">kepung = surround, encricle, besiege Is that BI not KM?</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Lia bagitu, na, orang di propinsi Yudea bangun lari suda pi gunung. Orang yang di kota ju bangun lari suda. Deng orang yang di kampong sonde usa maso pi kota lai.<bt>Seeing that, people in Yudea province [should] get up and run to the mountains. People in the city also get up and run. And people in the villages shouldn't enter the city again.</bt><v n="22" />Te Tuhan kirim itu hari-hari susa dong ko hukum orang yang sonde mau dengar sang Dia. Itu samua jadi pas deng apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir su tulis memang dari dolu.<bt>Cuz the Lord sends those difficult days to judge people who don't want to hear/obey Him. That all happens exactly in accord with what the Lord God's spokesperson/s have written beforehand long ago.</bt><note reference="21:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 9:7</note><v n="23" />Itu waktu, orang yang paling kasian, andia parampuan yang ada dudu parú, deng mama-mama yang ada kasi susu ana mera. Itu waktu, anteru dunya dapa susa, deng orang Yahudi samua sangsara barát, tagal Tuhan Allah mara sang dong.<bt>At that time, the people who to be most pitied, are the women who are pregnant and mamas who are nursing newborns. At that time, the entire world will have difficulty, and all the Yahudi people will have heavy suffering because the Lord God is angry with them. [EXEG: Gk. normal phrasing for “on the earth” NRSV and impact in vs. 24, although some want to take the also legitimate rendering “on the land” (restricting it to Israel), from context of 20,21,24. This rendering carries both as a parallelism.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** added EXEG note (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** added EXEG note (Helong)</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Nanti musu bunu sang dong saparu, deng tawan saparu, ko jadi budak pi mana-mana di ini dunya. Ais orang asing yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah, datang inja-inja bekin kamomos di kota Yerusalem, deng kuasai kota pung isi, sampe dong pung waktu tu, abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later enemies will murder some of them, and capture some of them to become slaves everywhere in this world. Then foreigners who don't know the Lord God will come and step all over making Yerusalem city dirty/defiled, and control all of the city's contents/inhabitants, until their time is over.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tawan == BI?? kuasai = BI???"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tawan == BI?? kuasai = BI???</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Manusia Tulen pung datang<bt>The Authentic Human's coming</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:29-31; Markus 13:24-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais Yesus kasi tau so'al Dia pung datang kambali bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti kalo Manusia Tulen su mau datang kambali, ada tanda-tanda kaluar di matahari, di bulan, deng di bintang dong. Di bumi ju ada tanda, andia laut mangamok deng angin ribut bésar, deng galombang raksasa nae datang. Ini samua bekin manusia dong taku deng bingung, sampe dong sonde tau mau bekin apa lai.<bt>Then Yesus told about His coming back saying, “Later when the Authentic Human wants to come back, there will be signs coming out in the sun, in the moon and the stars. On earth there will also be signs, such as the sea running amok and very big noisy wind/storm, and giant waves rising coming. All this makes humans afraid and confused, until they don't know what to do anymore.</bt><note reference="21:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, Yeskial 32:7, Yoel 2:31, Dunya Model Baru 6:12-13</note><v n="26" />Kuasa-kuasa yang ada di langit dong tagoyang harba-biruk. Lia bagitu, orang dong jadi taku mau mati, tagal bumi su mau calaka!<bt>The powers which are in the sky will shake in tumult. Seeing like that, people will become very afraid, because the earth is about to have disaster!</bt><v n="27" />Ais itu, baru orang dapa lia sang Beta, &lt;Manusia Tulen, turun datang deng awan&gt;. Beta turun deng kuasa, deng Beta pung hebat samua.<bt>After that, only then people will see Me, ‘the Authentic Human, coming down with/by cloud&gt;. I will come.down with power, and with all My amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="21:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, Dunya Model Baru 1:7</note><v n="28" />Kalo ini tanda samua su mulai jadi, na, bosong angka kapala suda, te Tuhan pung waktu su sampe ko kasi salamat sang bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>When all these signs have begun to happen, na, you must lift up your heads, cuz the Lord's time has arrived to save you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** added begin (Helong)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** added begin (Helong)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama dari pohon<bt>Comparison.story from a tree</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:32-35; Markus 13:28-31)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais itu Yesus angka satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong taro kira bae-bae sang pohon dong.<bt>After that Yesus began to speak a comparison.story saying, “You-pl pay attention carefully to the trees.</bt><v n="30" />Kalo dong pung daon su mulai kuning, itu jadi tanda bilang, musim panas su deka-deka datang.<bt>When their leaves begin to yellow, that is a sign that the hot season is nearly come.</bt><v n="31" />Bagitu ju deng itu hari-hari susa dong. Kalo dong su muncul datang, itu jadi tanda bilang, Tuhan Allah pung parenta su deka-deka datang.<bt>Like.that also with the difficult days. When they appear, that becomes a sign that the Lord God's rule is nearly come.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Beta kasi tau memang! Dari samua orang yang idop sakarang ni, nanti ada yang balóm mati, te itu hari-hari susa su muncul datang.<bt>I'm telling you (=mark my words)! From all the people who live now.adays, there will those who have not.yet died, when those difficulty days have appeared.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ameen: Here he seems responding to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">ameen: Here he seems responding to some recognition of the Kingdom on their part, so "Dass good! An I like tell you guys dis too," the regular Rabbinical teaching formula, could fit, as taking them one new step beyond their current understanding. It's not as if the disciples were complete buffoons that never caught on to anything, as they are sometimes made out to be in a kind of low comedy scenario (also in Jesus Christ Superstar).</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Biar langit deng bumi su ilang, ma Beta pung Kata-kata batahan tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if the sky and the earth disappear, nevertheless My Words will endure continually.” [EXEG: Gk is “my words” (broader), not “these words of mine” (more restricted).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** deleted /ni/ to broaden it,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** deleted /ni/ to broaden it, as in Gk.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong parlú jaga-jaga Tuhan pung datang<bt>We-exc need to carefully watch/be on guard for the Lord's coming</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais Yesus sambung Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jaga-jaga, te takuju sa Beta su muncul datang! Jang sampe bosong su sonde tau pikir deng batúl lai, ais bosong ada idop deng minum mabo, deng barepot cari idop ena-ena sa. Jang sampe bosong sonde baca dia pung tanda, tagal bosong batasibu deng urusan laen.<bt>Then Yesus connected His speaking saying, “Becareful, cuz suddenly I will appear! May it not be that you no longer know how to think correctly, so you are living getting drunk and busying yourselves seeking to just live pleasantly. May it not be that you don't read the signs, because you are preoccupied with other matters.</bt><v n="35" />Jang pikir bosong sonde kaná. Te Beta datang takuju. Deng kalo Beta datang kambali, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa sambunyi diri dari Beta pung muka.<bt>Don't think you won't be affected. Cuz (elaboration) I (will) come suddenly/unexpectedly. And when I come back, there will not be a single person who can hide himself from My face. [EXEG: TH] [NOTE to daughter translations: if you have a word for something like a spring trap, add it at the end of the second sentence “...suddenly/unexpectedly like a trap...” to close match the Gk. Initiated by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) “like a trap” was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) “like a trap” was undertranslated in earlier version</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo Beta datang kambali, sonde ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Kalo Beta datang kambali, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa sambunyi diri dari Beta pung muka.</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jadi jaga-jaga tarús. Sambayang jang putus-putus, ko biar bosong bisa batahan di teng-tenga itu susa samua. Deng bagitu, kalo Beta su datang kambali, bosong sonde malu badiri di Manusia Tulen pung muka.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), always be watching. Pray not stopping, so that you can endure in the midst of all that difficulty. In that way, when I have come back, you will not be embarrased to stand in front of the Authentic Human.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Tiap hari Yesus pi ajar di Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ma kalo su malam Dia kaluar dari Yerusalem ko pi tidor di kampong di gunung Saitun situ.<bt>Every day Yesus went to teach at the Central Worship House. But when it was night He went.out of Yerusalem to go sleep in a village on Saitun mountain over.there. [EXEG: Does “spend the night on the mount of Olives mean 1) Bethany (village on side of the mountain away from Jerusalem, about 3-4km/2mi.), or 2) mount of Olives/Gethsemane (on the side facing Jerusalem)? Marshall notes both possibiblities “it is possible to regard Luke's phrase here as referring to Bethany (Mk. 11:11f.; Mt. 21:17), but in 22:39 similar phraseology refers to the place where Jesus was arrested, which was nearer the city at Gethsemane. Jeremias, Jerusalem, 61f., accordingly holds that in the present verse Luke has mistaken the place of arrest (Gethsemane) for Jesus' usual lodging place (Bethany) out of ignorance of local geography. But both Jn. 18:2 and Lk. 22:39 imply that Jesus had spent several nights in the area of Gethsemane, and it is possible that we have two separate traditions, or that Jesus stayed in both places on different nights.” See also TN note at 19:29. Mark 11 has Jesus in Jerusulem during the day and sleeping in Bethany at night. TH, LN, BAGD, and Green describe the Gk word as meaning “to lodge”, which in English, at least, would not imply curled up in a garden.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:47</note><v n="38" />Papagi sakali, banya orang dong su datang bakumpul, ko mau dengar Dia ajar di Ruma Sambayang Pusat.<bt>Very early in the morning, many people had already come gathering in order to listen to Him teach at the Central Worship House.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos cari jalan ko mau bunu sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The chief priests seek a way to murder the Lord Yesus</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***expanded title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***expanded title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:1-5; Markus 14:1-2; Yohanis 11:45-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="22" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, su deka deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari bae, andia pesta Roti Sonde Pake Ragi. Di itu hari bae, dong ju horo domba ko bekin pesta Paska. Dong bekin bagitu ko inga tempo dolu, waktu dong pung nene-moyang kaluar dari Masir.<bt>At that time, it was near the Yahudi people's holiday, which was the feast of Bread Without Yeast. On that holiday, they also cut/slaughter a sheep to may a Paska feast. They did like that to remember the time long ago, when their ancestors come out of Masir [DISCOURSE: Expansion from vs. 7; background info appropriate here]. [KT: several MTT teams reacted against “Trailfood Bread”, not just because it was so different from the Indo, but it also did not evoke focus on ‘yeast’ to them. July 2014.]</bt><note reference="22:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27</note><v n="2" />Itu waktu, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong ada cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu sang Yesus. Ma dong taku itu orang banya bekin kaco, tagal dong suka dengar sang Dia.<bt>At that time the chief priests and the religion teachers were hunting for ways to murder Yesus. But they were afraid those many people would make chaos/riot, because they liked to listen to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aneloosin: not &quot;kill&quot; directly, but &quot;get"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">aneloosin: not "kill" directly, but "get rid," a euphemism.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yudas jual buang sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yudas sells.off/betrays the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:14-16; Markus 14:10-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dari Yesus pung ana bua dua blas orang dong, satu pung nama Yudas Iskariot. Waktu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos cari jalan ko mau bunu sang Yesus, setan dong pung bos ada maso pi Yudas pung hati.<bt>From Yesus' twelve underlings, one was named Yudas Iskariot. When the chief priests were seeking a way to murder Yesus, the head of the evil spirits entered into Yudas liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ais dia kaluar pi cari kapala agama pung bos-bos deng kapala jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dia mau basakongkol ko jual buang sang Yesus kasi dong.<bt>Then he went out to go seek the heads of religion and the head guard of the Central Worship House. He wanted to mutually.conspire with them to sell off (=betray) Yesus to them.</bt><v n="5" />Waktu itu bos-bos dong dengar Yudas pung omong bagitu, ju dong sanáng mau mati. Dong janji bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu! Kalo lu mau jual Yesus kasi sang botong, pasti botong bayar.&gt;&gt;<bt>When those bosses heard Yudas speaking like that, then they were very happy. They promised saying, “Ok! If you want to sell Yesus to us, surely we will pay.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do we want bosses here; does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">do we want bosses here; does carry the right connotation?</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Yudas satuju. Ju dia mulai cari-cari salák ko jual buang diam-diam sang Yesus kasi sang dong, ko biar orang banya dong sonde tau.<bt>Yudas agreed. Then he began to look for opportunities to sell off Yesus quietly to them, so that the many people would not know.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong sadia pesta Paska<bt>The Lord Yesus' underlings prepare the Paska feast</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:17-25; Markus 14:12-21; Yohanis 13:21-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ju orang Yahudi pung hari bae tu su sampe, ko dong mau horo domba ana ko bekin pesta Paska.<bt>Then that holiday of the Yahudi people arrived, for them to (ritually) slaughter a lamb for the Paska festival. [EXEG: undertranslated “Feast of Unleavened Bread” so as to not skew focus. It's in vs.1 where it belongs for foreground-background info.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais Yesus suru Petrus deng Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua pi lebe dolo, ko sadia kasi kotong makan pesta Paska sama-sama.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Yesus ordered Petrus and Yohanis saying, “You two go ahead to prepare for us-inc to eat the Paska feast together.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju dong dua tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Botong musti pi ator meja di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Thent the two of them answered saying, “Papa! Where should we go prepare the table?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong maso pi dalam kota Yerusalem, nanti bosong dapa katumu satu laki-laki ada masa'a kumbang aer. Pi iko sang dia sampe di ruma.<bt>He replied saying, “If you enter into Yerusalem city, you will enter a male who is shoulder.carrying a clay.pot of water. Follow him to a house.</bt><v n="11" />Kasi tau tuan ruma di situ bilang, &lt;Botong pung Bapa Guru ada minta kamar ko mau pake bekin pesta Paska deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Ada, ko?&gt;<bt>Tell the house owner there saying, ‘Our-exc Father Teacher is requesting a room to use to make the Paska feast with His underlings. Is there one?&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampa &gt; kamar @@ May 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tampa &gt; kamar @@ May 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Nanti itu tuan ruma kasi tunju sang bosong satu kamar luas di lante atas. Dia su sadia langkáp itu kamar. Tenga cuma bosong dua pi sadia makan di situ sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>That house owner will show you a wide room on the floor above (=not ground floor). He has completed prepared that room. The only thing lacking is for you two go just go prepare the food there.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais dong dua pi. Ju dong katumu deng samua yang Yesus su kasi tau memang sang dong. Ju dong sadia makan Paska di situ.<bt>So the two of them went. And they encountered everything which Yesus had told them beforehand. And they prepared the food from Paska there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pesta Paska<bt>Paska Feast</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:26-30; Markus 14:22-26; 1 Korintus 11:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu samua su siap, Yesus dong datang. Dia ame tampa di meja, deng Dia pung utusan dong ju dudu makan pesta.<bt>When everything was ready, Yesus (collective) came. He took a place at the table, and His commissioned.one/apostles [EXEG: Gk. ‘apostles’ here.] also sat.down to eat the feast. [EXEG: NRSV &amp; Marshall's phrasing “took his place at the table” is ambiguous between 1) sat at the head of the table, and 2) he sat down. Passover Seder rules suggest #1, but safer interpretation is just #2 as NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** removed “at the (head of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">*** removed “at the (head of the) table”</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su talalu kapingin dudu makan ini pesta Paska deng bosong, lebe dolo dari Beta dapa sangsara.<bt>Then Yesus told them saying, “I greatly desire to sit and eat this Paska feast with you-pl, before I obtain suffering.</bt><v n="16" />Tanda ini bae-bae. Te abis ini, Beta su sonde dudu makan ulang pesta Paska deng bosong lai. Nanti orang tau deng taráng-taráng bilang, Bapa ada pegang parenta, baru Beta makan pesta ulang lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Take good note of this. Cuz after this, I will not sit again to eat Paska feast with you anymore. Later when people plainly/clearly know that, Father is ruling, only then I will eat feast again.” [EXEG: “until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God” has complex possibilities, and wide range in translations. This rendering (also in 18) leaves open at least 3 possibilities: 1) until resurrection, 2) glorification at ascension, 3) glorification upon return and rule. Extensive work with one consultant.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tarús Dia angka ame galás yang ada isi bua anggor pung aer. Ais Dia minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, ju sorong itu galás kasi sang dong. Tarús Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tarima ini galás, ko bosong satu-satu minum.<bt>Next He picked up a glass which was filled with grape fruit liquid. Then He requested thankyou to the Lord God, and he extended that glass to them. Then He spoke saying, “Accept this glass, in order for each one of you to drink.</bt><v n="18" />Inga, é! Mulai ini malam, Beta su sonde minum aer anggor lai. Nanti orang tau deng taráng-taráng bilang, Bapa ada pegang parenta, baru Beta minum lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember! Starting from this night, I will not drink grape liquid again. Later when people clearly know that Father is ruling, only then I will drink again.” [NOTE: See EXEG note at 16.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais Dia angka ame roti satu balok, ju Dia minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti, ju sorong kasi sang dong. Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini roti ni, Beta pung badan yang Beta sarakan kasi sang bosong samua. Tiap kali bosong makan ini roti, bosong musti inga sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He picked up a loaf of bread, and He requested thankyou to the Lord God. Then He broke that bread into.bits, and extended it to them. He said, “This bread here, is My body which I hand.over to you all. Each time you-pl eat this bread, you must remember/think of Me.” [EXEG: Gk aspect on last clause is on-going “do this (durative) ... as a memorial, not just this once”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**** tightened to better reflect Gk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">**** tightened to better reflect Gk aspect (Helong)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="touto poieite ... anamneesin: do this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">touto poieite ... anamneesin: do this (durative) ... as a memorial, not just this once.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong musti makan ini, ko inga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Bosong musti makan ini, ko inga tarús sang Beta.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Waktu dong su makan abis, ju Dia angka ame galás isi aer anggor. Tarús Dia omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini anggor ni, Beta pung dara, yang tapo'a ko kasi salamat sang bosong. Tuhan Allah pake ini dara ko ika janji baru deng bosong.<bt>When they were finished eating, then He took a glass filled with grape liquid. Then He spoke again saying, “This grape here, is my blood, which is poured out to save you. The Lord God uses this blood to tie a new promise with you.</bt><note reference="22:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:31-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ma ati-ati, te ada orang yang sakarang dudu sama-sama di ini meja, yang nanti jual buang sang Beta.<bt>But becareful, cuz there is a person who now sits together at this table, who will sell Me off.</bt><note reference="22:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 41:10</note><v n="22" />Memang Beta, Manusia Tulen, musti mati iko Tuhan Allah pung mau. Ma orang yang jual buang sang Beta tu, awas! Te nanti dia pikol dia pung calaka!&gt;&gt;<bt>It's true that I, the Authentic Human, must die following the Lord God's will. But that person who sells Me off, should be careful! Cuz (elaboration) he will carry/bear his own misfortune!” [STYLE: Strong wording, almost veiled curse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma awas, te orang yang jual"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma awas, te orang yang jual buang sang Beta tu, nanti pikol dia pung calaka!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus pung ana bua dong mulai batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira sapa yang mau bekin jahat sang Dia bagitu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus' underlings began to ask.each.other saying, “Who do you think it is that will do evil like that to Him?” [NOTE: Check each language, if v.23 should also be utusan to match v.14.? Greek only uses pronoun 'them' here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong bakanjar so'al sapa yang paling bésar<bt>The Lord Yesus' underlings argue about who is the biggest/most.important</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ju Yesus pung ana bua dong mulai bakanjar bilang, sapa dari dong yang paling bésar.<bt>Then Yesus' underlings began to argue about who from them was the biggest/most.important.</bt><note reference="22:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:1, Markus 9:34, Lukas 9:46</note><v n="25" />Ma Yesus togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Di suku-bangsa yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan, raja dong tendes dong pung rakyat deng parenta lebe-lebe. Padahal dong mau ko rakyat subu sang dong bilang, &lt;Bapa yang tolong rakyat&gt;.<bt>But Yesus scolded them saying, “In the nations who don't know the Lord, the rajas press.down/oppress their citizens by ruling with excessive demands. But they actually want the citizens to call them saying, ‘Father who helps citizens&gt;&gt; [EXEG question: who calls them benefactors? TH, TN, NIV, CEV rulers call themselves; NLT, Marshall, irony, sarcasm--want to be called; Gk /euergetai/: helper of the people, benefactor (not defender as in TB)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***revised; added NOTE"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***revised; added NOTE</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euergetai: helper of the people, benefactor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">euergetai: helper of the people, benefactor (not defender as in BI)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Yesus togor sang dong, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma Yesus togor sang dong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Di bangsa-bangsa yang sonde kanál Tuhan, raja dong parenta lebe-lebe dong pung rakyat. Padahal dong mangaku bilang, orang yang pegang kuasa dong yang musti bela rakyat.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma bosong sonde bole bagitu. Yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia pung idop musti batúl-batúl jadi sama ke orang kici ko layani samua orang. Yang mau jadi bos musti layani sama ke tukang suru-suru.<bt>But you may not do like that. The one who wants to become a big person, his life must truly be like a small/unimportant person to serve all people. The one wants to be boss must serve all that a low.ranking.servant. [NOTE to daughter translations: Compare wording with Mark 9:35. Flesh it out similarly.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***revised to avoid a number of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***revised to avoid a number of problems</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neooteros: youngest. SK &quot;Who goin listen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">neooteros: youngest. SK "Who goin listen to da younges?"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma bosong sonde bole bagitu. Yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Ma bosong sonde bole bagitu. Yang mau jadi orang bésar, musti jadi sama ke ana kici. Yang mau jadi bos musti layani samua orang.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:25-27; 23:11, Markus 9:35; 10:42-44</note><v n="27" />Bosong pikir coba, orang bésar tu, yang mana? Orang yang dudu di meja, ko, yang layani meja? Su tantu orang yang dudu tu, dia yang orang bésar, to? Padahal Beta sonde bekin diri bagitu. Beta datang ko layani sang bosong.<bt>You try and think, which one is the big person? The person who sits at the table, or, the the one who serves the table? Surely the one who sits is the one who is the big person, right. However, I don't make myself like that. I came/come to serve you.</bt><note reference="22:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:12-15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Bosong ni yang salalu sama-sama deng Beta waktu Beta kaná sangsara.<bt>You here are the ones always together with Me when I am afflicted with suffering.</bt><v n="29" />Beta pung Bapa su angka sang Beta ko pegang parenta di Dia pung karaja'an. Jadi sakarang Beta ju angka sang bosong,<bt>My Father has lifted/appointed Me to rule in His kingdom. So now I also lift/appoint you,</bt><v n="30" />ko biar nanti bosong dudu makan satu meja deng Beta di sorga. Beta ju kasi kuasa ko bosong parenta dua blas suku yang ada di Isra'el.&gt;&gt;<bt>so that you will sit and eat at the same table with Me in heaven. I also will give power for you to rule the twelve clans who are in Israel.” [EXEG: judging = Marshall “judicial function”; TH, all versions; only Green and TN, evokes both judge and ruler; see also context of vs. 31 “sift like wheat”; So ‘rule’ has support, but is problematic, but ‘judge/decide cases’ may also be too narrow for meaning in context.]</bt><note reference="22:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 19:28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau nanti Petrus manyangkal sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus tells that Petrus will deny Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:31-35; Markus 14:27-31; Yohanis 13:36-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u. Setan dong pung bos ada mau coba kasi pisa bosong samua dari Beta, sama ke orang tapis barás ko kasi pisa dia pung katák dari barás.<bt>Then Yesus told Petrus saying, “Pe'u (nickname). The boss of the evil spirits will try to separate you-pl from Me, like a person winnows rice to separate the dregs/husks from the rice.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katák = ; sift (?)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">katák = ; sift (?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di tulisan bahasa Yunani, dong subu Petrus pung nama laen, andia Simon.<bt>In the Yunani language writing, they mention Petrus' other name, which is Simon.</bt></note><v n="32" />Ma Beta ada sambayang kasi sang lu, Pe'u, ko biar lu parcaya tarús sang Beta. Nanti kalo lu su kambali datang di Beta, na, lu musti kasi kuat lu pung sodara dong pung hati.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I am praying for you, Pe'u, so that you-sg continually believe in Me. Later when you have come back to Me, then you must strengthen/encourage your siblings' livers.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***iko &gt; parcaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">***iko &gt; parcaya</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ju Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, Papa! Beta sonde akan kasi tenga sang Papa. Te beta sadia maso bui sama-sama deng Papa. Biar mati sama-sama deng Papa ju, bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus replied saying, “No, Papa! I am not going to leave Papa. Cuz I am prepared to enter jail together with Papa. Even to die together with Papa, would be ok.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u! Dengar bae-bae. Ini malam, ayam balóm kokore'o, ma lu su manyangkal tiga kali bilang, lu sonde kanál sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Pe'u! Listen carefully. This night, the chicken will not.yet crow, but you-sg will already have denied three times saying, you do not know Me.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung orang musti siap kaná susa<bt>The Lord Yesus' people must be prepared to be afflicted with difficulty [NOTE: title supported by TN, Marshall, Green]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais ju Yesus omong sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tempo hari, waktu Beta utus sang bosong ko pi kasi tau Beta pung Kabar Bae pi mana-mana, Beta bilang bosong sonde usa bawa doi, tas, deng sandal. Itu waktu, bosong ada kurang apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus spoke with them saying, “That time when I commissioned you-pl to go tell My Good News everywhere, I said you didn't need to take money, bag, and sandals. At that time, what did you lack?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju, Yesus omong sang dong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">Abis ju, Yesus omong sang dong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Tempo hari, waktu Beta utus sang bosong ko pi kasi tau Beta pung Kabar Bae pi mana-mana, Beta larang ko sonde bole bawa doi, tas, deng sandal. Itu waktu, bosong ada kurang apa?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Tempo hari, botong sonde kurang satu apa ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they enthusiastically replied saying, “At that time we did not lack a single thing!&gt;</bt><note reference="22:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:9-10, Markus 6:8-9, Lukas 9:3, 10:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais Dia omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma sakarang su laen. Kalo bosong ada doi, na, bawa. Kalo ada tas, na, bawa ju. Kalo sonde ada kalewang, na, pi jual bosong pung baju satu, ko béli.<bt>Then He spoke further saying, “But now it's different. If you have money, na, take it. If a bag, na, take it also. If don't have a fighting.sword, na, go sell one of your shirts/clothings, to buy one.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="himation: outer garment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z" status="Information">himation: outer garment</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Te orang Yahudi dong anggap Beta ke orang jahat. Ais sabantar lai dong datang tangkap sang Beta. Te itu kaná pas deng apa yang ba'i Yesaya su tulis memang bilang:<bt>Cuz the Yahudi people consider Me like an evil person. So in a little bit more they will come capture Me. Cuz that fits exactly with what grandfather Yesaya wrote beforehand, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dong cap ame sang Dia sama ke orang jahat!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;They stamp/brand/categorise Him as an evil person!”&gt;</bt><note reference="22:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Dong kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Botong ada bawa parang dua.&gt;&gt;<bt>They told saying, “Papa! We've brought two machetes.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="does this need a better transition"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">does this need a better transition to finish above quote</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Cukup su. Sonde usa omong itu lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “Enough! It's not neccessary to speak about that anymore!” [EXEG: Gk ambiguous. 1) enough swords; 2) enough said. UNSs couldn't get either--too vague. Problems with #1, so under consultant guidance we went with #2 (see Ex.Summ, strongly supported). Our protocols preserve ambiguity where BOTH are given by UNSs and BOTH are acceptable. In this case they got ZERO meaning, so we went with the safer, and avoided the more problematic.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi sambayang di gunung Saitun<bt>The Lord Yesus go to pray at Saitun mountain</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:36-46; Markus 14:32-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Abis makan Paska ju, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong kaluar pi gunung Saitun, sama ke biasa.<bt>After eating Paksa then Yesus and His underlings went out to Saitun mountain, like usual.</bt><v n="40" />Sampe di situ ju, Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti sambayang ko biar bosong jang kaná coba'an.&gt;&gt;<bt>Arriving there, He told them saying, “You-pl need to pray so that you don't get afflicted with temptation.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="coba'an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">coba'an</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais Dia ondor dari dong sadiki. Dia jalan sonde talalu jao, ju tikam lutut ko sambayang bilang,<bt>Then He backed.away from them a little. He walked not too far, and knelt to pray saying,</bt><v n="42" />&lt;&lt;Papa! Kalo Papa mau, na, angka buang jao-jao ini sangsara dari Beta. Ma jang iko Beta pung mau; biar iko Papa pung mau sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>“Papa! If Papa wants, na, pickup and throw this suffering far away from Me. But don't follow My will; let it just be Papa's will.”</bt><v n="43" />[Ais Tuhan pung ana bua satu dari sorga datang ko kasi kuat Dia pung hati.<bt>[Then one of the Lord's underlings from heaven came and strengthened/encouraged His liver.</bt><v n="44" />Te Dia su sangsara satenga mati, sampe Dia pung karingat tetes kaluar sama ke dara.]<bt>Cuz He was suffering very greatly, to the point that His sweat drops came out like blood.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tetes ?? CHECK"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">tetes ?? CHECK</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:43-44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae sonde tulis ayat 43-44 ni.<bt>The oldest and best Yunani language writings do not write this verse 43-44.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Sambayang abis, ju Dia bangun ko pi katumu deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Ma dong ada tidor, tagal dong talalu cape deng hati susa.<bt>After praying, then He got up to go meet His underlings. But they were sleeping, because they were exceedingly tired and their livers were distressed. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><v n="46" />Ais Yesus togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Akurang ko bosong ada tidor?! Lebe bae bosong sambayang ko biar coba'an datang, na, bosong sonde jato.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus scolded saying, “Naa! Why are you sleeping?! It's better you pray so that if temptation come, na, you will not fall.” [EXEG: NLT. Although wording in 40 &amp; 46 is similar (but not identical) in Gk. phrased differently here like NLT to broaden the reader's fuller understanding of the possibilities of what is meant.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong tangkap sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They capture the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:47-56; Markus 14:43-50; Yohanis 18:3-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Yesus masi omong bagitu, te Yudas (satu dari ana bua dua blas orang tu), datang deng bawa orang banya. Dia datang deka-deka sang Yesus ko mau paló-ciom sang Dia.<bt>Yesus was still speaking like that, when Yudas (one of those twelve people), came and brought many people. He came close to Yesus in order to hug-kiss Him. [NOTE: Gk is only "kiss"; KM here is a single complex action. Check individual daughter lgs.]</bt><v n="48" />Ma Yesus togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Yudas! Lu mau jual buang sang Manusia Tulen ni pake ciom, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus scolded him saying, “We, [+get attention] Yudas! Are you trying to sell/betray off the Authentic Human with a kiss, or (what)?” [+tag]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Waktu Yesus pung ana bua laen dong dapa tau Yudas pung akal jahat bagitu, ju dong tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Botong lawan sang dong sa, ko? Te botong ada bawa parang.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus' other underlings found out Yudas evil plan like that, then asked Yesus saying, “Papa! Do we just oppose/fight them? Cuz we have brought machetes.”</bt><v n="50" />Ju satu dari dong cabu dia pung parang, ais potong bekin putus satu orang pung daon talinga sablá kanan. Itu orang tu, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung orang suru-suru.<bt>Then one of them pull out his machete, and cut severed one person's right ear. That person was the servant of the big boss of the Yahudi priests (=high priest).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Suda lai! Jang lawan sang dong!&gt;&gt; Ju Dia sonto itu orang pung talinga, ais bekin bae sang dia.<bt>But Yesus replied saying, “Stop! Don't oppose them!” Then He touched that person's ear, and healed him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Orang-orang yang datang tangkap Yesus tu andia: kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, tua-tua adat, tukang jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat, deng orang laen lai. Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Bosong pikir Beta ni, orang jahat, sampe bosong datang tangkap sang Beta pake kalewang deng kayu kudung, ko?<bt>Those people who came to capture Yesus were: the religion bosses, the traditional elders and the guards of the Central Worship House, and other people too. Yesus asked them saying, “How is it? Do you think that I here am an evil person, so that you come capture Me using swords and night.sticks/clubs? [EXEG: Gk /machaira/ is the same word in vs. 36, 38, and 52. It is a semi-generic term that includes a range of sharp cutting instruments from dedicated fighting swords and sabers down to knives and daggers (LN, BADG). So the teams and UNS's feel it is appropriate to be context relevant in the translation of the term. Soldiers, guards, and symbols of fighting wars are translated “sword”. In an occupied territory with soldiers fearful of attacks by rebels, it is appropriate for fishermen to have access to machetes (as work tools) rather than happening to have full-fledged fighting swords handy. Hence the different translations.]</bt><v n="53" />Tiap hari Beta ajar sang bosong di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ma sonde ada satu orang datang tangkap sang Beta ju. Ma biar sa! Ini, bosong pung waktu su. Sakarang setan dong pung bos yang pung kuasa ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Every day I taught you in the Central Worship House, but there was not a single person who came to capture Me. But never mind! This is your time. Now it's the boss of the evil spirits who controls this!” [EXEG: “power of darkness” = Satan reigning; unpack metonymy as per TN, TH, Green.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="EXEG: Do we need or want"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">EXEG: Do we need or want a ftn about “powers of darkness”? *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:53" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:47, 21:37</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus manyangkal sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Petrus denies the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:57-58, 69-75; Markus 14:53-54, 66-72; Yohanis 18:12-18, 25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Ais dong tangkap ame sang Yesus, ju dong hela bawa sang Dia pi kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung ruma. Petrus ju ada iko sambunyi-sambunyi dari balakang.<bt>Then they captured Yesus, and they dragged brought Him to the house of the *high priest. Petrus also went following along secretly from behind.</bt><v n="55" />Di itu ruma pung kintal orang ada bekin api unggun. Petrus ju pi iko dudu panggang api di situ.<bt>At that house's yard people had made a camp.type.fire. Petrus then went to also sit and warm himself at that fire there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="api unggun = campfire Is this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:05Z">api unggun = campfire Is this Indonesian?</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Ada satu hamba parampuan dapa lia sang Petrus dudu deka api. Dia lia bae-bae Petrus pung muka, ais dia lapor kasi tau orang laen di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee! Ini orang ju iko-iko sang Yesus!&gt;&gt;<bt>A female servant saw Petrus sitting near the fire. She looked carefully at Petrus' face, then she reported told the other people there saying, “Hee! [+problem]This person was also following along with Yesus!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Ma Petrus manyangkal bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Beta sonde kanál itu Orang ma. Lu ada tau apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus denied/mislead saying, “No! I do not know that Person [+protest]. What do you-sg know?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="58" />Sonde lama, ju ada satu orang buang mata ko lia sang Petrus, abis omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang, lu ni, satu dari Yesus pung orang dong, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Not much longer, then a person look over and saw Petrus, then spoke saying, “Surely, you-sg here, are one of Yesus' people, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Lu sambarang sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus protested saying, “No! You are just being thoughtlyess/reckless!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="59" />Kira-kira satu jam lai ju, ada satu orang laen lai omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Woi! Beta tau, ini orang ni, Yesus pung ana bua satu, te dia ju orang Galilea.&gt;&gt;<bt>About one more hour then yet another person spoke saying, “Woi! [+challenge] I know this person here is one of Yesus' underlings, cuz he is also a Galilea person.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Ma Petrus manyangkal deng karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu omong kosong tu!&gt;&gt; Pas Petrus omong bagitu, ju ayam kokore'o.<bt>But Petrus denied strongly saying, “You're speaking emptily there (=lying)!” Exactly when Petrus spoke like that, then the chicken crowed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Ju Yesus bale muka ko lia sang dia. Ais Petrus inga Yesus pung omong tadi tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini malam, ayam balóm kokore'o, ma lu su manyangkal sang Beta tiga kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus turned his head to look at him. Then Petrus remembered that earlier speaking of Yesus' saying, “Tonight, the chicken will not yet crow, but [contrary to expectation] you will have already denied Me three times.”</bt><v n="62" />Inga ame bagitu, ju Petrus jalan kaluar dari itu kintal deng manangis makarereu.<bt>Remembering that, then Petrus went out from that yard crying sobbingly/remorsefully. [NOTE to daughter translations: Helong team had problem with /makarereu/ here, seeing it as "loud", whereas KM UNS's saw it as indicating remorse and/or grief. Is this a FT problem for other lgs?]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong papoko deng hina sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They beat and be.offensive.to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:67-68; Markus 14:65)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Ais, itu orang yang jaga sang Yesus mulai olok-olok sang Dia, deng papoko barmaen sang Dia.<bt>Then, those people who were guarding Yesus began to mock Him, and repeatedly beat Him.</bt><v n="64" />Tarús dong tutu ame Dia pung mata pake kaen, ais dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Kalo lu jadi Tuhan pung jubir, na, coba lu rai! Sapa yang falungku sang lu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they shut His eyes using cloth, and asked saying, “Hoi! [+disbelief] If you-sg are the Lord's spokesperson, na, try to divine/discern! Who is it that is punching you?</bt><v n="65" />Ais ju dong maki ancor sang Dia.<bt>Then they verbally abused/swore.at Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: /maki ancor/ is idiomatic Kupang. Don't be literal with ancor here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maki ancor ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">maki ancor =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus di tampa urus parkara agama<bt>The Lord Yesus in the place of deciding religious litigations</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check this for key term consistency;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">check this for key term consistency; urus or putus</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:59-66; Markus 14:55-64; Yohanis 18:19-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66" />Papagi sakali, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama, deng tua-tua adat dong su bakumpul ko urus Yesus pung parkara. Ais dong suru ko orang hela bawa Yesus datang di tampa urus parkara agama.<bt>Early morning, the heads of the Yahudi religion, the religion teachers, and the traditional elders had gathered to handle Yesus' litigation/case. Then they order that a person drag bring Yesus to the place of dealing with religious litigations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Papagi sakali, samua orang di tampa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Papagi sakali, samua orang di tampa urus parkara agama tu, basakongkol ko mau bunu sang Yesus. Yang dudu di situ, andia agama Yahudi pung kapala-kapala, guru-guru agama deng tua-tua adat dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="67" />Waktu Dia su maso, ju dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba lu kasi tau dolu! Lu ni memang batúl-batúl itu Kristus, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When He had entered, then they asked Him saying, “Tell us! Are you here truly the Kristus, [+tag question]?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar Beta manyao batúl ju, bosong sonde parcaya.<bt>And/then Yesus replied saying, “Even if I answer the truth, you-pl won't believe.”</bt><v n="68" />Ais kalo Beta tanya bale sang bosong satu hal, pasti bosong sonde manyao.<bt>Then if I reciprocate and ask you something, surely you won't answer.</bt><v n="69" />Sonde lama lai, Tuhan Allah mau pake Dia pung kuasa hebat, ko angka nae sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Ais Beta dudu di Dia pung sablá kanan ko parenta sama-sama deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Not much longer, the Lord God will use His amazing power, to raise Me up, this Authentic Human. Then I will sit at His right side to govern/rule together with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***removed paragraph; deleted opening /ma/"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">***removed paragraph; deleted opening /ma/</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:69" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong samua tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, lu pikir lu ni, Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then they all asked saying, “If that's the case, do you think that you here are the Lord God's Child, [+tag question]?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang, bosong pung omong bagitu, batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “Yes, that speaking of your's like that is correct.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: Helong team found this vague."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">NOTE: Helong team found this vague. Is this a FT problem for other lgs.? OK in Dhao</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="71" />Ju itu orang yang urus parkara dong rame-rame omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong samua su dengar sandiri, aa? Dia angka diri jadi Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Ini, hojat! Iko kotong pung atoran agama, kalo ada orang bekin diri sama ke Tuhan, itu orang musti mati. Jadi karmana? Kotong sonde parlú saksi lai. Hukum mati sang Dia su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those people who handle litigations ethusiastically talked saying, “We-inc all have heard ourselves, right? He lifts himself to be the Lord God's Child. This is slander/blasphemy! According to our-inc religious regulations, if someone makes himself the same as the Lord, that person must die. So (consequently) how is it? We-inc don't need witnesses anymore. Sentence Him to death.” [NOTE to daughter translations: /Ini hojat/ works well for Kupang, but is often hard to reflect in other lgs. It is implied and reinforces the problem. ALT: Sonde bole bagitu! Or omit. Make sure the text still flows.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa sang Tuhan Yesus pi gubernor Pilatus<bt>They bring the Lord Yesus to gubernor Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:1-2, 11-14; Markus 15:1-5; Yohanis 18:28-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="23" />
      <v n="1" />Ma, yang urus parkara agama Yahudi dong tu, sonde ada pung hak ko hukum mati orang. Andia ko dong bawa sang Yesus pi mangada sang gubernor dari pamarenta Roma di situ, andia Pilatus. Dong mau ko gubernor yang hukum sang Dia.<bt>But, those who were taking care of Yahudi religious litigations, did not have the right/authority to sentence people to death. That's why they brought Yesus to face the Governor from the Roma government there, who was Pilatus. They wanted that the governor be the one to sentence/punish Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu, ju samua orang yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Abis itu, ju samua orang yang dudu di tampa urus parkara agama tu, bawa sang Yesus pi mangada sang Gubernor Pilatus. Dong mau ko Gubernor hukum sang Yesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi sampe di gubernor pung muka, ju dong kasi tau Yesus pung sala-sala dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang ni, tukang lawan pamarenta Roma. Dia ajar bilang, orang jang bayar pajak kasi pamarenta. Dia ju angka diri bilang dia ni, Kristus, orang Yahudi pung raja.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) arriving in front of the governor, then they told Yesus' wrongs saying, “This person here, is a habitual opposer to the Roma government. He teaches that people shouldn't pay tax to the government. He also lifts himself up saying that he here is Kristus, the Yahudi people's raja.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dengar bagitu, ju gubernor tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Lu ni, orang Yahudi pung raja, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then the governor asked them saying, “Is that true? Are you the Yahudi people's raja [+tag question]?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl. Sama ke pak omong tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, “True. It's like what father  (=you) says there.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pak yang omong bagitu."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Pak yang omong bagitu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Pareksa abis, ju gubernor mangada itu kapala agama pung bos-bos deng itu orang banya. Ais dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta sonde dapa ini Orang pung sala sadiki ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>After examing him, the governor faced those chief priests and those many people. Then he said, “It's like this. I don't find this Person has even a little bit of wrong.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma dong batahan bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, pak gub. Ini orang pi ajar di mana-mana, tusu-tusu rakyat ko marontak. Dia bekin kaco mulai dari propinsi Galilea sampe di kota Yerusalem sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they persisted saying, “No, father gub. This person goes teaching everywhere, poking (=encouraging) citizens to rebel. He had made chaos starting from Galilea province to Yerusalem city here.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor kirim Tuhan Yesus pi raja Herodes<bt>The Governor sends the Lord Yesus to Raja Herodes</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dengar bagitu ju, gubernor tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, dia ni, orang Galilea, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then the governor asked them saying, “If that's the case, is he a Galilea person?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, pak. Dia dari Galilea!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, “True, Father. He is from Galilea!”</bt><v n="7" />Dapa tau bagitu ju, gubernor suru dong antar sang Yesus pi mangada sang raja Herodes, yang parenta propinsi Galilea. Itu waktu, dia ada di kota Yerusalem.<bt>Finding out like that, then the governor ordered them to take Yesus to go face raja Herodes who governed Galilea province. At at time, he was in the city of Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***fixed ambiguity (Feb 2008)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">***fixed ambiguity (Feb 2008)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Naa, raja Herodes su dengar banya carita so'al Yesus, deng dia su kapingin lia sang Yesus dari dolu. Dia ada harap-harap ko bisa lia Yesus kasi tunju satu-dua tanda heran. Andia ko, waktu dong antar Yesus pi sang dia, dia pung hati sanáng.<bt>Naa [+shift], raja Herodes had heard lots about Yesus and he was desiring to see Yesus from before. He was hoping to be able to see Yesus show one-or-two miracles. That's why, when they brought Yesus to him, his liver was happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu dong bawa sang Yesus pi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Waktu dong bawa sang Yesus pi sampe di raja Herodes pung muka, ju dia sanáng mo mati, tagal dia su dengar banya carita so'al Yesus, deng dia su kapingin lia sang Yesus dari dolu. Dia ada harap-harap ko bisa lia Yesus kasi tunju satu dua tanda heran.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ju Herodes tanya macam-macam hal sang Yesus, ma Dia sonde manyao apa-apa.<bt>Then he asjed all.sorts of things to Yesus, but He didn't relpy at all.</bt><v n="10" />Herodes masi ba'omong deng Yesus, ma kapala agama pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong mulai omong ulang lai Yesus pung sala macam-macam sang raja.<bt>Herodes was still talking with Yesus, but the chief priests and the religion teachers began to accuse Yesus again of all.sorts of wrongs. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk here is ambiguous between whether Herod had finished and the accusations started as simultaneous or sequential. English translations vary on that point. So if simultaneous as above is problematic, then just use a sequential connector ‘then’.]</bt><v n="11" />Ais raja Herodes deng dia pung tantara dong mulai iko ejek deng olok-olok bekin hina sang Yesus. Ju dong kasi pake sang Dia satu baju bagus sama ke raja dong biasa pake, ais dong ejek tarús. Ais dong kirim pulang sang Dia pi gubernor Pilatus.<bt>Then raja Herodes and his soldiers began to also riducle and say derogatory things about Yesus. Then they put on Him some nice clothing like rajas ususally were, then they continued to ridule. Then they sent him back to governor Pilatus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="consistency: ejek or olok? are they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">consistency: ejek or olok? are they the same ***juba &gt; baju; /ais dong ejek tarús/ added to stop thinking that they were genuinely showing honour to Jesus<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Dolu itu gubernor deng raja Herodes bamusu. Ma mulai itu hari dong dua basobat.<bt>Previously that governor and raja Herodes were mutual enemies. But starting from that day the two of them were mutual.friends.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basobat = is that indonesian or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">basobat = is that indonesian or km</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor kasi jato hukum mati sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The Governor gives a death sentence to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:15-26; Markus 15:6-15; Yohanis 18:39--19:16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais ju gubernor Pilatus pange itu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat laen dong, sama-sama deng itu orang banya, ko datang bakumpul dengar dia pung putusan.<bt>After that, governor Pilatus called those chief priests and other traditional leaders together with those many people, to come gather and hear his decision.</bt><v n="14" />Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong bawa Yesus datang sang beta, deng tudu sang Dia bilang, Dia suka tusu-tusu rakyat ko malawan pamarenta Roma. Beta su pareksa sang Dia alus-alus di bosong pung muka, ma beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa.<bt>He spoke saying, “You-pl brought Yesus to me, and accused him, saying He likes to stir up the people to oppose the Roma government. I have examined Him very carefully (in detail) in front of you, but I have not found any thing He has done wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apostrephonta: turning the people away from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">apostrephonta: turning the people away from allegiance to Rome was the hot button the leaders pressed. "misleading" in some translations misses the political overtones because it sounds like maybe Jesus' doctrine wasn't pure enough for the religious leaders; but Pilate wouldn't have taken that argument as seriously as he took "apostrephonta."</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Raja Herodes su pareksa sang Dia lai, ma sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa ju. Andia ko dia kirim kambali ini Orang sang beta. Ini Orang sonde ada pung sala apa-apa, jadi beta sonde bisa hukum mati sang Dia.<bt>Raja Herodes has also examined Him, but didn't find any thing He did wrong either. That's why he sent this Person back to me. This Person hasn't done any wrong, so I cannot sentence Him to death.</bt><v n="16" />Jadi beta mau putus bagini: beta suru firuk sang Dia, ais beta lapás sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), I am going to decide like this: I will order to whip Him, and then I will release Him.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong mulai batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde bisa! Bunu sang Dia. Lapás sang Barabas sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then they began to yell enthusiastically/boisterously saying, “Not.allowed! Murder Him. Just release Barabas.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">[Dong batarea bagitu, tagal tiap taon kalo orang Yahudi dong bekin pesta Paska, gubernor biasa lapás satu orang bui iko dong pung mau.]<bt>[They yelled like that, because every year when the Yahudi people had Paska feast, the governor usually released one jail person according to their desires.]</bt><note reference="23:17" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ayat dalam kurung ni, sonde ada di tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua dong.<bt>This verse in the parenthesis, is not found in the Yunani language writing which are the very oldest.</bt></note><v n="19" />(Barabas ni, maso bui tagal dia jadi tukang kipas, marontak lawan pamarenta Roma di kota Yerusalem, deng dia ju bunu orang.)<bt>(This Barabas, was put in jail because he was a habitual fan-er (stirred up the people) to rebel against the Roma government in Yerusalem city, and he also murder person/people.)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma gubernor mau lapás sang Yesus. Jadi dia tanya ulang sang orang banya dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana kalo beta lapás sang Yesus ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>But the governor wanted to free Yesus. So he asked again to those many people saying, “How about it if I release this Yesus here?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ma dong samua batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang sa! Paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they all yelled boisterously saying, “No! Just nail kill Him on the crossed wood! Nail kill Him on the crossed wood!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma gubernor rasa itu sonde batúl, ais dia tanya ulang lai kali yang katiga bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko beta musti paku bekin mati sang Dia bagitu? Dia pung jahat apa? Beta su pareksa sang Dia, ma beta sonde dapa satu alasan ju, ko mau hukum bekin mati sang Dia. Jadi biar ko beta suru firuk sang Dia sa, ais lapás sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the governor felt that that was not right, so he asked again for the third time saying, “Why should I nail kill Him like that? What is his evil? I have examined Him, but I have not found even one reason why I should sentence Him to death. So (consequently), just let me order to whip Him, and then free Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ gantong changed to paku to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">@@ gantong changed to paku to avoid impression of "death by hanging" juga = to ju??<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma itu orang samua batarea lebe kuat lai, ko paksa mau paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang. Ahirnya, gubernor sonde bisa tahan,<bt>But all those people yelled even louder, to force him to nail kill him on the crossed wood. Finally, the governor could not endure anymore,</bt><v n="24" />ju dia putus iko dong pung mau sa.<bt>so he decided to just follow their will.</bt><v n="25" />Ais dia lapás sang Barabas, yang tukang marontak deng tukang bunu orang tu. Ma dia sarakan Yesus pi dong pung tangan, ko biar dong bekin sang Dia iko dong pung mau.<bt>So he freed Barabas, that habitual rebel and habitual murderer. But he surrendered Yesus to their hands, so that they could do to Him according to their desire. [NOTE to daughter translations: mirror the ambiguity of the Greek here and preserve “they” and “their hands” in last sentence. Specifying who actually has the rights and doesn't have the rights to crucify Jesus would make the info load inappropriately heavy here. The solution is to put “Roman soldiers” in vs. 26.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong paku tagantong sang Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang<bt>They nail hanging the Lord Yesus on the *cross (crossed wood)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:32-44; Markus 15:21-32; Yohanis 19:17-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais itu, tantara Roma dong hela bawa sang Yesus kaluar dari kota Yerusalem. Di tenga jalan dong katumu satu orang dari kota Kirene, nama Simon. Dia baru datang dari luar kota. Dong paksa sang dia ko pikol ganti Yesus pung kayu palang, ais jalan iko Yesus pung balakang.<bt>After that, the Roman soldiers pulled brought Yesus outside of Yerusalem city. In the middle of the road they met a person from Kirene city, named Simon. He was just coming in from outside the city. They forced him to substitute carry Yesus' crossed wood, then to walk following behind Yesus. [DISCOURSE (referent): Roman soldiers. Initiated by consultant. (See note at 23:25).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** restructured to remove ambiguity (Feb"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">*** restructured to remove ambiguity (Feb 2008) ; *** (2009) added “Roman soldiers” because of referent tracking issues in vs.25</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di tenga jalan dong katumu satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Di tenga jalan dong katumu satu orang yang baru datang dari kota Kirene. Dia pung nama Simon.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Itu hari, banya orang datang iko manonton sang Yesus. Ada ju mama-mama yang manangis makarereu sang Dia.<bt>That day, many people come to join in watching Yesus. There were women who cried sobbingly/remorsefully for Him.</bt><v n="28" />Dengar dong manangis bagitu, ju Yesus mangada sang dong, ais omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mama-mama dari Yerusalem. Sonde usa manangis kasi Beta. Lebe bae manangis kasi bosong pung diri sandiri, deng bosong pung ana-ana dong.<bt>Seeing them cry like that, then Yesus faced them, and spoke saying, “We! [+get attention] Mothers of Yerusalem. Don't cry for Me. It's better to cry for your own selves and your children.</bt><v n="29" />Te nanti beso-lusa susa bésar mau datang, sampe orang omong bilang, &lt;Parampuan yang paling barontong, andia parampuan yang sonde parná barana, deng yang sonde parná kasi susu ana mera.&gt;<bt>Cuz tomorrow-the.next.day (near future) great difficulty will come, to the point that people, say, ‘The women who are the most fortunate, are women who have never given birth, and never nursed newborns.’</bt><v n="30" />Waktu itu susa bésar datang, orang dong sangsara mau mati, sampe dong minta bilang, &lt;Lebe bae, gunung-gunung rubu datang ko tendes ame sang botong su!&gt; Dong ju omong bilang, &lt;Deng sangsara bagini, lebe bae bukit-bukit kubur ame sang botong su!&gt;<bt>When those difficult days come, people will suffer greatly, to the point that they will ask saying, ‘It's better, [if] the mountains fall over and crush us down!&gt; The also speak saying, ‘With suffering like this, it's better the hills bury us!&gt;</bt><note reference="23:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 10:8, Dunya Model Baru 6:16</note><v n="31" />Naa, kalo orang bisa bekin susa bagini buat orang yang sonde ada pung sala, apalai deng orang jahat?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift], if people can cause suffering like this for people who have not done wrong, even more.so with evil people?” [EXEG: following Marshall, Barclay, CEV note &amp; TN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Have a look at NCV"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Have a look at NCV</Message></Annotation><note reference="23:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang bisa bekin bagini kasi pohon yang masi idop, apalai deng pohon yang su mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>The original Yunani language writing says, ‘If people can do like this with trees that are still living, even.more.so with trees which are dead.”</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Waktu tantara dong bawa sang Yesus tu, dong ju hela bawa dua orang jahat ko mau hukum bekin mati sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>When the soldiers were bringing Yesus, they also dragged brough two evil people to punish kill together with Him.</bt><v n="33" />Dong sampe di satu tampa, nama &lt;Tulang Kapala&gt;. Ju dong paku sang Yesus deng itu dua orang jahat, di dong satu-satu pung kayu palang. Ais dong tanam kasi badiri itu kayu palang dong. Dong paku tagantong orang jahat satu di Yesus pung sablá kanan, deng yang satu lai di Dia pung sablá kiri.<bt>They arrived at a place, called &lt;Head Bone (=skull)&gt;. Then they nailed Yesus and those two evil people on each one's crossed wood. Then they planted standing up those crossed woods. They hung one evil person on Yesus' right side, and the other one on His left side. [NOTE to daughter translations: Luke version doesn't mention proper name of ‘Golgotha’; just ‘Place of the Skull’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong sampe di satu tampa, dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Dong sampe di satu tampa, dia pung nama Golgota. Dia pung arti, bilang, &lt;tampa tulang kapala&gt;. Ju dong paku sang Yesus deng itu dua orang jahat di dong satu-satu pung kayu palang. Ais dong tanam kasi badiri itu kayu palang dong. Dong gantong orang jahat satu di Yesus pung sablá kanan, deng yang satu lai di Dia pung sablá kiri.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />[Itu waktu, Yesus sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Lupa buang ini orang dong pung sala, te dong sonde tau apa yang dong bekin.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[At that time, Yesus prayed saying, “Father! Completely forget these people's wrong/s, cuz they don't know what they do.”]</bt><note reference="23:34a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kalimat dalam kurung ni, sonde ada dalam banya tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae.<bt>That verse in parentheses, does not exist in many of the oldest and best Yunani language writings.</bt></note>Ais ju tantara dong hela lot ko mau tau sapa yang dapa Dia pung pakean.<bt>Then the soldiers pull/drew lots to find out who got His clothes. [NOTE to daughter translations: if RL discourse structure requires this irrealis clause to be fulfilled (made realis), then add “and they divided up his clothes” /Ju dong bagi Dia pung pakean/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="23:34b" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Banya orang datang manonton di itu tampa. Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong olok-olok sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su kasi salamat orang laen, ma sonde bisa kasi salamat Dia pung diri sandiri. Kalo Dia ni batúl-batúl Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su pili memang, na, tenga ko Dia turun sandiri dari itu kayu palang suda.&gt;&gt;<bt>Many people came to watch at that place. The Yahudi leaders ridiculed Yesus saying, “He has saved other people, but can't save His own self. If He here really is Kristus, whom the Lord God choose beforehand, na, let Him get himself down from that crossed wood.” [EXEG: not chief priests here, but leaders.]</bt><note reference="23:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Itu tantara dong ju ejek sang Dia. Dong kasi minum sang Dia anggor asam,<bt>Those soldiers also ridiculed Him. They gave Him sour grape(juice) to drink,</bt><note reference="23:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:22</note><v n="37" />deng batarea olok-olok bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu ni batúl-batúl orang Yahudi pung raja, na, kasi salamat lu pung diri suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>and yelled mockingly saying, “If you here really are the Yahudi people's raja, well.then save yourself!”</bt><v n="38" />Dong tulis di satu papan bilang,<bt>They wrote on a board saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini orang Yahudi pung raja.&gt;&gt;<bt>“This is the Yahudi people's raja.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús dong paku itu papan di Yesus pung atas kapala, ko kasi tau alasan dong hukum sang Dia.<bt>Then they nailed that board above Yesus' head, to tell the reason they punished Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Satu orang jahat yang paku tagantong di Yesus pung sablá ju iko ejek bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu batúl Kristus, ko? Kalo bagitu, na, kasi salamat sang kotong samua su!&gt;&gt;<bt>One of the evil people who was nailed hanging at Yesus' side also went along mocking saying, “Are you really Kristus? If that the case, na, save us all!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ma itu orang jahat satu togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu ni, sonde taku sang Tuhan Allah, ko? Te lu ju dapa hukum mati sama ke Dia.<bt>But the other evil person scolded him saying, “Weh! [+attention, +rebuke] Don't you know to be afraid of the Lord God? Cuz you also got a death sentence like Him.</bt><v n="41" />Kotong dua kaná hukum pas deng kotong pung jahat. Ma ini Orang sonde bekin jahat apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>The two of us got punishment fitting with our-inc evil. But this Person has not done any evil.”</bt><v n="42" />Ju dia omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus, é! Nanti kalo Pak su maso pi Pak pung karaja'an, na, inga sang beta, é.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he spoke in addition saying, “Yesus! When Father enters into Father's kingdom, na, remember me, ok.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta janji! Ini hari ju, lu maso pi dalam sorga sama-sama deng Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, “I promise! Even today you will enter into heaven together with Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paradeisooi: from a Persian word for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">paradeisooi: from a Persian word for a rich person's private hunting park, a place well kept and pleasant. Our word "Paradise" comes from it. SK "O cute!"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mati<bt>The Lord Yesus dies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:45-56; Markus 15:33-41; Yohanis 19:28-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44-45" />Itu waktu, su tenga hari. Ma matahari sonde bacaya, ais galáp gulita tutu ame itu tampa sampe jam tiga sore. Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat ada gorden bésar yang tagantong ko pele Tuhan Allah pung Kamar yang Paling Barisi. Takuju sa, itu gorden tarobe putus bagi dua.<bt>At that time, it was midday. But the sun did not shine, so extreme darkness covered over that place until three in the afternoon. At the Central Worship House there was a big curtain which was hung to block.off the Lord God's Room that was Most Clean/Holy. Suddenly, that curtain tore separating in two.</bt><note reference="23:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 26:31-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Di itu tampa &lt;Tulang Kapala&gt;, ju Yesus batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Sakarang Beta sarakan Beta pung roh pi Bapa pung tangan.&gt;&gt; Dia omong abis bagitu, ju Dia pung napas putus memang.<bt>In that place ‘Head Bone (=skull)’, then Yesus yelled saying, “Father! Now I surrender My spirit to Father's hands.” He finished speaking like that, then His breath stopped right away (=he died). [NOTE to daughter translations: Luke doesn't use the proper name of Golotha, so here probably best to say “Place of the Skull”.]</bt><note reference="23:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 31:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Ada komandán tantara Roma yang badiri deka di Yesus pung kayu palang. Waktu dia lia Yesus pung mati tu, ju dia puji Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini Orang batúl-batúl Orang hati lurus, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>There was a Roma soldier standing near Yesus' crossed wood. When he saw that death of Yesus, then he praised the Lord God saying, “Awii! [+impressed] This Person is truly a straight livered Person (=honest/not guilty)!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dikaios: not &quot;righteous,&quot; but in this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">dikaios: not "righteous," but in this context "innocent, not guilty"</Message></Annotation><note reference="23:47" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata bahasa Yunani di sini, dia pung arti ju bisa bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Orang sonde ada pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yunani language words here, can also mean, “This Person does not have wrong/s.”</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Waktu orang banya yang bakumpul di situ dapa lia Yesus pung mati ju, dong manyasal, ais pulang deng hati susa.<bt>When the many people who were gathered there saw Yesus' death, they were regretful, and then went.home with distressed livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapu dada = check"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">sapu dada = check</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Ma Yesus pung orang dong ada badiri dari jao, ko lia Dia pung mati. Mama-mama yang iko sang Dia dari Galilea sampe di Yerusalem, ju ada di situ.<bt>But Yesus' people were standing far off, watching His death. The women who followed Him from Galilea to Yerusalem, were also there.</bt><note reference="23:49" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 8:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kubur sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They bury the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:57-61; Markus 15:42-47; Yohanis 19:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50-51" />Waktu Yesus su mati, ju ada satu orang cari jalan ko mau kasi turun Dia pung mayat dari kayu palang ko kubur bae-bae sang Dia. Itu orang pung nama Yusuf, dari kota Arimatea. Dia pung hati lurus, bekin banya hal yang bae. Dia ada tunggu-tunggu ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung pegang parenta. Dia ju anggota yang dudu urus parkara agama Yahudi, ma dia sonde satuju deng dong pung putusan ko hukum mati sang Yesus.<bt>When Yesus had died, there was a person who sought a way to take down His corpse from that crossed wood to bury it well/respectfully. His name was Yusuf, from Arimatea city. His liver was straight (=righteous), doing many good things. He was waiting for the Lord God to reveal His ruling/governing. He was also a member who sat to take.care of Yahudi religious litigations, but he did not agree with their decision to sentence Yesus to death. [EXEG: high level explication vs.50-53. Joseph wanted to bury Jesus well/respectfully. Noted by Marshall vs.52, and Green. Suggested by a consultant.] [DISCOURSE: In local RL discourse (foreground-background), fits best here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added “to bury ti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">*** (2009) added “to bury ti well/respectfully” and note added (NS)</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Tagal dia mau kasi turun Yesus pung mayat dari kayu palang, andia ko dia pi mangada sang gubernor Pilatus ko minta mau urus itu mayat.<bt>Because he wanted to take down Yesus' corpse from the crossed wood, he went to face governor Pilatus to request to take.care of that corpse.</bt><v n="53" />Dapa isin ju, dia pi kasi turun. Ais dia bungkus itu mayat deng kaen alus. Tarús dia pi taro itu mayat dalam satu lobang batu, yang orang baru pahat abis. Itu tampa kubur tu, balóm ada yang pake.<bt>After getting permission, then he went to take it down. Then he wrapped that corpse in fine cloth. Next he went to put that corpse in a stone/rock hole, which people had just chisled. That burying place, had not yet been used.</bt><v n="54" />Yesus pung mati tu, kaná deng hari Jumat. Waktu Yusuf dong su kubur abis tu, hari su sore. Kalo matahari su tanggalám, na, orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang su mulai.<bt>Yesus' death happened on Friday. When Yusuf (collective) had buried it, it was already late afternoon. If/when the sun went.down, then the Yahudi people's worship day had started. [EXEG: See Marshall, NCV, TN, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ftn on Day of Preparation of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">ftn on Day of Preparation of the Sabbath ?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Itu mama-mama yang datang sama-sama deng Yesus dari Galilea, dong ju pi iko sang Yusuf ko mau tau dia taro itu mayat di kubur mana.<bt>Those women who came together with Yesus from Galilea, they also went to follow Yusuf in order to know where he put that corpse in the grave. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure it is clear “followed from behind” not “accompanied” Yusuf.]</bt><v n="56" />Lia bae-bae itu kubur pung tampa, ais itu mama dong pulang ko sadia rampe deng minya wangi. Waktu matahari tanggalám, ju dong barenti karjá, iko orang Yahudi pung atoran hari sambayang. Dong tunggu hari sambayang lewat, baru dong mau pi siram Yesus pung mayat.<bt>Watching/Seeing carefully that grave's place, then those women went.home to prepare grave.spices and fragrant oil. When the sun went down, then they stopped work, according to the Yahudi people regulation for the worship day. They waited for that worship day to pass, then they wanted to go sprinkle Yesus' corpse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entoleen: commandment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">entoleen: commandment</Message></Annotation><note reference="23:56" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:10, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus idop kambali!<bt>The Lord Yesus lives again!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:1-10; Markus 16:1-8; Yohanis 20:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="24" />
      <v n="1" />Hari Minggu amper siang, itu mama dong bawa itu minya wangi deng rampe ko pi Yesus pung kubur.<bt>Sunday almost dawn, those women brought that fragrant oil and grave.spices to go to Yesus' grave.</bt><v n="2" />Sampe deng sampe ju, dong dapa lia batu bésar yang dong pake ko tutu itu kubur pung pintu, su taguling pi pinggir.<bt>When they arrived there, they saw the big stone which they (non-referential) had used to close that grave's door, was already rolled to the side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akwardly long sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">akwardly long sentence</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tarús dong maso pi dalam kubur, ma dong sonde dapa lia Yesus pung mayat di situ.<bt>Then they entered into the grave, but they did not see Yesus' corpse there.</bt><v n="4" />Jadi dong tabingung-bingung.<bt>So they were very confused.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Takuju sa, ada dua orang yang pake pakean mangkilat, datang badiri di dong pung sablá.<bt>Suddenly, two people who wore shiny clothes, came and stood at their side.</bt><v n="5" />Itu mama dong taku mau mati, ais tondo sampe di tana. Ju itu dua orang tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong datang cari orang yang idop di orang mati dong pung tampa?<bt>Those women were very afraid, so they bowed to the ground. Then those two people asked saying, “Why are you-pl coming looking for people who live in dead people's place?</bt><v n="6" />Yesus su sonde ada di sini lai! Te Dia su idop kambali. Mangkali bosong su lupa apa yang Dia parná bilang waktu masi di Galilea, ko?<bt>Yesus isn't here anymore! Cuz He already lives again. Probably you-pl have forgotten what He once said when still in Galilea, [+tag question]?</bt><v n="7" />Te Dia kasi tau memang bilang, nanti dong jual buang Manusia Tulen pi orang jahat pung tangan. Ais dong paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang. Ma dia pung lusa, Dia su idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He had foretold that, they would sell off the Authentic Human to evil people's hands. Then they would nail kill Him on the crossed wood. But the day.after.the.tomorrow, He would live again.”</bt><note reference="24:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:21, 17:22-23, 20:18-19, Markus 8:31, 9:31, 10:33-34, Lukas 9:22, 18:31-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dengar bagitu, baru dong dapa inga Yesus pung omong dolu tu.<bt>Hearing like that, then they remembered that speaking of Yesus previously.</bt><v n="9" />Ju dong pulang capát-capát, ko kasi tau samua-samua sang Yesus pung ana bua yang sablás orang, deng orang-orang laen yang iko sang Dia.<bt>Then they quickly went home, to tell everything to Yesus eleven underlings, and the other people who followed Him.</bt><v n="10" />(Mama-mama yang pi kubur tu, andia Yakobis pung mama Maria, deng Maria dari kampong Magdala. Ada ju Yohana deng barapa mama laen lai. Dong tu yang pi carita ini samua kasi Yesus pung utusan dong.)<bt>(The women who went to that grave, were Yakobis' mother Maria, and Maria from Magdala village. There was also Yohana and several other women. They were the ones who went to tell all this to Yesus' commissioned ones.) [NOTE to daughter translations: Q: Why is this in parenthesis? A: background out of place.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma waktu ana bua dong dengar itu carita, dong pikir itu mama dong omong kosong sa.<bt>But when the disciples heard that story, they they thought that those women were just speaking emptily (=decieving).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma Petrus bangun ko lari-lari pi kubur. Sampe di sana, dia lia maso pi dalam itu kubur, ma dia cuma dapa lia kaen bungkus mayat sa. Tarús dia pulang deng pikir-pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini su karmana ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus got up to run to the grave. Arriving there, he looked inside that grave, but he only saw just the cloth that wrapped the corpse. Then he went home thinking/mulling it over saying, “How is this [possible]?”</bt><note reference="24:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu yang sonde tulis ini ayat 12.<bt>Some of the Yunani language writings don't write this verse 12.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dua orang katumu sang Dia di jalan pi Emaus<bt>Two underlings meet the Lord Yesus on the road to Emaus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 16:12-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu hari ju, Yesus pung ana bua dua orang pi satu kampong, nama Emaus. Dia pung jao kira-kira 11 kilo dari kota Yerusalem.<bt>That same day, two of Yesus' underlings went to a village, named Emaus. It's distance was approximately 11 kilometres from Yerusalem city.</bt><note reference="24:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;60 <span class="Italic">stadia</span> dari Yerusalem&gt;&gt;. 60 <span class="Italic">stadia</span> tu, sama deng 11,1 kilo.<bt>The Yunani language writings say, “60 <span class="Italic">stadia</span> from Yerusalem. 60 <span class="Italic">stadia</span> are the same as 11.1 kilo.</bt></note><v n="14" />Dong jalan deng ba'omong Yesus pung mati.<bt>They walked while mutually talking about Yesus' death.</bt><v n="15" />Takuju sa, Yesus sandiri deka-deka sang dong dua, ais jalan sama-sama deng dong.<bt>Suddenly, Yesus himself came near to the two of them, then walked together with them.</bt><v n="16" />Ma dong sonde kanál, kalo Dia tu, Yesus, te Tuhan ada bekin ko dong jang kanál.<bt>But they did not recognize that He was Yesus, cuz the Lord made it so they didn't recognize [him]. [EXEG: NLT + TN]</bt><v n="17" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua ni, asik ba'omong apa, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked them saying, “What are you two so busy talking about?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar bagitu, ju dong dua badiri. Dong pung muka tingka ke susa sakali.<bt>Hearing like that, then the two of them stopped (walking; LIT: stood). Their faces were like they were very distressed.</bt><v n="18" />Ais, yang nama Kleopas, tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak ni, tingka ke orang baru, yang sonde tau apa-apa yang baru-baru jadi di Yerusalem ni, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, the one named Kleopas, asked Him saying, “Father here is like a new person who doesn't know anything about what just happened in Yerusalem here, right?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju Yesus tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada apa tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked saying, “What's that?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Yesus, dari Nasaret tu! Dia tu batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Deng Tuhan kasi kuasa sang Dia ko bekin tanda heran macam-macam. Dia ju pintar ajar orang. Orang dong samua sanáng deng Dia. Deng Tuhan ju sanáng deng Dia.<bt>They replied saying, “About that Yesus from Nasaret! He is truly the Lord God's spokesperson. And the Lord gave power to Him to do all.sorts of miracles. He is also skilled in teaching people. All the people are happy with Him. And the Lord also is happy with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ sanang deng or sanang sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">@@ sanang deng or sanang sang ??; ko clause initial???</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma tau-tau, te botong pung kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat tangkap ame sang Dia. Tarús dong sarakan sang Dia pi gubernor ko hukum mati sang Dia. Ais dong paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang.<bt>But contrary.to.what.one.might.expect our-exc Yahudi *chief priests and the traditional elders captured Him. Then they surrendered Him to the governor to sentence Him to death. Then they nailed killed Him on crossed wood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tau-tau = contrary to what one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">tau-tau = contrary to what one might expect</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Mula-mula botong samua harap bilang, Dia tu, Kristus, yang datang kasi lapás botong pung bangsa dari orang pamarenta Roma yang tendes sang botong. Ma hari Jumat baru-baru ni, dong su bunu sang Dia.<bt>In the beginning we all hoped that He was the one who was Kristus, who came to free our nation the Roma government that oppresses us. But last Friday, they murdered Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Sakarang botong su tamba bingung. Te tadi botong pung mama dong datang lapor bilang, pagi-pagi dong ada pi kubur.<bt>Now we-exc are even more confused. Cuz earlier our women came to report that, early morning they went to the grave.</bt><v n="23" />Ma dong carita bilang, Yesus pung mayat su ilang. Ais dong dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga, yang kasi tau sang dong bilang, Yesus su idop kambali!<bt>But they narrated saying, Yesus' corpse had disappeared. Then they saw the Lord God's underlings from heaven, who told them saying, Yesus had lived again!</bt><v n="24" />Dengar bagitu, ju botong pung kawan barapa orang lari pi kubur. Ais dong ju dapa lia sama ke itu mama-mama dong pung omong tu. Dong sonde dapa lia Yesus pung mayat ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then several of our friends ran to the grave. Then they saw like what those women had said. They also did not see Yesus' corpse.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Dong dua carita abis bagitu, ju Yesus togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pung bodo lai! Akurang ko bosong sonde mau parcaya apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su kasi tau memang dari dolu!<bt>The two of them finished telling the story like that, then Yesus scolded them saying, “You-pl are stupid! Why did you not want to believe what the Lord's spokespersons had told beforehand from long ago.</bt><v n="26" />Te dong su tulis bilang, Kristus tu, musti dapa sangsara macam bagitu, baru Dia tarima hormat deng kuasa yang hebat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) they had written that the Kristus, must suffer in that way, only then would He receive honour and power that is amazing.” [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><v n="27" />Tarús Yesus ajar sang dong, samua yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis memang so'al Kristus. Mulai dari ba'i Musa pung tulisan, sampe deng jubir-jubir laen dong pung.<bt>Then Yesus taught them, everything which the Lord's spokespersons had written beforehand about Kristus. Starting from grandfather Musa's writing, until the other spokespersons'.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Waktu dong su amper sampe di Emaus, ju Yesus bekin tingka ke Dia mau jalan tarús.<bt>When they had almost arrived in Emaus, then Yesus made as if He wanted to walk on.</bt><v n="29" />Ma dong dua minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Tenga manumpang sa deng botong ini malam, te matahari su mau tanggalám ni.&gt;&gt; Ju Yesus maso sama-sama deng dong pi dalam ruma.<bt>But the two of them requested saying, “Papa! Just spend the night with us tonight, cuz the sun has already gone down.” So Yesus entered together with them in the house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Waktu dong dudu mau makan, ju Yesus ame roti satu balok. Tarús Dia sambayang minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, ais Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti. Waktu Dia sorong itu roti kasi dong dua,<bt>When they were sitting about to eat, then Yesus too a loaf of bread. Then He prayed requesting thankyou to the Lord God, then He divided up that bread. When he extended that bread to the two of them, [EXEG: TN, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogeesen: pronounce a blessing (not &quot;gave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">eulogeesen: pronounce a blessing (not "gave thanks," which is a different kind of thing in local culture)</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />baru dong dua kanál bilang, itu, Yesus. Ma takuju ju, Dia ilang dari dong pung muka!<bt>only then did they two know/recognise that that was Yesus. But suddenly, He disappeared from in front of them!</bt><v n="32" />Ju dong dua ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Waktu dengar Dia omong bekin jalás jubir dong pung tulisan tadi, kotong rasa tingka ke kotong pung hati ada manyala-manyala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the two of them spoke.to.each.other saying, “Waa! When hearing Him speaking making clear the spokespersons' writings earlier, we-inc felt as if our livers were shining.” [NOTE to daughter translations: watch out for literal translation here. “Hearts burning” usually means anger in eastern Indonesia. The term the TB uses is not known by educated translators. Look for something positive in the range of "inspired".]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed hati tabakar &gt; hati manyala-manyala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">***changed hati tabakar &gt; hati manyala-manyala botong changed to kotong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Itu waktu ju, dong dua bangun ko pulang memang pi Yerusalem. Dong katumu deng Yesus pung ana bua sablás orang, deng orang laen dong yang ada bakumpul di situ.<bt>At that time, then the two of them got up to return right away to Yerusalem. They met Yesus' eleven underlings, and other people who were gathered there.</bt><v n="34" />Ju itu ana bua dong kasi tau sang dong dua bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Tuhan Yesus su idop kambali! Tadi Dia kasi tunju diri sang bu Pe'u.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those underlings told the two of them saying, “Certainly true! Lord Yesus lives again! Earlier He showed Himself to elder.brother Pe'u.”</bt><note reference="24:34" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang &lt;Simon&gt; di sini. Simon tu, andia Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Yunani language writing says &lt;Simon&gt; here. Simon is Petrus' other name.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais, itu dua orang ju carita samua yang jadi di jalan, sampe dong dua bisa kanál sang Yesus waktu Dia bekin pica-pica roti.<bt>Then those two people told everything which happened on the road, to.the.point. that they could recognize Yesus when divided the bread.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus tunju muka sang ana bua dong<bt>The Lord Yesus reveals himself to the underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:16-20; Markus 16:14-18; Yohanis 20:19-23; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:6-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Waktu dong masi bacarita bagitu, takuju sa, Yesus sandiri su badiri di dong pung teng-tenga. Dia kasi salam sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Saloom!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were still telling like that, suddenly, Yesus himself was standing in their midst. He gave greetings to them saying, ‘Saloom!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ma dong takuju deng taku, te dong kira itu hantu.<bt>But they were startled and afraid, cuz they thought it was a ghost.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ma Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong taku bagini? Bosong sonde parcaya bilang, ini Beta yang su idop kambali, ko?<bt>But Yesus spoke saying, “Why are you afraid like this? Don't you believe that this is Me,who lives again, [+tag Q]? [EXEG: see TN display]</bt><v n="39" />Coba lia Beta pung tangan deng kaki. Ini Beta. Sorong tangan ko raba sandiri sa! Biar bosong parcaya bilang, ini Beta, bukan hantu. Te hantu sonde ada pung badan, ma bosong samua bisa lia Beta pung badan, to?!&gt;&gt;<bt>Come look at My hands and feet. It's Me. Just extend your hand to touch for yourselves! So that you believe that this is Me, not a ghost. Cuz ghosts don't have a body, but you all can see My body, right?!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Masi omong bagitu ju, Dia kasi lia sang dong bakás luka di Dia pung tangan deng kaki.<bt>Still speaking like that, He showed them the wound traces (=scars) on his hands and feet. [NOTE: In John 20:27 Gk says put your hand/finger IN my side, so impression that this is not a fully healed dried and filled in scar. Some lgs distinguish between “fresh/wet wound” and “old/dry wounds”.]</bt><v n="41" />Dong sanáng mau mati, tagal Yesus su idop kambali. Cuma dong babingung, te dong sonde bisa mangarti karmana ko bisa jadi bagitu. Ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong makan apa di sini, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>They were very happy, because Yesus lived again. Only they were confused, cuz they could not understand how it could happen like that. Then Yesus asked them saying, “What are you eating here?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thaumazontoon: too good to be true:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">thaumazontoon: too good to be true: "totally max out."</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ju dong sorong kasi sang Dia ikan panggang sapotong.<bt>Then they extended gave to Him a piece of grilled fish. [EXEG: Gk “grilled, broiled, baked”, not “fried” as in TB. Don't be surprised if you get challenged on this.]</bt><v n="43" />Yesus tarima itu ikan, ais Dia makan di dong pung muka.<bt>Yesus accepted that fish, then He ate it front of them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Tarús Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Bosong masi inga waktu Beta sama-sama deng bosong dolu? Beta kasi tau tempo hari bilang, samua yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong tulis so'al Beta tu, musti jadi. Andia dari ba'i Musa, dari jubir laen dong, deng dari buku Lagu Puji dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He spoke saying, “How is it? Do you still remember when I was together with you previously? I told one time that, everything which the Lord God's spokespersons had written about Me, had to happen. That is, from grandfather Musa, from the other spokespersons, and from the book of Praise Songs.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Torah, Nevi'im, Ktuvim, the three divisions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">Torah, Nevi'im, Ktuvim, the three divisions of the Hebrew Bible</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tantu bosong su lupa apa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">Tantu bosong su lupa apa yang Beta kasi tau tempo hari, bilang, samua yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong tulis so'al Beta, itu samua musti jadi.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais ju Dia buka bekin taráng ko dong mangarti batúl Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi pung arti.<bt>After that, He open and explained/made clear so they could truly understand the meaning of the *Scriptures.</bt><v n="46" />Dia omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis bilang, Kristus, yang Tuhan kirim datang tu, musti dapa sangsara macam-macam, ais Dia mati. Ma nanti dia pung lusa, Dia idop kambali. Ko dong su tulis samua na!<bt>He spoke further saying, “The Lord's spokesperson wrote that, Kristus, who the Lord sent, must get all.sorts of suffering, then He would die. But later on the day.after.the.tomorrow, He would live again. They've written all of that [+obviously]!</bt><v n="47" />Sakarang Beta kasi kuasa ko bosong bawa ini Kabar Bae ni, pi samua suku-bangsa mulai dari Yerusalem sini. Kasi tau sang dong bilang, orang yang mangaku sala deng kambali pi Tuhan, nanti Tuhan hapus buang itu sala dong samua.<bt>Now I give power for you to take this Good News here to all the nations, starting for Yerusalem here. Tell them that, people who confess wrongs and return to the Lord, the Lord will completely erase all those wrongs. [EXEG: NLT takes “in his name” as “with my authority”. See CEG word study on “name” as summary.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epi tooi onomati autou: in connection"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z" status="Information">epi tooi onomati autou: in connection with him (put at the end so as not to overload the syntax)</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Bosong musti jadi saksi ko carita bilang, Beta dapa sangsara, ais mati, tarús idop kambali.<bt>You must become witnesses to tell that I suffered, then died, then lived again.</bt><v n="49" />Nanti Beta kirim datang Roh yang Barisi, yang Beta pung Bapa su janji. Ma bosong musti tunggu sa di kota Yerusalem sini, sampe tarima kuasa dari sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later I will send the Holy Spirit, whom My Father has promised. But you must wait here in Yerusalem city, until recieving power from heaven. [EXEG: as per NLT, CEV note, TH, TN, and Marshall]</bt><note reference="24:49" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:28-29; Yohanis 14:16-17; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ta'angka nae pi sorga<bt>The Lord Yesus is lifted up to heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 16:19-20; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Satu hari, Yesus bawa sang dong kaluar kota. Waktu dong sampe deka deng kampong Betania, Dia angka tangan ko omong kasi berkat sang dong.<bt>One day, Yesus brought them outside that city. When they arrived closed to Betania village, He lifted his hands to speak giving blessing to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="should proper names not pronouns be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:44:06Z">should proper names not pronouns be used to start a new section?</Message></Annotation><note reference="24:50-51" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:9-11</note><v n="51" />Dia masi omong kasi berkat bagitu, ju Dia ta'angka nae pi sorga.<bt>While He was still speaking giving blessing like that, then He was lifted up to heaven.</bt><v n="52" />Lia bagitu ju, dong samua tikam lutut ko sémba sang Dia. Ais dong pulang pi Yerusalem deng hati talalu sanáng.<bt>Seeing like that, they all knelt to worship Him. Then they returned home to Yerusalem with livers that were very happy.</bt><v n="53" />Tiap hari dong bakumpul di Ruma Sambayang Pusat ko angka puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Every day they gathered at the Central Worship House to lift up praises to the Lord God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Pak Teo! Beta pung carita sampe sini dolo.<bt>Mr Teo! My story stops here. [DISCOURSE: high level closure following RL patterns.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Saloom,<bt>Shalom, [DISCOURSE: common Finis to indicate end.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Lukas<bt>Lukas</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>